review_1.Review: For the price not worth going back. Thing more the add than that!

review_2.Review: Entertaining some guests from out of town, they remarked how this was the best meal they had in sf.Wagyu skewers, beef noodle soup, hamachi (best value!), and the a5 dumpling was our favorite.

review_3.Review: Food was outstanding, service was relaxed but good. Their beef noodle soup, wagyu, and uni were the highlights, but everything else we tried was excellent too.There was an event taking place that evening. Made it a bit livelier but didn’t interfere with our dinner.

review_4.Review: waited for 15 minutes in an empty restaurant and other than water no-one showed up. Food choices seemed very limited. waited 10 more minutes and walked out. No apologies, no words of how can we do better. I understand these are tough times, but having a restaurant in an expensive neighborhood, least you can do is have some service

review_6.Review: There’s no sign outside so you have to look for the restaurant. The food was fantastic but the ambiance is weird. It didn’t feel like a restaurant. It felt like just a bar. It feels mediocre for the price but I’d say food was great…

review_7.Review: Yum yum yum. Innovative dishes with really thoughtful and unique combinations of spices, textures, and ingredients. Drinks are awesome too!

review_8.Review: There are so many places in San Francisco to spend too much money for okay food. This is not that. This is a thoughtful omakase menu by a wonderful chef who has poured her soul into each dish. A mix of uniqueness, fantastic taste, and love. We felt so privileged to get to experience this—on our list, it will be one of those few places that we discovered before everyone else did. We will be back, and will be telling our friends!

review_9.Review: Items in our order was forgotten, had to be reminded.  Never got our water cups refilled.

review_10.Review: Had chef's omakase tasting menu - our entire group loved it! Beautiful presentation and quite filling. Momo toast, Chawanmushi, A5 Wagyu were some of our favorites. Cocktails were creative and delicious.

review_11.Review: The food and Japanese whiskey flights were incredible. The service was outstanding. It was perfect for our birthday celebration. Highly recommend. It's a small menu and each dish was outstanding.

review_12.Review: Food is amazing.  Try the uni dishes or the beef noodle soup!

review_13.Review: I looked for a unique dining experience to entertain business guests in SF this week and I found a gem with 5A5!!! I let the excellent Cheif Cat select and have us served family style and WHAT A CULINARY TREAT!!! From Starters to Entrees, nothing disappointed. Her last Entree was the Beef and Noodles, which all of us raved about - really an exceptional dish.If you want to skip the traditional Steak Houses of SF for a unique culinary experience, it’s 5A5!!

review_14.Review: Food was wonderful and excellent service by Josue. The beef noodle soup was incredible, but the scallops were amazing.

review_15.Review: Cool place. Excellent food. Highly recommend the beef noodle soup

review_16.Review: Wonderful dinner, some of the best noodle soup I've had anywhere and the lobster tempura was excellent.  Great environment.

review_17.Review: Great cocktails and great food. Service was great and the Chef even came out to talk with us.

review_18.Review: Fantastic. Can be loud at times, but that's me, not the restaurant. The atmosphere is great.

review_19.Review: Delightfully deceiving! The food was outstanding, and the chef delivered made-to-order dishes that blew our minds. Thank you!

review_20.Review: Good food, but not commensurate to the high prices.

review_21.Review: Excellent food: loved Chef Wong’s take on the Asian menu - highly recommend! Check this place out and you won’t be disappointed

review_22.Review: A5 was soooo melt in your mouth tasty. Tried both A5 items on the menu & a number of others. Cocktails were creative and presentation was fantastic!

review_23.Review: Intimate but fun, lively setting with a mix of diners and happy hour guests. Short rib beef noodle soup was delish, a5 wagyu skewers were a fav too. Chicken wings/wangs were a bit messy but great crunch/texture. Reasonably priced for the quality

review_24.Review: Delicious and cute with highly attentive service. The entrance is a bit hard to see but worth the hunt. The beef soup is the highlight if you want something hearty but all the bite were delicious. We ordered almost everything between two people and a Japanese whisky flight. Shrimp toast was more delicious then it had any right to be. Wagu dumpling with it's rich broth was also surprisingly exceptional. Salmon collar was also decent portion and so fatty and flavorful. The melon salad with the salmon in a fish sauce dressing should be it's own dish. I'll be back.

review_25.Review: The two cocktails I has were amazing (Black & Gold + Forget Me Not), but the Change Your Life bowl did not live up to the name and the shrimp and uni toast was also underwhelming

review_26.Review: Great to see 5A5 reboot happening. Excited to see this come out of soft opening. Outstanding vibes and people.

review_27.Review: The food is extremely salty for me as a Taiwanese living in the US for about 7 years. Service is good. Noted that the restaurant charges an 18% service fee on top of the tips, which, together with the item price, makes the experience over-priced. I would try other fine dining options which would not lead to having to drink five glasses of water in an hour. The taste of standard Asian restaurants is also more of the taste of my liking.

review_28.Review: Fantastic meal, great selection of different small plates for us to try. A5 Wagyu skewers and beef noodle soup were our favs. QR code ordering/payment was easy and efficient.

review_29.Review: My experience was awesome! Went for a friends birthday and am very happy about my decision.

review_30.Review: Loved the service and the food. I would definitely recommend to another and come back to this place. Food was fresh and exquisite .

review_31.Review: Nice restaurant. Food was great our server was not the best.

review_32.Review: Awesome experience, waitress was knowledgeable and absolutely wonderful.  Wait staff was impeccable.Would recommended and dine here again

review_33.Review: Not at all worth the money. The waygu is good, but I don't understand why they'd serve it covered in cheese - shouldn't the flavor of the meat be able to stand on its own? Also, any non-waygu meat you order on the menu isn't prime - the quality isn't good and it came out cold. I'd rather go to another steakhouse or just cook at home. It'd taste a lot better and for a fraction of the price.

review_34.Review: This is a really nice date night restaurant. We arrived a little late bc of traffic on the bridge which the hostess was very accommodating which I appreciated. We did change our table to one over. If you are seated by the kitchen it is a little uncomfortable bc your chair will be just a tad out of the walk way and the noise from the kitchen is a distraction to your conversation. Outside of that my date for the evening ordered the lobster tail which he has decided to never eat at another restaurant it was so good, and 32ounce Ribeye with loaded mashed potatoes. His steak was cooked to perfectly medium and was very tender.I ordered a Pear Watercress salad which was fairly good and the Where is the Beef? option since I am vegetarian. Of course with any steak house you should be there to eat steak but I just cant lol. The risotto wasn’t cooked all the way through so there were some moments where it was hard, the lentils were dry however the carrots, zucchini and squash were all amazing. (which wasn’t much).If we should ever go again I would just order the side dishes and would be satisfied with that.All in all it was a very nice night and my date enjoyed his dinner and we together enjoyed the atmosphere and service.

review_35.Review: Mediocre, not worth the money. Steak quality wasn’t as expected and came out cold. They market waygu beef, but then smother it in cheese and butter.

review_36.Review: Loved the waygu carpaccio, tasty drinks, the prime rib was flavorful with the rosemary broth and horseradish sauce. The house made bacon bread, yum!

review_37.Review: Took my boyfriend here for his birthday. It was the perfect experience, food & service I could have asked for. I cant wait to go back for the next occasion!

review_38.Review: Best steak dinner in recent memory. Absolutely loved it!

review_39.Review: I was so disappointed by their t bone steak.  I had never had t bone steak served on the cold plate and even though I asked for medium well, the steak was well done. Also, the gnome steak was covered with sweet sauce and fries egg. Why do they need fried egg on the top of the good meat??! I have eaten at Benjamin New York, Peter Rugar and they have never disappointed me with the quality of the meat.  Do not go for T bone steak

review_40.Review: The food was OK. Unless you are willing to fork out over $200 for 4oz of Japanese Wagyu, you can pretty much get the same kind of meat at any decent steakhouse. We tried a t bone and bone in rib eye and Mac and cheese. The meats were good but not especially flavorful.  Hubby can cook and season a piece of quality steak at home with better result. The Mac and Cheese was good, horribly rich. You can taste the cheeses, cream and truffle. Waiter was nice and we got to sample their 2 kinds of bread and 2 complimentary amuse bouche. We sat in the back where a large table was celebrating a birthday.  Bit the birthday boy was loud and obnoxious.  Not planning to come back.

review_41.Review: Good service. Great steaks... could nearly cut it with a fork! The sides of mashed potatoes and creamed spinach were excellent.  The coffee combination dessert was out of this world!  Expensive but worth every penny. We would definitely return.

review_42.Review: We have had Wagyu beef in several diff

review_43.Review: Amazing all around! The Wagyu is a MUST and the Ribeye is fabulous! :) Can't wait to go back

review_44.Review: Service was a bit too attentive. We wanted to have a drink and casually order, and was checked on for an order, 3x in 15min. Too much.Steak not cooked to the way we each preferred and 3 of us (out of 4) had to send back.Disappointing as I was hoping I found my go-to regular place.Positives: good drinks, quiet, comfortable, enough variety of food.

review_45.Review: This restaurant is where you should take your date on a anniversary or bd. Not for a first date. My lord them prices are off the food chain.  Just a 4 oz or 8 oz of waygu will cost you between 175$-330$. So make sure you save up money before you make reservations here.

review_46.Review: Celebrated 2 birthdays & Valentine’s Day all in one

review_47.Review: Amazing food!  Absolutely one of the most favorable and definitely the most tender steak I’ve ever experienced.  We ordered the $85 rib eye.  Its over 2 inches thick and takes an hour to cook but well worth the wait.  We also ordered the truffle Mac n Cheese and Caesar salad.  It’s rich but very tasty as well.  I would recommend this steakhouse to anyone!

review_48.Review: Service was excellent, and the food was great.

review_49.Review: The food was great as expected but what really made this an amazing dinner out was the service! We never once felt like we had to look for someone to get another drink as they were extremely attentive. Also my husband has some allergies and they made sure to ask upfront and adjusted his meal for this without any issues.

review_50.Review: Way overpriced for the food you get. Sorry but it’s the truth!

review_51.Review: It was ok not great I like Alexander steak house better

review_52.Review: Loved, loved, loved the whole experience.  Highly recommend it!

review_53.Review: Decent place though nothing to go over the top about.

review_54.Review: The interior ambience was very nicely.  The service was very good.  My only complaint is that my NY steak came out luke warm as if it was sitting for a little while before being brought out to me.  Perhaps the server was waiting fir the other food and my steak got a little cold.  I would try this place again but will probably try other steak houses first.

review_55.Review: Been here twice - the food and staff are amazing. We love it for a Friday after work date night. This time however the music was a bit louder than last time and meant people at the tables also talked louder.

review_57.Review: Pretty nicely stocked bar, good variety of Japanese whiskey (pretty overpriced though). So, I asked for my usual Oban (was kn the menu). They didn't have it in stock, so I moved to Macallan. Appetizers were good (we got the fried Shishito peppers and wagyu sliders). Steaks are nice quality and there medium (That's what I usually order) is pretty nice and tender inside. So, happy about it. The 7 deg Coffee desert was a nice portion and would be good for 3.to share :)Overall a great experience. Staff is very attentive.

review_58.Review: Excellent service. Average food. High prices. Very... meh.

review_59.Review: Excellent, but expensive restaurant, great for special occasions.  Great for special occasions.  Can't go wrong with any of the American cuts, but best known for their Japanese waygu if you're willing to pay up for a top dollar experience.

review_61.Review: The food was insanely expensive, marginally tasty, and very small meat portions. The steaks showed up on room temperature plates and the meat was warm, not fresh off the grill. The waiter resisted making eye contact with my female dining partner when she was choosing the wine. The waiter keep t looking at me.I tried 5A5 because I couldn’t get a reservation at a local steakhouse (Harris, house of prime rib, etc. ). But given the choice, next time Morton’s rather than 5A5.

review_62.Review: Brought wife for birthday.  Very disappointed.  Took about an hour to get our food.  Waiter only checked on us maybe 2 times in a 2 hour window.  Dead bug found on plate and the manager didn’t stop by to apologize or anything.  I usually don’t complain, but when you pay $200 for a meal, it should meet a certain standard.

review_63.Review: The service does not match the price.  The taste of the food is average, not like the restaurant selling premium beef.  The steak recommended by the waiter was not delicious, too.

review_66.Review: Food was inconsistent. My husbands steak was less than an inch thick. No what he expected for a New York. Our friends ordered prime rib. They said it was good but not outstanding. For the price they expected outstanding. We ordered 2 desserts, both only OK. It was my birthday so they could have told I would get  a complimentary dessert but they didn't. It came after we ordered and ate dessert. My daughter called the restaurant and ordered 4 after dinner drinks to surprise us. They never came. She was not charged but it ruined a nice surprise. We will not return. Too many other place we like that serve good food, have great service and are less expensive.

review_67.Review: They have high quality food - but I had to ask for sauces on the side - because they wanted to smother great pieces of meat with sauces and sides. Don’t overthink it.Great service, fun weird ambiance, super expensive but only on the A5 Wagyu, everything else was reasonable.

review_68.Review: i used to love this place, but the last few times have been disappointing. I've been here 10+ times and the food just isn't what it used to be. Salads are very small, the ribeye was flavorless and the bacon in the mashed potatoes was incredibly chewy. Unfortunately the last visit was my last. They push the kobe beef, which is insanely expensive and even with no wine dinner for 2 was north of $250 - kinda silly for bad food and sharing of app, salad and steak.

review_69.Review: Great food. Excellent service. I would definitely recommend this place to all the people i know.

review_70.Review: Great food. Really great food. The Steak - no matter if you get the expensive Waygu or the still expensive non-Waygu steak - is cooked very well and tastes oh so yummy. The add-on sides, too, are very good. We had mashed potatoes and mac-n-cheese... granted they were yummy, as they should be for almost $20 a serving.  The steak - my wife never tried Waygu before, and since we also had a gift certificate, she wanted to try it. Luckily the gift card covered her $170 4-ounce Waygu ribeye steak. They do talk it up, saying that the cows are played classical music, are massaged daily, have Tolstoy read to them... and sure it melts like butter in your mouth, but roughly 4 bites at $40+ a bite later... it still ends up in the same place as the $20 potato and the $20 mac and cheese. Don't get me wrong... it's an experience to realize you're eating a figurative "Cash Cow," but not one I would spend my hard-earned money on again.   Nice time though. Wish they catered more to children... when we asked for a glass of milk for our daughter, it seemed as if we were putting them out a bit and inconveniencing them. It took probably 20 minutes or so for them to bring it out. The place, though, is not good for kids under say, 12, or those who don't eat "adult" food. They do have a "vegetarian" meal: beets, carrots and assorted veggies for 25 bucks. At that price, though... best to just stick with the 15 dollar truffle fries.

review_73.Review: Great, full of sophisticated flavor food!! My teen son was a really impressed, which is really rare:) he mentioned that one day he certainly will be back here again!!! Highly recommended for people who appreciate high quality chef’s art work...

review_74.Review: Food was mediocre. Not worth it for the price. Better food quality at Ruth Chris

review_75.Review: Order medium rare steak, but received medium cook. Menu doesn’t have vegetables listed, so we thought it was included when our waiter asked what vegetables we wanted. Found out all vegetables were not included. This was my 2nd time I went to this restaurant. 1st time was satisfied so I returned. This time I wasn’t satisfied and I don’t think I’ll come back the 3rd time because I paid so much for the steak that wasn’t what I wanted.

review_76.Review: I told the manager that this was the absolute worst dining experience I have ever had.  Not that he actually asked or cares about my experience as evidence in his total lack of customer service. I actually sent my steak back and was so disappointed that I didn’t bother to ask for a replacement.  Salad.  Bland.  Lacked flavor. Steak. Bland.  Lacked flavor. Mashed potatoes.  Bland. Lacked flavor. Clearly the Chef doesn’t know cooking 101.  Salt and Pepper.  Service was terrible. 20 min to get a sparking water. Really had high hopes as it was labeled a steak lounge.  Avoid.  So many other places to try.

review_77.Review: Service was great. Prime rib, mushrooms and sides were poor to average.Oysters and marrow were good.

review_78.Review: The vibe And scenery of the restaurant was so pleasant. Staff was courteous. Service was fast and in a timely manner. Food was hot, delicious, and fantastic overall. Definitely recommend!

review_79.Review: I’ve frequented 5A5 many times in the past. I’ve heard others give mix reviews about 5A5 because of the service but I always thought those experiences were flukes, but this last time we went we were finally victims of the bad service everyone was talking about. Our dining experience was awful because of the poor service. We came to celebrate my parents’ 35th wedding anniversary and while it was noted in my reservation, not once were my parents greeted. We never got our sparkling water refilled (which, mind you, is $9) and we felt like our server was purposefully ignoring us. He would literally stand about 2 feet from our table and not once glance at us to check in even though we were trying to get his attention. We didn’t do anything wrong, so I don’t know why we got the type of service we did. We even noticed he would revisit a table twice before coming to our table. On the receipt his name was “John” - it was unfortunate and we were all really disappointed with our dining experience. They get the two stars because the quality of the meat is superb, but lost their other stars and our dining loyalty due to poor service.

review_80.Review: We enjoy a lot our Christmas Dinner, the food was amazing.

review_81.Review: From the moment we walked in, our dining experience was phenomenal. We we were greeted warmly and seated immediately. It was our first time there and our server made sure we were taken care of. Rebecca was VERY knowledgeable about the food AND the drinks.  Every recomendation she made, we took and we were never disappointed.  We had the bone marrow, soup du jour, wagyu rib eye, bone-in rib eye and truffle mac and cheese... EVERYTHING WAS DELICIOUS.  We also had the japanese whiskey flight and the love with gin.  We left fully satisfied. I would highly recomend this place.  Food, service, ambience was TOP NOTCH.

review_82.Review: We went down 5A5 for Xmas dinner. The 4 Steaks were AMZING!Whiskeys were great! Very intersting and exciting atmosphere.We will definitely be back!

review_83.Review: Very good ambiance and atmosphere. Also very good whayu cuts of A5 beef . I highly recommend this restaurant.

review_84.Review: The food is very good. The service was good. The waiter very friendly and professional.

review_85.Review: It was my first time there. I’d go again for happy hour.

review_86.Review: Great place for a special occasion! I booked 5A5 with no problems for my boyfriend's birthday and the food was spectacular. Come on an empty stomach because their steak portions are generous. I loved that they gave a special birthday dessert.

review_87.Review: Food didn’t come out prepared the way it was ordered. For the price the value did not meet expectations

review_88.Review: For the price, I expected superior steak...but I've had better at numerous other restaurants. Good meatball starter. Good mac n cheese with lobster, but at $32, I expected a larger portion. Great service!!

review_89.Review: My fiancé loves this place we have been here 5 years in a row and we love it. Service spot on and food was spot on!

review_90.Review: Food was good. Ambiance was good. Was ignored after dinner and had to flag people down to get the bill

review_91.Review: Not good , not bad. Been here over 5 times. Seems to of lost its touch. Service could of been more friendlier.

review_92.Review: The Filet Mignon and New York steak were overcooked, while the prime rib was undercooked.

review_93.Review: Would never come here again. The service was horrible and the manager rather take care of guests he knows, then other guests at the restaurant. If you like poor service and below par, steak then this is the place to go. Otherwise go to other steakhouses in SF.

review_94.Review: Great service just really loud at times and bathroom is it the way !

review_95.Review: Unfortunately the mashed potatoes were the highlight. Tomato bisque was pretty good. The steak was just ok, definitely not the quality I expected for the price.

review_97.Review: Celebrate my birthday, the service wasn’t that great. I can tell our waiter judge us by the way we looked. We were a young couple and it seem like, he assume we couldn’t afford anything. He check on us once and never filled up our waters. We spent $350, so the food was good but the lack of service and attention by our server was disappointing for the price we paid.

review_98.Review: Great experience. Will be back steak was fantastic and wine was very good

review_99.Review: Our server was so great!! He laughed with us and was very attentive. So was the sommelier!

review_100.Review: I would recommend this place for the food (for meat lovers), service and ambiance.  However, you need to save up the $ to dine at this place.  With drinks and one dessert to share, the bill was more than $700 for two adults and two kids.

review_101.Review: The front of the house, our server, and management were welcoming and hospitable.  However the ambience is in need of an update, and the food is overpriced and close to inedible.  You'd be better off grilling your own steak and preparing your own dinner.

review_102.Review: As a chef excellent is the standard. Ambiance is exquisite.

review_103.Review: The steaks were not cooked as we ordered. The MR came out more medium, the medium came out basically rare. The wagyu steak we had was ordered medium, but apparently the chef did not agree and basically sent it to us seared. Only one person tried it. For $300 dollars for an 8 oz steak, we should get it as ordered. Mashed potatoes and lobster tempura were delicious. My bill for 5 ppl was more than $1000, and I wasn’t thrilled. :(

review_104.Review: This was my second visit to 5A5 so came with some expectations. As a business dinner, we were received and tabled in a congenial and professional fashion. Table was in the middle which was a disappointment, but not a criticism. Our waiter was a bid weird - the guy did not follow the normal sequence of looking after us - no drink requests, no starters, etc. Went straight into the wagyu presentation - all chatty and informative discussion with him. Nevertheless, got our drinks, bone marrow starters and dry aged T-Bones with a side of wagyu rib cap. The flow was good, food excellent, and an overall positive experience. One complaint - the steaks and the plates they came on was presented as "careful very hot" - but in fact was quite cool - below expected standards.

review_105.Review: Service was friendly and attentive! Food was delicious. Steaks were cooked to perfection. Enjoyed every bite!

review_106.Review: Service was great! Food came out quick, and was very good.

review_107.Review: The restaurant is San Francisco's answer to sexy for the price the staff could be a little more attentive opulent price tag mediocre service New York strip cooked to perfection mashed potatoes creamy truffle macaroni and cheese okay but nothing to write home about mix drinks incredibly stiff

review_109.Review: Decor and service were great but food was underwhelming.

review_110.Review: Service and Presentation was excellent.  Choices were good and the food was fantastic. If your looking for a 5-Star,  this is it.

review_111.Review: The rib eye we got was tough and very bland. Probably needs more seasoning. Not as tasty as it use to be.

review_112.Review: Great business place but a bit overpriced and noisy

review_114.Review: Decor and room quality was a little best up and smelled a little dank but the food was fantastic.

review_115.Review: Is it possible to lose weight at a steak house?At 5A5 you can do just that.How?Well for starters they will likely forget half of your order.That's what happened to us.  We ordered a wagyu steak along with cremini mushrooms and mac-and-cheese.Only the steak arrived.And this was after the waitress had already apologized to us about the lateness of: our drinks; our waters; our menus - everything.Finally I asked for the manager.  It was telling that he didn't know that he should have already made an appearance."What happened," I asked.  "This used to be my favorite restaurant.  Now it's a hot mess."The manager had no idea.  He allowed that the service was slow and unorganized and gave lip service about making it up to us. "I get where you are coming from - but we still don't even have my credit card back.  This is a mess from start to finish.  I couldn't imagine bringing a client here."To be fair, the steak was delicious.  So if you like your steak with a side of unpredictability, 5A5 is perfect.

review_116.Review: Anniversary dinner was amazing. Food is always good and consistent and the drinks were on point. We'll be booking 5A5 for years to come!

review_117.Review: No longer has tomahawk steak and no longer has the night club. The menu isn't much to choose from IMO and slightly over priced... HOWEVER the service was great and the food was delicious! So, you're sure to always have great food and service.

review_118.Review: One of the best meals of my life the tempura lobster is unreal!

review_119.Review: Beautiful restaurant and beautiful food.  The service was what I expected for a fine restaurant.  Our server was friendly, acknowledgeable and very attentive.  The food was cooked perfectly and melted in our mouths.  We were very disappointed to find our teen aged daughters had to share a large common restroom with men down stairs from the main restaurant.  One would think a fine dining establishment could at least have a separate powder room for their female customers instead of a football stadium style bathroom in a poorly lite basement in which they were forced to share with men.

review_120.Review: We needed more recognition of the inherent irony present within the experience.

review_121.Review: Our server was great, the food was delicious, the palette cleansers from the chef were a nice touch, and we had an overall great Anniversary dinner.

review_122.Review: The steak was smothered in some sort of A-1 type steak sauce... huge disappointment for a $70 filet. The drinks were absurdly slow... pre-dinner cocktail arrived a minute before dinner, wine ordered for dinner came after meal was finished, cappuccino arrived once dessert was complete. Pretty disappointing for a restaurant of this caliber.

review_123.Review: We have a bad experience.We have been asked if we have any dietary restriction and my husband said "no cilantro", the waiter looked kinda rude way as if he said something weird and said "we don't have cilantro in anything" but when he brought the carpaccio we ordered, surprise there was cilantro on top if.Also, we don't know how could they manage to make one of the steaks undercook (even blue) and one of the steaks overcook (more than medium) while we ordered as "medium rare".Lastly, Our steak tartar had silver skin, one of the last things you would expect in steak tartar.We wouldn't go back to this place again.

review_124.Review: Excellent food and and service. The price is fair for the area$$$$$$$$$$

review_125.Review: It was a pleasure eating at this place.

review_126.Review: AMAZING! There is no other word to describe the food for 5A5. It was the best steak i've ever had and the truffle mac n cheese so good I could come back just for that!

review_127.Review: Service and cocktails were great but steak was just ‘ok’.

review_128.Review: Would have like to order more drinks as we were having good conversations but the waiter was not very attentive. Also, the 4oz steak was not worth the price we paid for it.

review_129.Review: Incredible. Worth every penny. Such beautiful food and atmosphere.

review_130.Review: Food and service were excellent. We will definitely be going back.

review_131.Review: The food was great, although some of their prices are through the roof. Service was perfect and the ambiance was awesome

review_133.Review: We were looking for an out of the ordinary steak house in the Financial District and this popped up on Open Table. Little did we know that it was a Japanese steak house specializing in various forms of Wagyu as well as whiskies. After being presented with four of the most marbled steaks I have ever seen, three of us opted for a 32 oz bone in rib eye (American) which was fabulous. We started with an excellent wedge salad as well as heirloom tomatoes and our colleague the vegetarian ordered the entry entitle “where’s the beef” which was an array of roasted vegetables. The two sides we ordered were the sweet potato and the button mushrooms, both of which were delicious.The wine list was adequate and relatively reasonable and the service was excellent.I highly recommend this restaurant and we will definitely be back.

review_134.Review: Food very good meat top quality but the price you pay for all is not coherent with the lack of service and table equipment.

review_135.Review: It was my 3rd year anniversary and we wanted a great steak to celebrate.  We've never had Wagyu so decided to try this place.  The servers were very courteous and provided examples of the different Wagyu beef that they had.  In addition, the presentation was spectacular as seen in the attached pictures.  The server also provided excellent recommendations of drinks to pair with the Wagyu beef. We were so full by the end of the beef, that we had to take home the sides.

review_136.Review: Great options. Steaks come with a lot of dressings but the team is happy to accommodate anyone who wants their steak naked and pure. Food was great. Superb spirit and wine selection.

review_137.Review: one of the best ribeyes in recent years!  our server was great too!

review_138.Review: 5A5 was a great experience for my date and I. My date is originally from St. Louis and had never experienced such a high class place before. The service was good for the most part. My only issue was with the helper bringing our plates out. He spoke very fast explaining what we were having and left very quickly.  Other then that the service was impeccable. Jessica our waitress was AMAZING for the start. She noticed my dates menu was nasty and she brought over a new one that was clear for her to read. Down to her explanation of the wagyu meats. My date was very IMPRESSED and so was I. I definitely would prefer this restaurant to all my friends and family.  Its definitely a great experience.

review_139.Review: Great dinner not a lot of side options we only did the Mac n cheese to share but it was still nice

review_140.Review: Food and service were spectacular - I was slightly disappointed everyone around us got amuse bouche but it didn’t spoil the night.  I thought that the space could use a freshen up to fit the environment.  Some lights above were missing filters and the windows to the exterior needed a change to darken the setting.

review_141.Review: The A5 experience was amazing. The staff are great. Wagyu came out perfect.

review_142.Review: Too expensive and the food tastes normal but the price is too high. Appetizers and main course are just a little but the price is too expensive. Not worth the money to spend.

review_143.Review: We like that it has 4 different styles of wagyu and it has 4oz options so we could try different types out!Somehow we prefer the crossbreed wagyu over the 5a wagyu though.For starters we ordered lobster tempura and steak tartare. They were amazing!I normally can't eat raw food but dining here was fine!

review_144.Review: Food was ok, not great. Each dish felt like a little much in a gilding the lily sort of way. The oysters didn’t even taste like oysters because of all of the other ingredients on them. Every steak came with some sort of topping. I prefer when good ingredients are kept simple to let them shine. Restaurant itself was very nice, great staff.

review_145.Review: Great flavorful food. Fantastic service. Seating is not crampy and is spacious. Very happy with everything.

review_146.Review: Still the easiest place to get true Nippon Wagyu 5A5 in the Bay Area. Great service, and they accommodate triple corkages with class and grace. To those who thought it was too loud, the dance music has been turned off. To those who demand EDM with their Wagyu, just ask or bring your MP3.

review_147.Review: Great place to catch up with friends/family while enjoying delicious cocktails and food.

review_149.Review: 4.5 stars.  The steaks are good.  The prime rib was so-so...not the best.  The Wagyu, of course, was delicious.  Sides and desserts were good; I really liked the sorbet.  It was refreshing after a heavy meal of steak.The only down side was the service could have been a bit more attentive.  It took a little while to get the server to take our order after explaining the menu, and then once we get our meal the server hardly came by to refill the water or ask if we need any other items.  Would have been nice if they left the bottle of water on the table.  Then I could have just helped myself to the water since I tend to drink a lot of water.

review_150.Review: Celebrating a birthday and everything was great. The food was delicious and the service was good and attentive. The 32oz. rib eye is a  must try for meat eaters. The oyster shooters were delicious and the fries and ‘truffle Mac and cheese added to the good food and experience. I would give 4 1/2 stars five is difficult as It would have to be spectacular to get a five in my opinion. It was close to a five, either way it’s a great place with good food.

review_151.Review: Does not seem organized.  Food did not come out in sequence, server removed courses before we were done, entree came and had to wait for 5 minutes before getting up and asking for utensils.  Lots of people running around, but no coordination.  Meat was under cooked and I got three apologies but still had to wait yet again to get a spoon to eat m souffle with.

review_152.Review: Really solid, best steakhouse I've been to in SF.  Pricey, but what you get is really good.  Went for my girlfriend's birthday and they threw in a birthday dessert and ceviche on the house.  Steaks and sides were both amazing.  Great selection of Japanese and American oriented options from a meat and booze perspective.  Thoughtfully walked through the nuances of Wagyu beef, the processes behind it, and what you're supposed to look for as a consumer.  We loved all of the food and the service was excellent.  Overall, strongly recommend.

review_153.Review: The steak was cooked good. The appetizers were good. That was a highlight of the night. The rest sucked. as soon as we (6 of us) sat down the guy asked us what we wanted to drink and then pointed straight at a $300 bottle of wine. Putting the host in the spot. He then brings out flight of Japanese steaks that costs $550 and begins to rave.  Extremely uncomfortable.he didn't feel like a waiter, but he felt like a salesman trying to upsell. I was just there for steak dinner. Instead I felt like I was shamed because I didn't choose what he suggested.  Never felt so ashamed to for choosing $70 steak, $17 fries and $18 a glass wine, and a $20 souffle.  After tax and tip, the bill came out to about $900 after for the 6 of us.  Never felt so small spending so much.  Fool me once shame on you, fool me twice shame on me.  Not going back here.

review_154.Review: The Waygu carpaccio was incredible. The Waugu steak should have been an overpriced appetizer. Beautiful dinner but pricey for what it was.

review_155.Review: Wasn’t sure how pricey things would get, but man was it worth every penny. Amazing service, wonderful food, and a beautiful environment. Recommend to anyone looking for a little higher price date night!

review_156.Review: Didn’t have the way go.  Bad mistake.  The bone in rib eye less than 2nd rate.

review_157.Review: While the food and ambience were amazing, the service was so poor I don’t know if I could recommend this place to anyone. We had been recommended by someone who works for MasterCard and takes his clients here - I had to let him know he might want to think otherwise!! It took 45 minutes to even get our first drink. The birthday boy ordered a martini right when we sat down and that took 25 minutes. We sat before other nearby tables and we saw our waiter constantly at those tables but we literally had to wave our arms to get him over to our table. People had come in and eaten and paid their bill and we were still waiting for our food. Once we got our food though - it was all amazing! Everyone loved their steaks and I had the Chilean sea bass which was so good! The honey shrimp appetizer was delicious as well. They also did some cutr plates with happy birthday on it for the birthday boy! Just too bad about the service as I can’t recommend anyone coming back here. There were 5 of us all in a variety of service industries and we were all taken aback by the lack of service to our table.

review_158.Review: Unusually poor service. Made the high price point seem especially unreasonable

review_159.Review: Steaks were sub par. 30 dollars an once and drizzled all kinds of stuff on top?  Not a fan. Over engineered and did not hit the mark.

review_160.Review: You go all that way and don't have the Wagyu??  Our family split a 4oz. Rib Eye...... It's really different.  We all loved it and wished we were richer!  Also, the Carpaccio was excellent.  Our daughter said, "I loved everything".  She's the least adventurous, but picky.  She's right.  Everything is super solid and the steak speaks for itself.  Not exotic, but very high quality food. The wine that we had was excellent...   ....the house by the glass.  And I highly recommend the Japanese Whisky flight.

review_161.Review: The food was absolutely delicious.  The waitress was a very knowledgeable and gave us a background on the different meats.  She was very engaging and helpful in giving us recommendations.

review_163.Review: Great food!  Great service!  Great experience!

review_164.Review: The wagyu is fantastic, as is the service.  The prices are sky-high for the wagyu, but for an amazing treat it is worth an indulgence.  The noise is a little much, many of the booths have seats that face each other, if you get a big mouth near you the noise level can be close to deafening.  Just be prepared for a budget busting, but fantastic experience of wagyu and possible rock concert like noise levels if you are surrounded by loud mouths.

review_165.Review: Our server, Katherine was great.  The A5 Experience was a once-in-lifetime fantastic epic event for my birthday.

review_166.Review: One of the best steakhouses in town. A bit pricy but worth every dollar. Great for business meals

review_167.Review: Full disclosure: we didn't try the Waygu items which they are known for.  That said, we stuck with the "regular" items which we'd hope would be a notch below but still pretty decent. Honestly, the prime rib, NY strip, and ribeye were a bit disappointing. Nothing memorable, and meat wasn't as tender, flavorful and juicy as we expected. We also tried the filet which was probably the best out of all the steak entrees we had.  Sides were very good however - sweet potato gnocchi and mashed potatoes w/maple bacon were standouts. Service that was slow and lackluster. Waiter seemed to be distracted by other tables and more attentive with them. We watched as servers at other tables asked if they'd ever been there, then went on to explain the menu and how it works. We got none of that. Wine glasses stayed empty and food took an unusually long time to come out. All said and done, we liked the ambiance and would be willing to go back to give them another try... with much lower expectations.

review_168.Review: The Steak and the drink are the best. The service are great.

review_169.Review: I tried to cancel my reservation and it was a $25 charge per person to cancel, which was really frustrating because it would of been $200 just to cancel the reservation. Because it was too much to cancel, we still had to go to dinner. When we got to the restaurant there were only 3 other tables with people the whole night. Not a very fun atmosphere, but the food was fine along with the service.

review_170.Review: 1st time here. Arrived early so we had some drinks. All very delicious. And the food.....everything we had was delicious. The server, Benjamin was so awesome.  Always smiling even when he was busy.  Great service,  great food, great drinks.

review_171.Review: Overpriced for overall quality of the wagyu. Gave us upset stomachs.Roka Akor is best for the price

review_173.Review: Yes I would recommend the food to friends but the service was terrible, we had a white lady as our waiter not sure what her name was, but she valued the people next to us more than my parter and I, not sure why? But her manager kept serving for us instead of our actual waiter, she did not deserve a good tip.

review_174.Review: How does a steak house screw up two steaks by the time my husband and other guest got their steaks back which after 25 minutes I think they would get it right we were done with our dinner Very disappointing

review_175.Review: Unique steakhouse offers much more than the big chains - more selection and more options.Steak Tartare was quite good and artfully presented - could have used a few more toast points, but honestly the house made bacon bread was also a great backstop for the beef.The steaks have different toppings based on the cut - ours came with truffle foam and Boursin, we also sampled poutine with cheese curds - I preferred the later as it really amped the flavor profile of our tender, yet lean filet.Superb service by Hana was icing on the cake.

review_176.Review: The steak is the reason to come here. Fantastic!  Also excellent we’re the scallops and meatballs.  Salad and desserts were nothing special.   Our server and all of the staff were informative, friendly and attentive and really made the occasion special.

review_177.Review: We really like our waitress (Rebekka) she was great help and very informative about the food as well as the history of the Wagu.

review_178.Review: Great atmosphere, food are fine, but the price are not worthy

review_179.Review: Excellent service!  The manager Mcdermott was particularly a joy to interact with!

review_180.Review: Beautiful plating  and a NY cut A5 steak that melts with every bite. Nice finish with an amazing banana soufflé with coffee ice cream!

review_181.Review: I found this little gem of a place last year.  I went in, sat at the bar and enjoyed a 4oz steak and beverage. I returned with a friend 2 days later. The staff remembered me and treated me like a queen. Fast forward a year, visit to San Francisco for the weekend, I returned for dinner with my mother. Ben, one of the servers, REMEMBERED me from a year before!!! He remembered I was with a girl friend and why I was up in SF!! Again, treated like a queen! Thanks for your excellent service, individualized service, yummy food and drinks!!! It became my favorite steak place last year and remains my favorite in San Francisco.

review_182.Review: Food was and cocktails were great as always. Service was great as well! Love coming to this place!

review_183.Review: Ben our server was extremely knowledgeable and takes a lot of pride in his work, we were thrilled to have him guide us through this amazing restaurant experience.

review_184.Review: Great food and we had an amazing waiter. Everything was perfect!

review_185.Review: Excellent service! I couldn't decide on a wine and was allowed to sample 2 kinds to assist with my decision! The way is the best we have had! Would definitely recommend and go back again!

review_186.Review: Overall the steak was OK. Not great, not the worst but not cooked to my liking. I had the T-Bone and from a discount steak place I’d honestly have found less fat on the fillet and more tender sirloin so really when you are paying probably 2-3 times more here you’d expect more.Maybe their more expensive options are what they want you to go for but if the mid-range menu pieces aren’t a focus then why have them at all let alone at that price. I’d recommend the Cheesecake Factory over this unfortunately.Service, decor and ambience was perfect.

review_187.Review: The food was amazing and our waiter was great. My wife and I appreciate his attentiveness. I gave four stars because it is overpriced even for a Wagyu steak. I enjoyed everything else other than the price.

review_189.Review: The food was overly priced for the quality. As a steak person I feel like adding all the extra stuff to the steak takes away from the meat. If you truly have high quality meat there is no need to add the sauces and and tater tots on top of a steak.

review_191.Review: A phenomenal experience from start to finish . . . we both enjoyed that Kobe . . . and the service couldn’t have been any better.

review_192.Review: This is hands down my new favorite place to eat and hangout in SF. I love the food and the ambiance is excellent. Definitely recommended for a romantic upscale date or a great dinner with friends.

review_193.Review: Food was horrible.  High priced and bad steak. Was overdone and flavorless. A lot of it was masked with disgusting sauces.  I’ve had better steak at outback.

review_194.Review: It wasn’t noisy because it was empty. The appetizers were amazing but we came for steak...with “steakhouse” fully in the name one would expect their steak to be spectacular but the thick cut really took away from any flavor. They served us a chewy steak. The lobster tempura was amazing though, as well as their cocktails.

review_195.Review: The food and service was amazing ! I would highly recommend this to anyone looking for a great food and service

review_196.Review: service was outstanding, servers very knowledgable, food was incredible, very very pricey but expected that going in.

review_198.Review: Such an experience and our waiter was the best! Will have to comeback again, as everything was great, the truffle fries were such a great start, the meat, amazing, and their drinks just added to it. The dessert topped it off!

review_199.Review: First time here. Love it. Great experience. I like the food and service. One thing I think they can improve a little more is the prime rib because the prime rib is a little disappointment. There is some part of the prime rib is not chewable. Overall, I have a great time celebrating my birthday here. Definitely want to come back and try the happy hours.

review_200.Review: Dinner was executed perfectly per usual. Noted we were celebrating my husbands promotion at work and we’re gifted a delicious dessert after our fabulous meal.

review_201.Review: We celebrated our 23rd wedding anniversary with great food & drink  The awesome service & the surprise anniversary dessert made it extra special!!  Thank you for making it a memorable evening for us. 🥰

review_202.Review: Steak and prime rib were excellent. Service was great. Wine selection superb. Only reason they don’t get full stars for food was that they served Chinese broccoli with cheese. Fusion I understand, but Asian inspired food with dairy never works...also wasn’t clear from the menu that they would serve it like that. My date (non-Asian) was also taken aback...otherwise a fantastic evening. I didn’t send it back, we just tried our best to eat it

review_203.Review: Absolutely recommend this 5-star dining experience!  Incredible service, excellent food quality and a lovely setting.  The best of the best.

review_204.Review: Amazing steak but paired with enough jellybean foods to make Charlie from the gang salivate.  More milk please.

review_205.Review: The food is amazing, the service is superb! Dry Aged T-Bone and the Bone In Ribeye are a must have! Definitely will make a trip back.

review_206.Review: The environment was very noisy, the steaks were just okay, but the appetizer scallops were amazing, and the service was wonderful.

review_207.Review: We had the private dining room, I highly recommend if holding a business meeting or private setting!

review_210.Review: We drove up from LA cause we got bored of LA dinner, so we were like “let’s get dinner in SF” haha

review_211.Review: Waiter knew the menu and the food very well. He  kept a smile on his face, stayed checking in us. Everything was just perfect.

review_212.Review: Review is long overdue but we really liked our dining experience here, definitely will be back again!

review_213.Review: It was my boyfriends birthday it was a great experience and amazing food

review_214.Review: Overall a great dining experience. The only thing noticeable was it was really loud and hard to hear throughout my conversation

review_215.Review: When we arrived, we were seated outside of the main area in a dark corner when there were clearly tables available. Then, when we ordered, the server was clearly trying to push the most expensive dishes. She suggested the lobster tempura - it arrived over cooked and the flavor was lackluster. The $80 ribeye we ordered was not seasoned nor was it tender. We ordered it medium rare. Also, they didn’t slice it for us. Typically, when you go to a steakhouse and you order a 32oz bone-in ribeye, they slice it for you. Not the best experience and I will not be returning.

review_216.Review: 2nd time in a month. Great place to host business guests as it’s unique and fun.

review_217.Review: Great service, a bit pricey, especially wine list. Great location.

review_218.Review: It was kind of loud, and they ran out of the steak I wanted. It was only 7:30 too. The steak was decent, but I could have gone to Outback Steakhouse for the same quality of steak.

review_219.Review: This place is always an awesome experience. Today lacked a little. Will still come back, maybe an off night for the staff

review_220.Review: I love steak. I love steakhouses and frequent them often. I’m from out of state so no conflict of interest. I can’t think of many places I’d put above this one. Probably one I’d say that ties is Angus Barm in NC, but only in terms of steak quality. This place had a much better environment. The T-bone was falling off the bone and tasted amazing. Was plenty big enough.

review_221.Review: Love the ambiance, whiskey and steaks. Really overpriced but def fun for how unique it is.

review_223.Review: 5A5 made our night very special.  Ben was an EXCELLENT waiter!

review_224.Review: Server was an odd guy who seemed a little clueless and absent. Food was great, a5 wagyu was delicious. For the money I’d expect a server to be on point.

review_225.Review: Food was awesome, steaks and fish and apps. Service was great. It is just a little loud is the only negative I have but I would endure the noise anytime because the food and service was great

review_226.Review: Outstanding food, drink, service, & atmosphere at a premium price.  Well worth going for extra special occasions.

review_227.Review: Good wine and food, but for the price I’ve had better steaks in SF and our fillets were over cooked

review_229.Review: The food was alright, not all that great to be honest.

review_230.Review: Our waiter Ben  was very knowledgeable and helpful on the wine selection wagyu beef suggestions.  Both of which were very very good.

review_231.Review: Yummyyy and they have great service !

review_232.Review: Total tourist trap with overpriced basic food and horrible service

review_233.Review: Total trap. Have no idea how the ratings are so high. Very underwhelming food, terrible service, average drinks. This place can’t last forever if they don’t get their act together. I liked their overall food concept but was so let down by nearly everything.

review_235.Review: Great restaurant and great food! Great vibe with excellent service

review_236.Review: Great service and delicious food! Sweet potato gnocchi is a must!!

review_237.Review: An outstanding experience! Ali was the best and we've never had better steak!! Thank you for the wonderful evening.

review_238.Review: A phenomenal meal all around. Incredible, first-rate service.TO make a long story short 4 of us shared the Wagyu experience which has 4 pieces (one of each cut of Wagyu) of steak that we shared with 3 sides. They were all incredible. Wagyu is everything you think it can be and more, and my favorite was the rib eye. It's about $38 an oz but worth it for a special occasion.

review_240.Review: It did start rocky as our reservation was at 7:45pm. We got there on time and checked in with the hostess. She mentioned that it is backed by at least 20 mins, so we waited in the bar area. 45 mins went by and we noticed that people that came in after us started getting seated before us. I walked up to the hostess and asked how much longer it would take, i gave my name, she was scrolling through the list and asked “You checked in with me right?”  I nodded yes, then she continued to scroll through her list. I mentioned i did check in at 7:45 and it was already 8:30. She said please give me a couple of more minutes to get you a table. After that we were then seated. Other than that, the dinning experience was great for a valentines day night.

review_242.Review: Everything was delicious. Great food great service very attentive.

review_243.Review: Overall all good - Service was good but Resturant was busy so service was impacted ..,this is the time where manager needs to jump in and help the staff ..

review_244.Review: Way over priced for what it was. Although, the service was great but too noisy to have a nice conversation at your table. Much better restaurants in San Francisco to go to!

review_245.Review: I loved ALL of it, and I left so full!  Great service, great food, and great atmosphere. I have a couple of special needs (omissions) with the way I eat, and not only was it easy to navigate the menu, but once they knew what I needed, folks really looked out for me during service.  Wonderful!  Can’t wait for another Date Night, or a big family celebration!  I’ll be back!

review_246.Review: Loved the place! Came here for our date night. The only thing that was a bit disappointing was that we ordered the rib eye to be medium rare and it was a bit over cooked. I think it was more medium well... We were a little disappointed because this is a steak house. That being said our waitress was great, apps were great and enjoyed the ambiance. We would come back!

review_247.Review: Nice place. Overpriced. Overvalued. Nice for a special occasion if you're impressed by ambiance and flashy wealth. You pay for the Wagyu selection which from what we tasted, was delicious. Our service was pretty poor and from the visible tables near us, that was the popular opinion.

review_248.Review: The steak didn't worth the price.  I was surprised that my bill came before server asked us if we like to have dessert and coffee.

review_249.Review: The server wasn't very friendly or patient. They were sold out of 3 dishes I was interested in. Ambiance was nice, but too loud. Food was really good, but somehow felt a little lacking in composition.

review_250.Review: Amazing experience from start to finish. The team here is working on all levels

review_251.Review: Excellent food and service! Outstanding for Wagyu lovers and the “Where’s the Beef?” Veggie platter was perfect for vegetarians -artfully plated and delicious.

review_252.Review: Made reservations for a 30th birthday dinner, put in the back, not the main restaurant area. Service was very slow...seemed understaffed. Food was good but the location and service left us unhappy...we will not return.

review_253.Review: The waiter was intense, and an easy individual to dislike.  Without qualification, we were directed to some of the most expensive wines on the menu.  Finding something sub $100 was challenging.The quality of food did not justify the price - a chewy steak, covered in BBQ sauce an egg!   In summary, an expensive restaurant failing, on this occasion, to deliver a premium experience.

review_255.Review: overall a good meal.  Lobster tempura amazing, tuffel fries great.   Prime rib was ok.   Really the worst part was the noise.  My girlfriend and I felt it difficult to have a conversation.

review_256.Review: Best steak I’ve ever had...A5 Wagyu amazing!!! Amazing dinner in every way!

review_257.Review: Delicious steak, it was my fiance's birthday and we were treated very well.

review_258.Review: Great place for a get together dinner for me and my old college mates.

review_259.Review: We came here for a birthday dinner, and the food did not disappoint. However, we noticed that the level of service we received was nowhere near the service given to all the tables around us. Our waiter, and other waiters we noticed, were constantly checking in on their guests and seeing what was needed. However, at some point, we did not see our water for almost half an hour. We were not updated on why the food was taking so long to be prepared either. A simple update would have sufficed. The food was great, but for the price I expected much better service.

review_260.Review: Steak was excellent- the most expensive I’ve ever had, however it was Kobe A5 and it was awesome! Servicewas great - highly recommended

review_261.Review: Amazing rib eye, amazing quality food and worth the price. The absolute best!!

review_262.Review: First time here won’t be the last. Very very great service, food, drinks. Scenery very well lit, relaxing talking amongst family and friends. Wagyu is a must!

review_263.Review: Great business dinner with attentive staff and prompt service and seating. I came early on Saturday night (630pm) to avoid peak Sat night and was relatively quiet.

review_264.Review: Was not impressed! Took my wife there in January for her birthday and didn't have a great experience. The hostess was rude with my wife to start with. The waiter we had was creepy.  It felt like he was hitting on my 14 year old niece every time he came to the table. The food was ok! Way overpriced in my opinion. I've had a better steak dinner at The Stinking Rose! Definitely was a birthday to forget for my wife. Will never go back there. Too bougie for our taste.

review_266.Review: We've dined here several times.  Each time was spectacular!  Service was on-point.  Food was outstanding.  We didn't go too crazy this time.  4 of us and only 2 ordered the wagyu.   For a Sunday, they were very busy.  Ran out of prime rib, but I ordered the bone-in rib eye and it hit the spot...it's HUGE.  Steaks were great, but I think their sides really stand out as well.  We devoured them.  Fun place...Go.

review_267.Review: The Wagyu Beef, service, ambiance was spectacular.

review_268.Review: i've been to 5A5 10+ times over the years, but the food has gone downhill. The last trip was 3 of us - shared 2 steaks, 2 salads, one appetizer and two sides and 2 beer each and the bill was $350!!! and the food was lousy. The steak wasn't flavorful and we order the ribeye. The salads were sub par. The beer was cold and the service was amazing, but unless they improve the food i would be hard pressed to go back.

review_269.Review: There are many other choices besides just steaks. We loved the appetizers!!! The waiter who waited on us was so friendly and acknowledgeable. Overall we had a good time and really enjoyed the delicious food! We definitely will come back.

review_270.Review: The TBone was cooked perfectly. However, the sauce with egg on top was too overpowering in flavor. Enjoyed it but next time I will have the sauce provided on the side.

review_271.Review: Food is good. Price tag... maybe not worth it. Our waiter had horrible manners. He was curt and condescending. For what reason.. I have no idea seeing as he was serving and not being served. But maybe that was the issue... he was serving a black family who spent several hundred dollars on a meal. Sorry I can't remember his name, but buyer beware.

review_272.Review: 3 star for service is strictly for the bartender on Christmas Eve. Sooo incredibly rude and dismissive. It was shocking!

review_273.Review: I am into whiskey and scotch so I wanted to taste the Hibiki 12 yr but they didn't have it to drink. I went with the Hibiki 17 yr. It was great but I prefer the Hibiki Harmony. I started with the beet salad and my girlfriend had the American wagyu meatballs. When I saw them I knew they were soft and flavorful and they did not disappoint. We brought our own St. Supery Cab. It paired great with the NY strip and the dry-aged T-Bone that I had. The steaks were like butter. Maybe next time we will splurge for the Japanese Waygu. SUPERB!!

review_274.Review: Excellent wagyu steaks, the 4 steak tasting platter was awesome, service very good. My only complaint is it is very expensive. But definitely a dining experience.

review_275.Review: I was visiting San Francisco for my birthday and 5A5 came highly recommended and it was great service and food

review_276.Review: Spent our annual holiday dinner here and it was nothing short of amazing. Service, food, drinks... it was all good!

review_277.Review: What a pleasant surprise....Great food and service.From start to finish a very nice experience. Our server Scott, made sure our evening was a memorable one. The prime rib and sea bass dinners were absolutely exquisite. Just go and enjoy.

review_278.Review: Had to wait 30 mins past our reservation.  The steak was not flavorful, they add way too many toppings to make up for the lack of flavor in the meat. For the price I was expecting it to be the best steak I’ve had, and I was let down.

review_279.Review: Expensive but worth it! Great service and food.

review_280.Review: Amazing prime rib and the best oysters I've ever had in my life! This will be a must when I visit San Francisco again.

review_281.Review: Service was absolutely phenomenal and the servers went above and beyond to explain the menu in great detail to ensure our experience was world class.

review_282.Review: Fantastic lay-out and service, but over-priced for the quality of food and drink.

review_283.Review: We were there for a birthday celebration. An awkward event occurred with one of our guests which resulted in a few comped drinks (which was appreciated). Lobster tempura was delicious, most of the steaks were prepared perfectly, the truffle Mac and cheese as well as the creamy spinach were very good . The birthday boys bone-in ribeye was rare as opposed to medium so that was disappointing for him. He ate what he could and brought home the remaining steak (the majority) and seared it in a cast iron later that evening. Overall , a good experience.

review_284.Review: Way too loud. Practically shouting at my own table and they couldn’t hear me.

review_285.Review: Disappointing! Great ambience, attentive wait staff, but poor performance in the kitchen. Really bizarre choices with respect to sauces and stale/rancid garlic on the prime rib. It appears that 5A5 is using choice rather than prime beef and the filet was dry. The St. Emilion was rougher than most Merlots and not as good as it should have been. Loved the jazz, but it could have been less intrusive (overly loud). Walked into 5A5 with high expectations which weren't at all met. As noted, the kitchen needs a change of staff.

review_286.Review: It was my girlfriend’s birthday and I had planned for us to go there a week in advance. We arrived early to our reservation and they seated us which was amazing since it was around a little bit after prime time hour. After about 5 minutes of waiting we were served water and our waiter comes over and speaks to us about the 5a5 experience. Granted it sounded phenomenal but it was a little pushy, I get it though. After we turned down the 5A5 experience that’s when I noticed that our waiter stopped paying attention to us. After another 8-10 minute wait he decides to come back and take our order. We decided to order the duck soup, scallops, t-bone New York and filet mignon which were all amazing. We typically judge a place by how often they fill our water which I think speaks to how attentive the staff is. We waited with empty glasses and eventually ask for water, this happened two occasions. The restaurant was not busy. Our waiter constantly walked around and made eye contact with us, but never once offered to refill our water unless we waived him down or another staff member. The food itself was very good. As we were getting full we once again were passively waiting for the waiter to come by and check in on us or at least ask us how our meal is going. Stopped by once to check in and not to be seen for another 20 minutes. After we finally get his attention and ask for some boxes and the check he brings out a desert menu for us to look at. When I originally made the reservation I had made a note to ask if they could bring a little dessert out for my girlfriend. Right as we are getting ready to pay (waiting for 15 min for him to grab my credit card) he finally comes to our table with the birthday dessert for my girlfriend. We take our time to eat the dessert, again with empty water glasses. Another 15 min go by after we’ve finished and our server comes back with our check. All in all, food was great, but the lack of attentive service doesn’t make this place worth.

review_287.Review: Good place good service! ...need to try another food soon!

review_288.Review: Exotic meat well prepared steak style with good service. Nice side dishes and ambiance.

review_289.Review: Excellent steaks, even if you don't pony up for the namesake A5 Wagyu or hybrid.   Interesting combinations and well executed sides.

review_290.Review: This was our second time here. Our first was for my wife's birthday 4 years ago and we loved it so much we had to come back. Everything was amazing. We got there before our reservations so we sent to the bar the get a drink while we waited and had a great conversation with the bar manager. Super friendly friendly staff and the food is off the charts good!

review_291.Review: Great place and we’d all go back.  Food ranged between 4& 5 stars.  Service was too notch.

review_292.Review: For a 500 dollar meal I expect attentive and professional service.  We sat waiting for water and menus  and watched tables around us get served immediately, while we sat and tried to get someone on the floor s attention.  Waitress said she didn’t see us ...we were again left waiting to place our food order while she was off in conversation with another waiter.  That type of treatment ruins my experience.

review_293.Review: The hostess was welcoming and the menu surprisingly interesting.  Unfortunately, the waiter focused upon upselling the Wagyu beef, and was clearly less attentive after we ordered routine steaks.

review_294.Review: Have been here about 5 times and unfortunately, this time was disappointing.  Waiter spent ten minutes over explaining meats and specials - for a business dinner, just too intrusive.   And of course, pushing the $400 per person menu.  Was disappointing indeed.

review_295.Review: Food and service was good,   but I have to complain about something trivial.  I have been to 100s of restaurants  in  SF ( less and more expensive ) ,  never have I been asked to show my id after having my credit card taken.  It may be policy or whatnot,  but it really rubbed me the wrong way.

review_296.Review: This place is very good. I cannot think of one thing that I ate that I did not like. I specifically enjoyed the sliders. This also felt a lot more casual than most high priced steak places. There were a lot of families and a lot less people dressed up in business atire despite being near the financial district. Overall, it was a great experience. I'm already planning a trip back!

review_297.Review: Food was great!!!  Drinks were good too, i would go back again

review_299.Review: Waiter’s speech was strictly rote, dishes overpriced and only ok. Hostess was very nice.

review_300.Review: The food was wonderful, but thought it was very expensive even through it was the top of the line beef.The $60 to $180 price for the wagyu beef, was more than I was willing to pay.The creativity of most of the meal, however was wonderful and tasty.

review_302.Review: My dry aged t-bone was 24oz but I’d say 6oz was actually edible, the rest was bone or very tough.  Should have went with the ribeye or filet.

review_303.Review: So we went to 5a5 steak lounge to celebrate my hubby's 40th birthday.  We were greeted by a friendly hostess and seated fairly quickly.  There were several seats open and we were seated at the smallest table in the whole restaurant.  There were other couples enjoying booths and cozying up to one another and being that I made this reservation over a month ago stating it was my hubby's 40th birthday,  I had hoped for better seating.  That aside... our experience was great.  The ambiance is a little loud but it's a beautiful restaurant and very hip.  Lots of young people.  I had read some reviews before coming so we started with the hamachi spoon and the lobster tempura appetizers which were both fantastic! For dinner we each ordered the bone-in rib eye. There is no indication of size on the menu.  This thing was huge!  About 1.5 in thick and had to weigh 24oz. It was more like a tomahawk steak. The waiter did ask us if we were sharing and we said no,  but never mentioned  that it was enough to feed 2-3 people.  That's ok.  I made steak and eggs for breakfast the next day and my 12yr old son was stoked! ...And the steak was delicious!   In the future I think we'll just share. We had the truffle mac and cheese and pesto asparagus as our sides and both were delicious.  I also want to mention 2 times during our meal one of the chefs in the kitchen brought out a little bite appetizer, compliments of the chef.  That was a nice touch.  I had the raspberry cheesecake for dessert and it was great.  My hubby didn't want dessert but they brought him out a beautiful plate with a tiny chocolate cake bite.   Very sweet.  It was a bit on the pricey side but what great restaurant in SF isn't?  [About $400] overall I would definitely recommend coming here for a nice specialoccasion.

review_304.Review: The A5 Wagyu Beef Filet is divine and cooked to perfection.

review_305.Review: Full transparency - the bar and drinks were a bit disappointing and concerned me about my choice for a new client Open World dinner.  I got a kettle one dirty martini, very dirty.  The bartender and waiter both heard me loud and clear because it came exactly as ordered “very dirty”.  That said, it was served in a champagne glass.  Therefore, not only was the presentation underwhelming (glass not chilled nor was the drink chilled) but the portion was probably the smallest I’ve ever received...at any restaurant.  I almost suggested leaving but read too many great reviews about the food.  Our waitress was excellent as well as the food!  Thank goodness things took a 180 turn as Oracle is expected to provide our clients a great dining experience.

review_306.Review: The steak was bland, overpriced for the flavor and quality. It looks and feels like a cheap hotel lobby restaurant. Do yourself a favor and go to Ruth Chris.

review_307.Review: The amuse bouche of hummus and pita didn’t make any sense for a Japanese steakhouse, also weird for a start to an expensive meal. Appetizers of hamachi crudo and lobster tempura were good, the crudo would make much more sense as an amuse bouche. My New York strip wasn’t very good, my husbands bone in ribeye was good. The server totally forgot about us mid-meal and we had to wave someone down to get our check a couple times. Overall the value isn’t there, much better steakhouses abound in SF.

review_308.Review: Second time in 3 months and it did not disappoint!  Loved every bite.  We both agreed it is now our new favorite place to dine in the City.  Can’t wait to bring friends next time.

review_309.Review: Very pricey for what you get... service was mediocre. Food is ok but not fit for the price.

review_310.Review: Decor & ambience at this restaurant were very nice.  Service was excellent.  The downside? The food.  We ordered Ribeye Wagyu and Prime Rib with 1 appetizer and 2 side dishes for the two of us.  The Wagyu was nice,  but not outstanding for the price ($150+). The prime rib was a disappointment as it had a lot of tendon such that I ended up leaving more than half of it on the plate.  For $37, I think I could get better prime rib elsewhere, and yet this is a restaurant known for its beef?  So my conclusion is this may be a nice place to bring business clients, but not so much for a couple having an evening meal.  With 2 drinks, our total bill came out to more than $320 before tip.

review_311.Review: Great service, slightly over priced but I would come back for another special occasion.

review_312.Review: Great food and geat service.  We celebrate our anniversary here every year.

review_313.Review: Horrendously overpriced.  Quality of meat was just so-so, everything is drowned in sauces masking the true flavor of the meat.  Very expensive wine list.  Unisex bathroom was in serious need of attention.  Overall if you want to spend this kind of money in San Francisco there are way better places to go.  Do not recommend.

review_314.Review: A5 wagu NY Strip was worth every dollar I spent on it! If you like steak - you must have it at least once!

review_315.Review: Dined for the first time on a Friday in October 2018. Tried out their happy hour to check out the restaurant first and was pleasantly surprised with everything they had. The interior was very loungey, the menu obviously with a Japanese bent. Happy hour options valid only in Lounge, we were first sat at the table but was moved to Lounge. Service was decent and we enjoyed the food.We ordered Truffle Fries, Roast Beef Panini w/ Tomato Dashi Bisque, and Baby Back Ribs and they were all great. Beef Panini had a decent amount of beef with the right mixture of Provolone in nice grill-marked paninis. Bisque was rich and tasty. Baby Back Rib had gochujang added to the traditional BBQ sauce and came out as an interesting mix. Even the coleslaw with the rib was one of the best I had ever had. Would like to come back again!

review_316.Review: The noise level was almost unbearable. I couldn’t hear our server and my ears were ringing when we left. The food was awesome, especially the wagyu. Try the Mac and cheese. Crazy!!

review_317.Review: Don’t listen to any reactionary nonsense from your server : GET THE BEST WAGYU FILET either four or eight ounces. Unreal Flavor.Also: do not get the sampler. It’s a rip, see paragraph the first.The creamed spinach is the best in SF.The Wagyu 5A Filet is the best steak.I’d bring Wine, because the bill will give enough pause without bottle shock addenda-Great tables for four FOR TWO HERE!!!Super comfy. Good staff. Thx 5A!!

review_318.Review: We celebrated our three-year wedding anniversary, and I wanted a special dinner with my wife: they delivered. Service was excellent, the food was amazing, and they even provided with complementary champagne and dessert. I would definitely return.

review_319.Review: Regular menu items (non Waygu cuts) too expensive with side dishes charged as al a carte.  For 36-66$ dudes should be included or drop entree prices 8$

review_320.Review: Service and food was amazing! Highly recommend for a nice evening out.

review_321.Review: My experience that was sub par. The ambiance was soo outdated... As an interior designer I was dying.  The steak was good but not anything outstanding. The service was great but my overall experience was "meh" for the prices.

review_322.Review: We've dined here several times as the owners are also the owners of the Modernist private social club on Steuart St.,of which we are members.  Great steaks, wonderful and knowledgeable service makes for a memorable dining experience.  They offer three levels of meat quality, including the quintessential A5 wagyu cuts.  Offered is a tasting option of 4 cuts of A5 beef for about 600 bucks.  We ordered this the last time we were here, but not this time.  Had the huge rib eye and a couple of cuts of the NY and filet wagyu this time.  All were phenomenal.  Highly recommend meat lovers come to enjoy the passion of beef.

review_323.Review: Everything was absolutely perfect. Had about 10 items total from the menu and every single dish was delicious or better. Highly recommend to anyone looking for a nice dinner.

review_324.Review: Go for the steak, stay for the edemame, lobster tempura and whiskey cocktails.
