review_325.Review: We tried the lobster tempura (tasty, but not to die for), Wagyu filet (tasty) and Ribeye (meh) and the mashed potatoes and mushrooms as sides.  The sides weren't anything special, the mushrooms were too sweet.  We basically walked away with a big bill and not feeling too great about it.  Server was attentive until food was delivered, then he got very busy table.

review_326.Review: Everything was amazing It was my wife’s birthday and she felt like royalty in there thanks a lot guys!!! The T bone and oysters were delicious!!

review_327.Review: It was a birthday dinner for a friend. There was a table of 6, they were very loud...

review_328.Review: The food was delicious. Tried the duck soup, the truffle fries, lobster tempura, salads, tartar and oyesters as apps. All amazing. Then family shared the Wagyu A5 steak and it just melted in our mouths. I would say we all prefer the A5 steaks without the toppings (cheese, risotto, etc). Good meat should stand on its own. But it was amazing.

review_329.Review: Food was yummy. The lobster tempura is to die for.

review_330.Review: Exciting experience, I love that they had the option to try all 4 meats. They also bring the meats out beforehand to show them to you.

review_331.Review: We’ve eaten here many times. Never disappoints. Great service from everyone and excellent food. I wouldn’t recommend this place for kids but we brought our kid and they made her feel welcome.

review_332.Review: Absolutely an experience for sure. Best place to celebrate with that special someone! Service and attentiveness was phenomenal! Food was amazing!

review_333.Review: Service was awful as untrained and unfriendly staff was asked to work at this steakhouse. Each course was  late and cold. I will not recommend this restaurant.

review_334.Review: Awesome food and service.  Can’t wait to go back!

review_335.Review: We can not stop taking about how the overall experience was. We will definitely be back.

review_336.Review: We went here for my birthday, had a great time. The food was good, the staff for friendly and welcoming and in general, the place had a perfect vibe. We are going to come back with friends; we are sure they will love the food and the atmosphere of the restaurant.

review_337.Review: We had a group of six in town as tourists and picked 5A5 as it was in close proximity to the hotel we stayed at. I was pleased with the service! We had a seat at the bar for a few casual cocktails before our reservation - all staff was friendly and knowledgeable. I had both fish and steak - both of which were melt-in-your-mouth delicious! Good tequila selection and great ambiance. Would recommend 5A5 for a more intimate gathering as it's a tad on the romantic side.

review_338.Review: Everything was great. Food was amazing. They didn’t remember that it was for a birthday occasion even though I put it on the reservation, so would be good to remind the host/waiter that when you get there.

review_339.Review: Appetizer portions were good size and the lobster tempura was so fresh and cooked well!  Beef dishes were cooked to preference perfectly! We shared the peachy dessert and it was heavenly!  We definitely recommend 5A5!

review_340.Review: I had a great time at dinner with my friends. Food was amazing as expected, service was wonderful and I can definitely see myself coming back.

review_341.Review: We love a good steak so on our trip to san fransisco for our anniversary we thought we would try this spot.  My husband and I were blown away... seriously, our eyes rolled back after every bite of either the A5 steaks we had, or the truffle Mac & cheese, or the mashed potatoes, or the asparagus!   This was the most amazing dinner we have ever had!

review_342.Review: This was honestly one of the worst dining experiences I have ever had and easily the worst value meal I can think of.  I'll preface the rest of this review by saying I do not mind paying premium prices generally associated with fine dining, but for food to be expensive and waste otherwise amazing produce while providing nothing but disappointment is another thing entirely.2 x cuts of wagyu ruined by poor cooking and unimaginative, disrespectful recipes.1 lobster ruined by throwing it in a discount mac and cheese mix. 1 serve of powdered mash potato and a chicken as dry the Sahara and you've got a perfect recipe for wasting $600.They should not be able to purchase or sell wagyu of any level, the kitchen should not be cooking outside of an outback steakhouse. If I owned or managed this establishment I would be doing a hard reset or working out if a steakhouse was really my wheelhouse. This review is not directed at the front of house.

review_343.Review: Best steak we ever ate. My doughter (12) finished her rib eye steak in some minutes only...

review_344.Review: Unless you’re prepared to spend $150 on 4oz of Japanese Waygu beef this place isn’t worth it. Food was just ok and overpriced.

review_345.Review: When we first arrived we were seated at the back of the restaurant, pretty dark and hidden. We noticed some tables had white tablecloths and others did not...ours. We then asked to be seated elsewhere, preferably under the beautiful lit up the ceiling, and we were. Pros: decent server, fancy overpriced cocktails, and my company. Cons: fatty filet, no mash potatoes available and a limp Cesar salad. For the price you pay, the ambiance is really all you get. Location and vibes, cool, but the food was mediocre.

review_347.Review: The Mac & Cheese is the BEST we've ever tasted... the rib-eye, a little too chewy, and the gravy should be put on the side... Good ambience and a nice place to try for a special occasion!

review_348.Review: I’ve been here five times and every time it is a great new experience.  The first time i came Ali was my server and my husband and i will forever request him from now on.  His knowledge and advice are always a go to and he’s so calm and patient a great observant of his guest that you truly feel like you are at a five star restaurant.  The good quality is impecable and you get your m keys worth, of course being with my husband the company was better.

review_349.Review: I always love coming here with my family because the people are welcoming and cater to our needs.

review_350.Review: Oscar our food runner/bus boy was amazing!! Was always at our table within seconds of needing something! Food was amazing, and owner, manager, and Oscar went above and beyond to making our night one to remember!

review_351.Review: One of the few restaurants that have A5 wagu imported. You can easily share the sample A5 tasting platter with a few friendly to have an amazing experience and reduce the cost. Otherwise, the local filet is also amazing. Definitely recommend for a special occasion or fancy friends’ get together.

review_352.Review: Food and drinks are really good but it is expensive!

review_353.Review: Great service and great food. Steak was cooked to perfection!

review_354.Review: Food was really good, but the asparagus was undercooked to the point we didn’t eat it. The service was polite but she was very quiet. Other than that, we loved our experience here and will return. (Not much to complain about 😉)

review_355.Review: It is a steak house and the thing I loved most about is was their beet salad and I love meat. Don't get me wrong, the meat was fine... it just wasn't worth all that money. I just got their regular filet mignon since the meat they are famous for is worth hundreds of dollars... and I simply can't afford it.  The ambiance is nice... a good place to have a conversation.

review_356.Review: It always a treat to eat at 5A5. We do choose our timing as conversation can be difficult when the restaurant is in full swing.

review_357.Review: A very disappointing experience food and service wise. Don't spending the $$$, but want to get it back. Kokkari next door much,much better.

review_358.Review: Food was great but I didn’t like how close we were sitting to other couples.

review_359.Review: Never have I ever enjoyed food as much as I enjoyed the 5A5.  The food was top notch and the bartender was the best.  Though a high price, it was worth every penny !  Highly recommend for a date night or special occasion.

review_360.Review: We had come when they had first opened and have not had the opportunity to return since.  I am so happy to say that the food is still great!   The sliders were so yummy I could have had it for my entree.  We shared the sweet potatoes fries and shishito peppers as well.  Both very tasty starters!   I had filet mignon and hubby had the ribeye.  We loved it all!   Too full for dessert but maybe next time we will save some room.  Putting this place back on my radar...for sure!

review_361.Review: Great wagu beef and service was amazing . The dessert selection were delicious  but get there early if you want a good seat

review_362.Review: The food was fantastic. Had the wagyu beef crossbreed, shared sides of truffle fries, truffle mac n cheese, bacon asparagus and the peppers with Bonito flakes and I was WOWED. Drinks were tasty but felt that waiter could have been more attentive with refilling water and checking if cocktail refills were needed.

review_363.Review: A must try! Great food, the staff go above and beyond.

review_364.Review: Amazing food, good atmosphere, acccomodating service.

review_365.Review: It’s a first time for us & we plan to return in the near future to celebrate a special occasion or treat out-of-town friends to a great dining experience!!!

review_366.Review: The food and service was amazing. Thanks for making our evening so special.

review_367.Review: It was great. Was for my husbands birthday. Dinner was amazing. Would definitely come back and recommend to a friend.

review_368.Review: Loved the food, great serviceA bit noise for a biz dinner

review_369.Review: The food is as good as always.  The service was worse than you would get at a Denny’s. The server only ordered one starter, mine came after my company was finished eating his.  Then we ordered two sides, the server brought 2 spoons but only one side.  He never checked back.  When we told him we never received the second side he said order desert it was on him.  Then the check came and he charged us for it.  He was an absolute mess!

review_370.Review: Amazing cocktails,  food was ok not great selection of A5 presented better than prepared.   Would not return.  Service could use an upgrade.

review_371.Review: Amazing serviceGot a lot of complimentary dishesLoved the steak

review_373.Review: We both had the Filet Mignon -  outstanding!  Cooked to perfection, and the its sauce was very good too.  The appetizers were not as stellar as the steaks.  Although our server was very nice we thought the overall service was slow and not very attentive.   Because the steaks were so delicious - we'll return!

review_374.Review: Poor service, very high prices, noisy, no table clothes (did not match the price).

review_375.Review: The food was excellent and the service we had was the same.  It was a slower night so we were fortunate to get outstanding service.  The chef made it special for my friend's birthday by bringing in dessert with a personal message written on a plate.

review_376.Review: What happened to 5A5?i took my partner here and was a little embarrassed. 1. The chair sit was ripped and felt deflated. Ok, so I get it lots of folks eating here. But with a dinner tab for 2 at $270.00 can you replace your seats with theybare clearly ripped?2. Waited 10 mins for bread to come to the table, finally just stopped a waiter. Not for me anymore. My attempt to make an impression fell flat.

review_377.Review: Ordered the wagu ribeye, which we have had before and it was amazing, this last trip for our sons Bday we had our Ribeyes  they were very chewy, we were all very disappointed, management made good and took the cost off our bill, I would have expected a better quality control in the Kitchen, when your paying $150 for a 4oz Wagy you’d expect it to taste like butter .All in all great evening with the Family

review_378.Review: Everything was just okay.   For the price of the meal I expected more.  Started off by ordering dirty gin martinis which they forgot the dirty part.  Ordered the Ribeye which was good but wasn’t blow away by for the $79 price tag.  Also had the mashed potatoes which weren’t anything to write home about.

review_379.Review: Everything was great. The food, customer service, and the variety provided with so many different things and combinations was all good!

review_380.Review: This was a great place for dinner.  I took my wife to 5A5 for her birthday and they were absolutely great.  The manager would check on us during our meal to make sure our champagne glasses were filled and that we were doing ok.  In fact the waiter and the manager kept bringing us these tasty bites to eat while were were there.  I remember the fresh chivichi on a chip that was so good I would have ordered that as an appetizer.  If you're in San Francisco I would definitely recommend this restaurant.  Great food and great service.

review_381.Review: We didn’t get served until I asked the manager who our waiter is. The steak was chewy. Only the appetizer were the money we paid.

review_382.Review: Overall it was okay.  Definitely not special, definitely not worth the cost.  I was celebrating my godson’s bday and first year college finish. Only had one night to spend with him until later in the summer.  Searched a bunch of places and chose this one so excited to go.  Service started very slow and inattentive but improved.  Food was “eh”. I purchased their high end cuts and wasn’t blown away.  Wine by the glass was terrible.  $20 a glass for J Lohr Cab.  Terrible.  Charge me $20 for JUSTIN or something comparable.  Will not go back.  Just not worth it.  I spent $425 including 20% tip for 3 people and I have had much better for that cost.

review_383.Review: Wow.  Shocked and saddened a nice steakhouse would let a loud mouth cursing rude techie bro ruin EVERYONE's nice dinner experience.  Not one person tried to tell him he was being extremeley loud and rude. We were left for almost 15 minutes to not order when we sat down.  Not the level of service I would expect from a steakhouse.  If we are paying for it, you all should be able to deliver.  Not impressed at all.  Would never recommend.

review_384.Review: Prime rib was really cold and tough Service was good

review_385.Review: The circular room is loud and we had a table of drunken yelling people banging on their table right next to us. Service was slow but food was good

review_386.Review: Main dishes were ok sides were weak. Service was alright.  Some of the cheaper ones on the list were astronomical   J Lohr $90 come on!   However good steaks are hard to find in SF so if your from the mid west you will be disappointed.

review_388.Review: The service was great but the food is so so.

review_390.Review: Service was mediocre. The place says dress code is dressy, but half the restaurant was wearing t shirts and jeans. The food was over priced, and over sauced. We had the A5 experience and weren't blown away by the experience. I'll save my money and head back to Alexander's Steakhouse in SF next time I was some Wagyu. Better yet, go to Japan. $1,300.00 for 3.5 people (3 adults and 1 toddler). The hostesses had attitude problems. I mean smile you're working in customer service for goodness sakes.

review_391.Review: My wife and I loved this place. Friendly staff knowledgeable about the different types of steak and the free dessert on a spoon was delicious. I will be back when I’m in San Francisco again.

review_392.Review: One of my go-to spots in San Francisco, for a high quality appealing menu with a fantastic ambiance. Whether it's a romantic date, a friends birthday, or an important business meeting... this place never disappoints and I can consistently count on A- or better. It's not my all time favorite place in the world, but the consistency in quality, service, and ambiance really sets it apart.

review_393.Review: Food is excellent and the service was impeccable, thanks Scott!

review_395.Review: Food was underwhelming, lack of flavor. The steaks were tough, you would expect more from a $72 steak. My husband even thought tads steaks for $7 were far better.

review_396.Review: The food is delectable and portions were perfect for me!! They offer 4oz steak portions. The steak just melts in your mouth! The veggie plate very flavorful with fresh perfectly cooked veggies!! The service was impeccable. We were treated very well by the manager, the bartenders, the servers and the rest of the staff!! I felt a little like a celebrity with the attentiveness:) This is my new favorite steak place! I ended up going 2 nights in a row!

review_397.Review: The food portions were perfect!! The food was absolutely delectable!! Great service!! Love the place!!

review_398.Review: This is an expensive restaurant, but every item on the menu is specially prepared, in ways that remind me of Iron Chef dishes. Flavors are delicate, unusual.

review_399.Review: I have been to 5A5 about 6 times...it never disappoints. Boy do they know your beef. Whether you are in for domestic cuts or springing for Wagyu, they handle the prep with aplomb.

review_400.Review: It was an awesome dinner , service was great, great food and drinks. It made our friends birthday dinner more special.

review_401.Review: Every dish was wonderful, highly recommended place for dinner.

review_402.Review: Prime rib was awesome!The service was not too bad

review_405.Review: Best steak I’ve had in the US!!!Strongly recommended!

review_406.Review: Amazing restaurant.... we are from Australia and eat out at some of Melbourne best steak restaurants i.e. Rockpool, meat & wine co. , steer and we were very impressed with what we were served at this restaurant. The wine and whisky list was just enough, the steak list very impressive. To top of the experience... the service was impeccable! So pleasant, tentative, respectful and knowledgeable. We would definitely recommend this venue as a ‘must eat at’ spot when visiting San Fran!

review_407.Review: Ordering family style allowed us to taste a variety of items.  We totally enjoyed the waygu ribeye and the bone-in ribeye.  In addition, we ordered a variety of sides and starters.  The octopus salad and mashed potatoes was delicious, as was the cauliflower.  For dessert, we ordered the creme brulee trio and the sorbet.  The black sesame creme brulee stood out for all of us.  The restaurant surprised us with a chocolate cake surprise for the birthday girl.  The wait staff was attentive, friendly and helpful.

review_408.Review: Awesome resuatuant, amazing food!Service was perfect

review_410.Review: Heard about this place., it was okay, nothing stands out. Lobster tempura appetizer was good, which was big enough for a meal. Hubby had the 32 oz bone in rib eye steak which was okay, but wouldn’t order it again.

review_411.Review: Server messed two things up. Steaks were good but not great. And my friends couldn’t even convince me to keep the bone for broth.

review_414.Review: Nice restaurant, nice staff, Wagyu seemed to me overpriced—maybe I just prefer Angus

review_415.Review: Great food! Fast service. Lots of booths too!

review_416.Review: Great prime rib, best i ever had

review_417.Review: We went here for a friend's birthday dinner.  The atmosphere is great.  Very swanky.  The service was excellent.  They brought out the different types of wagyu and explained each type.  They have a great wine list.  Very pricey but we will go back for another special occasion.

review_418.Review: Overall food and service were good, but I have had to ask for a complimentary anniversary desert when I don’t order from desert menu. I always had complementary desert with this beautiful letters and decorations every time but we had to ask this time which is no nice.

review_419.Review: Great service, incredible food in an upscale setting!

review_420.Review: The food is good. The waiter was not friendly though. Very rough in food handling and groaned when we ask for service.

review_421.Review: Great dinner. The bathrooms are super funky..

review_422.Review: Liked the lounge atmosphere, and was  pleased to be offered various ice options, but it was disappointing to have the gin for a gin and tonic measured using a jigger.  You see this in hotels, but not usually in high end restaurants.   I was also surprised to see the bartender being responsible for serving food in the lounge which left the bar unattended for some time early on a Monday night.  As for the food, the mac and cheese looked very basic, but the Ribeye steak was huge and flavorful.

review_423.Review: Great food, excellent service.  Perfect for a date night.

review_424.Review: The food was good, I would not rate it as 5 stars. My entree Sea Bass was cold, the waiter was very good at taking it back to warm it up, but at this restaurant I would have never thought it would be cold in the first place.

review_425.Review: $28 for a side of Lobster Mac n Cheese that had 2 pieces of Lobster the size of a quarter, small pours on our cocktails,hostess and waiter forgot to celebrate our daughter’s birthday, good  service by the bussers and runners though.Not a horrible experience, just not a good one for our family if you’re gonna charge $500 for four people.

review_426.Review: Rosie was our waitress and she was delightful.  Food was very good and I liked the amuse bouche,  and also your mango version of a palate cleanser.  Nice touches.

review_427.Review: Only suggestion would be to dry age all the steaks. Otherwise, service was exceptional, from the servers to the front of the house. I would go back.

review_428.Review: We came here for our anniversary dinner and it did not disappoint! Love the little extras sent out from the kitchen, our steaks were perfect, and the drinks were perfect!

review_429.Review: Dinner was great! Service was amazing! Ben took care of us all night!

review_430.Review: send off dinner for a number of friends heading to South America for 6 months. The service was fantastic, our waitress and the rest of the staff were friendly, provided great (not just the most expensive) recommendations.

review_431.Review: Food was delicious as always and we got a late reservation so there weren’t too many people in the restaurant. Service was amazing.

review_432.Review: Delicious and fantastic. A phenomenal menu with great friendly  service.

review_433.Review: Food tasty but so cold half the dinner was inedible. Although offered a replacement didn’t want to hold up the rest of the meal. Too expensive for this kind of service but the food was tasty.

review_435.Review: Food was exceptional. The service was a little uneven and slower than expected for the price you pay

review_436.Review: Valentine’s Dinner. A5 Wagyu filet was expensive but incredibly good. Tempura lobster tail was sublime.

review_437.Review: Beautiful layout, crisp, uncluttered, although there is a serious need to re-carpet the stairs down to the lower level, they looked like something out of a frat house.  The lobster bisque was delicious but it needed to be served much hotter, I had to eat it faster than I'd planned to avoid cold bisque.  I asked for bread with it but it was never brought to me which was upsetting because the tables are set with a bread plate and a butter knife.  What's the point if there is no bread??  Confusing.  The New York strip was very good as was my husband's prime rib.  The cauliflower and mushroom sides were fine, nothing spectacular.  We enjoyed our meal but not for the $222 we paid for it.  We didn't even have wine.

review_438.Review: They ran out of our first choice and the waiter said that happens regularly by “this time,” which happened to be 7:30...that’s pretty early to regularly run out of prime rib at a steak house.  We ordered two glasses of wine neither of which were served by the time we’d finished our appetizer.  When asked the waiter said they had to go to the wine cellar to get the bottle of Grenache.  This was one of four or five reds served by the glass...like running out of prime rib how do you not have bottles of your glass pours at the ready?  He ought to have comped the wine by the time it arrived but he didn’t.  The food was very good.The service, not so much .

review_439.Review: The food was generally good, though simple requests for excluding ingredients due to allergies were met with "the chef won't do it because it won't look good in presentation." This makes business dinners difficult and ended up putting a damper on the evening.

review_440.Review: I enjoyed the food, service, ambience and would consider visiting again.

review_441.Review: Great Great Food !!!Nothing than exceptional service !

review_442.Review: Best steakhouse in SF.  A little noisy, but the steak... the steak is king.

review_443.Review: High end dining, great service, our food was prepared  exactly as we ordered it. Wife's birthday and they even brought out a beautiful happy birthday plate for her. Wonderful experience.

review_444.Review: I saw this resto online and it catches my attention. We went for there for my boyfriend’s bday dinner. I’ll tell you everything was perfect! The prime rib and fillet mignon was delicious!! We also tried the hamachi, iceberg lettuce and wagyu sliders! They gave us complimentary champagne and desert with happy bday on it! All the food was cooked in perfection! If I can give 10 stars I will! 😍

review_446.Review: Had a wonderful experience! Excellent service! I will be going back!

review_447.Review: Disappointed! Tried 5A5 for the first time last week. We had the truffle fries, lobster tempura, wagyu sliders, steak tartare, New York steak and the fillet.. the only decent food was the fries and NY steak. Tartare was tasteless, lobster tempura was very soggy, sliders were average, fillet mignone super tender but the glaze was terrible. So many fine dinning options in SF to return here.  Our server was nice.

review_448.Review: Visiting from out of town and we really enjoyed great steak and wine.

review_449.Review: host didnt allow me to sit at the table

review_450.Review: Wagyu was overpowered by too much butter. Sommelier described the Pinot Noir as “bubblegum” and having a very fruity note, neither of which was accurate.

review_451.Review: Apple parsnip soup was great and filet mignon was delicious. Chef offerings were a nice touch. Service was wonderful. My dining companion didn't care as much for the prime rib (not necessarily because it wasn't good, but he wished he hd ordered a filet instead). Place was a bit noisy but overall a positive experience.

review_452.Review: We made reservations and arrived an hour early.  The host was able to accommodate us.  We were seated immediately but their chair was defective. We raised the issue and was moved to another table right away.The food is great and customer service is excellent! A little bit pricey but it’s worth the experience.

review_453.Review: Good food. Great service. Good for a date. Best steak I ever had.

review_454.Review: This place was amazing! Our waiter plus the staff here were all so pleasant. They took care of my friend and I so well. We were celebrating her birthday and the dinner was so awesome that it had my friend in tears. It was beautiful haha. The food was great! I loved the mac and cheese with lobster and the tempura lobster tail. And of course we ended it with dessert. Yum yum yummm!!  So bomb! Can't wait to come again with my husband next time.

review_455.Review: Amazing service , amazing food . I recommend to everyone

review_457.Review: I had the opportunity to dine here on NYE.  The food was pricey, but they did have a special prixe-fixed menu evening with a lot of culinary options. The ambiance was wonderful (not too loud) and the service was just as pleasant. Particularly, the large-sized filet mignon!The only complaint I have what that the $50 non/refundable deposit was not clearly stated when I reserved the time slot. Other than that, I would definitely dine here for another special occasion.

review_459.Review: Hadn't been to 5a5 in several years and wanted to bring my wife here for the first time.  The food didn't wow me, especially with the prime rib that we asked for medium rare and got medium.  Our drinks came out seemly slow considering there did not appear to be any patrons in the bar area; bartenders appeared to be standing around chatting with each other.  Our server was very good and attentive to us.  Overall, the rating will be much lower than what I had given the restaurant on previous visits.  Still a good restaurant for eating steak; though I may suggest saving the prime rib for a steak house that specializes in prime rib.

review_460.Review: Excellent service. Fantastic steak. Unnerving prices for the special steaks. Not sure if the value equates to the quality but that’s more me than the restaurant. Great restaurant and service and will return.

review_461.Review: Food was good I’m not a truffle person and so didn’t order the Wagyu meat as every one of them had a truffle sauce. Every type of drink I wanted they didn’t carry no Crown Royal, no Pinot Grigio but what I did eat the Filet Mignonette with garlic sauce was fabulous mashed potatoes awesome.

review_462.Review: The server Jeff did a great job! The food was excellent.

review_463.Review: My duck was good.   Others had the filet of sole that was WAY too salty.   Our server was not rude, but not polite either.   All in all.....a so so experience that I won’t be returning to.   Also, as a side note, the most expensive red wine by the glass was from one of the worst wineries in Healdsburg.   At $22.00 per glass, they should be ashamed of themselves.   Instead, we ordered a half bottle of the Rafanalli.  They should be bringing in perhaps Seghasio zin for that money.   I live in Healdsburg and no restaurant in Healdsburg would serve the choices they offer by the glass.

review_464.Review: Order your choice of meat without anything on top and everything on the side.

review_465.Review: Very disappointing! The A5 Wagyu Ribeye was excellent,  U.S. Filets were average, and the 32oz. U.S. Ribeyes were poor (very tough). Sent one ribeye back and I never do that ever! Slow weak service, messed up the order twice,  and we spent $1250 for a party of six. Live and learn. If you go... only order the A5 Wagyu!

review_466.Review: Really delicious dinner! We had the bone-in rib eye...shared it as it weighed in at 32 oz. Enough for three hungry people.  Simply perfectly prepared.  The mashed potatoe side was heavenly.

review_467.Review: Came here for our annual xmas steakhouse dinner with the girlfriends. They sat us at a 2-seat table where the sides come up, but only opened 1 side stating the couldn’t open the other because of another table nearby. They also said they couldn’t seat us at any of the other open tables because they have people coming. I guess our reservations meant nothing.Thankfully the table next to us was kind and didn’t mind the other side being open. The oysters were good, nothing special. I had the ribeye and the girls had the t-bone. We’ve had our share of steaks before and found 5a5 to have really fatty steaks, not marble fat, but chunks of fat that we would have to cut off.  The sides were okay and we didn’t try dessert. Overall, not impressed nor would I take my husband here. Waiter was nice but the overall experience and food were lacking.

review_468.Review: I brought my family here with great excitement, but sad to say I was deeply disappointed by the service in particular but the main courses as well. It has been several years since I have dined here and I can recall having an absolutely fabulous experience back then. Unless someone else organizes a dinner here, I don't believe that I will be coming back to 5A5 given all the choices available in the city.

review_469.Review: Staff was not attentive for the first hour of our dinner.  I had to ask the hostess to send the wait staff to take our wine order, bring the wine, take the order, etc. Staff needs to be attentive that business dinners with 9 people need immediate attention to drinks, ordering, and swift execution throughout.

review_470.Review: This place probably had it's glory 10+ years ago and now is simply a highly overpriced restaurant. Prices are not nearly in line with quality of everything: food, service, ambiance. There's probably a hundred places in the city way better than this at half the cost.

review_471.Review: The best thing about 5A5 is the food.  Everything we ordered was delicious and perfectly prepared.  The downside and the reason I won’t go back are 2 things.First everything was way overpriced.  Wine list too expensive, dinners too expensive, sides and starters too expensive.  Fortunately for me it was a business meal,  but even though my company paid, it was out of line.Second reason was that the waiter was condescending.  He gave me the impression that he thought I was cheap for only ordering the $90 bottle of wine, not the $250 bottle he recommended.   He also padded the bill by suggesting way too much food for the 4 of us to eat.  At steak places like this sides are shareable,  but he wanted us to order 4 for the table.  We did order 3 sides and ate less than 1/3 of each.  There are much better restaurants in SF.

review_472.Review: The place si excellente but The price Is very expensive

review_473.Review: Our waiter was very attentive and knowledgable.  Food was pricey but very delicious.   The wagyu experience was recommended medium rare and was excellent served that way.   The lobster tempura was wow.

review_474.Review: This was my third visit in three years. The first two occasions were exceptional.  The food was sub standard.  The mash potatoes looked and tasted like slop. However the oysters were excellent. Overall very disappointing.

review_475.Review: It was perfect once again. The servers was great. Food perfect.. Atmosphere great!  I was able to perfect my proposal to my girlfriend in the perfect way there. Thank you so much! An she said Yes!

review_476.Review: Awesome experience. Jeff our server was A5 class!!!!

review_477.Review: Very accommodating towards special dates such as birthdays and anniversaries. Cocktail was bitters heavy. Probably that's how it's made but I didn't like it much. It was somewhat like a old fashion with honey but didn't taste anything but bullet rye and bitters.Food was good love the mashed potatoes. Filet Mignon was super tender.The bussers skill was amazing I wish I could bus that well he cleared the whole table and wiped it in one go. One thing that kind of ruined my whole experience was that I wrote don't let any one pay but me... and I didn't so I was mad.  But overall good place would come back here again.

review_479.Review: Recently, we celebrated  a birthday and the overall experience was fantastic. The chef offered a complimentary appetizer- crab over a cucumber slice that was delicious.  We dined in prime rib (cooked to perfection), mashed potatoes, cauliflower and mushrooms- all were a culinary delight.  Our waiter was extremely knowledgeable about the wine list and suggested the Pinot Noir which complimented the meal.   The birthday dessert was small bites was sufficient to whet our senses.

review_480.Review: Nice place for many different occasions. Nice friendly and professional services. Good foods and atmosphere. Place I always recommend to my friends.

review_481.Review: We have dined here before and the meat is beyond wonderful. Delicious, and cooked to perfection. The only thing we did not like was dessert. We ordered a dessert to share andit looked like they threw some things on a plate. It was ill prepared and looked like a 5 year old made it. So stick with the food and forget the dessert!

review_482.Review: If you like steak, this is NOT the restaurant to visit!  2 friends and I visited on Saturday night, and we were excited to try 5A5 given the reviews.  Clearly, the owners have several family members reviewing this place, because no independent reviewer would give this a passing grade.  The meal started with slow service and a 30 minute wait for our reservation.  But, that was forgivable as the bar has a nice atmosphere.  Once we were seated, we started with the Shisito peppers (actually very good, highlight of the meal), and Wagyu sliders.  The sliders were a foreshadowing of what was to come...the meal slid downhill from there!  Despite being ordered medium rare, they were served almost raw.   Nothing "special" about these, and tasted like any slider you would get off the "passed trays" at any mid-level wedding.  They make a big deal out of their Wagyu here, and we all expected something more. Salads were next, the baked salad with an egg.  This dish was ok.  Then the trouble really began.  The 3 of us ordered the $80 Ribeye.  I only mention the price because there is an expectation of a good piece of meat.  Again, not only were all 3 of our dishes WAY undercooked, the meat was tough, filled with gristle, and we were forced to send all of them back.  It was inedible.  Honestly, we spent the night listing places we had better steak at, and it didn't take Morton's or Joe's to beat it.  We're talking Applebee's, Chili's and business class on United were better.  The sides we ordered, the spinach, mushrooms, and cauliflower were serviceable, but again, nothing special. The manager Matthew was the one bright spot.  He apologized profusely, and did what he could to salvage the experience.  But, after being there for hours, we weren't about to wait for another hour for a new steak.  He didn't seem at all surprised by how poor the food was.  I'm guessing his main job is apologizing to customers for the food.  We left still a bit hungry, and definitely disappointed.

review_483.Review: Had the filet and it could have used a slight rub prior to cooking.... i did enjoy the garlic sauces with it howeverThe gnocchi is a must!

review_484.Review: Overall not bad but less than expected

review_485.Review: the food here is absolutely amazing, and the service is excellent!

review_486.Review: This was out first time to this restaurant and it was fantastic.  The food, service and ambiance are all in harmony.  The waiter took the time to explain the entire menu and did not rush us in ordering right away.  I would highly recommend this restaurant for an intimate night out or just to have dinner with friends.  We plan to return!

review_487.Review: Great service; well-presented dishes.  The wine was also excellent!  - Taken.

review_488.Review: Service is superb food is good nice selection of wines. Attentive server gem to the neighbood.

review_490.Review: Appealing ambiance with open arrangement of tables. I dislike dark restaurants and this was a refreshing change of indirect lighting which helped to elevate my mood. The wagyu beef was truly an item not to miss if your wallet (corporate or personal) can stand the assault!!!!  Our waiter, Chris, had worked there five years was very good and it was enjoyable interacting with him during our meal. The appetizers we ate, recommended by Chris, were very good (lobster tempura and the shishito peppers). Our t- bone steaks were very good and  cooked as requested.

review_491.Review: Great find. Really good food and service. Ambiance was quiet and comfortable. It is not a loud restaurant. We did not get the complimentary sparkling wines as it was advertised on Open Table at the time of making the reservation. I was not going to ask for freebies but if you do advertise it the hostess or the server should be aware of any specials offered. The people seated around us did get it, so it might have been an oversight. I don’t personally think oversights are acceptable at a restaurant of this caliber, so no 5 stars because of it. I would come again.

review_492.Review: We went for my husband's birthday. The food was delicious, but a little pricey. Overall, we enjoyed it very much.

review_493.Review: Everything was amazing. Thanks for the great food and service!!

review_494.Review: Love this place.  We've tried several different places for date nights but always end up coming back.  They even have in their system our favorite booth so we get seated there every time we come.  The special attention they give to their return customers is 2nd to none.  Food is always on point and plentiful.  One of my top 5 restaurants in SF.

review_495.Review: We ordered 2 of the very, very pricey Wagyu steaks and never was presented the certificate to validate. Steak was good but not as good as what I had elsewhere... tougher. Not seeing the certificate and the overall toughness of the meat makes me suspect of what was served.

review_496.Review: Awesome Steak!I am definitely coming back!Learned a lot about Wagu beef. We had the sampler, although expensive I was able to taste the difference's in the Fillet, NY, Ribeye, and Cap.  Service was spot on.  Very attentive. Location easy to find and park.

review_498.Review: Place  is a pedestrian tourist  trap so avoid.

review_499.Review: Great food. Great place for a business dinner. Steak was amazing.

review_500.Review: Terrific meal with an impressive selection of Wagyu beef.  I enjoyed the garlic crusted prime rib with mashed potatoes.  Atmosphere was trendy and the waiter Scott was superb.  Would go back again.

review_501.Review: Outstanding food.  Service was lacking.  Had a difficult

review_502.Review: While we had a pleasant evening and the service was good, my wife and I just really felt that almost all of the food had some issues with flavors not working well together.  Since it left a lot to be desired for the price, we felt it was an overpriced dinner and most likely will not go back.  I had the lobster bisque, but it was not a great flavor and since the lobster meat was added to it in the center (it was nice presentation) it didn't seem to go well with the bisque for some reason or do anything for the flavor.  My wife had the grilled romaine salad and we agreed it was interesting, and maybe the best of what was ordered -- which shouldn't be the case at a restaurant showcasing steak.  My filet was cooked perfectly and was very tender; however, the demi glace and green garlic flavors conflicted and didn't make the overall taste something I would recommend to anyone or order again. She ordered the t-bone because the ingredients peaked her interest, but it was a very strong flavor warranting a few bites only.  The truffle mac & cheese was ok, but not anything great or special.

review_503.Review: As the demanding foodie that I am, Oh boy!  It was delicious!  From the Japanese Oysters to the gorgeous delicious Rib cup 4 oz, creamy spinach and delicate and tasty scallops!  Simply the best!  Well done cheffs!

review_504.Review: This was a great restaurant and the filet was excellent! I think some of the sides were just OK but what they are know for meat wise was amazing!

review_505.Review: Excellent food all around. NY strip was beat I've had. Tender like a filet with the flavor of a strip. Great service and good wine selection make for winning  combo.

review_506.Review: I had specifically asked for a quiet table but was placed between the bar and dining room. It was so loud! Not a good location for a business dinner where we wanted to have a meaningful conversation.

review_507.Review: Great service and food. Prime rib was 86'd but the ribeye was excellent. Best creamed spinach I have ever had

review_508.Review: We had a large party and we usually pay our own bills. We were told that they could only charge even number charges on four charge cards. My wife broke down each persons bill and what each owed as she has done for our family for the past 28 years. They have a app now so it's much easier to take a picture of bill and separate it. She puts amount on paper and the amount to be charged .to each card He charged the different amounts but I have never heard of this before.  The person who delivered the bill to the table , sat the bill on table no communication no eye contact and left not sure what that was about. This was not the waiter or our server he was great. Overall good food great service but these other two incidents threw me for a  loop.

review_509.Review: Visiting San Francisco for Labor Day weekend and this was our last night here. We found 5A5 on open table and based off all the awesome reviews we decided to give it a try. So glad we did! First of all, the hostess was very sweet and professional. We arrived 30 minutes early and she told us she would have a table for us soon and we could go to the bar/lounge while we wait. The bartender, Michael, was outstanding. By far, the best service we've ever received. He was very knowledgeable and friendly. The restaurant was very clean and had a nice intimate setting. Perfect for date night! We started off with the tempura lobster and the shishito peppers.  I ordered the filet mignon and my boyfriend ordered the tbone. Both were cooked to perfection and seasoned well.  By far the best restaurant we visited in SF and one of the best I have ever dined at. Job well done. Highly recommend.

review_510.Review: If you're a steak lover, then this is the ideal restaurant for you. We started off with the Lobster tempura and U10 scallops, then had the A5 Wagyu Ribeye that was amazing. Including the truffle mushroom butter that was on top of it.If you can get pass the $$$ price per ounce, then I recommend this restaurant...

review_511.Review: Great food, a bit pricey. Service was good, not spectacular but good none the less.

review_512.Review: It was great. We were warmly greeted upon our arrival and seated right away by the hostess. Our waiter Scott was awesome, checking in on us throughout our meal. We will definitely be back!

review_513.Review: Definitely going back. The best experience i've had.

review_514.Review: Overall the experience was good. My steak came out medium when I ordered medium rare and my colleague's steak came out medium rare when he ordered medium. I'm pretty sure the kitchen switched our orders and we ordered different cuts of meats so it wasn't something we could switch... for the costs, this mistake should not occur. The service was great. Very friendly. The appetizers and sides were great too. Just wish my steak was cooked correctly as the seasoning was very good on mine.

review_515.Review: We were celebrating a new job offer and tell you the truth they way we were welcomed to the lounge was exceptionally classy !The food was more than amazing; the presentation of the menu items was outstanding. The waitress was smiley and helpful she explained the types of meat and the wines and the champagne. We enjoyed Prime Ribs, truffle fries and asparagus, and cauliflower .. all was served hot and super tasty! Will definitely go back again !

review_516.Review: As usual 5 star service, favorite steak spot

review_517.Review: Scott was a fantastic server to start.. the A5 filet was spectacular, the bone in rib eye was huge and the mashed potatoes were incredible.. we will be back!

review_518.Review: Service: ultra professional and detailed Food: we didn't have a dish that wasn't absolutely amazing! Beautiful presentation, incredible flavors, high quality. Price/value: people often think of price and value as the same thing... They are  not! Is it expensive to dine here? Yes, if you choose the certified Japanese Wagyu steaks. Value - you may only find a handful of restaurants in the US that actually serves REAL Wagyu steak. So for what you get, the value is amazing! I would highly recommend this steakhouse! Thanks for the incredible dining experience

review_519.Review: I love this place and the lobster tempura is screaming!!!

review_520.Review: Went here with my wife and adult daughter while visiting our daughter in SF. Excellent food, with a combination of Japanese and "foodie" influences. Didn't go all out and order the Waghu beef; the NY strip was excellent on its own.

review_521.Review: This place was amazing. We are celebrating an anniversary and 5A5 was recommended. The service was great and the food even better. The modern ambiance was exactly what we were looking for.

review_522.Review: Fun, creative take on a traditional steak house. Great food, great wine, great service.

review_523.Review: I arrived about 5 minutes early and checked in.  Let them know my date was running a little late and I will wait at the bar.  When she arrived, I was told that they canceled my reservations because I didn't check in.   Which I clearly did.  Was then told it would be about 5 minutes.  30 minutes later after going to the hostess twice, we finally got a table.  After 10 minutes wait they decided menus might be a help.The waiter then proceeded to splash my date drink all over her.  Luckily it only hit her face, into the eye and down the arm.  Upon her cleaning up some, we decided to leave.   Not wanting to make a bigger display, we just asked for the bill for the drinks and proceeded to leave.  At this time the manager decided to try to make it up.  He tried so hard that he followed us next door to Kokkari.I will never step into this place again, but highly recommend Kokkari next door.  It was amazing service, and they went out their way to make night great for us anyway.   We go out at least one night a week.  This week it is The Boulevard and next to La Mars.  This is the first time I ever felt the need to write a review.   DO NOT GO TO  5A5 Steak Lounge.PS:  the system made me put something in for value and quality of food.  I must be honest, we never tried the food.  So the values are just place setters

review_524.Review: From beginning to end the service was awesome!!!! The food was amazing especially the tempura lobster!!!

review_525.Review: I thought the food was only ok. I always wanted to try it. I did and wasn't too impressed. Taste of the food was only ok. For the prices they charge, I can go some place else for a more reasonable price.

review_526.Review: Impeccable service. The food was great but a little on the heavy side on the sauces and glazes.

review_527.Review: The food was fine and the service adequate. But my friend and I ordered a few different small plates and the server said that the items were served family style and would be sent separately (as in sent out in courses), but we received all the food at once:  salad, soup, fries and lobster tempura - so we were forced to eat some of the hot foods after they had cooled considerably.

review_528.Review: It was awesome... loved the atmosphere, food & service

review_529.Review: Nice food, good services. A place where I always come back whenever I'm in SF. Everything looks fine except the wine list. The lists have changed with less quality wines than before. But I still love to have dinners with my friends there anyway!

review_530.Review: An unserem Abend war sehr laut. Man konnte sich fast nicht unterhalten. Trotz vieler Kellner ca fünf haben immer Details gefehlt. Mein Steak für 65$ war nicht Medium.  Schönes Lokal nur laut mitbedingt guten Service und somit im Preis-Leistungs-Verhältnis eher nichts empfehlen

review_531.Review: My wife and myself were celebrating our 12 year wedding Anniversary and your team made our moment even more special than what it already was.  From the moment we were greeted, till our ending coffee, our server made it a night truly to remember.  She was very out going, understood our needs. Excellent service.  Thank you so much!!!

review_532.Review: 3rd time coming back. Food are tasty as usual. Will surly come back again.

review_533.Review: It was my boyfriend's birthday and we were there to celebrate it. Everything was so amazing. The service was incredible great. The food...omg words can't explain it. The best I've ever tasted in SF so far. Definitely an awesome place to go to. Don't miss it out!

review_534.Review: I've eaten here a few times for bother personal and business meals. Food, drinks and services is always great. The bar was quiet for a Saturday though.

review_535.Review: Chef drenches Wagyu and other steaks in heavy sauces.

review_536.Review: Steaks are ok, but not  would expect more from this place/ They aded sevral toppoing on top of the steaks. You do not taste the great flavour of the steaks because of this.

review_537.Review: Everything about 5A5 steak Lounge was perfection❤The service, perfection. The ambience, perfection. The food and drinks, perfection. I would give 10 stars if I could.

review_539.Review: Our waiter was excellent. The food was great and a bit unique.

review_540.Review: I can't say enough good things about 5A5! The service, food, and atmosphere combined for an amazing experience for my friend's 30th birthday dinner. Our group of 7 people all had a great time. Don't skip the sweet potato gnocchi!

review_541.Review: It was outstanding! Great service from Scott. I recommend this steak house to everyone! Food was prepared to perfection!!

review_542.Review: I ordered the Waygu Beef Sliders Medium Well and they were still bleeding.  So I sent them back and said I am okay with medium well but to me medium well is not bleeding on your plate.  When they came back they were still too pink inside for me.  I nibbled around the edges that were done enough for me.  Someone else ordered the Mary Free Range Chicken and it was pink inside too.  I guess we are just used to food cooked until it is done.   This did affect my ratings but it is probably more me than the restaurant.  It is just hard to know what medium well is in restaurants as they did not give me any range.  If the waiter had said medium well is going to be bleeding then I would have said well done.  And I did not think to ask.

review_543.Review: The food here was excellent this was our first time here and it was my daughter 21st bday she enjoyed this place I did as well. Did I mention the food ! Mashed potatoes and lobster Mac and cheese was a hit !

review_544.Review: Really fantastic steaks!  Great service, nice ambiance, highly recommend

review_545.Review: Very attentive service.  The lobster tempura was amazing.  The New York steak was just pretty.  The banana bread desert was very good as well.  Overall, not quite worth the price, but undoubtedly a very good meal.

review_546.Review: Impressively awful. I don't ever write reviews either.They did not have 7 different things we ordered off the menu. 4 different wines (a Merlot, the Rose and two others), Bombay Sapphire gin and two other things.We asked for tap water and got bottled water which I reiterated we didn't want but, they still charged us for. Our appetizer's were comped but, it was still a $250 meal for 3 people who weren't just expensing a business meal. Although that's how it felt we were being treated.'These people have money to spend, let's upsell them on the meat, the wine, (even) the water'It was laughable. We went to Kokarri and drank wine there afterward, they actually had what we wanted and atmosphere there is top notch by comparison.

review_547.Review: The steak was superb! Our server Ali is the best!

review_548.Review: The staff knew what they were doing and the food was amazing

review_549.Review: We had a great server who went above and beyond to make us happy. The place itself has great food but I keep coming back because of the excellent service

review_550.Review: My bridesmaids and I came for my bachelorette dinner before we went out dancing. Staff were amazing and very professional. They greater us and congratulated me for getting married and chef gave us comp green smoothie shots (I don't remember what's it's called, it had no alcohol and it was so yummy) our food was made just how we asked and the drinks were so good too. At the end I got this  dessert and chocolate writing read congratulations with two rings and rose petals. I was beyond excited and happy. We had so much fun and that was just the beginning of the night.

review_551.Review: Great service, great food!Our server brought out samples of each of the four types of Wagyu beef the restaurant serves, and described each one. Everyone in our party ordered a cold sushi spoon appetizer. The hamachi-uni spoon was excellent.For my meal, I got the wagyu beef sliders (2 per order) and the truffle mac and cheese.  The truffle flavor was very prominent, I enjoyed both of my orders!My date ordered the mushroom side prime rib with foie gras served on top for an additional cost. This add-on was not advertised on the menu, but he saw it in an online review. He thought the steak was cooked perfectly and very tender, and I agree. Our friends got another steak and the maple bacon mashed potato and prosciutto asparagus.  Everything was amazing!My cocktail was pretty good. Everyone else in our party tried scotch. Our friends got the 3-scotch tasting, and enjoyed that.The only negatives are the noise level (hard to hear conversation across the booth) and the booth style seating where we sat was significantly lower than the table, so it was a bit awkward to be cutting steak at that angle.

review_552.Review: So, first I don't love how before you have taken a breath, they are shilling a $600 kobe sampler. Secondly, why does everything have to have a truffle sauce on the sampler? You don't think fake truffles are a little overpowering for kobe beef? I also think it is funny when they offer prime rib and are sold out 30 minutes after opening in a room that is barely 25% full. But my main concern is that we asked for medium rare and were served a steak that was blue in the middle. The tables on either side of us had similar issues (for example woman asked for medium and was served rare). The only crucial  thing a steakhouse has to do is cook a steak to specifications. Massive fail for $170.

review_553.Review: Lovely staff and the food is amazing!

review_554.Review: Service was excellent. Food was not perfect. Steak had to be sent back. Overall lacked much to be desired.

review_555.Review: My fiance and I came here for our 7th anniversary.-STEAK: Filet mignon & NY STeak- very tender and flavorful-SIDES:Mashed potatoes (w/candied bacon) & Prosiutto asparagus-DRINKs: Margaritas, measured by the ounce not worth the price. Be prepared to spend $300 minimum per couple..

review_556.Review: Hostesses were not attentive , told us to wait at the bar as they seated a big party and forgot about us for 20 minutes as the place was 1/2 empty ! Not even an apology .

review_557.Review: Excellent food, excellent service, super trendy steakhouse in SF. Recommend the Bone-in Ribeye or any of the A5 Wagyu steaks. Will definitely return.

review_559.Review: Extremely prompt service I flew in from Chicago and took my girlfriend and it was nothing less then perfect, fast, prompt, and polite service.   Food was next level good and the chef sent us complimentary tastes of desert and bite size sausages coming back very soon

review_560.Review: Took a little while to get the menus from a server but once we got them everything was amazing. ( my guess was he had a lot of other table so I ybderstand)  Server was attentive.  Checked in on every dish.  Chef created absolutely amazing dishes and they were presented beautiful.  I would recommend this lounge/restaurants to all of my friends

review_561.Review: Great dinner, our regular filet and A5 japanese wagyu ribeye were cooked perfectly. The A5 was the best steak we've ever had (better than other places that serve wagyu). The lobster tempura was to die for, hamachi shooters were a fun starter.Service was friendly and on point, fun, modern atmosphere - not stuff at all.

review_562.Review: Chose this restaurant for my boyfriend's birthday dinner.  We were excited to try it out. They were out of the steak we wanted as well as mashed potatoes and the sides were served room temperature. We complained to our waiter but he just apologized and that was it. Our prime rib was ok. I expected better ambiance and food quality for the price.I was told to try Epic in SF and now I wish we would have. We were also disappointed there was no valet.  Parking was difficult to find as expected.

review_564.Review: We consider ourselves steak connoisseurs. We have eaten in NYC's Peter Luger, Sparks, etc. this place blows them away. Knowledgeable and friendly waitstaff. Absolutely melt-in-your mouth 11-12 grade wagyu ribeye and cap. And we mean if you let a piece sit on your tongue, it melts like "butta". Generous shareable sides, Creative desserts, special Table-side Scotch and Whiskey service. Just outstanding. A bit pricey, but its once in a lifetime steak. We were there for our anniversary. Recommend highly.

review_565.Review: We came here to celebrate our wedding anniversary and were not disappointed. The service is superb and the food is incredibly made. The 2 pound rib eye is a sight to be hold. I would definitely recommend this restaurant.

review_566.Review: I ordered a bone in Ribeyes 32 oz It is a little bit well done for a medium rareAnd I was expecting it will be done perfectly, crispy on the outside and tender in the inside. But I'm disappointed.On the other hand, the lobster tempura is well deserved a try. I will definitely recommend it.

review_567.Review: Insanely expensive for ok service and ok food. Also, they don't know how to cook steak! I ordered a $60 steak medium-rare and it came out well done! And my girlfriend ordered a $50 steak medium that they messed up TWICE. First time it came out blue. Sent it back and it was only medium rare.For such an expensive place, it's absolutely unacceptable that they can't get an order right. I left feeling hungry and ripped off.I am pretty sure that I'll never come here again. If I drop $300 on a dinner for two, it has be flawless.

review_568.Review: Three times was not the charm.  Came with family for a late birthday celebration.  Had been here twice before and thought it was a decent steak place.  This time three of us had the prime rib.  Each  was ordered medium rare but came out rare.  This would have been tolerable had it not been so tough.  Admittedly, we did not shell out for their 200$ wagyu beef but at a steak restaurant one would expect that even the standard "domestic" cuts should be decent.  This turned out to be a D+.  Could not have measured up to a usda choice roast I could have purchased at the local supermarket.  Will not be returning.  Waiter was friendly and accommodating.

review_569.Review: Although this place can be loud the food is amazing! Great service and cool decor

review_570.Review: Food was just "ok". Staff was nice. Drinks good.

review_571.Review: We were very disappointed with this restaurant.  While the food was good (not great), the portions were too small given the prices.  Highly overrated and expensive considering the portions provided.  Wine list limited as well.

review_572.Review: Usually have a great experience, this last time the service and food was sup par for the price.

review_573.Review: Service was slow and waiter made mistake and overcharged on bill

review_574.Review: The food was great and the service was even better! Loved it and i will definitely be returning soon!

review_575.Review: This place was fun and the service was fantastic!!! Was pleasantly surprised especially with our last minute reservation.

review_576.Review: Best meal I have ever had. Definitely try the Wagyu filet. Expensive but worth it.

review_578.Review: The waiter was very attentive. We don't usually splurge on an expensive meal but enjoyed our dinner and the service was wonderful.

review_579.Review: Great food but server was not great. Apparently they often sell out of the prime rib early in the evening, we were there at 7:30 and it was already gone. Our server was not very kind in explaining this. He was even rude at times. I explained to him that I had a bad shellfish allergy and he kept questioning me, saying things like, "well how allergic are you anyway?". I also had a bug in my wine and my friend had one crawling on his wine glass. We still tipped very well but this was NOT the service I would expect for a $511 meal. Overall delicious meal though. I think it was just a server issue.

review_580.Review: Think everyone in our party would agree, the beef was the best we've ever had!

review_581.Review: The food was fabulous. The waiter staff worked as a team, and were very efficient; however, I felt like our waiter forgot about us at times. The music was very loud. It sounded like I was in a night club. It was by far the worse part of my dining experience. My husband and I shouted at each of from across the table the entire time.

review_582.Review: Loved it so much going back April 14th to celebrate my better half birthday!

review_583.Review: Lobster tempura was the highlight of the meal for me but to be honest the prime rib, creamed spinach, truffle Mac n cheese were very good as well. The service was impeccable. Our server Scott was very knowledgeable and his wine pairings were on point.

review_585.Review: Food was great. I had the 32oz t bone steak. Great flavor.

review_586.Review: Everything food wise was delicious. The atmosphere was warm and inviting and it seemed like everyone was having a great time. We started with the tempura lobster appetizer. Fresh and delicious. Now on to dinner. My wife got the 10oz prime rib and I got the bone-in ribeye. Both were flavorful and tender. We also got the Truffled mac n cheese and the white cheddar mash. Both were phenomenal. Our server was super friendly and gave us a lot of great suggestions. We will back back sooner than later.

review_587.Review: Came to A5a for my wife's birthday. Easy valet parking in SF was a plus. Good food and great ambiance, however I ordered the potatoe gnocchi as a side dish and someone forgot the order. The server  brought our steaks and cream of spinach (which was Delish) but the gnocchi was either forgotten by the waiter or the Chef; either way, the server advised that the gnocchi would take a long time to prepare so I elected the Mac and cheese by default...........and with disappointment.

review_588.Review: This place was booked for a business meal. Nice atmosphere. Pricey, good for client and team meetings.

review_589.Review: Food was amazing. Our server Kelsey was great.

review_590.Review: great find! delicious apps, dinner and amazing dessert! bartender and waitress was super fun! great suggestions! would definitely go back when in town again

review_591.Review: Just not good at all. The decor was dreadful, the noise too much to have a conversation. The wine menu was almost unable to be read because of poor printing. The beverage manager didn't know his wines and couldn't explain their value. The food was pretty good but the service ruined that. Would not recommend!

review_592.Review: DISAPPOINTED!!!!  I am not sure whether most of the reviewers ate at the same 5A5 that I did.  The food was on the lower side of average and the service was lackluster.  Our server was very pompous about the quality of food but unfortunately the chef did not deliver.  This restaurant certainly does not deserve to be mentioned in the same discussion with other top quality steak houses.

review_593.Review: After trying to find a restaurant in SF that would fit everyone in our groups tastes I came across 5A5 on Open Table and looked at the menu and found something for everyone.  The décor was beautiful and loved the way the tables were placed in a circle.  First, the service is outstanding.  The food was delicious and the presentation was beautiful.  For those of us who are more adventuresome we had the Wagu beef tartar and lobster along with many other plates and the person who was just a steak eater had a perfectly cooked filet.  I must say I'm not a desert person but we ordered two for the table were not only delicious but the presentation was out of this world.  It was the perfect evening.

review_594.Review: Food and Service was great, good  ambiance

review_595.Review: Great service! Ben was excellent! We went for our anniversary and we got a very cute complimentary anniversary dessert. We would definitely go back.

review_596.Review: Excellent experience, but rather loud. If you have a larger party, it will be difficult to converse with those not directly around you. The food is delicious, though, and the staff is attentive.

review_597.Review: Great place and we were coming from far away and ran into traffic, they politely held our table 30 mins after our reservation! Thanks for making our date memorable!      ---A.Huizar

review_598.Review: Went for Valentine's Day, pre fixed menu was 120 each. Food was not worth it at all. We were very disappointed and it ruined such a special occasion for us :(

review_599.Review: The absolute most incredible steak culinary experience ever

review_600.Review: We tried 5A5 on our trip to San Francisco. The food was ok, a bit pricey for what it was. The service was great though and they had some interesting drink options.

review_602.Review: I was quite disappointed with this restaurant. I had read reviews and thought it would be a good place to celebrate my brother's birthday. However, I wasn't too pleased with the service since our server was not very attentive. The food was quite average considering the price. Also, the hostess at the start wasn't very friendly when she greeted us. It was okay, not sure if I will be back anytime soon.

review_603.Review: Wow.... best tasting steaks ever!  They service is top notch...can't wait to return

review_604.Review: The service and ambiance were great.  The food was good and probably worth the price.  The one complaint I have is that almost all the sides (including the vegetable options!) come with some sort of pork in them.  I made a comment about this to our server, but I'm not sure if the feedback got to the chef or not.  But seriously, why do creamed spinach, asparagus, mashed potatoes and cauliflower ALL come with meat in them??  I understand it's a steak house, and I'm not opposed to meat - I like it a lot!  But having pork in almost every side dish you offer is insensitive to people who don't eat pork.  Let's keep the veggie options (at least SOME of them) free of meat!

review_605.Review: Average at best.  I've had much better steaks at better prices.  The mac-n-cheese was good.  We did not receive any bread at our table.  Will not go back.

review_606.Review: Amazing experience. Truly like a 5 star restaurant and the food was exquisite!

review_607.Review: Great menu, awesome presentation, impecable service and a unique ambiance.

review_608.Review: Their house cocktails are really good.  The service is good but not the best.  Their steaks are over priced and not that great.  Looking for a good steak to eat, this is not the place.

review_609.Review: Dining here was an AMAZING experience! Worth the money!

review_610.Review: Amazing service, great atmosphere and an outstanding menu with unique Wagyu cuts.

review_612.Review: Was ok but I expected more. We were seated for more than 15 mins before server came to take drinks order

review_613.Review: Pretty much what we ordered was under seasoned. The ribeye was probably the best dish of the night. The pork belly that was on the house tasted like it came out from cha siu bao. I used to think that this place serves pretty good food but last night's dinner was such a big disappointment.

review_614.Review: My wife and I wanted steaks and all the trimmings and 5A5 didn't disappoint.  Service was top-notch and the food was outstanding.  The chef came out to greet us during our meal.  We ordered the wagyu rib cap, wagyu/holstein filet mignon, prime rib and bone-in rib eye...we had a lot of meat.Also tried the hamachi app, and the mac n cheese(with lobster) and creamed spinach sides.  Couldn't ask for a better meal or experience.

review_615.Review: First time eating at this restaurant, service was great, food was amazing and the layout was very modern. Definitely enjoyed this place for my first time. Would definitely recommend it to anyone wanting to try a Steakhouse that's worthwhile.

review_616.Review: This is my go to steak place in the City. Absolutely love the service, the food is delicious and the drinks are amazing. One of my favorite restaurants.

review_617.Review: The taste of the food and most definitely the service did not match the $600 dinner for four.  You shouldn't have to ask three times for butter. You should't get an eye roll when you ask for the  drinks that got forgotten about at a restaurant of that price point.

review_618.Review: The food was amazinggg, the cleanliness and service was not. I booked a reservation wayyyy in advance and the table we were given was next to a pole and not desirable for an advance booking. Last minute reservation or walk-in sure, the table would be fine for that.  My bread plate and the table were dirty, they ran out of spoons, so they never gave us any. So we couldn't eat part of our meal. Good thing I didn't get the soup. They ignored us because we were placed at a bad table. When they took our plates to box the food, they placed dirty dishes directly on my food!!! Carry what you can and come back, don't put dirty dishes on my food. Overall very disappointing. Food amazing, I doubt I would go back.

review_619.Review: Service was top notch. To be clear I did not have the Waygu steak which is what they are known for. My girlfriend and I chose a t-bone and a ribeye along with the mushroom side. Both those steaks were average middle of the road in terms of texture and flavor, and came heavily coated in their respective sauces (I knew this going in). I'm from New York, and this is the context I'm using for this review - I eat steak on the regular and unfortunately I wouldn't return for either of the two steaks listed above. The restaurant staff was incredibly friendly and exceptional in their quality of service. I will return to try the Waygu.

review_620.Review: We went to new years and the food was horrible

review_621.Review: New Year's Eve price fixe dinner was horrible. Steak was barely warm, sides were nothing special. Apps were a joke. 3 raviolis!! 3! Salad was wilted. We will never be back! Best part was the drinks at the bar. Very good!!

review_622.Review: Left in the  middle of NEW YEARS EVE dinner as service was horrendous. Had to wait over 45 minutes between courses. Soup came out cold, etc.Terrible experience!

review_623.Review: We both got sick after eating there for New Years and couldn't enjoy midnight hitting!Service was impeccable.

review_624.Review: Poor service, unfriendly service, very very small portions for price paid as well as not top quality food for the price charged. Would not reccomend to friends.

review_625.Review: New year's eve pre fix menu was not outstanding that we thought. Amuse bouche great, first course great when it come to my entree which is the fish. Fish is frozen in the middle area so as my friend's fish too so we sent it back and got a so called cooked fish now but other than that nothing special so bland dessert not very good. I am sorry but I am just being honest there is no love in that cooking and we paid $600 for nothing. Just love the job if you are asking for $150 ++ a person then make the most outstanding of it. New Year's is once in a year only so better cook with passion. That's all

review_626.Review: We were completely disappointed with our NYE prix fixe meal.  For being a self claimed high standard steakhouse we had good expectations going in but our steaks were tasteless and overcooked.  Probably the worst steak we've ever had! The beets in the beet salad were overly salted and tasted like they had been soaked in a brine too long.  We overheard a person at a table next to us complaining about the same thing.  She sent hers back while we only ate a small portion of ours.  There was no question that like we overpaid for a poor quality meal and we were extremely dissatisfied.  We were tempted to dispute the charges but we let it go. The wait staff was good enough and we tipped very generously despite the bad experience.  We were a party of two and spent $500 for a terrible meal!  Money down the drain!!  We will never go back!

review_627.Review: Food was okay, everything was okay. People around us were sending food back because it was to cold. You pay for excellence and recieve okay food and service. Wouldn't recommend when it's busy, possibly better when it's slower and they can handle it.

review_628.Review: Came here with my fiance after reading great reviews and we're not disappointed! Had the tuna and the lettuce cups to start with then I had the fillet mignon which was honestly the best steak I have ever eaten! Great ambience and interiors, Perfect for a date night!

review_629.Review: High-end, well aged, top grade beef. Great space. Heavy food but very tasty. Impeccable service.

review_630.Review: Great steak restaurant within the financial district , but our steaks were  over done. The cost they charge, you would think they could gets this right.

review_631.Review: Food and service were both great!

review_632.Review: Great service me and my wife loved it we would go back great food service and atmosphere

review_633.Review: Everything was great! Except the wagyu beef was a bit cold. Atlas, great ambience, great service, with great company.Recommend! 🤪

review_634.Review: Good food, but not a typical steak house. This menu had an asian flair. It's also pricey, but that's typical for a steak house. Just be prepared for $30 for the cheapest option which you won't end up getting since it's too small. Sides are also additional (not included). That being said, the food was delicious! They know what they are doing in the kitchen.

review_635.Review: This place has a great rib eye --- it was tremendous although slightly greasy.  Wish they seared their steaks.  And how can you NOT have a baked potato??  Should have sides not drenched in oil/butter.  Even the edamine was dripping in sauce.  Why would you put cauliflower in a cream sauce.  Hey chef, young people want to eat healthier.

review_636.Review: 2nd time here. Food are great as usual. Would appreciate if we have more size options. 32oz is just too big for me.

review_637.Review: From the moment we walked in we should have known this would be a terrible dining experience. Our waiter didn't explain the cuts of the meat properly. My husbands boss ended up with a rare steak when he ordered medium well. My husband ended up with a massive cut of rare meat. We didn't have a chance to tell our waiter to change things as he never came back to check on us. Very embarrassing to us as we picked the restaurant for this dinner.

review_638.Review: Our evening began with a nice plate of bread and delicately seasoned shrimp, courtesy of the chef.We placed our drink orders in and they arrived in a timely manner. The Oaxacan Cocktail is the best on the menu. Would have drank those the entire night but wanted to try every drink on the menu.Our soups were the first to arrive, Lobster Corn Soup and Zoup du Jour (Saffron Mussel Soup). They were both very tasty, the first had a strong curry base while the second tasted more creamy, buttery. Next came the shishito peppers. By far the best variation I've ever had. Peppers were not to spicy and had a sweet reduction on top of the Truffle shavings. This was a must have for sure.Our steaks finally came, the T-Bone with egg.
