The best steak paired with their special sauce I've ever had. Definitely next time, I'd love to try their wagyu steak. Unfortunately, the service was a bit weird. Our empty waters sat there for half an hour before being filled. Our final order of cocktails came out way late too. It seems that once they give the final dish, they stop coming to check.

review_639.Review: We used to love dining here. The food was always excellent. I feel like the execution has diminished. If I'm paying so much for the steaks, they should be seasoned well. And if I request a certain doneness, it should come out that way where I shouldn't have to send it back and take a while before coming back out to me. Service continues to be impeccable though.

review_640.Review: This was hands down the best steak I have ever eaten. This place blew away STK in Las Vegas that had held that place in my heart. Recommend ten fold.

review_641.Review: This was horrible. We chose this place given the good reviews for steak. They gave the high-priced sales pitch with the marbled (aka fatty raw meat) upon our arrival, which simply turned my stomach. We ordered, and low and  behold, they were completely out of our choice. Apparently you need to be there in the first 30 minutes of opening to consume the prime rib (per our waiter). We left. And we went to the kitschy but reliably good House of Prime Rib for prime rib (which was worth the 2 hour wait - which tells you how unimpressed we were with every aspect of 5A5).

review_642.Review: To charge these types of prices you have to be dialed on all levels of service....booth was not comfortable, felt worn like I was sitting on wood under the seat...flickering fake candles didn't stay lit...fruit flies near the booth...no serving utensils with appetizers...steaks and sides where delicious but the lack of attention to detail on other things wouldn't bring me back due to the price.

review_643.Review: Ordered two wines. One not available. One took over an hour to find and was presented at the END of the meal. My wife is a sommelier and she was horrified by this. I won't be coming back.

review_644.Review: We had a 7:45 reservation and were a few minutes late and they still seated us promptly. The service was outstanding. I had the Sirloin and my Date had the Prime rib. Both were tender and perfectly cooked. Friendly and courteous waiter. All in all a very enjoyable time at 5A5.

review_645.Review: Excellent Dry aged T-Bone. Ordered Foie Gras as well.

review_646.Review: Awesome restaurant.  Good service, nice decor, friendly and attentive staff, great food.

review_647.Review: too loud, too expensive for the quality of steak                                         .

review_648.Review: Was told about this spot but was not impressed! If you are hungry this is not the place to visit!

review_649.Review: This was one of the best places I've picked to go on an anniversary at first I was nervous because I thought it wasn't romantic enough but it blew me away. The ambiance was just so right and the waiters not waiter really took care of us by bringing complimentary food. Although it is a bit pricey it was still worth it and the steak was amazing! Overall I give it a 4.8 out of 5 it was a really good experience for my girlfriend and I who left satisfied and full

review_650.Review: I took my boyfriend to 5A5 for his birthday. Neither of us had been there before so it was a nice surprise. The service was amazing. Never were we left with a drink even close to empty or crumbs on our table. There was a snack compliments of the Chef that was delicious. I had the prime rib and my boyfriend got the bone in ribeye and they were both cooked perfect and tasted great! The prices were as expected. Would definitely go back !

review_651.Review: The appetizers are really good. Steak is a bit saltier than expected. Would prefer the raw/original taste of the steak instead of tasting the sauce or cheese.

review_652.Review: Had eaten here before, a couple years ago on a week night,  with young Asian clients, but made the mistake of coming again recently with a date on a weekend. Trendy crowd, odd 90's retro decor, with loud blaring  disco music. Don't think we will be back since it's obvious the crowd they are marketing to (dare I say the crowd that has more money than sense) ,  doesn't really care about the food or the dining. As mentioned in previous reviews, this place is about up selling, starting with the presentation of hunks of-- dried out looking-- meat. You'll see the prices on the menu when you look for them; I wasn't shocked because I know what Japanese Wagyu retails for. None of the entrees seem to be served with accompaniments so if you are hungry (which is why we went!) expect to order many add ons. Why are there no steakhouses that serve plain baked potatoes (a big profit maker!) ?  Why do we need 10 ingredients in every side dish or salad?  So they can charge $12+ for a plate. Food here is WAY too overworked and busy.  Waiter seemed insulted that we only wanted wine by the glass; very limited selection.  The whole evening was just too weird.

review_653.Review: Great ambiance and awesome customer service! The meal was amazing as well.

review_654.Review: If you love great steak, the Wagyu kind - this place is unbelievable! You'll pay a hefty price per 4oz piece - but the flavor and texture is phenomenal!

review_655.Review: Bad service, food was bad and cost was outrageous

review_656.Review: Amazing experience.  We tried the Wagyu beef.  A must at this restaurant.  It is pricey but when you try it you'll see why.  My husband and I tried the filet mignon Wagyu style and it slices like butter.  For the appetizer try the Octopus,  it melts in your mouth.  So yummy.  Our dinner choices were prime rib and filet mignon regular style with mashed potatoes and creamed spinach sides and those choices were amazing too.  Service was awesome.  You never had an empty water glass.

review_657.Review: Great food and service! The Wyagu steak is amazing!!!

review_658.Review: Amazing experience.  At first we though we had been given the best table in the house.  Then after looking around it was apparent that all the tables and booths were excellent.  The architect deserves special praise for that.  Starters were delicious.  The steaks were perfect.  Service was excellent.  Even the bathroom is special. We've had favorite restaurants for years and now this one jumped to the top of our list.

review_659.Review: The quality of food was good, but it was noisy. It wasn't comfortable to talk with my husband with the ambience.

review_660.Review: Steak was very good. Servers were very nice and accommodating. I would refer this place to any steak lovers.

review_661.Review: Celebrating 2 year anniversary at a place we've never been and we were quite happy. The food was delicious, our waiter was patient with us, sizes were mostly proportional to prices (We had the mac and cheese and felt it should have been a bigger portion). Otherwise the prices were what we expected and we would go back if only we lived in or near San Francisco but we don't.

review_662.Review: Vegetables very salty.Quality of meat ok but preparation not really outstanding

review_663.Review: Service was horrendous, decor was tacky and the food didn't nearly live up to the price tag. The biggest turn off was that restaurant staff made zero effort to accommodate a patron with food allergies. Would never set foot in this place again.

review_664.Review: Food and space are very pretentious. We left after cocktails and appetizers.

review_665.Review: I brought my mate here for her birthday and she absolutely loved it! The food, service, (Leila P.) and ambience was perfect! Will definitely be returning to dine.

review_666.Review: We were going to see a play at the Eureka Theatre across the street. We checked out the local restaurants before deciding on 5A5 Steak Lounge.  The valet server who took our car was great, he told us to pick up the car after the play. The Mixologist at the bar concocted a Tanquray Martini, she sprinkled the class with vermouth before pouring in the gin and added a orange spray. Delicious! The waiters are numerous and were top notch and fun, especially, Ali. The menu  gave us many delicious choices.  We started with an amuse bouche, wonderful, enjoyed the best hamburgers, truffle fries and mac and cheese.  Dessert was three small scoops of ice cream which tasted like they were made by the pastry chef.We will come back to 5A5 Steak Lounge soon.

review_667.Review: The food was fine, but wouldn't pay that much to go there again--many other steak houses in the city with better food, especially for the price. Certainly many places that are that expensive with MUCH better ambiance. Food aside, I *really* didn't like the ambiance of the place, the lighting was super bright, it was very loud, and gave the impression of sitting in some sort of modern but cheap cafeteria where you're basically shouting to hear the person sitting across the table from you. The bathrooms are gross, all one bathroom for men and women with a trough sink ... no thank you. The booths feel really close to each other which is exacerbated by the way that they are arranged where it feels like the people next to you are filling the empty spaces at your table bc they are arranged kitty-corner. Also, the valet left the lights on in my car and when we came out the car was dead and the valet offered no assistance and we found jumper cables and got the car started by ourselves. Try House of Prime Rib, Alexander's, Ruths Chris, Espetus, etc etc. before this place.

review_668.Review: Amazing steaks! Really good service, with a wonderful menu. So happy I was able to use my rewards points.

review_669.Review: I wasn't impressed at all.  Granted, I didn't have a steak, but what I did have, salmon, mac and cheese (very bland) had no great appeal.  This place looked like it was going to be a great place, but I was mistaken.  The noise was almost unbearable as well.  Now, realize that I dine out at least twice a week and always search for amazing restaurants, but, I'm sorry to say, I won't be going back here.  The pentacle reviews were overstated.  Oh, as a side not I also worked in the restaurant biz for 15 years.  I'm not a rookie.  I'm sorry to be leaving this review.

review_670.Review: Two big problems with the experience.  The first was that our entrees took well over an hour to come out.  It was acknowledged by the staff as they came by multiple times to apologize.  But what got really frustrating is they apologized a final time and asked if we wanted something else to eat while we waited.  He offered a few different appetizer options and we selected one.  That appetizer then appeared on the check as they charge me for it!The second big problem is they asked if we ever ate there before.  We both said "no."  He then proceeded to show us their lineup of steaks and asked if we ever heard of that kind of steak.  We both said "no."  My business guest chose one and the waiter simply took the order.  He never found it necessary to let us know the steak was 256 dollars!  That seems like an obvious curtesy given we've never been there before, never heard of that steak, and the prices aren't listed online.  Very very money grubbing place.

review_671.Review: An expensive birthday treat for my daughter but well worth it. Creative menu, well trained, friendly waitstaff . I can't remember a better meal. The imaginative sides more than complemented the delicious steaks. Everything was a treat down to the desserts and the Japanese whiskey flights. I highly recommend that Mac and cheese, the creamed spinach, sautéed mushrooms, and bacon topped mashed potatoes. I assure you, the flavors will light up your palet.

review_672.Review: I set up this reservation for my husband while traveling on business.  He was hosting clients and his manager.  He said it was a great experience.  Good choice for business dinner.

review_673.Review: NY Strip was cooked to perfection, nice flavour and the shrooms were great (they had run out of asparagus!)Unfortunately the Foie Gras was cold in the middle, bad job ... Poor choice of red wine ( no Malbec!?!) and even poorer selection of wines by the glass... Oh well.

review_674.Review: Brought my mom here for her birthday. Great food and service, however would not recommend for families. Seems like most of the crowd are with friends or work colleagues, or on a date.

review_675.Review: We dined at the bar and had great service.  The oysters are a very good choice as they are prepared with a tasty variety of items with just enough kick.  My husband had the prime rib, and was very pleased.  I had the Tajima Filet and the demi glaze and mushrooms added great flavor.  The restaurant did a very good job with my "special" ordering.  The Flying Lotus drink is very good.

review_676.Review: I have been there twice, I love it ! High recommendation ！

review_677.Review: Old and tired. The years it's been here show

review_678.Review: The Lobster Tempura was "to die for" and the salads were yummy, too.  All of us were disappointed in our filets and we probably should have sent them back.  The one that was supposed to be cooked well-done was cooked medium at the most and all three of the filets were served lukewarm (at best).  As I mentioned, we should have called our server over and asked her to take them back and warm them up but our server never checked on us.  We were not alcohol drinkers and I cannot help but think our lack of ordering alcohol may have contributed to the inattentiveness of our server.  If we ever went again I would order two orders of Lobster Tempura and I would make them my entree.  I would go back just to have that again!  As far as steaks go, we would go to a different San Francisco restaurant.We did love the ambiance of the restaurant and everyone was extremely nice and welcoming.

review_679.Review: The food was good, well prepared and presented. Couple of things that were not up to par for a restaurant that charges the price it does. One, made a reservation and showed up little early and waited patiently in lounge area. Was told that they would call us up when table was ready, our time comes up but they forget about us and help others to their tables before us even though they came later. Two, host sat us in right next to a big group even though there were open tables away from the big crowd. Three, server was attentive initially but after bringing the food out we did not get checked for drink refill or any follow up. Also took 10-15 mins to get our bill after we had asked for the bill.

review_680.Review: One of SF's better steakhouses with a really nice atmosphere.  Convenient to the business district.  Attentive service.

review_681.Review: the service is excellent but the steak unfortunately is not. i would recommend trying the non-steak options. those were all pretty decent.

review_682.Review: My colleagues and I came here for a client dinner. It was amazing and the clients were impressed. Don't forget to ask for the whiskey cart!

review_683.Review: The restaurant was great and the steaks were incredible.  The restaurant was a little slow as we came at 9:00 pm on a Monday.   The owner actually came to our table and spent a little time explaining their menu.  I don't live in San Francisco but I will definitely eat here again.

review_684.Review: Our server Scott was the best, he made our birthday celebration wonderful.  He was so polite and perfect in serving and adequate placing the utensils, wonderful personality and that is what makes the restraunt awesome.  Best server ever. He should be a head waiter. I highly recommend to coming back because he works there and for his perfect service.

review_685.Review: Pretentious and the food under delivers.  I had the lobster tempura and it was greasy and lacked flavor.  My husband had the sliders and there were good, but nothing special.  We passed on the entrees and the desert list left us wanting as well.  There are many, many restaurants in San Francisco and I recommend you look elsewhere for a delicious dining experience.

review_686.Review: The food was AMAZING.  The scallop appatizer is a must.

review_688.Review: The food was great overall. Not amazing where I have to come back again but don't mind coming back...if this make sense. The T-bone steak was very tasty  and it's so big we could have shared. Service was a bit slow but our servers were nice.

review_689.Review: Disappointing dinner. Recent changes in bar staff resulted in the absence of wines and standard top shelf booze selections. Server was largely inattentive. Steaks and Prime Rib was decent, but not world class as the name or other reviews had suggested.

review_690.Review: Seemed like the restaurant was stuck in the 90s from dishes to plating to ambience. They executed quite well on everything and the service was excellent, but it did seem like a bit of a time machine. The exception were the amuse bouche, which were generally quite interesting and delicious.

review_691.Review: I love steaks. I love whiskey. This place has it both. I came here with my wife to unwind after another work week. They have a nice assortment of Japanese Whiskeys (tasted ok) but also had a nice selection of scotches too (I stuck with my Macallan). She had a T-Bone, I had their Wagyu Filet. My thinking: you go to a burger spot for their burgers, not something else on the menu.Wagyu Filet was definitely an experience you will need to experience. It is on the pricier side (around 140ish for 4 oz) but I feel that its worth it. You can taste the laziness of spoiled life of the meat with every bite.WILL DEFINITELY COME AGAIN FOR WAGYU!

review_692.Review: We haven't dined here this year. We had great experiences in the past. The appetizers were tasty. The steaks were top notch, the same quality as Roka Akor. This time, we felt we ate at Outback. (I haven't been to an Outback since college. Outback possibly serves better steaks.) The hamachi shots, the salads, the entrees taste cheaply made with inferior ingredients.The heirloom burrata salad had very little burrata. It's just a pile of tomatoes without any flavor.no efforts were put into this dish. The free bites were overly seasoned, so sweet and overpowering. It was gross.The lobster tempura  was the only acceptable dish.The New York steak looked so sad. It looked like the meat had sat in the kitchen for a week. It tastes chewy.  We couldn't finish it.The sweet potato gnocchi was very salty and heavy. It's not SF cooking. It's more of "fancy" Midwest cooking.  This was a very disappointing experience.  We rarely visit the same restaurant more than once a year because there are so many cool new ones to try.  This return trip was horrifying. Now we can permanently cross 5A5 off our visiting list.

review_694.Review: Restaurant had come highly recommended, which made the experience even more disappointing. The bone in ribeye was just OK, the mushroom side dish and creamed spinach were very good.  There was an extremely long delay between the appetizer and main course.  Then our waiter completely disappeared and we sat with empty plates in front of us for far too long once our main dishes were done.  We had to chase him down for the bill.  The decor is very dated and the bathroom stinks - literally.  They smelled and were dirty.  I booked this for a business dinner and I left embarrassed that I had recommended it.  Don't make the same mistake.

review_695.Review: The place was overrated, over priced, and the waiter was slower than slow.

review_696.Review: Downstairs where the bathroom smells like old garbage from a compactor. It maybe also the old carpeting they have downstairs.  Some Febreeze spray can help the foul smell Side dish we ordered "Shrooms " were way too salty!  Really salty! Music from the bar were so loud and can be heard at the dining area ....The kind of music chosen was not appropriate with the atmosphere where people are trying to have nice dinner. Servers were great!!! Kitchen staffs were great!

review_697.Review: Great food as always. The staff is wonderful and overall great dining experience.

review_698.Review: The last time  I came here it was very nice so that is why I went to this restaurant again. However this time I went the steaks were not as good and was not worth the price. I wish we gotten a discount. My partner ended up dumping the steaks once he got home.

review_699.Review: The service was unprofessional given the price point.

review_702.Review: Service is good and decor is nice. The streaks are good but can be pricey. Been here many times before and this time it was a bit of an disappointment. I had the skirt steak which they had pieces of ginger which did nothing to help with the steak and it actually took away from the flavor. We also had he rib eye which was better but over all I expected more and it seem to be just okay but nothing to write home about. It was still an okay night but it was nothing special. They still have a good steak and good service, but nothing to brag about especially considering the price you pay, which is not cheap.

review_703.Review: Love love love this place. It is one of our favorite. We do prefer to come earlier as the food seems to be fresher. The waitstaff is awesome!

review_704.Review: I have been looking for a good steak house in San Francisco for some time, now I have found it.  The steak was excellent, the appetizers, meal and dessert top notch.  It is a modern setting, not the old school wood paneled steakhouse.  Everything was pricey, but very high quality and definitely worth it.  Perfect for a special event or to impress a customer.

review_705.Review: Great food. However, a steak restaurant should not run out of prime rib hours before closing time. Summer crowd of tourists more interested in their cell phones than their company and the food. Some furniture in disrepair; booth sofa torn, so we asked for another table. Service friendly enough, however amateurish, unexoected for a high end restaurant.  Wine should be offeret and served with the meal, not into the meal.

review_706.Review: Service was wonderful but food was terrible. The fries were luke warm and some of it was kind of soggy - ? re-fried. Also the steak was a big disappointment.  Steak was again luke warm, lack of seasoning.  Worst steak house I have been to (believe me, I have been to many top steakhouse in US and Tokyo).

review_708.Review: Over priced  and so noisy. If you want to pay 150 for a Japanese steak,  this is the place for you.

review_709.Review: Have always totally enjoyed this restaurant. Their food & service is unsurpassed .

review_710.Review: We come back to 5A5 because the meal is memorable. Yes it is expensive but we come back for special occasions when we want Wagyu. They have delicious sides like truffle mac and cheese or the creamed spinach. They also have other domestic steaks that are also very delicious. The service is excellent and the ambiance can be very romantic.

review_711.Review: As always, I had a wonderful dining experience at 5A5.  The steak I got was cooked to perfection and was exactly what I was hoping for.  The staff are extremely accommodating and try to make your visit as great as possible.  Thanks for a fantastic dinner!

review_712.Review: Scrumptious steaks, a tad on the modern side compared to the old school steak houses.   Never disappoints.

review_713.Review: Amazing food. Amazing service. We were there to celebrate my husband's new job - and the kitchen staff gave him a small complimentary dessert with "Congratulations!" written on the plate in delicate chocolate icing calligraphy. It was beautiful!Chairs were oddly low (or tables were oddly high), resulting in feeling like we were kids at a too-tall table. Everything else was fine.

review_714.Review: The food was good, but there wasn't anything spectacular about it especially for the prices that you were paying. My friend and I shared the NY strip steak (amongst many other dishes) and we found this to be extremely salty which was disappointing since it is a steakhouse. I'm not sure that I'll be back again.

review_715.Review: 5A5 has a great bar. Ashley is an excellent bar tender.  The food, specializing in meat and steak, is very good.  Management is involved and very friendly.  All employees are attentive.  We plan to return

review_716.Review: Great service. Love the location. Awesome staff. Ambiance is outstanding. Unfortunately, food leaves a lot to be desired. It was good, but no dishes were unforgettable. At the price point, you expect "mind-blowing."

review_717.Review: Unfortunately, the restaurant was more hype than quality.  My husband & I spent $200 for our dinner.  He liked the taste of the filet; I didn't like my chicken at all.  It was dry and I should had returned it.

review_718.Review: Always enjoy coming to eat here. It is a little pricy however you pick your poison depending on what you order. Food is great here

review_719.Review: I was a little disappointed. Not as good as before. I had great experiences before and this time the food was very mediocre. Cocktails were good.

review_720.Review: Well, this was way expensive for not impressive food. Can't imagine who would want to pay upwards of $100 for a beef entre. Definitely NOT kid-friendly.

review_721.Review: Very welcoming ambiance and staff! Food is awesome prime rib is the best!

review_722.Review: I am no foodie, and I'm far from a steak expert, but this was one of the best meals I've ever had. Absolutly everything was delicious.

review_723.Review: I picked this place out after searching for some time for a place that was beautiful and that also had great food. I was very excited about this place, I had chosen it over many others to celebrate my boyfriends 30th birthday and on top of that the itinerary I had created was a surprise. We arrived early and were seated in a less than desirable area of the restaurant. My boyfriend mentioned to the hostess that we would prefer to sit in a more central location to be able to enjoy the full ambiance of the restaurant (after all it was his 30th birthday and it should be a unique and special experience). This was the first fault of many that we endured while trying to dine here.. Which is very disappointing since I booked through open table and I usually have a great experience when I do at other restaurants. Then we ordered our drinks which came after waiting a short while. For appetizers we ordered the kale salad and the truffle fries, for main entrees we ordered the salmon and Wagyu ribeye plus a side of asparagus. This is where things went awry, we waited and waited and waited... Nothing... People around us got their food and we only had bread.. Finally we spoke to the manager who offered to comp our drinks but we declined, I wasn't going to wait any longer and pay that type of bill for such a terrible experience. I would not recommend this place to anyone, not even people I dislike.. I feel that this may have been a fluke but is it really worth risking your special event and feeling the way I felt when I left? I highly doubt it.. Just a warning.

review_724.Review: 5A5 is a nice place and has really good food.  But last Saturday evening they allowed a Birthday party with 5+ children in a private room that was just getting started around 6pm.   The noise and the children walking around is not something you want or  expect when you having a $300 dinner.  The manager finally closed the door after an hour but the evening had been dampened by then.  Plus, the table next to us not at all dressed appropriately and was watching the Warriors game with sound.  I am not sure restaurants understand that when they enable and tolerate very rude people it ruins the experience for many.

review_725.Review: Food is pretty good but not worth the high prices. The steak is great quality but slathered in only ok sauces. Plus the noise level is high and the seating is awkward (more like a hotel lounge) which makes it near impossible to have dinner conversation. If I was in the mood for steak would not return – probably go back to my normal joint which is House of Prime Rib. Same kind of place but considerably bettern

review_726.Review: Disappointed in ambience. Too many kids, that were loud and ruined the experience.

review_727.Review: very good， me and my wife love it

review_728.Review: I brought 4 friends to 5A5 who have never been there before and they had an amazing time.  They loved the service and the food was over the top.

review_729.Review: Everything was great except that server told us that they could not split the soup that we ordered. She at least tried, but it was weird that they couldn't just give us another bowl to share.

review_730.Review: This is good steak place.  If you are a steak purist this may not be your place.  While they do have great cuts of meat.  This includes their excellent choices in A5 Wagyu cuts.  They add different sauces to their steaks rather than let the meat stand alone.  That is fine for me but may not be if folks like their steak bare or with the sauces on the side.  It was different for me.  The sides were very good.  There were very unique pinafores.  We had their mushrooms which was good as well as their mashed potatoes.   Dessert was great.  Quality is what you would expect from a higher end restaurant like this.  Why I felt I had to write a review, was because of the service.  I felt we were not treated right by our server.  It was not busy the night we went.  Our server took our order and repeated it three times to us.  Also wrote it down.  I thought that was cool. But then one of our main dishes was missing.  And our server was no where to be found.  I had to track down our server to ask about our missing dish after all of our other dishes were brought out.  When the server finally came to check on us and we informed him of the missing dish, he blamed the mistake on us.  This was after he repeated the order to us three times in the beginning.   That piece kind of ruined our experience.  If he just apologized and owned the mistake we would have been fine, but to blatantly just say it was our fault.  There were three of us there they heard him repeat the order three times and witnessed him write it down.  After that again we did not see our server for extended periods of time.   I had to get up and find our server for our bill.  That one piece did not sit well with us.  Not sure if we would go back especially with other great steak places like Alexander's and Bobo's.

review_731.Review: Had the bone in rib eye. Very tasty but a bit undercooked for medium rare. Possibly due to it being a 32oz cut and almost 2" thick but would rather have it cooked a bit more evenly and thorough for medium rare. Was medium on the outside and rare in the middle. Definitely needed more attention when cooking. Next time if we return will order medium but then it may be well done on the outside and medium rare in the middle. Iceberg salad was amazing as was the house cab (good pairing with the rib eye) and mashed potatoes. Unfortunately the asparagus side was overcooked and a bit droopy.

review_732.Review: I wanted to go some place nice and memorable.  We were rewarded with a great experience.  The steak was great and the dessert was a great finish.  The rib eye my husband ordered was huge.

review_733.Review: We were in SF for weekend celebrating my wife's 40th birthday & friend said 5A5 steak was the best they ever had, so we made a reservation & arrived a bit early. They were kind enough to accommodate us but table was directly under A/C vent & my wife was freezing whole meal despite asking several staff to turn it down. We switched sides, but she was still pretty uncomfortable.  We should have moved. Not the restaurant's fault obviously, but we were surrounded by tables with small children who were clearly over the steak lounge vibe, was a surprise on the so-so ambiance.We didn't opt not for the Wagyu beef but still paid hefty prices for a filet & bone-in rib-eye.  My wife orders her steak well-done (I know...) but usually isn't a prob but they brought out a charred piece of meat so dry & tasteless that we were shocked!  We hardly ever send food back, but this hockey puck went back.  They were quick to bring out a replacement, maybe too quick as 2nd steak was closer to medium than well, but by then she wasn't prepared to send another steak back again.  We had truffle mac & shrooms as sides. Mac was avg, shrooms were very good.  We didn't notice until half-way through our meal other tables were getting an amuse-bouche compliments of chef, but we never did. No biggie by itself, but just added to an overall slighted feel.Early I mentioned on the sly to waiter that it was her birthday & he let the staff know, but at the end of meal we were presented with dessert menus anyway & when we didn't order anything there, we were given check like it was time to go...no birthday desert. The bill was wrong (they charged us twice for the bad filet and the replacement both) so I had to send that back too. They clearly forgot the birthday desert (I get its complimentary so don't expect anything ), but by then I told them not to worry about it when waiter brought the corrected bill back and he seemed to take offense & brought it anyway. We left it untouched - bad B-day experience!

review_734.Review: Deserts where beyond great. I had the ribeye and it lacked flavor the wife had the prime rib and said it was good but not great. The lobster appetizer was excellent. Mac and cheese was a big let down. The overall vibe of the restaurant and presentation of the food was above expectations!

review_735.Review: I come here every time I am in the city. My new husband and I had our first (marital) dinner date here. The food is delicious and the truffle Mac and cheese it a must try. The staff is friendly and attentive. This is one of the BEST restaurants in the city! And yes, I've been to most restaurants in SF :)

review_736.Review: Steaks were cooked to perfection, very good though expected a bit more taste. Side dishes were excellent and plentiful. Ambiance is enjoyable, atmosphere not overly loud.

review_737.Review: NICE QUIET PLACE.   WE HAD A GIFT CARD VALUED AT $100.  OUR MEAL COME TO UNDER $200.  PRIME RIB WHICH  IS LIMITED OFFERING---OVER 160Z--WAS COOKED PERFECT .  IT WAS BETTER THAN THE HOUSE OF PRIME RIB ( IT WAS EXPENSIVE BUT WORTH IT). I HAD THE BONE-IN RIB-EYE.  AGAIN, COOKED PERFECT.  OUTSTANDING!!! I WOULD HIGHLY RECOMMEND IF YOU CAN PAY $200 FOR AN OUTSTANDING MEAL. GREAT PLACE.

review_738.Review: The ingredients were good quality, but all our food was overly seasoned and smothered in a lot of different flavours so that you could not taste the nice ingredients. My husband's steak came smothered with a cup of sauce that was sickly sweet and incredibly salty at the same time, he spent ages scraping it off to attempt to eat some of it. Call me old-fashioned, but  steak sauce should come on the side, specially one so overpowering as this...

review_739.Review: The overall quality of the experience was amazing! I felt like we had our own personal chef!

review_740.Review: We had a wonderful evening! From the host to the bar staff to our waiter, the service was terrific. I chose the foie gras, octopus salad, truffle fries, and chocolate creme brulee. It was all delicious! Highly recommend.

review_741.Review: Two of us went for a nice dinner. Had been once before. We both had steaks, she had the fillet and I had the T-Bone.  Both were absolutely delicious.  Very good service I felt and would certainly go back again.  Surprisingly not very busy considering the quality of the dinner.

review_742.Review: Went for a special birthday, we just had the regular meats not the special Wagyu.  so was very nice service super great

review_743.Review: This was excellent - quiet, an excellent selection of steak plus some other good dishes for people who might not want steak.

review_744.Review: I am an Alexander's Steakhouse guy, thought I would try another Kobe place. The steaks were just as good,  atmosphere was a bit ROWDY  for my liking. It is advertised as a LOUNGE so I  cannot complain, service was good , but not as good as Alexander's. I will continue my KOBE journey and report back.

review_745.Review: The food was amazing, and those truffle fries were divine. Along with the exceptional flavors of every course that Chef Chen created!! I will definitely be going back there just for the food & recommending all my friends & family!! Keep up the good work Chef!! You deserve all the praise, food is what brings people together & creates good memories forever!! 😋😊

review_746.Review: My guests and I had a fantastic dining experience! Thanks to the team.

review_747.Review: 5A5 is our go-to restaurant for special occasions and again they did not disappoint.  The food was fantastic and we had excellent services.  I look forward to going back again.

review_748.Review: Make sure that when you get your steak it is prepared how you specify.  Ordered a medium steak,  received well done piece of cardboard. I couldn't eat more than three bits and the waiter never came back for me to even send my dish back.  Considering what I paid for my meal I was not impressed.

review_750.Review: We had the Wagyu Rib Eye and the Tajima F1 Filet and I can say it was the best beef I've ever had! If you're looking for authentic, melt in your mouth, marble, top quality A5 100% Japanese Miyazaki Wagyu beef, you have to give it try here. It was soo good! Buttery goodness! The Tajima F1 was really tasty too. You can tell the difference of course between the 100% Wagyu and the Tajima but I really enjoyed the cut and it was very flavorful and tasty with a good buttery-ness too. We also had the truffle fries which were one of the bests we've had also. It was an overall great experience at 5A5 and the food was superb. The server and waitstaff were great and attentive. Our server was very helpful as well. The palate cleanser sorbet and compliments of the chef tasting was very yummy too.

review_751.Review: I had expectations of the everyday steaks being super tasty but they were just average. I guess when you specialize in the upscale beef  you are wanting us to order that instead. The meal was costly and taste was just average. So it was over priced. Service was great.

review_752.Review: Hamachi plate was outstanding. Prime rib was good, but didn't blow my socks off or anything. Wagyu steaks look incredible, but way out of my price range at 120-150 each.

review_753.Review: We loved this venue. Nice decor, and seating is beautifully arranged, providing a very intimate feeling. We really enjoyed lounging at the bar prior to being seated at our table for five. We were celebrating both a 68th birthday and 20th anniversary, and it was made very special by the staff by bringing out two complimentary desserts with the words Happy Birthday and Happy Anniversary written in chocolate syrup! Service was excellent: very attentive, without being overwhelming or intrusive. We tried two of the A5 Wagyu beef offerings, along with the dry aged bone-in T-bone, filet mignon, rib-eye, several sides, and appetizers. Dessert selection was minimal and more "fancy" than flavorful. The meats were tender and cooked to perfection. The flavor of each dish was unique and intense, but when you put everything  together in a meal, it almost overwhelmed your palate. The biggest downside was that everything was overly salted.We anticipated spending a lot of money, but thought $1,000 (including tip) was a bit high for a party of five. The atmosphere was amazing, and we had a fantastic evening; we may return again, but only for a special celebration.

review_754.Review: For the price of this place, suggest going to Ruth's Chris or similar. Overall the place was a bit pretentious  and the food (we had TBone and fish) was really not that great and covered with a lot of sauce to make up for taste. Tables did not even have proper tablecloths. Servers were friendly though and the chef provided a few nice appetizers.

review_755.Review: Two of us dine there for a special occasion (birthday). We split one of the kobe steaks, and it was so good. Really expensive, but really good. The service was excellent, and they had no hesitation about splitting servings for us light eaters.

review_756.Review: Just wanted to briefly say that the hybrid beef is excellent, a good choice if you're interested in the higher-priced selections but can't quite spring them.  I really enjoyed it.  Also, they have a very sane corkage program.  We brought a nice old california cab that they were very happy to open for us. We'll come back.

review_757.Review: Ordered the wagyu sliders, truffle fries, wagyu ribcap, wagyu ribeye, Creamed spinach and mash. All excellent dishes! Our waiter was knowledgeable and attentive. Will definitely be back.

review_758.Review: I took a colleague to dinner here as he wanted steak and I wanted to try the restaurant. We ordered our meals (an appetizer, 1 steak, 1 prime rib, two sides to share and a bottle of wine).  The appetizer arrived promptly and was good. More than 30 minutes later, our waiter returned to tell us they were out of prime rib. This was probably 45 minutes after we had ordered! He brought (rubbery and overcooked) lobster tail to tide us over. When our meat arrived, neither were medium rare as we ordered and both side dishes were wrong. The meat wasn't especially flavorful either. Our waiter tried his best, but multiple mistakes on a $400 dinner for two is unacceptable. I won't be going back nor do I recommend this place.

review_759.Review: It's difficult to find a great steakhouse in SF with this beautiful ambience. The staff is warm and helpful, the chef sends out palette cleansers between courses, and the food is amazing. We tried the kobe beef for the first time and were not disappointed!  Extra recognition to the host who made sure we had a quieter table per my request - service is top notch.

review_760.Review: Came here for Valentine's Day Dinner.  Made reservations online for 8:00pm, was told to get a cocktail first and was seated very shortly.  I think it's great when a restaurant makes a specific menu for a special day, it makes it easier to order and we know the food will come out great.  We brought our own wine and our server opened it easily for us.  The server really knew the menu and told us which dishes he preferred!  The food was great and we even got to sample a small peace of fois gras.  Overall, I was very happy with the dinner, I will come back for another date night!

review_761.Review: I was here back in 2014 and again in 2016.  I think the experience for the quality of the food was slightly worst compared to 2014.

review_762.Review: Overpriced.  Could only order off the fixed menu over Valentine day weekend.  The filet was tender, though not very flavorful.  It was my original understanding that the regular menu would also be available to order from.   I really had my heart set on trying their prime rib.

review_763.Review: Very attentive service! Great food, the other guests gave me a little bit of a snobby vibe, considering I've wined and dined in France - this level of snobbism was unnecessary.

review_764.Review: Pre-valentines celebration (2/12)  was great and we were able to choose a seat for a 7:30pm time. The waiter showed us different types of steak and was very helpful.Always go for the best- Wagyu steak! It's on the pricier side so we tried the next best thing: half Wagyu, half Holstein (Australian). Which was really good! We were told chef tends to cook on the rare side so I said medium well and it was prefect! My husband got the filet mignon- equally great. Service was attentive and we received a lovely amouse busche.

review_765.Review: Last time I was here was 4 years ago, but the atmosphere and the quality of the food is still as good as ever. Came here for a birthday celebration and ordered truffle fries, a A5 and a 50/50 wagyu Holstein steaks. Truffle fries were just as addicting as they were years ago although the fries were more on the shorter end than last time, probably got the end of the batch. The steaks were perfectly cooked to the medium well I wanted. The restaurant was very understanding because it was Superbowl weekend and the festivities pushed back our original reservation time a whole 2 hours. They still were able to seat us despite the later hour and even prepared a beautiful birthday plate at the end of our meal for my guest's birthday. Will definitely come back again for another special occasion.

review_766.Review: Food was somewhat flavorful but temperature was off.

review_767.Review: Went with a client and ended up having the most expensive dinner of my life.  This place is not for the frugal!We did the A5 Experience and added on the other two Waygu options as well.  The A5 steaks were out of this world.  One of them was so marbled that it could literally be cut with a spoon.  If you are a steak lover this should be on your bucket list.

review_768.Review: Our server was amazing, food was great and wine list was the best

review_769.Review: My husband and I were in town for our honeymoon, and after much searching we decided on 5A5 for our steak dinner. First of all, I must say the service was by far the best we've ever received at ANY restaurant. Everyone, especially our waitress, was so friendly. Our water was constantly being refilled, even when there was still 3/4 left. The presentation of the food is outstanding. Everything was beautiful. Prices were reasonable for the quality of the food too! Only complaints: I ordered the Filet, and the sauce on the filet was not really necessary. Although my steak was delicious, I think it would have been better without the sauce. The more simpler, the better when you are eating quality steak! We ordered the lobster for our appetizer and it was nothing special... However the bacon wrapped dates, cauliflower, spinach were great. They also gave us a yummy brownie that said "congratulations" on the plate. Overall, I would recommend 5A5. Excellent service and beautiful presentation of food, as well as good food.

review_770.Review: First, had reservations but had to wait 35 minutes, when the restaurant wasn't full. Not sure what that was about, there was no explanation and no apology.  The apps were okay. The bone-in ribeye was very good, and I recommend it if you go. However, we also ordered a Tajima steak, which is 50/50 wagyu/holstein. It was good, but doused in sauce and totally not worth the price (the bone in ribeye was better). Also, the wagyu prices were way over the top, some 50% more than other restaurants I've been to (for example, high end steakhouses in Vegas... I'm not saying it's worth it at those restaurants, but I can't understanding why the prices are so much higher here). Fortunately we didn't order the overpriced wagyu.  Anyway, the food was okay, just not worth the money, and the restaurant has a kitchy feel to it; high end prices, but mid-tier ambience. Save your money.

review_771.Review: exceptional!  Food was delish!  Amazing options, great wine, service was spot on!  Truffle fries, waygu sliders, shasitio peppers for apps.  Great evening with friends!  Can't wait to go back!

review_773.Review: All the steak dishes are fantastic. The lobster tempura is the best... Must order! Side dishes are tasty. Dessert options could be improved.

review_774.Review: This is a steak house I go to when I visit SF. Last couple times, I splurged on Wagyu beef, which was their specialty. They were sublime, but cost $250 - 500 a dish. So, that is for business dinners. This time I went with a friend and was embarrassed to order an extravagant main course. So, I tried their dry aged T Bone. The sauce and the soft poached egg on top were nice. The meat was ok. It was a solid steak, but not exceptional. My friend had the prime rib which he liked. We both loved lobster tempura appetizer. The wine list is stronger for CA and OR wine, which is fair since it is a west coast restaurant. The ambiance is lively, chic but not too loud.  The server this time was rude, but last few times the servers were nice. It was probably because we went there relatively late in the evening.

review_775.Review: The foie gras was cut to a sliver and came burnt. Many food and alcohol items were not available.

review_776.Review: Great food and our server was fantastic. However long wait for a reservation while there were empty tables killed the experience. The older man -GM? Perhaps?-appeared overwhelmed in half empty restaurant, acted incompetent and was rude. Never again

review_777.Review: Everything was very good at 5A5. I ordered for an appetizer the scallops, the shrimp, and the lobster tempura.  Then had the crab salad, and some bread with bacon baked into it.  The Waygu 4oz Rib eye was the star of the night, completely unbelievable taste!  The New York as my entree couldn't compare after eating the Waygu.  Recommend the mashed potatoes with bacon  cooked in maple syrup as a side.Next time I'm ordering this: Two cocktails, the crab salad, 8oz Waygu Rib eye, and the mash potatoes.

review_778.Review: Top notch food all night, but the sous-veed duck was the star and should be consumed at all costs. Crazily is was even better than the New York strip, which was well cooked but a bit tough. The filet looked fantastic on the tables next to us, but we didn't get the change to try it.Also, my goodness, the lobster bisque. Oh lordy, I need more of that in my life. It too was incredible. A must if it's available when you go.Additionally, the service all night was truly great. Friendly and attentive without being annoying in the slightest.

review_779.Review: I thought the food was just a "C" but the service was a good "A-".   I was with a group of 5 and it was a limited fixed menu for NYE.  It may be better experience with a full menu.  Everyone in my group kept saying everything was "okay".  I will say after 4 days in San Francisco I did not eat anywhere where the food and service were solid "A's".  I've been to many big cities and eaten at many fine dining restaurants and I can't say I would automatically recommend it.  But, everyone there seemed nice including management.  Management did come by the table to check on us (which was nice) but we elected not to say anything with everything being okay. I don't usually complain unless things are terrible.

review_780.Review: The food was delicious total bill came out to 350.00 . Not bad for the nye 4 course dinner for 2 . Drinks and bar was horrible . Worst cocktails I had thank god for the free champagne that the waiter gave us. Over all I would recommend the steak house but service was slow and drinks were horrible. Ended up going down to pier 39 for the alcohol

review_781.Review: If you like medium rare prime rib, you have found a home.  I have had it about 6 times, and it has been one home run after another.  The service and atmosphere are excellent. Wonderful tomato bisque soup and superior creamed spinach.

review_782.Review: Very different steakhouse. Wonderful flavors with an Asian flare. Great service.

review_783.Review: While the entrees (sea bass, filet mignon, T-bone) were delicious, the sides (creamed spinach, mac and cheese, truffle fries, and sliders) were really delicious. Everything was excellent from the bacon bread to the palate "cleansers" to the entrees, sides, and little pieces of sweets at the end.Service was excellent- very cordial and attentive waiter- Ben, and attentive wait staff. I liked the touch of holding a folded napkin between the water glass and the diner when filling the glass to prevent splashes. We had a great time!

review_784.Review: 5A5 is a restaurant where the food never disappoints. My husband and I have been here many times for both special occasions, and just entertaining guests in from out of town. The Food - The food here is experimental, rich and truly an experience. This restaurant serves bacon bread as a complimentary starter - an indication that you are really in for fun dining experience. Start with the hamachi spoon appetizer. The flavor combination of uni, strawberries, pickled seaweed and ponzu sauce is really remarkable. For a main course, trying one of the cuts of meat that 5A5 is known for is a must. If you want to spend a bit more for true luxury, the wagyu beef selection is perfectly marbles for a mouthwatering meal. If you can get there early enough, try the prime rib. This sells out most nights, but is worth getting there a bit early. If you a good piece of meat, but don't want to break the bank or get there at 4:00p - the filet mignon is your dish.Ambiance - 5A5 has a great 1950's lounge vibe. Lots of round leather booths, dark lighting, and a bar that looks like it could be from a scene in Mad Men. Great place for drinks with friends or dinner.Service - Generally, the service here is really great. We went on a night where service we quite slow. From meal order to meal arrival, was probably about an hour or more. Granted, with good food comes good wait patience. While the food did take a bit of time to arrive, the staff frequently checked in on us and made sure that our drinks and bacon bread were filled.Overall, great steaks, and really unique food combinations. Definitely work trying.

review_785.Review: Fabulous host and hostess took great care of my wife and I. The staff was on par with the best I've experienced in the city. Good arrived promptly and as ordered. Descriptions of the plates could have matched the presentation and flavors. I will return several times.

review_786.Review: 2nd time here; both for business dinner. The steaks were very good both times. But on this recent visit, the service was very slow. It took a long time for us to get a hold of our server to order food and dessert at the end. The noise also was a little too loud; none of us were really able to hear each other speak. And to make things worse, one of my colleagues' car was broken into (he had the car valet at the restaurant).

review_787.Review: I've been to 5A5 a few times now and every time has been a great experience.  The service is fantastic - attentive but not pushy in any respect.  The ambiance in the restaurant is relaxed but upscale with a more modern feel to it.  On top of all that, the food is wonderful - my steak came out done to perfection and I haven't had anything there that I haven't liked.  Thanks for a great experience!

review_788.Review: Came from out of town to this restaurants after reading some.good reviews. However...good food means nothing without good service!!! Started off asking if we wanted cocktails. They didn't arrive until minutes before the food. One of the cocktails they were out of ingredients...weren't informed until the other cocktails came out. Then made a New drink but brought the wrong one to the table. Also out of desert on the menu...When we complained...they seemed indifferent. Out was hard to get anyone's attention  and customer service seemed only genuine by our buser Jorge. He was attentive and smiling and in our opinion of the four of us felt he was much more deserving of serving the food than just water and clearing plates..He was great and helped to handle our other requests that no one else seemed to care about!! He should be promoted!!!

review_789.Review: The food was delectable, but the service was amazing!!!!  We all had a wonderful time!!!!

review_790.Review: Food was great, service was amazing, drinks were fantastic!!!!

review_791.Review: If you have the money and want to experience one of the best steaks that melts in your mouth, this is the place for you.  It is very pricey and you might get sticker shock.  However, there are other bite size tasting that you can try without breaking the bank!

review_792.Review: I have been to my fair share of steak restaurants in San Francisco and I have to say the service and food here was exceptional. Although it does come with a hefty price tag, it is definitely worth the visit.

review_793.Review: Made my reservations on open table. Of course received the email reminder but also received a personal call reminder from the restaurant. Parking was easy and free on the street. It was Sat night at 6.Hostess was ok. She had to finish her conversation with her coworker before greeting us. She didn't offer to take our coats but saw her take others.Waiter was great. Although he didn't go in depth about the different meats as a friend of mine led me to expect, he was very friendly and attentive throughout the meal. He never rushed us and in fact encouraged us to stay for dessert.The steaks----absolutely great! My husband ordered Wagyu ribeye. It was expensive but really distinct and mouthwatering and I will be coming back for it. I had the filet mignon. It was tasty and perfectly cooked, but paled in comparison to Wagyu. We had a party of 6 and everyone enjoyed their meals. The dessert of creme brûlée was awesome!Loved this restaurant and will be back!

review_794.Review: The waitress was amazingly knowledgeable about the steak and all of the items on the menu. She was soo attentive to our party of 10 and we truly appreciated her. It was a wonderful steakhouse " experience". We were there for several hours and it didn't even feel like it because it was such a great atmosphere. Everyone in my party had a wonderful time. I will definitely be back.

review_795.Review: We were in the mood for steak for a birthday celebration with 4 guests. This steak house did it up right. The peppers before dinner were best ever. Truffle fries were lukewarm. T bone steaks, macaroni & lobster, mushrooms and bacon mashed potatoes were as good as it gets. The restaurant has a sleek sophisticated look. Our primary server, Scott, was assisted by the type professional staff a steak house requires. Definitely worth a meal or two at this very nice restaurant!

review_796.Review: The first steak we ordered was sold out. So we ordered an alternate, 3 sides, and two appetizers. 10 mins later we were told that steak was sold out too, so we again chose something else.  When the $60 steak arrived it was very undercooked, so we sent it back. Our ($40 worth of) sides sat on the table for 10 minutes. The steak came back cooked properly but the sides were completely cold. All the food was okay but the place didn't live up to the hype. Or server Scott was great, but otherwise it was a total waste of money.

review_797.Review: Our reservation was for 8:45pm for 5 people.  We changed it to 10 people when we got there at 8:30pm.  We didn't get seated till 10pm.  We sat at the bar and the service there took a long time for a beer.  They didn't even poor the beer in a glass we just took it in a bottle.  Service was really bad till we sat in our table.  The manager came by and compt us for some stuff knowing that they made a mistake.  The service and food was great after we sat down.

review_798.Review: A lovely restaurant that is way too expensive.  Also the portion sizes of meat were laughable.My steak was so small and looked stark on my huge plate.  And that is because absolutely nothing comes with your meat.  Every side dish is extra.  Beautiful restaurant, though

review_799.Review: he servers were friendly.  The chef would send extra nibbles and samples for us to taste.  This made me feel special.  Some of the tastings were interesting and unlike anything else that I have had.

review_800.Review: I went here for a birthday dinner and wished I hadn't. It was only the two of us with a late evening reservation, yet the service was so slow that it took an hour plus for us to receive our dinner after ordering, and any time we needed our server we had to flag her down. Hoping the food would make up for the service, we were highly disappointed in that area as well.  I honestly would not recommend this restaurant to anyone.

review_801.Review: Excellent dinner house with lots of energy! The tables were a bit high but the overall decor is modern and trendy! The food was excellent, the wine list ample, and service was on the money! Great place for couples or groups. A bit noisy but fun. I'd go back! :)

review_802.Review: I love the lobster Mac n cheese. I also got the ribeye which was okay and tokimonsta for a drink.

review_803.Review: Four of ordered steaks cooled to the Chef's recommendation and they were perfect. Our group had the 4oz and 12oz NYs, the 4oz Tenderloin and I braved the 30oz bone in ribeye, but didn't realize it was 30oz until the roast arrived on my plate; it was amazing.

review_804.Review: When a friend from Germany said he was looking for an organic, grass fed steak. I found  the 5A5. The food and wine pairings were incredible and the vegetable sides delicious. It was a bit noisy, but the temperature of my filet, black and blue, was superb.

review_805.Review: I was looking for a steak house in the downtown area. This place looked trendy and a bit loud. The hostess took us to a quieter section of the restaurant which was not that much quieter. The server was nice, we placed our order and probably because it was a Sunday night, almost every side dish we ordered was not available. They were probably waiting for the Sysco truck to arrive on Monday with supplies. Anyway the steaks arrived and they were not practically special or all that tasty. It was just mediocre. Needless to say I will stick with the Morton Steakhouse when in SF or better yet, stick with the Outback.

review_806.Review: We went for my brother-in-laws birthday but needed to get back to our parking garage in time.  It took over an hour for us to get our steaks, and the garage had closed.  The food was delicious. Just allot the time to enjoy it.

review_807.Review: The food was delicious and our server was great! The only thing I would change is the fact that it smelled like cigar smoke near the end of the visit.

review_808.Review: I love steak and this place really hit it out of the park for me. The ambiance was a bit dark but everything else was wonderful. I had the Dry Aged Bone-in NY 22oz, medium rare, and it was absolutely delicious. I cut the sous vide egg on top and the wondrous yolk popped out. Then, I mixed it with the bacon jam on the bottom, as the waiter recommended and the combination was mind blowing. The bacon jam was not over powering and the egg really was "perfect." My steak was perfectly cooked, tender, and juicy. I did not leave a single piece of it on my plate. All that was left was the bone. I would highly recommend this place if you are looking for a steak that is complex, but that's not to say you shouldn't try anything else on the menu!

review_809.Review: No complaints from me! I chose 5A5 for my boyfriend's birthday dinner and we were both happy with our meal. Making a reservation through OpenTable was really easy and the host even made sure to get the name of the birthday celebrant for the complimentary dessert at the end of the night (very nice touch!) The ambiance was classy and quiet enough for a romantic dinner.The Food:After looking at the menu (and drooling), we decided we wanted to try a lot of the items so we ended up sharing all of our plates and it was just the right amount of full.We had the soup of the day poblano soup, truffle mac & cheese, shrooms, bone-in rib eye, and a complimentary birthday chocolate cake dessert.To start, the sourdough and bacon bread was really delicious and I liked eating it with our appetizer soup.We had the soup of the day, poblano pepper soup which I  had not previously had before. It had a really nice and rich flavor! The peppercorn bone-in rib eye was the star of the show and was a lot of meat even when sharing. We got it medium rare and it came out perfect. I have only been to a few steakhouses before but this is definitely the best that I've had so far. The garlic mushrooms and mac & cheese were a good compliment to our steak with just the right amount of flavor.The Service:Service here was phenomenal! We were instantly greeted, seated on time, and our waiter walked us through the menu and gave suggestions which I really appreciated. He also checked on us regularly throughout the night which was really great!Food came out on time and palette cleansers in between dishes were interesting and delicious as well.I definitely want to come back and try the Wagyu experience...ONE DAY! $$$$

review_810.Review: Great food and great service. The steak was amazing and so were the mashed potatoes. Will be back!

review_811.Review: When I booked I did not know any thing about this restaurant, best we found in SF  food great and the layout of the tables brilliant

review_812.Review: We really enjoyed the side dishes and apps. My steak was underdone and my husband's was overdone and we didn't feel that the meat quality was that great.

review_813.Review: Lucky us! My boyfriend's boss gave him a gift card to this beauty of a restaurant. Otherwise, I'm not sure if/ when we would have tried it. The place is amazing, with impeccable lighting. What s classy joint! We were the first ones in for a 5:30pm reservation, besides a large party that had congregated at the bar, waiting for their table as well. The wait was like 5 minutes, if that. Very prompt! As we had gotten there early. I cannot begin to describe how awesome this experience was. So I will just get into it. The explanation of the menu was very thorough and very warm. Our waiter was awesome! The service we received was top notch. Including the guys bussing the table. We had a great view of the kitchen and it looked so calm in there. It was very reassuring! We ordered oysters, prime rib, boneless rib eye, beet salad with whipped goat cheese, truffle mac and cheese w/ lobster and creamy spinach. Everything was delightful. The oysters were the starter and it was a plethora of flavors in our mouths. They had a chili sauce on there with caviar. It was the first time I tried caviar and I was impressed. The whipped goat cheese on the beet salad was exquisite, as well as the reductions. The meat was beyond perfection. I like my meat rare and that's what I got. My boyfriend Mike felt like his medium rare was borderline medium. But the greatest medium ever. And that's what he actually wanted. He wants medium rare a bit more towards medium. The mac and cheese had chunks of lobster and may be the best thing I've ever tasted in my life. And the creamy spinach was surprising, with the crispies in it. It was a delicious contrast with the cream. A nice touch was the little extras that got sent out, compliments of the chef. There was a gnocchi with creamy truffle sauce. And warm sourdough bread, soft inside and crusty on the outside. And bacon bread as well. He sent out a palette cleanser before our main courses. We were taken care of! They even took my cost and remembered it!

review_814.Review: Could not ask for better service or food. Will absolutely, without a doubt, come back the next time we are in town.

review_815.Review: One the best steakhouses I've been to in the states. Sure you might personally like a different ambiance, but you can't beat the deliciousness of the menu items.

review_816.Review: I am not much of a meat eater but on this occasion I ate every bite of my Filet Mignon. It almost melted in my mouth. The service was excellent and the restaurant was beautiful. We will definitely go back again.

review_817.Review: I don't think I would eat here again. It was..fine. Steaks aren't that good (though we didn't try the A5 steak. Appetizers were good and so were drinks. I don't think it was worth the price.

review_818.Review: Great place to eat. Excellent service. Would definitely recommend.

review_819.Review: Took my team here again for another team dinner while in the Bay Area. They are always pleased. Even our resident foodie. Everyone loved his wine selection.

review_820.Review: Awesome place with delicious food that will please your palate.  Flavors are amazing.  Service is excellent.

review_821.Review: it started really well, my wife and i first time here, appetizers are really good, lobster tempura, truffle fries. Kind of a nightmare after that coz the main course came 40 mins or maybe even longer that we thought we are already forgotten, i even told my wife maybe we should just pay and leave, we got seated like at the corner of the restaurant too, the table behind us which are like a group got a better and faster service than us even tho we came in before them.

review_822.Review: Mostly delicious food, lovely fish appetizers, sea bass entrée good, filet mignon good, A1 steak overpriced and over salted, not worth the money.  The sides were great, lobster mac, creamed spinach, all good.  And excellent presentation for all dishes throughout.  But the service was poor from start to finish, from arrival and having to wait at the entrance for no apparent reason, to an over-busy server, wine arriving too late for the course it accompanied, water glasses never re-filled (the bottle of sparkling water was put in an ice bucket across the room, we had to go and get it ourselves on many occasions), had to wait for service on several occasions. Embarrassing when you're on business. The ambience was very three star, not unpleasant but nothing of note. We had better food, service and ambience at Harris's and Ozumo on the two previous nights.

review_823.Review: We went here for my birthday dinner last night and for the most part it was good. The best part is the ambience. Appetizers and sides were good but our waiter talked us out of the filet mignon and into the bone-in NY strip. It was inedible for most of it and you couldn't even fully chew the meat. You had to chew it until a point and spit it out. Completely unacceptable for a place this upscale. We were disappointed to say the least.

review_824.Review: Took my wife for her birthday! Great food and service. Enjoyed the steaks!

review_825.Review: This restaurant is awesome. Food is delicious. Great Staff and Servers. Great knowledge of the wine. My steak was cook perfectly. Of course you pay for it. It is an expensive place. But if you're looking to treat yourself and you love steak this is well worth it.

review_826.Review: I wanted something special for my 30th birthday -- a great steak. I'm not a huge food buff, but 5A5 looked great and turned out to be spectacular. No snobbery whatsoever: great food, terrific drinks, and a low-key lounge atmosphere made it the perfect place to have a celebratory meal. Will definitely be back for my 31st. Who am I kidding? I'll be back next month!

review_827.Review: The food is really good and great service. We are definitely going back again.

review_828.Review: THE AMBIANCE OF THE RESTAURANT, THE WAIT STAFF, THE FOOD AND ALL THE COMPLEMENTARY SAMPLES WERE GREAT. THE STEAK, LOBSTER MAC IS A MUST, OMG SO GOOD, I WOULD DEFINITELY RECOMMEND TO ANYONE TO EAT HERE 5 STARS. BIG PORTIONS COULDN'T EVEN FINISH IT ALL.

review_829.Review: For the price I expected a little better steak. My major complaint is only partly the fault of the restaurant. Once again a couple decided to bring three young children to a fine dining experience. Why, why, why. The man at that the table was wearing jeans and a t-shirt which in my world is already disrespectful, but allowing one child to have loud crying outburst while another child climbs on the backs of the booth disrupting the group behind them is just unacceptable. If your children cannot behave like young adults in an adult setting please don't take them out to restaurants where they don't belong.

review_830.Review: The sides were great. We got the mushrooms, potato gratin, and truffle Mac and cheese. The bone in rib eye was excellent but the prime rib was sub par- both presentation and taste was not great.Service was slooooow. We received the main courses over 30 minutes after finishing our appetizers. Waiter was not attentive, and the succession of the meal was not smooth.Paying these type of prices, I would expect a seamless experience and this was just not the case. Appetizers were not great and service was even worst. I will not return here based on my experience.

review_831.Review: newer waiter.... a little unseasoned .... food was creative and good...but a little over-priced

review_832.Review: Had one of the best experiences here! The food was great and the staff was very attentive to our every need. The filets were like butter and lobster tempura was...you just will have to try it!

review_833.Review: Our server was tremendously helpful and knew the wine list and steak temperatures very well.

review_834.Review: Overall the ambiance is great, modern and vibrant.  The service was spot on and not overly attentive, but present.  But if you are a 'Steak' foodie, this is not the spot for you.  The selections of cuts are pretty good, but the sauces overwhelm their flavor.

review_836.Review: Enjoyed the uniqueness of 5A5. Great service and staff is ultra friendly. Great for one on one nights yet dim setting so watch the camera flash settings. Overall, will come back for special occasions.

review_837.Review: The service is wonderful here. It's one of those places where the servers make sure your water stays full. I like. The waiter was very attentive, informative and pleasant. The servers explain your food when presented. The restaurant is very pretty and loungey. They have some really expensive meat. The thing I liked best is when they called to confirm my reservation and they made it a point to ask if I was celebrating any sort of occasion or the like... I said as a matter of fact it's my fiance's birthday. So they made a special note of it and at the end of our meal, they had the cutest little dessert on a square plate that read 'Happy Birthday, Ivan in chocolate.' It was very sweet of them. =) This review was a 3 for the food which was good but not amazing...the service gets 6 stars imo.

review_838.Review: Steak sizes are enormous! For a health-conscious city, it makes no sense to me how they can justify serving 22oz (T-bone) and 30oz steaks (Ribeye) for a single person. WTF? Don't get me wrong - the steak was delicious! But the serving size was over the top!!My companion and I also order Brussels sprouts and creamed spinach to accompany our steaks. Brussels sprouts were far underdone and the spinach far too salty.Lastly, our server seemed extremely bored, and not in the mood to work. In my extensive experience of dining in fine SF restaurants, one can often rely on a bright personality from the serving staff to enhance the dining experience. NOT HERE. Our server offered the most brief and colorless answers to our queries about food and wine choices. And it wasn't because he was too busy.My advice: SF has much better dining experiences to offer. Take a pass on this place!

review_839.Review: Extremely knowledgable waiter. Staff was very attentive. Recommendations were spot on. The Prime Rib was the best I've had. NY Strip was also great. Ambiance is really cool. Five stars all around for the best dining experience we've had in a week of traveling Carmel, Monterey and San Francisco. Well done.

review_840.Review: Chose the place based on the ambiance and menu.  Was happy that I picked this as a meet up spot with my friend.  Got a wonderful description and viewing of the waygo cuts that were offered.  I never knew a cow got daily massages to improve the marbling of the meat.  This persuaded us to try that waygo tartar appetizer which was wonderful.  I also got the beet salad which was visually stunning, well prepared and very delicious.The main course was american filet mignon with brussel sprouts as the side.  The meat was cooked perfectly and seasoned just right.  My only gripe was that I wanted a little more of the sauce but I can understand how the chef wanted the meat to be the star of the dish.  The brussel sprouts were done well and had a great flavor that wasn't too salty.Overall a great experience and a wonderful restaurant.  Will be back again for dinner with friends and maybe even a special occasion.

review_841.Review: Food was very good, excellent NY steak and equally prime rib.  Good drinks, very good salads, the sides were about so so, but OK.  Handsome space and pleasant ambiance and low noise level.  We were seated in Siberia, although the restaurant was not full.  Were we placed there because we came from open table?  Otherwise the greeting was fine.  Service was pretty good (Siberia was a little off the beaten track for servitors)Tom Reynolds

review_842.Review: except they burnt one side of my husband's steak. Anytime you are paying more than $100 for a piece of steak, it should be well cared for by the chef and in this case, it was not. That is very unfortunate because I thought everything else was great, even their cocktails. Be sure to try their bacon bread! The service was on-point as well.

review_843.Review: The food was great but it was very over price. There are so many other great places in San Francisco to eat that has great food for less money. My wife and I had dinner there and it cost us $310.88 with the tip. It wasn't that great to coat that much $$$$$.

review_844.Review: The contemporary architecture is appealing, the beef is great. When there is an event/group in the bar area, the sound carries, likely because of the round structure of the restaurant. I'd recommend 5A5 if you're really wanting steak and you have a larger party (vs romantic dinner/party of two) - service was extremely attentive.

review_845.Review: Great selection of fine beef.  Portions are adequate.

review_846.Review: Although pricey, the food is EXCELLENT! Service was outstanding!  Will return but will have to be special occasions!

review_847.Review: My boyfriend and I went there for our 2 year anniversary and they took very good care of us. They checked his coat at no cost, called us a cab when we were done and when I did not like my salad they took it back with no problems. The modern feel of the place was nice and the food was very good. My problem was I dressed up nice for a upscale steak house only to have people in there with pants sagging and boxers showing while wearing a hat, and another person in a basketball jersey. It really took away from the overall upscale feeling. But they did go out of their way to give us a special dessert with happy anniversary written on it.

review_848.Review: I wanted to find a place to take a friend for his birthday and this turned out to be a great choice.  My friend got there early and had a drink at the bar where he said the service was good and the drink even better.  We were seated after being asked which of a few choices we preferred and had a tour of the menu by an informed, passionate, professional server.  We each ordered an appetizer, salad, and entrée.  Everything was served beautifully, promptly, and at the proper temperature.  The staff was attentive and engaged and our needs were important to them.  The only down side was that one of the side dishes was not great but, it was not so poorly executed that we returned it. Overall it was very nice.  I plan on returning and recommending A5A to friends.

review_849.Review: The service was perfect and food was excellent . Worth going and will be back again

review_850.Review: Service was good but getting our dinner took quite a long time. Not only us but other tables did not get their dinner in a reasonable amount of time.
