Our prime rib was delivered at room temperature (maybe sitting out too long) but the au jus made it better. The mac 'n cheese as the potato au gratin were very good. The brussel sprouts had too much balsamic vinegarette so we expressed our dislike and they took it off which we're glad they did. We would go back and try other items.

review_851.Review: when half the restaurant is corporately booked ... you should immediately advise your guests to enter at their own peril, offer alternate dining at another restaurant or at the very least get the corporate party to book the entire restaurant and close to the public...the restaurant really tried to cope with the 2 hour long barrage of animal house/wall street corporate junket/hedonistic chants, but it was simply ridiculous...the restaurant did discount our bill by 25% and grant free desserts, but it was way too late and an unfortunate management decision to allow the mixing of dining patrons and a corporate party who thought they were behind the curtain in Las Vegas....we can especially thank the effusive,  lovely and outspoken employees of MGA Healthcare Staffing Inc  and its president David Zowine for a whole new level of debauchery and inappropriate corporate citizenship  (no confidentiality needed as they told us who they were as they walked by our table)...we had out of town guests celebrating a 60th birthday and 30th year wedding anniversary...at least I could say they got a lasting impression...although you never want to leave a restaurant thinking you were just filmed against your will as part of a really poor reality TV show scene...

review_852.Review: Slow service. My prime rib was close to room temperature and underseasoned. Creamed spinach was nice but the sweet potato au gratin was a miss. Drinks were okay. There are too many better options for steak in SF for me to return here. Even for wagyu you're probably better off at Alexander's who go into meticulous detail about how the beef is sourced.

review_853.Review: Amazing dinner, wonderful service and ambiance, doesn't get much better than this!

review_854.Review: These people know how to cook a prime rib roast.  They also know how to cook veggies.  All of that with impeccable service in a truly beautiful location.  It is simply wonderful.

review_855.Review: I was able to partake in the Monday Prime Rib specials when they were advertised.  I want to state for the record, BOTH meals were Extraordinary!!! We were truly blessed to have the same materdee for both visits, which truly enhanced the meal.  His Mannerisms, Maturity, and knowledge of the restaurant,  were impeccable! The entire meal was exceptional, and worth every penny!!  The icing of the meal was the desert.  We had the Banana Dolce, and I have to say that the Chef truly outdid himself with this desert!!  Can't wait for the next visit.  It won't be for at least [3] months!! LoL..

review_856.Review: The appetizers were good. The A5 steak tartar was great quality and I enjoyed how the fat oil was made into a white powder. The foie gras and the wonton pineapple appetizer was good after the wonton was sent back from being burned. The A5 Wagyu was great quality. However the rib cap I got was slightly on the saltier side. Maybe instead of butter topping they can add foie gras as a side option. The A5 prime rib was delicious. The macaroni with lobster side dish had to be sent back more than once. The first time it came back cold. The second time it was watery. We instructed a worker that we didn't want it anymore because we were done with our entree. The made another macaroni side dish that we honestly didn't want. Our server Jake was very hospitable and tried to make us as comfortable as possible. I will come back because the quality of steak is hard to get anywhere else in the bay area.

review_857.Review: Absolutely fantastic food and presentation.  The wait staff is courteous and friendly and very knowledgeable. Had an amazing dinner and will definitely going back again!

review_858.Review: 5A5 never disappoints. The ambience, the eclectic décor, the amazing food but most of all- ethnic diversity in an SF restaurant- the rarest of occurrences nowadays. I've loved 5A5 since they opened and one of the reasons is that I always feel comfortable there, welcomed there and I actually experience the old ethnic diversity that SF used to be known and appreciated for. Again I say, the food and beverage menus are amazing- 1st rate everything from the welcomes to goodbyes. But there's so much more @ 5A5 - SF has become so homogenous as the new industries coming in to town make this City cookie cutter bland. I walk in to 5A5 to experience ambience that I cannot get in other restaurants- I get the San Francisco I grew up in, when everyone didn't look just alike. I don't know what you're doing 5A5, but keep doing it. I recommend you to all of my friends and family and they enjoy dining @ 5A5 too.

review_859.Review: Appetizers were flavorful, steaks delicious. Some very high priced steaks, most are priced around &40-50. Sides were cold when they came out, but quickly replaced when we told our waitress.

review_860.Review: This is my second time at 5A5.  I love the steaks and lobster appetizer.  The service is exceptional.  My only concern this visit was the amount of bacon in every side dish offered.  The mash potatoes, the brussell sprouts, and the spinach.  All I tasted was bacon with essences of the other veggies.  It was a little disappointing.  It dominated the flavor in my mouth. I could barely taste my steak.  The bread even had bacon in it.  And believe me, I love bacon but in moderation.  The experience reminded me of a heavy garlic Italian restaurant.  I don't recall so much bacon in everything the first time I ate at 5A5.I hope they will be revising their side dishes to have less bacon moving forward.  BTW - I asked to have the bacon pieces removed from the mash potatoes and the flavor was still in the potatoes.  Wishing for less bacon....

review_861.Review: First time here for Father's Day dinner with my family. Service is great! Our server was knowledgeable and she always greeted us with a smile. We had the 5A5 experience and it was amazing! Bacon bread, and truffle Mac N Cheese with bacon syrup was also excellent. We will definitely come back to 5A5 Steak Lounge to try their regular steak!

review_862.Review: Really had high expectations going in, but 5A5 didn't live up to any of them. Sevice was awkward, wine list disappointing with no imagination, steak was cooked properly but covered in a sauce that I thought was intended to hide something, and ambiance that included kids screaming. Not so great an experience.

review_863.Review: Went here to celebrate an early Father's Day, the experience could have not gone better. My father and I got there about 30 minutes early we sat at the bar area enjoyed a couple of cocktails and just about lost track of time, the host kindly walked up told us we will hold your table until you're ready to eat we did not want to interrupt, we don't see each other that often I told the host and thanked her for their patients. Sat us down enjoyed a great meal and the staff heard we were celebrating Father's Day and brought over a dessert for us to enjoy. Appreciated all that the staff did to make this night an experience that I will always remember.

review_864.Review: Went here for the first time for our wedding anniversary. The entire staff was great! Ali was awesome!

review_865.Review: My friends and I was here back in September 2014 for the $39 Prime Rib Dinner. The foods and service was great that we decided to come back again in June 2015 when 5A5 offer the same promotion. As always the service is outstanding and the food is great. The Prime Rib was cook to perfection and tasty.

review_866.Review: This is the second time I've been here with my family. We each ordered the prime rib special and it was a great deal. The soup AND salad starter was nice, plus the sides are big enough to share between four people so that you get to try a variety of items. The prime rib was prepared in a nice, tasty way and we were each pleased with our pieces of meat. We are tempted to go back to try the specialty Wagyu beef, which is very pricey. But we'd like to try it for the experience! Desserts are unique and tasty, too. We had very good attentive service, as well.

review_867.Review: Although the food was good.  The waitperson attentive and knowledgeable.  The ambiance was more to my dining partner's liking than mine.  It was a special occasion, but I didn't find the restaurant particularly special.  Adequate for an upscale, expensive restaurant is really all I can say.  I was thinking I would order the Japanese Kobe steak, but I was not prepared to pay $140 for just the entree.  So I ordered the prime rib and it was just fine.

review_868.Review: Be prepared to spend some money but it'll be well worth it. The service was awesome and the food was amazing. We got the A5 experience, which came with 4 different cuts of grade A5 wagyu beef. The meal is served ala carte so will have to order your sides separately. We ordered the mash potatoes with caramelized bacon and mac & cheese, it was fantastic. I would recommend this place if you are going out for a special occasion. Awesome food, great service a total package experience!!!

review_869.Review: Panic! We had to make changes very last minute in reservations for a very special occasion.  James assisted to make sure the occassion  would still go on.  Thank you so much! The private room was wonderful for our Party and the food , wine and champagne was fabulous! Everyone enjoyed the selection on the menu...the Wagyu was amazing!  Thank you June, for making the evening comfortable for us and assisting us with the projector to make it even more special.  The server gave us special attention and made sure we had everything we needed. The evening turned out to be memorable for all and my Daughter had a fabulous birthday and Doctorate Celebration!  Better than expected!  Thank you, Thank you, Thank you!!!!!!

review_870.Review: I personally chose this restaurant to celebrate my birthday at solely because of the lounge scene and gourmet dining. Little do I know the menu was selectively created by the executive chef of Alexander's Steakhouse. Even better! What stood out to me was that my party and I arrived a tad bit late, considering our reservation time was the latest you can set it to. As soon as I entered I was amazed at how lovely the restaurant looked. Totally better than the pictures on yelp for sure.  The staff were very energetic and pleased to be taking care of my party. The host and servers were very accommodating and made sure I had a birthday that I would never forget. Everything was onpoint, from the drinks that were recommended, to every bit of detail on the main courses.  The food sure was quality you can taste and not to mention the dessert which included these fudge bars which were on the house. Dining here is very affordable and a great place to go on a date on or celebrate anniversaries. I will definitely be coming back with more company. Thank you 5A5 Steak Lounge <3

review_871.Review: The fresh sashimi spoons are a must have appetizer. Go for the filet mignon, no need for the Japanese Wagyu. Accompany it with Brussels and scalloped potatoes!

review_872.Review: The quality of Food and service will always have me coming back. Favorite place to eat at in SF hands down especially during special occasions! Also, Props to the chef for the delicious accommodations! We left more than satisfied once again.

review_873.Review: Amazing food, wonderful server and romantic atmosphere! Can't wait to come back!

review_874.Review: Overpriced for Prime a Rib and Bone in Rib Eye that would be in a restaurant half this price.Not very tender.  Prime rib was smoked and had an off taste.  See atrip Advisor for detail.

review_875.Review: Got the NY Wagyu.. the most tender and juicy piece of meat I've ever put in my mouth. it's also very rich so a 4oz is plenty.. just make sure to get some sides and you will be very satisfied.

review_876.Review: From when we were greeted at the door to when they handed us back our coats we were met with exceptional service. The atmosphere was lively and colorful while still allowing for an intimate experience. I loved the round lighting element on the ceiling and the comfy booths. Our server knew everything about the menu and made excellent recommendations. The food arrived perfectly cooked, and just as described. All around this was a fantastic dinner choice.

review_877.Review: As always the food is so good.the flavors are so unique.The service is always the best.Its a must if you love excellent food

review_878.Review: Cool place. Good steak. Nice drinks! Fun night out.

review_879.Review: The staff was super friendly and attentive to all of our needs. The fresh oysters with the Champagne Potato Leek Soup was amaaaaazing! The foie gras was the best I've ever had and the A5 Wagyu ribeye is just.. omg. It just melts in your mouth and the flavor is just absolutely divine.

review_880.Review: On Time for 6pm reservation.  A quick scan:  dining room 15-20% occupied.  Showed to a table for 2 adjacent to open kitchen entryway.  Asked for another table.  "I'll have to check with the front."  Okayed by front.  Walked us 3' feet to other side of dividing wall.  Table for 2.  We'd like a table away from this area.  "I'll have to check with the front."  Back again.  As we walk towards back, we see an empty section with 6 or 7 tables for 2 to 4.  May we sit here.  Yes, and gestured to a table for 2.  May we sit side by side at a banquet table set for 3.  "We use this table for 3."  Yes, but we would like to sit next to each other, we have some business to discuss.  "I'll have to check with the front."  Okay, but we'll sit down here while we wait.  Disappeared down a passage opposite the "front" into a side room; never seen again.  From then was served by a pleasant and efficient waiter.  When leaving 2 hours later, not a single, twosome, threesome or foursome were in our section.  Guests with reservations, arriving on time should feel welcome, not an annoyance for expecting a good table or for thinking we're as important as the guests who "may arrive later," nor immediately shown to a table that should be held until full or for guests without reservations.  It's called hospitality and that's the business you're in!

review_881.Review: this is a great restaurant! great food, great service, great value!

review_882.Review: outstanding customer service. yummy food and drinks. add great company and what more can you ask for?

review_883.Review: Went to San Francisco from the East Coast to take in some sights and celebrate our anniversary - We chose this restaurant from Open Table Suggestion to have our special dinner.  We were seated and then our waiter Ryan came to the table- he immediately began to stare at my girlfriend in a very blatant and overt way. He left to get us water and when he came back my girlfriend asked him about the wine list- this whole time he acted like i didn't exist. My girlfriend asked about a particular wine - she was holding the wine list- Ryan (the waiter) then acted like he could find the wine on the list- he ran his finger up and down the list and then ran his finger over my girlfriend's finger as she was holding the wine list- he did it not once but twice-BTW the wine she was asking about was easily found on the list. A real creeper- he made our anniversary dinner a very uncomfortable evening- the restaurant is fine- just keep your date  away from Ryan!

review_884.Review: My very first dry aged T bone. Freaking amazing. Mac and cheese and the mashed potatoes are always great. Can't forget the shooters either!

review_885.Review: They keep the restaurant uncomfortably cold. Food was mediocre at best. Steaks were not cooked to order. Service was good, but not better than expected.

review_886.Review: Great food, amazing cocktails, and a very comfortable lounge feel. They have a large selection of steaks, wine, and liquor. We enjoyed our visit and will definitely go back.

review_887.Review: My family and I have been going to 5a5 since their opening, an accidental fine via Open Table.  This accidental fine continues to be rewarding time and again. We go there at least 2-4 times a year expecting and finding much satisfaction in their service, decor, and more than anything, their prime rib (with or without bone in)  is the best, moist, tender, flavorful, cook to your specification (mind was a perfect medium).  I have had their NY cut, it is sooo good, it did not need the toppings!  I always have them put them as a side.  Side to must have are Truffle Mac n Cheese, Cream Spinach, and oh yeah Mash Potatos!  Extras?  Try the Tempora Lobster.  Had this for the first time yesterday as a comp (due to their generous hospitality - our order was delayed due to the rush of patrons).  Delicious, not because it was a comp, it was just that good!  Plans to go back at any excuse to eat out. If you are think about trying 5a5, don't think, just try!  Won't regred it.

review_888.Review: I love this place for its 5A5 Wagu beef.  I've had it at other places, Petaluma and Scottsdale, and no one bets 5A5.  It just melts in your mouth.  It is an expensive meal, so I only bring people who I know are foodies and love steak.  It has great ambiance and can be kid friendly as the atmosphere is very lively.

review_889.Review: My boyfriend and I went Thursday, March 12, 2015  as a last minute dinner date. When we arrived parking was really easy and the atmosphere was great! Our waiter was really attentive and made sure nothing was missing at all times when he wasn't available everyone pitched in to help out. The appetizers where delicious as well as the main course. The food as well as the service was excellent and would definitely recommend and come back!

review_890.Review: Came here early and had a great meal. The quality of the beef is excellent, and perfectly prepared.Our server was very helpful and informative, and helped to make for a very nice evening.Great destination for carnivores!

review_891.Review: The prime rib was 60% fat. Also, I asked for medium rare but it basically came out mooing.

review_892.Review: Interesting 60's dacor - food was wonderful but small portions for the spendy cost!   tables  too close together - was stuc k between two load tables and could not visit with each other over the five quite inebriated next to us and the other two that had load man voices on the other side of us

review_893.Review: Been going to the restaurant for years, you must try the wagu!

review_894.Review: Our server, Rolando, was awesome! He was very knowledgable with A5 as well as other items on the menu! Everything was good but not amazingly wow as I had hoped. The tijima filet was better than the tijima ny. Their happy hour is awesomely priced as well! Will return! Interested in trying the 4 cuts of A5 side by side.

review_895.Review: FANTASTIC Wagyu beef cut. I don't think I can eat another piece of meeting in comparison. Melts in your mouth and it falls apart on your fork. My girlfriend and I took several minutes to savor every piece. Order the sauce on the side, not event slightly needed.Leila is a wonderful and delightful server who was SO attentive and full of recommendations. At one point,  I even asked myself "have I drank any water?" because my glass was filled to the brim.To top it off, the owner, Steven,  introduced himself to us personally and gave us certified Wagyu cards full of information about the steer including location, age, weight, name, etc.What a delightful evening.

review_896.Review: Our server was really good but the steak my husband had was tough.

review_897.Review: The meat was good quality - I had the bone-in NYS. The preparation was poor with inadequate color outside, and the steak was covered in a ridiculous sauce that you might expect from TGIF or Outback. Not impressed at all. Every steak comes with some kind of topping. High quality meat doesn't deserve this kind of treatment. Service was not impressive. Wrong drink order, wine took forever to be served (as in I ordered it at the same time as dinner and it was served after finishing my salad (which was a mediocre wedge). The sides were ok but again not special. This place is not a great steak house. Decent only.

review_898.Review: We went for our daughter's birthday dinner after she had researched restaurants and chose 5A5. The food was amazing from the melt-in-your-mouth filet mignon to the free range chicken. The potatoes au gratin were fabulous and we thorougly enjoyed all the delicious palate cleansers presented in between, a surprise treat. They brought out a lovely piece of  almond cake decorated with Happy Birthday at the end of our meal.Our server Jason was attentive and quietly took care of a wine mishap on our bill. We were pleasantly surprised at the reasonable prices, although you can spend much more on the Wagyu beef. The space has a luxury lounge vibe with live piano music and great conversation which can get a bit noisy but is part of the fun. We would highly recommend coming here for a special occasion or to impress a business client.

review_899.Review: Waiter was knowledgable and friendly.  My and I had the Wagyu sampler along with two side dish and it was more than enough food.

review_900.Review: Great happy hour, the oysters were the best ,very nice bar area, would go for sure after workfor cocktails and bar bites.

review_901.Review: It's been a while. But me and my girlfriend went here on a whim our first night in San Francisco...best idea. The service was fantastic, the steaks were delicious and the piano player was playing renditions of 90s songs. It was great. A classy, but not tight necked, steakhouse. I'll go back when I visit again.

review_902.Review: We are over from the UK and were looking for a nice steak and after searching TripAdvisor, picked here and we are so glad we did! Our waitress was super friendly and helpful - we had let them know when booking that we couldnt have dairy or wheat and everyone had been briefed which is always reassuring for us. The menu was also adaptable on ordering - also a big plus for us.Portions are huge, quality is excellent - my only mild gripe would be not being able to get a standard cocktail that wasnt on menu - definitely not a dealbreaker when everything else was so lovely. We aslo appreciated the muted music and being able to hear each other speak! I can wholeheartedly recommend, especially if you have special dietary requirements.

review_903.Review: I would love to return to try the waygu beef sampler the next time I return, but the service was excellent. I love that our waiter told us all the details of our dishes when we were served. My prime rib was flavorful, especially on the edges - but my boyfriend's steak could have been better.

review_904.Review: Kinda awkward atmosphereColdLoungey style but music and lighting didn't fit the vibeScallops and steak were very deliciousKinda fusion trendy steakhouse menu Wish the atmosphere and service was better

review_905.Review: Great service fantastic food thumbs up

review_906.Review: If you want the best prime rib in San Francisco, 5A5 is the place to be.Though I was a bit disappointed in the watery mashed potatoes.The service was very good.

review_907.Review: We were looking for great steaks, but not the stodgy feel of a traditional steakhouse.  We have  young adult kids and we were looking for a fun place to celebrate a birthday - and this was the perfect spot.  The steaks were high quality and well prepared, the sides were delicious, and the service was exceptional from start to finish.  The cocktails were creative and exceptional.  Best of all, the ambiance was perfect.  It has a great lounge feel, the table arrangements are perfect for conversation and well spaced from one another to allow for a sense of privacy, and the lighting was fun and modern while being warm.  There was a piano player at the front of the restaurant, far enough from the tables to allow for conversation - and he played a great variety of music that everyone enjoyed, regardless of age.  Overall, this was a great night, and the restaurant concept and service contributed immensely.

review_908.Review: Love the lobster tail and the king crab leg. Highly recommend the chief prime rib. The source have a little bit Chinese style.

review_909.Review: Service impecable, ambiance trendy and cozy.Food is excellent the Wagyu a bit expensive c/w others I ve been but worth the try.

review_910.Review: Tuna was dry with even watermelon not helping. STeaks were expensive but fair at best

review_911.Review: Our steaks were tough and tasteless. The wedge salad was limp and uninteresting. We had to ask for additional dressing just to eat it. The meal was expensive and not up to the ratings on OpenTable

review_912.Review: We had the A5 experience and it was truly an experience highly recommended.

review_913.Review: I went to 5A5 for my birthday with my wife and I must say....  it was a FANTASTIC EXPERIANCE!From the service to the food, I was impressed which is not an easy thing to do.wait staff were very antentive and seemed to care about our experience.  The ambience was romantic and sophisticated.the food was top notch. I had the bone in rib eye steak which was cooked to a perfect medium through out. Flavor was impressive and amount of food to price ratio was awome.the resturant is a bit on the pricey side but worth it hands down. I will definitely return for another visit.Look out New York, San Francisco has a contender for best steak house in my opinion.

review_914.Review: Service was great, food was outstanding.  I had the F1 NY and it just melted in my mouth.  The bf had the filet mignon and it was very tasty.  The lobster tempura was deeee-licious!! Highly recommended and definitely worth the price!

review_915.Review: The appatizers were great and so were the drinks. The steak was covered in sauce taking away from the flavor of the steak. I would recommend going here for a happy hour but not for a steak.

review_916.Review: From the customer service, to the ambiance, and to the food, everything was amazing! Very modern as well. I will definitely be coming back.

review_917.Review: I had my birthday celebration at 5A5 for the 2nd or 3rd year in a row.  The food and service were excellent.

review_918.Review: Underseasoned, dull, tired.  Honky tonk piano player was intolerable.

review_919.Review: While the steaks are great, the piano player just bangs on that piano making a nice restaurant very unpleasant with all that banging. Also, the coffees were not hot which is a serious minus for me.The waiter was very helpful, explained the menu--and the pricey steak options.Table very large and made it hard to hear the others at our table, especially with that loud banging piano.

review_920.Review: Had a wonderful dinner!  I took my 11 year old daughter out on a Date Night, dinner at the Steak Lounge and then we went to Shen Yun at the War Memorial Theatre.  Our dinning experience was great; we had dinner reservations at 5:30 when the restaurant opens, it was a Thursday evening an not very busy when we arrived, however, became more vibrate by the time we left at 7pm.  Our service was great, menu was explained, we were brought our "Chef Treats", a complementary tasting of something that was really good:)  My daughter ordered the 6oz Petite and it was perfect, I ordered the 15oz Prime Rib which was huge, I was unable to finish.....in addition we had two sides; the Bacon Mash Potatoes and the Macaroni and Cheese...both great.  I had two glasses of wine, our server was very descriptive about what wines I was ordering which is always nice.  We finished our dinner off with a great desert.  If you are looking for a great place to have a nice dinner, I would definitely recommend the Steak Lounge!!  I will be bringing my wife here, I think she was a little jealous about what a wonderful time my daughter and I had:)

review_921.Review: Customer service is great! Too bad they were out of the prime rib at 7pm on a Tuesday night. You would think they would have enough to last until at least 9pm but who knows, I guess it was really THAT popular. Tried the lobster tempura - Awesome. The truffle fries were OK, only because they were tiny pieces so it seemed like it we got the bottom of the batch of fries. Filet minon and boneless ribeye were very delicious nonetheless.

review_922.Review: My family and I were in San Fran for a week between Christmas and New Years.  This was the best meal we had while in town. Excellent food and service.  Skip the tourist traps on the wharf and head here. Your wallet will take a hit but it will be worth every penny.

review_923.Review: Best steak I ever had. You have to try the Japanese Wagyu, it just melts in your mouth.  Truffle fries are a must as well as the shishito peppers.

review_924.Review: the food by SF standards was average. You can get better steak for sure in the city. Not bad for a random date night. Bit pricey for the quality.

review_925.Review: Our party of four started with lobster tempura, king crab legs, and hamachi shooters. All of which were absolutely delicious. I ordered probably the best tasting prime rib I had to date. The mac n cheese and cream of spinach were just as good. The service was exceptional.

review_926.Review: Food was alright, I was expecting more from a steak lounge.Everything was tasty but truffle fries were a bit overcooked, really hard to bite down on.I was really looking forward to it because of the reviews on yelp.

review_928.Review: Best service I've ever received at a restaurant! The manager was wonderful-- very friendly and welcoming. Amuse Bouche was a lovely touch. Will definitely be back!

review_929.Review: Stopped by here on a Sunday night.  The restaurant has a great ambiance!  The drinks were amazing!  And the food was delicious!  Service was top-notch!

review_930.Review: Went to 5A5 to celebrate our 10th wedding anniversary and we were more than happy with the experience! The service was outstanding from the get go! The staff was understanding that we were a few minutes late. The waiter was very knowledgeable and gave us enough time to figure out what we wanted and picked up our cues when we were ready to order. We tried the Hamachi and Oyster starter and they were delicious. We also had the Lobster Tempura which was also outstanding! Since it was our anniversary we went for the A5 Experience and we were not disappointed! Going through the 4 cuts of meat they really did get softer and softer, butterier and butterier. To end the evening 5A5 gave us a nice little dessert with a beautifully decorated plate to commemorate our anniversary. Will definitely go back again to try more of the delicious dishes!

review_931.Review: We went on a Friday at 5:30pm, so it may be a different experience on an off-night. The noise was deafening due to the lousy acoustics in the room. The food is fine - nothing stood out - though I was partial to the brussels sprouts with meyer lemon. (You can decide for yourself what it means when the sprouts outshine the filet mignon.)  The service was spectacular - it made me feel guilty that I really didn't care for the noise, food and decor.

review_932.Review: If you order the domestic beef, prepare to be underwhelmed.  My NY strip was a mediocre cut, too thin, and as a result was overcooked instead of the medium rare I asked for. The Wagyu beef is probably spectacular, but it's SUPER expensive.  The level of obnoxious, pounding music made ordinary conversation impossible.  I understand that 5A5 probably isn't catering to a middle-aged crowd, so I guess normal conversation is not high on their priorities.  But if you like a $500 steak without being able to converse, this is your place.

review_933.Review: The filet steak was out of this world.  Absolutely delicious melt in my mouth.  The service was excellent and the booth was roomy.  I wish I could afford to return

review_934.Review: It was the second time my wife and I have ate here it's never a disappointment. Our favorite meal to order is the truffle Mac and cheese. We decided to order the Wagyu 100% steak and it was the best steak we ever had.

review_935.Review: Great steak house... hit all the marks on every level... food, service, style... good vibe... not sooo trendy like STK but not boring like Mortons... right in the sweet spot...  Hit the spot! food was awesome.

review_936.Review: The steak and ambiance in this restaurant are unmatched. Definitely a place I would recommend to big spenders who love a good steak in a "hip" setting.

review_937.Review: 5A5 is a place where the main ingredient of each dish you can actually taste through the accompanying-complimentary ingredients. Great food, excellent service.

review_938.Review: I was not prepared for their Wagyu.  I'd had Kobe (a type of Wagyu) before, but the marbling on the cut of meat i had there, was amazing.  Coupled with a bottle of Silver Oak...The service was on cue, competent and not over-the-top.  Well orchestrated and much appreciated.

review_939.Review: I had a good T-bone steak that cook perfectly, and the service was good.  But everything else was mediocre or poor.  I could taste the truffles in the mac and cheese for hours after the meal  Also, they start out by trying to sell you on the wagyu steaks - $500+ for the sampler plate.  This didn't feel like an upscale restaurant, it feel more like a lounge that serves food.

review_940.Review: Love everything about this restaurant from the food to the ambiance.

review_941.Review: Amazing. Was here once several years ago, and it was a nightclub with steaks. Now? One of the best steaks I've ever had (and I eat steak consistently). The beat salad, lobster tail tempura, truffle fries, and tempura peppers were awesome. The wagyu steak, while pricey at >130 for four ounces, was INCREDIBLE (and worth it). The only thing we weren't impressed with was the Brussels sprouts, which were a bit mushy, but the phenomenal service more than made up for it (our server even removed them from our bill without our asking).

review_942.Review: My husband and I received a gift certificate to A5A for our anniversary and enjoyed it. The food and  service were very good. We shared the chicken skewer appetizer and both ordered the NY strip for our main - both of which were very good. Dessert (the smore's) was the only slight disappointment, Although to be fair, we did finish it so it wasn't that much of a disappointment. Overall we'd definitely come back and recommend to friends.

review_943.Review: First time we had a pretty nice experience but this time....not at all. Service was very bad with one waiter pushing your plate already on the table to get more space ( like in a fast food chain). Food was pretty basic and for almost 300 $ I was expecting a much better meat .So, I will never go back

review_944.Review: Music was way too loud and did not fit the mood. Made it hard to talk and enjoy the meal.  Food was great but I was shouting all evening

review_945.Review: Was pleasantly surprised with the food. Very tasteful without being too salty. Nice atmosphere and had valet. Excellent service and will definitely go back.

review_946.Review: Very nice & accommodating staff; very pretty inside.  Moderately expensive, but quality wasn't really there in either steak we ordered (filet and ribeye).  In the bar prior to being seated the bartender was friendly, quick with service and the drinks were good.  It seemed like it took us forever to get another drink and have our order taken once we were seated and the restaurant was not very busy.

review_947.Review: Food and service was outstanding! Every dish was well executed and every bite was delicious.Do not miss the tempura lobster tails!!We have eaten at many of SF's fine dining locations and 5A5 is the best we have experienced in a very long time.

review_948.Review: Started out slow. Kind of hard to find our server and they messed up our first drink order. But i think we were just hungry, because as soon as the bread came, it was delicious and it only got better until the end of the meal. Prime rib, boneless ribeye, and the fish. "Delicious."

review_949.Review: Great atmosphere, Awesome service, Amazing food. We started with the hamachi & oyster appetizers which were bursting with flavor. We ordered the 4oz. A5 Ribeye Miyazaki Wagyu beef, the 10oz. Filet mignon, & an order of the macaroni & cheese topped with pieces of lobster tail. Both meats came out at the same time to differentiate the types of cut. Now I thought I had been eating the top choice whenever I would order the Filet mignon wherever I would go. This Filet mignon tasted like a regular Safeway steak compared to the A5 ribeye. So much flavor, super tender & juicy its a WOW type of flavor. The macaroni was exquisite & how could I forget about the amazing bacon bread! Super pricey but It's worth every bite! this place deserves 5 stars!

review_950.Review: Came recommended by a friend of a friend. Thought I was going to get a great steak. Steak was average. Prepared in Japanese style.Not bad, but not worth the price. Manhattan much better for a similar price. Waiter was great. Valet was asleep. Staff happy and personable.But a "tasting" plate of steak of four 4oz cuts for $525?? For $525 I want much more than a "taste". Rib Eye was just "okay". I don't usually go to a high end restaurant for mac and cheese, but it was a side recommended by the waiter.Had a great weekend in San Francisco. Would have been nice to say I had a great meal. A bit noisy. A 30th Birthday Party was next to us. Would have thought it was a 16th by the way they yelled and carried on.

review_951.Review: Wife and I had our date night here and we had a great time.  5A5 is a cool place with a great vibe.  Great lighting, live piano player, and excellent service.  We got the truffle fries and lobster tempura for an appetizer and both were amazing.  In fact all the food we had was amazing except for the steak oddly enough.  Sides and desserts were good, but the steak was nothing special especially for a place that calls itself a steak lounge.  My steak was covered in a bacon jam that overpowered the taste of the steak and the steak itself was a little tough and chewy.  Not bad, by any means, just not as good as I had hoped for.

review_952.Review: It was our first time dining at 5A5 Steak Lounge & it will not be our last. Layla* was our server & she was amazing! Informative & attentive! The food was tasty, but the exceptional customer service is what won me over. The whole staff overall was warm & friendly. I have nothing negative to say about my experience. 5 stars & two thumbs up in my book!

review_953.Review: Best waygu beef I've had. Wait staff was attentive and was always spot on with suggestions. The hamachi appetizer was amazing, and the chef even send out a little sample for you to try. It was a true 5 course meal that did not leave you wanting to take a nap. I would recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for a true dining experience. (Note: the noise level isn't a fair rating because the Giants had just won the World Series and everyone was watching/listening to the game on their phones. I would sumise that it is a very quiet dining room on a regular night).

review_954.Review: WOW!  We bought the Costco certificates and are still in shock over how amazing it was!  The food was incredible, the service was outstanding!  It was beyond a five star experience for a bargain price!

review_955.Review: we came special from SJ to dine at 5A5. highly recommended, for the food, service, and ambiance.

review_956.Review: The food was superb.  A perfect birthday celebration spot where the staff and the ambiance made for a memorable and lovely evening.

review_957.Review: We were recommended 5A5 by our hotel concierge. Mind you, it has a very clubby feel.  The menu is a mixture of American/Japanese meat options, especially with Wagyu beef.  Our salads, Wagyu sliders, and Lamb Duo were delicious!  It is kind of expensive but it is worth it if you want something other than your typical steakhouse chain offerings.

review_958.Review: We were there for the steak and it was not disappointing at all. Both service and food were awesome. Will be back.

review_959.Review: This was second time eating here... never again.Their dry-aged meat is pretty good, but too sinewy for the price.What kills this place for me, though, is the service.When I'm clearly enjoying a $130 half-bottle of wine, I don't appreciate people coming up to my table four times asking me if I'm ready to pay. Rushing customers is all-too-common in the US (and I've been a waiter, so, yes, I understand the logic of turning tables). However, at $225/person before tip, such behavior is simply unacceptable.

review_960.Review: I would certainly pick this restaurant for special occasions.  Items a little pricey, but overall my husband and I thank you from the bottom of our hearts for the great food, the extras, and we must applaud our waiter, Ryan W.

review_961.Review: 5A5 is our go-to, particularly when attending performances across the street at the Eureka Theater.The menu is great--hors d'oeuvres can satisfy for a light repast or the main menu is full of wonderful offerings.Perfect cocktails and service!

review_962.Review: The meals are amazing. If you like beef, this is your place.  The woman next to me got the ribeye and I think it was as big as her head.  I had the small portion of the NY steak and it was cooked perfectly.  I also had a lobster appetizer that was amazing.  If you like high energy, ask to be seated in the middle of the main room.  If you like it more quiet, you can be seated in the outer parts of the room.  All in all, great food and a good atmosphere. Highly recommended.

review_963.Review: Staff is phenomenal, food is good, and the pianist is amazing!

review_964.Review: I was running late... no problem... I dont drink alcohol... no problem, I wanted immediate service, no problem.  Quick appetizers.... no problem.  Amuse Bouch in between servings... no problem.  an actual rare steak that was hot on the outside, and warm on the inside.... no problem.  juicy chicken that was tasty with crispy skin... no problem.  Loved the service.  parking was a bear, but when is it not in the city.  I will be going back with friends in the future.  Fun environment that is made for groups.  i would have liked a bit more privacy, but hey its a public restaurant.

review_965.Review: I called ahead to reserve a spot for my brother's birthday and they were more than accomodating. Not only did they give us an awesome table, they were incredibly attentive, and brought out a birthday cake without me even asking!Other notable things: a complimentary mini-appetizer and palate cleanser...along with a visit from the owner of the restaurant!Everything was perfect. Will definitely go there again.

review_966.Review: The steaks and service was fabulous. I had the Waygu beef - it was rich as butter and fork tender.The bartender was great- you felt welcomed to the restaurant.A very hip vibrant feel- especially on a Monday night.

review_967.Review: This was a pleasant experience that I would not mind having at least once a month! Made reservations for a group of 6 to celebrate a birthday for a friend from out of town. In this instance, price was of no conern to us. We were celebrating and ready to enjoy every moment. Upon arrival, the hostess was welcoming and provided exceptional attention. She greated us enthusiastically, took our coats and seated us promptly. Once seated, our waiter was beyond expectations! He spent extra time explaining the menu, walking us through the Waguy beef raising process, provided us with options that were not only sharable, but patron favorites. He was constantly checking on us, refilling beverages often and made the entire experience worth every dime!

review_968.Review: Wonderful experience and overall dining. The appetizers and the main course (New York Steak) was superb.  I will definitely be back on my next bonus and/or other special occasions.

review_969.Review: Highly recommend this fabulous steak house.  The food and presentation were excellent and the owner is very passionate about visiting with their guests to ensure they are pleased with the food and experience.  Great place to take your date, significant other or special guest(s).  Wine list is superb as well.

review_970.Review: service was excellent, wait staff was very friendly. The 50% wagyu filet was very tender but not a tasty as the ribeye. Brussel sprouts were a little overcooked. Great place to go on a special ocasion

review_971.Review: Not the best Wagu I've had, but reasonably priced. The layout of the rest doesn't allow for much privacy, but real estate in SF is hard to come by.

review_972.Review: My friends and I had a great dinner here on a Saturday night.  I loved the crowd, the service, the food and the wine.  On top of that...our bill was surprisingly reasonable for what we ordered.  I'll be back here next time I'm in San Fran.

review_973.Review: I've been here several times and the service has been excellent. It hasn't been perfect but they always apologize and take care of anything that isn't right.It's an expensive place so you'll have to spend some money to truly enjoy the variety and quality of the menu.

review_974.Review: I picked this restaurant becuase I thought for sure the steak would be the star. Unfortunately, it was their weakest item. The atmosphere was nice, the service was good, but the filet was a bit tough. For the price, I expect it to be at least as good as what I cook at home, and it just wasn't. It wasn't a bad experience, but not a memorable one and I wouldn't likely return again in the future.

review_975.Review: We celebrated our engagement and a birthday on the same night. What can I say? it was really quite something. food was mind-blowing, service, like no other, amazing Vibe, and some great memories created. We wont forget it. EVER. thankyou!

review_976.Review: Went for dinner and T-bone was highly recommended by a colleague.  I usually have a filet mignon, but gave this a shot.  If you like T-bone, then 5A5 does an excellent job.  The meat was salted, nicely grilled to bring out a strong flavor of the steak, and the sauce over the steak was a nice complement and did not mask/overpower the steak.  I requested medium rare and they brought it out a bit too raw, but better this way than overdone and just had them fire it up a bit more.  As I said, I prefer a filet to avoid the chewy parts that other cuts of meat have.  5A5 did a good job, but did not convince me to convert to a T-bone nor porterhouse.  Next time, I'll try the filet and hope that the grilling and dry aging process is the same.

review_977.Review: Had a group of 6 of us from the midwest.  Food was excellent!  Everyone had something different and all were overwhelmed at how good it was!  Waitress was a bit slow but it allowed us to take all of scenery in and enjoy the ambiance.  Definitely need to come back!

review_978.Review: A5 ribeye was the best steak I've ever tasted. Dry aged bone-in NY strip with bacon jam and sous-vide egg was also excellent. We enjoyed the half-price wine on Mondays special as well!

review_979.Review: Tads steak in NYC is better than this place.    i'm a foodie and I have had steak everywhere (peter lugers, Sparks, Prime, Jacobs and Co, Mortons to name but a few.  To compare this place to tad's steak in NYC should tell you how bad this place is.  The steak was boiled literally no texture no searing .  I ordered a 26oz bone in ribeye and it was horrible I can make it better in my own frying pan (which says a lot)      I would never recommend this place to anyone.,

review_980.Review: It was my sister's 30 birthday, and 5A5 offered her a nice one with great food, best service and a little surprise cake. Thanks Laila to give us a great dining experience.

review_981.Review: Took my girlfriend here for her birthday and had a wonderful evening.  It's perfect for the special occasion that also calls for a hip scene.

review_982.Review: My girlfriend and I came in for our anniversary dinner. The staff was very attentive and knowledgeable about the menu. They were very considerate food allergies and preferences. I enjoyed the lighting and how it adds to the lounge atmosphere. The food was simply divine. We ordered the truffle fries with the sriracha aioli, the A5 experience for the entree with the potato au gratin for the side dish, and the sorbet tasting and opera cake per waitress' suggestion. The beef from the A5 experience was very tender and flavorful. The potato au gratin was a great compliment. The sorbet taster had a wide variety of flavors and the opera cake was delicious and had wonderful texture.

review_983.Review: Everything was amazing. I celebrated my birthday here with my boyfriend and it was perfect. The food was amazing and the service was great! I would definitely come back here again.

review_984.Review: The food from appetizer to dessert and everything in between was fantastic. Our waitress made our experience extremely enjoyable. Service was very attentive, suggestions were spot on, and the food came out with perfect timing. Overall we were very satisfied and would not hesitate to return.

review_985.Review: The king crab appetizer was wonderful.  My girlfriends filet was very good.  I had the steak for $14 an once, it was OK but not worth the price.

review_986.Review: I truly love this place. The service is outstanding. My friends and I went for the $39 Prime Rib Dinner the meal was great but the prime rib was a little chewy.

review_987.Review: Chose this location for a final dinner with friends before departing San Francisco. It was chosen based on reviews here and other similiar sites. The food was excellent, I had lamb chops the others prime rib.  The setting was great for conversation and an overall relaxing locale.  I especially enjoyed the timing of the course service, they were not rushed nor did they drag.  It was what fine dining should be, enjoyable conversation with the service just being part of the experience.  While some may be concerned about the prices, we felt they were comparable with fine dining in San Francisco. Well worth the time and would recommend 5A5 for special night out.

review_988.Review: We had a party of 6, two in the party wanted sparkling water.  The wait staff was very efficient at filling the tap water glasses but left the sparkling water glasses ignored.  The food was fantastic!  Would highly recommend 5A5 for dinner.In the lounge the piano player's song selections (at the time we were there 6:30 PM) were really fast and loud, a little too much for dinner ambiance.  His selections improved later.  we joked that he must be paid by the number of songs he played.  It actually had a few of us on edge!

review_989.Review: ordered the fried peppers and lobster tempora for starters, both good but nothing to write home about.  We ordered the 4oz Wagyu fillet and 4oz Wagyu rib cap, both were about $34 per oz, so be prepared to shell out some cash.  We loved both of the cuts, they were amazingly tender, flavorful and melt in your mouth.  We also had the truffle Mac and cheese, which was rich, creamy and delightful.  The Brussels spouts were also one of out favorite items of the night.  We finished the meal by sharing the peach tea dessert.  We don't drink alcohol so we both ordered water.  This place was great but for the almost $500 bill we expected the service to be a little more attentive and the experience to be a little more special.

review_990.Review: I really enjoyed my dinner here with friends as the food and decor weren't your standard top tier SF steakhouse fare. While they do have options to spend serious money (100% wagyu cuts), I really appreciated the refreshing enhancements they've added to their typical steaks. I'm definitely planning to visit again.-g

review_991.Review: This is the 2nd time I am back to this resturant in 1 month. The first time I was here, me and my husband celebrated our 1 year wedding ann. The resturant created a wonderful dessert for us. I had a very romantic dinner. The 2nd time is when I tell my friends/co-workers how great my first experience was, we decided to come back to celebrate a promotion here. The food we ordered for both time are all amazing yummy! I tried their F-5 fillet the firs time and really liked it. The 2nd time, I ordered Slow roasted prime rib, it was very juicy. The staffs all have beautiful smiles and the services they provided was five star. I highly recommended this place to anyone who has a special occasion and looking for some of the best food/steak in town.

review_992.Review: excellent and varied appetizers which are so large that they can serve as main course if you dont want one of their steaks

review_993.Review: We've never tasted steak like it - or paid so much for it. Still worth it for special that special occasion. Wine list is impeccable, as was the service. The Filet Mignon was like butter. We all ordered different steaks and they all had unique flavours. Quite an achievement. The side dishes are big enough for a family of four. Truffled mac & cheese is quite delicious. A nice twist to an old favourite. Leave room for desert. The wagyu sliders are great for two - and gives you a taste of the wagyu without having to pay a fortune (market rates).

review_994.Review: Bacon jelly with egg on the NY or a Rib Eye is to die for! Don't forget the Truffle Mac and Cheese to go with it.

review_995.Review: Excellent steak and sides. The food and service is quite consistent.

review_996.Review: I picked this place for romantic ambiance and special birthday dinner.   We were surprised to have screaming babies at the table next to us at such a high priced, chic venue.   Although i spoke to the hostess twice prior to arrival, she did not have us at a corner private table as requested, and attempted to place us in the middle of the restaurant surrounded by other groups, ignoring my special request.   The food was good, the waiter was very good, however, for the prices, the restaurant has to step it up...Won't be going back :(

review_997.Review: Two of us had dinner on 8/31/2014.  Food, service, and atmosphere were all great.  Would certainly recommend as well as return.

review_998.Review: Prime rib is always spectacular! they have the most flavorful rub and their bone in ribeye is a winner everytime!

review_999.Review: This is a beautiful restaurant handled by professional staff. This was my husbands and I first time at 5A5. We flew in from LA and was looking for delicious food in a nice setting. We came across 5A5 online. We made 830 Reservations. We showed up at 815, hung out at the bar and was seated timely. Our table was small and away from the ambiance. I asked if we could move to a bigger table and be seated in the booth area, central to the ambiance. The staff made it happen and we were pleased. Our service was exceptional, very personal. The Wagyu was AMAZING. Every bite melted in my mouth. The dessert, almond cake was superb. The entire experience deserves a 10 star rating.

review_1000.Review: Wonderful food, very friendly and attentive waiter, and surprising "gifts" from the chef.

review_1001.Review: I really wanted to like this place a lot but it's just not meant to be. I love the atmosphere! Loud energetic crowd! Mood lighting! It all works but the food is not for me unfortunately. I've had the bone-in ribeye and the bone-in NY... def have had better elsewhere. I also think I caught them on a bad night as it was almost impossible to flag someone down for water, hot water, the check... The 3 women ordered petit filets of varying degrees of doneness and all got the wrong ones.... doesn't sound like a horrible mistake but dim lighting meant no one noticed until after several bites in at which point they didn't feel like switching. Too bad.

review_1002.Review: Prepare for awesome. I have had a number of menu items.  Bone in New York strip is amazing. Prime rib is best in SF in my humble opinion.

review_1003.Review: 5A5 had a great ambiance, but I would not recommend it for the steak. My steak was very chewy, to the extent I spit parts out. It was more like a $16 steak than a $30 steak at a steak lounge. The chicken and other platters made up for the flavorless steak.Overall, not worth the money but worth the experience. Beautiful interior!

review_1004.Review: My family had a great meal and a wonderful evening. Totally recommend

review_1005.Review: GREAT FOOD, BEST SERVICE and overall AMBIANCE.  Just wish the overall scene and music at the bar would have been more energetic but still a great time and would definitely return.

review_1006.Review: Highly recommended.  The food was excellent and the service was top-notch.

review_1007.Review: Great atmosphere, food & service; but if you are with a group of people trying to talk to each other, forget it.  We couldn't even hear the waitress unless you were sitting right next to where she was standing.

review_1008.Review: We have eaten here before and really enjoyed our food our waitress and the entire experienc BUT this time was different!!It was suggested that I try the "A5 rib 4oz.  My husband had the prime rib for 28.00.  We got the bill and my LITTLE 4 oz. cost us $132.00WOW and it wasn't that good.  Husband's prime rib was fantastic.  Also we could not figure out the $81.88 added to the bill.Very expensive for two old foggies on retirement.??!!

review_1009.Review: 5A5 offers fine quality food. My favorite is the lobster tempera. I usually do not eat fried food but I do make an exception for this dish. Their Cesar Salad is delicious. Service can be a little slow.

review_1010.Review: Not sure what Opentable's VIP gets you, maybe a good seat next to the noisy kitchen or near the waiter station?   Other than the seating the food was good but not a place I would put in the top of my list to go to in the future.  Place was very loud.  I had the prime rib and wife had steak.  Both were very good.

review_1011.Review: Okay...it's not cheap.  But, frankly, we didn't know beef could taste like this.  And it was worth the price to experience it.  As a matter of fact, we shared the "5A5 Experience".  Everything was really outstanding.  The service, the salad, the side dish, even our table neighbors who became our new best friends when our entree arrived!  And Wagyu beef is the most amazing food on the planet.  Our server was friendly and helpful with suggestions, and we enjoyed the ambiance too.  Not super loud, but not what you would call a private romantic environment.  Overall, we enjoyed it immensely and we look forward to visiting again.

review_1012.Review: Service, food and overall experience was exceptional. Staff is very well versed in the art and science of hospitality and good food.

review_1013.Review: This was a wonderful dining experience. Well worth then price. My husband and I think it may have been the best meal we have had in a really long time. Highly recommend this resturant.

review_1014.Review: We had made early reservations, however, we were given a table in the back where they seated groups with kids. Next time, I'll insist on a booth since we made the reservation.

review_1015.Review: The service was super awesome! Employees are Very well trained and patienced in despite of my two crazy little munchkins. I would love to come back here. The service over all was great and very professional

review_1016.Review: Probably one of the only SF restaurants that stuck out to me.

review_1017.Review: Excellent value. Took a chance & 5A5 did not disappoint.Had the Maguro bite. Great balance of basil, mint & cilantro w/just the right amount of heat from the jalapeno.Small plate had the U-10 scallops 2 ways. Scallops poached so perfectly, Gordon Ramsay would be proud. The seared scallops were excellent as well, chimichurri & trout roe with pickled carrots really add an interesting flare to the dishFor my main I had dry aged bone-in ny 22oz w/bacon jam, sous vide “perfect” egg. Mix the yolk with the bacon jam & take a bite of this perfectly cooked steak. Order medium as they tend to lean to the medium rare side anyway. Finished w/4 oz. 50/50 F1 Tajima Filet. Cooked perfectly medium rare, silky smooth & melts in your mouth. Very rich

review_1018.Review: Went to 5A5 for my birthday, and we chose the perfect place! My husband and I are meat lovers, so 5A5 totally satisfied our happy tummy!

review_1019.Review: We had dinner with my son and his girlfriend's family.  I had called the restaurant earlier to confirm our reservation and we decided to have some fun with my son and his girlfriend because they pull a prank on me during Father's Day.  The server, Lynn was a bright young Asian lady, when she approach my son, she ask him if this was his engagement dinner!  This throws my son completely off and even his girlfriend's father was laughing because my son was blushing!  We had a  scrumptious dinner! For dessert, Lynn served my son a special dessert with a chocolate icing that say "If you like this, you better put a ring on it!" The food, the atmosphere and Lynn's playfulness made this a wonderful evening that we will not forget!

review_1020.Review: This was my first time at this restaurant. Everything I hear about it was a good experience for me and my wife. It was our anniversary and the dessert was a nice touch. Thank you to all that served us that night

review_1021.Review: The food was really excellent.  We had a variety of steaks which ranged from very good to superb. But we waited an hour for a table even with reservations, and they did not offer much of an apology.

review_1022.Review: My partner took me here for my birthday supper.  The food was fantastic; the atmosphere was vibrant; the service was exceptional.  On top of all that, the prices were reasonable.

review_1023.Review: Steak dinners are not a regular choice but when you have a craving for beef there is nothing better than a great cut prepared right. 5A5 did not disappoint. The entire meal from the Wagyu Tartare and beef sashimi to the bone in aged NY to sides and dessert were excellent. Nice wine list too. The service was outstanding from the moment we walked into the restaurant. The atmosphere was very nice and relaxed and made for a great dining experience.

review_1024.Review: Made a reservation the day of and my wife and I arrived an hour early. We decided to relax in the lounge area and order some drinks and appetizers. The Wagyu burgers were delicious. We loved the main dining area and the main course was great. Our personal favorite was the truffle Mac and cheese. Great service!!

review_1025.Review: Glacially potent and  realistically priced Belvedere straight- up Martini." "Lobster Tempura"starter induced an historic "mouth-feel"for me:  First the satisfying crunch of a perfectly crafted panko crust..followed by the explosion of briney lobsterjuice from an unimaginably moist and ample chunk of tail meat! Followed with the 6 oz. Filet Mignon. Tender and well seasoned.Hip restaurant. Intelligent table service. Back in a flash.

review_1026.Review: The food was very good but there were a couple of things I thought of as kind obnoxious. For example, in between the appetizer and the entree, they bring you this little mint-jelly-jello cube on a spoon as some kind of 'palette neutralizer' - it was stupid. It was also very noisy. But the food was good.

review_1027.Review: Well, we didn't pay 138 for 4 oz of Japanese beef, and my spouse enjoyed her roast beef enough. The shrimps should have been thrown out the day before, the lentil soup was the best thing I had. I could go on about how most things were either sub-par or ordinary, despite a too-cheerful waiter trying to upsell us. Won't go back.

review_1028.Review: Very tender beef, excellent meal and service.  A bit pricey but worth it for a special occasion or to impress guests.  The ultra modern decor is not to my taste, but then so little is.  Go for the food.  They import genuine Wagu and Kobe beef, and their domestic beef is Angus.  My T-bone was underdone but fine, so order one step more done than you really want.  Extra friendly and efficient staff.  They called 2 days in advance to confirm our reservation, and asked for any food allergies or sensitivities-- then the waitress repeated back what I told the caller and advised against certain selections.  What a great service.  I was impressed.

review_1029.Review: One of the best dining experience I've experienced in San Francisco. Our server was outstanding! She was knowledgeable with the menu, gave great recommendations, and was very welcoming and attentive. Phenomenal service.The only bad part of our dinner was the food runner who took and boxed our food. He tried to carry all the plates, and in doing so, stacked a plate right on top of our creamed spinach that was going to be boxed up! When we got our boxed food back, we realized he had thrown away my bone from my ribeye. There was still meat on the bone and I was looking forward to eating it at home! Also, he threw away what was left of our mac & cheese, which my girlfriend was looking forward to eating too. :(

review_1030.Review: food was a B+. Service was amazing and there were a lot of chef s complimentry dishes.

review_1031.Review: The food was Amazonas, and the service even better! If i could, i would bring the waiter back home with me to Norway. Outstanding knowlegde which made our experience top notch.

review_1032.Review: Dinner was a disaster.Lobster Tempura: Lobster was average, cooking in low temperature oil(?) caused it to be oily and unsatisfying.Soup du jour - Carrot and Ginger - was flavorless.The Iceberg Lettuce salad was among the worst I have had in a fine dining establishment. Yellow, almost rotting lettuce. The manager took it away, but the one he brought to replace it was not much better.Brussel Sprouts, which the server recommended, were horrendous.4 ounce Tajima F1 filet, medium rare, was nearly inedible. Tasted like the fuel that was used to cook it.Aumse Bouche was made with 'stale' prosciutto. Palate cleanser was without taste.I skipped dessert.

review_1033.Review: Business dinner with two others for an early dinner. Our waiter, Ali, was very thorough and energetic ... he recommended the Wagyu beef. Although it was tempting, we decided to go with their standard steaks. I highly recommend the appetizers including the Malay Satay, Shrimp, Wagyu Slider and the Truffle fries. The Prime Rib was excellent and so was the Ribeye. The restaurant was not too noisey, and we were able to have a nice conversation without being drowned out by the other patrons.

review_1034.Review: You wont be disappointed coming here.  We had the dry aged ribeye and it was amazing!

review_1035.Review: Visited 5A5 Steak Lounge on our first night of a week long trip to San Fran and liked it so much we returned for a second time a few nights later. Loved the diversity of the menu, the care and attention that went into the sauces accompanying the domestic cuts and the waygu??? What can we say -- a little tough on the pocketbook but very much worth it!! Bar far the best part of the experience though was the quality of the staff. Our server Layla was absolutely phenomenal -- extremely friendly, enthusiastic and knowledgeable -- and interacting with her was certainly one of the highlights of the trip.

review_1036.Review: Loved the lobster mash potatoes and really enjoyed the mushroom side plate (great if you enjoy a simply prepared wild assortment of mushrooms).The steak we ordered was smothered in sauce, which may be good for some, but if you're a traditionalist who wants a great steak that stands on its own you will be disappointed.  I saw other people ordered a prime rib that looked fantastic, for which I may go back and give it a try.

review_1037.Review: This is not your average Japanese steak house.  Live piano music accented the ambiance of this contemporary, upscale restaurant.  The service was first rate.  The food was expertly prepared and presented.  The lobster appetizer was flavorful as were the sliders.  Worth the splurge was the Wagyu beef.  Three of us shared an 8 oz. rib-eye.  The steak melted in your mouth - a culinary experience!  No doubt the American steaks would have been tasty for a fraction of the cost.  All in all, a great meal and an enjoyable evening,

review_1038.Review: I had a 4 oz A5 wagyu rib eye that was cooked perfectly, melts in your mouth and it was better than Alexander's Australian version.  My Son's bone-in rib-eye was huge and cooked just the right way, which is difficult because the thickness of the steak itself! and my wife's three small plates; tuna tataki, wagyu sashimi and lobster tempura was great, especially the lobster tempura that cannot be cooked any better; crunchy on the outside yet juicy on the inside!  Aside from the wonderful meal, their dessert was great too!  we are coming back for more next month with friends so we can try other dishes as well. Wanted to also mention their excellent services!

review_1039.Review: First time experiencing Wagyu Beef.  Loved it and 5A5!  Will be back for sure!

review_1040.Review: I would expect great beef from a Steak House, and 5A5 did not disappoint.  The $200 Wagyu steaks were not in the budget, but the "regular" ribeye was among the best I have had - great sear/crust, sauce, sides.  Everyone in my party (work colleagues) left happy.Hope to return soon!

review_1041.Review: This is my 1st time to this restaurant and I brought a friend who works for Singapore Airlines. She was very impressed with our waitress, Megan. She's very friendly,  efficient,  patient,  passionate about what she does. She has a great smile all the time. And check on us  to make sure we are okay with our food. What a pleasant evening with excellent service and great food. I'll be bringing friends to 5A5 again.

review_1042.Review: Fine meal, good experience, and a few things for the epicure.  There is Wagyu beef on the menu and a fine selection of whiskeys from around the world.  My companion and I each ordered a flight (three 1oz shots), one from the US and one from Japan.  The wait staff was very attentive and friendly without being overbearing, the ambiance leans towards trendy (flashy lights), and the chef sent out a couple tidbits to whet the appetite.  Would definitely dine here again.

review_1043.Review: First time at the restaurant which has been open for five years. The staff was excellent from the front door to the Matre D usering us out and telling us what direction we should take for our walk home.Food was exceptional from the 3 different cuts of beef to the all of the extras. Spinach, Mac & cheese, mashed potatoes and on and on. These were the moderately priced steaks in difference to the 5A steaks on the left side of the menu. Service was the BEST. Jake deserves an award besides his gratuity.The lounge and the Neil Young lookalike piano player was a hit. One glass of port became 3 glasses, and a whole lot of 60 & 70's music leaving just a great spot in our hearts for A5A .

review_1044.Review: We celebrated belated Father's Day dinner. My father had a great time there with unique and taste Wagyu beef. He had the rib cab and it tasted great. He was very surprised being served with a special dessert at the end for his recognition. A few things to improve.1) The table is leveled too high at the center section. I felt like a kid, eating with arms held high.2) The music from the pianist was too loud. I hope softer music was played.Other than that, it was great. I will definitely come back to treat my friends out.

review_1045.Review: Friendly ... Romantic ..vibrant... Delicious! You will definitely see me again!! Impecable service!

review_1046.Review: Excellent and attentive service.  Wife's filet outstanding...my ribeye just ok.  Ribeye prepared ok, just nit a good cut that night, low marbled.  Mac n cheese was excellent.

review_1047.Review: Everything we ordered was great. Over server was very attentive, but it was a little loud. But all and all, a great place for steak.

review_1048.Review: The open kitchen is fun to watch, but noisy.  The open floor plan makes you feel like you're in a high class lounge, but also adds to overall volume.  The food all had great flavor, but our meat and veggies were a bit underdone for our taste (fleshy center for medium rare & al dente brussel sprouts).  Since we were incredibly full from our appetizers and other side dishes, we were perfectly content with eating the edges of our filet and ribeye, and took leftovers home.  The service was GREAT!  From the moment we were greeted, to our servers attention, to the support staff clearing our dishes, filling our water and checking in on us.  Don't expect to have an intimate conversation, but do expect to have a fun, lively dining experience.

review_1049.Review: I dined at 5A5 Steak Lounge for my birthday followed by an encore visit several days later.  The staff was welcoming and genuine each time.  The atmosphere was comfortable and not pretentious.  Delicious food, generous portions, appropriate seasoning and just the right temperature.  I had a Wagyu steak for my birthday and while it was pricey it was worth cost. $$$ My second visit saw me ordering grilled chicken.  The menu is simple and most items are affordable.  The staff was very accommodating and even flagged a taxi for me as I hurried to the theater.  Give 5A5 a chance, I'm going back soon!

review_1050.Review: Great service and food, expensive but worth it for special occasion

review_1051.Review: I very much liked the menu concept. Fun, innovative

review_1052.Review: From our appetizers to dessert and all the mini tastings in between we were thrilled with every morsel. Ali is amazing!

review_1053.Review: Went here tonight for my 7 year anniversary dinner 3 hours and $240 later this place ruined our entire night ! Dinner took over 3 hours for two people 3 courses. They cooked our steaks wrong and then when they came out with the new ones they must have been out of sauces because my steak had almost no demi glaze or tarragon beurre fondue but they tried to cover it up with the herb salad. They tried to make it up to us with free desert and only made us wait 30 minutes for it. This place is a joke and they treated us poorly because we where from out of town. The manager told me he had never seen so many things go wrong in his 30 years in the business. Then comped us one app and desert that took 30 minutes that we didn't even want.

review_1054.Review: I had been here before and enjoyed the meal. This time there was nothing that we had - and we had about 17 different items because we were a large group - that was the least bit memorable. It was very disappointing. And very expensive. I would not recommend this restaurant to anyone. Even the steak was not particularly good.

review_1055.Review: Warm and welcoming,  food was great, it was definitely a 5 star experience. The ambience was wonderful.

review_1056.Review: Dinner was incredibl!,. Food outstanding, excellent service and great wine list. Make sure you save for dessert

review_1057.Review: This was the best steak I have had in a long time.the food is amazing,The service was so great.I cannot say enough about how wonderful we were treated.It is deffinately an food lovers paradise.

review_1058.Review: Initially, this restaurant looks and feels like a cold, modern, trendy restaurant. The decor is kind of a cross between 50's modernism and futuristic. The maitre d' seemed out of place here: an older gentleman from an old, stuffy restaurant. However, it is further from the truth. The maitre d' greeted you warmly upon entering. The waiter service was impeccable. He and his assistant were very knowledgeable and attentive, but not overbearing. The food and presentation were very good. Typical steakhouse pricing where everything is a la carte. What really surprised me was, upon leaving, the maitre d' thanked me by name, and made a comment about and remembered the brief conversation we had with him when he first seated us. Now that's service.

review_1059.Review: Highly recommend the new lunch offering - great price point, AMAZING food, quiet ambiance. I want to go back every day. Loved the bento box idea. It's like 4 lunches in one. Can't wait to revisit!

review_1060.Review: I've been here for dinner many times but it was my first time for lunch. I love the "bento box" concept. The portion is small so you get to sample many option. I order the eye of the Ribeye, lobster tempura, truffle mac & cheese & truffle miso soup. Everything was delicious and I didn't leave there over stuff.  The services as always are exceptional.

review_1061.Review: Wow! I'm very impressed with 5A5. I booked a 5:30 table for two on a Thursday, and the place was completely empty. The place quickly began to fill up, but the service didn't get distracted at all. The staff was very welcoming, and each person addressed by name the entire night and never stopped paying attention to the table, even when every other table was occupied. The cuisine looked like art, and everything was delicious! The Chef sent us 3 special "tastes" gratis. I was glad that the appetizer portions were small, because we wanted to order 3 courses. The best appetizer on the menu is the Mac n Cheese with lobster. I could have been content just eating this all night. The steaks came out perfect, dessert was spectacular

review_1062.Review: The service and food was A+. I went there for a formal business dinner & viewed the experience as excellent. I would also return with my wife now for personal dinner as well.

review_1063.Review: This restaurant exceeded many of my expectations from reading the reviews.  I had a late dinner there with my wife and everything from the ambience, the service and the food was outstanding.  The interior space was warm and inviting.  The tables are a mix of couches and chairs and made for an interesting layout leaving enough to know you're in a restaurant but still have that intimate feel with your dinner party.  The service from our waitress was very good.  She kept us well informed of the dishes and made a few suggestions which we selected.  The food was incredible.  We enjoyed the bites and appetizers and our steaks were cooked to medium rare perfectly.  Overall, it was a great dining experience and a night to remember.

review_1064.Review: I could not have been happier with the quality of service & food at 5A5. Everyone was very accommodating. Excellent recommendations from the waitress and the food was perfect from sampler to dessert. Definitely coming back for more.

review_1065.Review: Our server, Ryan, was absolutely awesome! He was so knowledgeable about the food and made amazing recommendations!

review_1066.Review: Wanted a steak place for my birthday and this one was within walking distance.  They specialize in Wagyu beef although they carry USDA Prime cuts on the menu.  The appetizers were excellent and the US Prime steak were cooked perfectly.  The sorbet desert was a delight to share. Only negative was that we were seated near the entrance to the kitchen so it was not a quiet romantic setting.

review_1067.Review: Blew me away. Food was great, service was outstanding.
