review_1068.Review: LOVE this place for light dinner/small plates  The Rib/Chip plate ... amazing.  truffle Fries and Chicken Yakitori are close runners-up for favorites.  Always have done the bar bites, not dinner.  Great pianist when we were there, too

review_1069.Review: Great start to our night out. Had a few drinks in the lounge before the rest of our group showed up as well as after our meal. Good ambiance and good energy in this restaurant. We also had great service as well. Overall great experience.

review_1070.Review: from start to finish - outstanding in every wayservice was top notch, attentive but not intrusiveserver very knowledgable, not pushy nor focused on upselling like some other placeson to the food - hamachi bites were fantastic, lobster tempura divinewe did a steak tasting, ordered family style for the tableprime rib- excellent, had a garlic/black pepper rub of sorts i believe, best prime rib i've had in the cityfilet mignon- super tender, lean cut. Very good steak, in general i like my steaks a bit more marbled so don't usually order the fileta5 wagyu- new york and rib eye cutsdrumroll please...Best.Steaks.Evermelt in your mouth, there is no comparison. Pricey, but well worth itgreat spot for a special occasion or business dinner

review_1071.Review: Great food. Great service. Great experience. Highly recommend.

review_1072.Review: The food just okay. Our waiter (Ryan?) was very nice but did not have a memory and did follow thru with anything we asked.  So, we asked to have each course sent separately but three orders came out at the same time.  Asked for the truffle fries to come first several times but received the Hamachi first then two minutes later out came the truffle fries then another minute later came out the Lobster Tempura (we said we needed to wait on the Lobster so we got the same dried up order 20 minutes later which was $24 and very disappointing). Asked for a espresso and the waiter asked if we wanted sugar and we said yes, right! it came with no sugar.

review_1073.Review: Great food, but the Waygu steak is not worth the whopping $$. We got it but regret not getting the bone is New York since it looked amazing and was priced normally for a steak house of this caliber. Great service and overall great place.

review_1074.Review: Love, love, love this restaurant.  The food is amazing.  Wine list is fairly extensive and at all price points. I was with 2 other friends and every item we ordered - from appetizers to entrees - was delicious.  The service was very good as well.  My friends live other states and have traveled the world for work.  They were very impressed with this restaurant so if you want a special place to go for dinner, go here!

review_1075.Review: Tried A5A on recent business trip into San Francisco, service was excellent, appetizers and sides were very good. Several of us had the same comment, everything was really good but what's the deal with the odd "jams" and sauces on the steaks? Frankly, if you are ordering a NY strip, you want to taste the steak, not the peculiar jams/sauces. Waiter gave us a tip to next time request them on the side or order without as he hears that "quite a bit" as to the steak. Likely some will like the unique preparation approach but for a traditionalist looking for a new steak place for a go to place (outside of the classic's we can all count on but you can access them just about everywhere of any demographic density) in S.F., not sure this is it.

review_1076.Review: I went in expecting a trendy steak place and wow did I get that and more.  The wagu beef app was amazing, the steak preparations were both interesting and added to the taste of the beef in place of overpowering it.  My only meal issue was the creamed spinach...not really creamed spinach...good but not the steakhouse classic.  The dessert was a tobacco ice cream served in a sazerac  cocktail...just amazing....really.  And then the scotch cart...makes my heart go pitter patter again just thinking about it...Seriously, worth the experience.   Great food and a great time.

review_1077.Review: Sorry but with the high prices, they had better knock your socks off.  And that just did not happen.  Yeah the place looks 'modern' but it felt sterile.  It felt more like a scene than a great restaurant.   And worst of all- I do not remember the food.  What does that tell you?

review_1078.Review: The service and atmosphere were fantastic. Stopped at the bar before dinner and truly enjoyed the bartender. Our waiter was also very good. Atmosphere was great. Loud but not obnoxiously so. The food was average. My steak was over done, not med rare as ordered, and not the best quality. They tout the Waygu beef at exorbitant prices but their "normal" priced cuts were below average, in our humble opinion.

review_1079.Review: The steak I shared was delicious, flavorful, and cooked exactly to specification.  We didn't splurge for the Waygu and it was still a big treat.  Actually, not big, and I really appreciated the 6oz option on the filet mignon and the 4 oz strip.  I love red meat, but I don't want a lot in a sitting these days.  While the steaks and presentation of their phenomenal meat is impressive, no need to be vetting your guests before coming here.  We had fish bites, octopus salad, tuna first, and it was all so fresh and divine.  Chef shares upon seating and the palate cleanser part was through, very nice touches.

review_1080.Review: Just fine dining . From my favorite appetizer lobster tempera, next the blue cheese wedge salad, I had the boneless ribeye, perfectly cooked, tender, the sides were perfect. Cream of spinach, smooth mashed potatoes, and yummy Mac n cheese. The gm KEVIN made sure everything was to our satisfaction. The waitress very knowledgable n friendly . Overall great dinner

review_1081.Review: I'm short on time but we loved our time here.  Just a great overall experience; including the food and service.  Can't wait to return!

review_1082.Review: I was recommending this restaurant a lot to friends and my husband finally decided to try it with me this time.  He was disappointed with the food quality.  He said: "it is not bad, just standard".  That was not the case when I went with friends last year.  What happened???  They should also be mindful of customers who is bringing in a very special purse (birkin- attending a gallery event).  They should know to bring its own little chair to sit on and not let it rest on my back.  Alexander pulled a chair for our purses.

review_1083.Review: A friend who lives in SFO recommended 5A5 to me.  I walked there to eat & the place was great.  I had an idea of what kind of location I was looking for, to eat dinner on my one night in SFO, and this place was it.  Ate at the bar, the staff was very attentive & friendly, there was a piano player doing his thing, the music was very nice.  The food was amazing.  Was worth it all.  I'm very glad I went in there.

review_1084.Review: Steak here is awesome.  Great vibe in the restaurant, and a real gem for meat lovers who enjoy a fabulous meal.  Our food server was perfect in her timing and execution, all the while unassuming, attentive, friendly and cordial.  During dinner I drank more than 12 glasses of water since I had a few cocktails at HH earlier and my water glass was never empty.  Most of the food servers and all the bartenders are super.  I've never had a mediocre experience, and recommend this restaurant to everyone who enjoys good food!

review_1085.Review: 5A5 was a great experience.  The food was cooked very well, and we were offered a couple of amuse bouches along the way.  I would recommend this restaurant.

review_1086.Review: Tried this on a whim for dinner on our last night on our recent trip to San Francisco (we go a few times of year just to eat all around the city).  Excellent food and great service at the bar (we had dinner there).  It will be added to our regular rounds on future trips.

review_1087.Review: It is always such a pleasure to go to 5A5. The service here is just as exquisite as the food is.  I took my boyfriend here for a surprise birthday dinner, every staff member made sure to wish him a happy birthday. They also brought him out a special dessert, a mini strawberry short cake, with "Happy Birthday Josh" written out it chocolate. It was really special.  The meal was great as well.  We had a feast of brussel sprouts, lobster mac n' cheese, half and half wagyu steak and a filet.  Everything was mouth watering.  Three days later, I am still thinking about the lobster mac and bacon bread.  If you are looking for a great dining experience, with great food with powerful flavors, and a place with great ambiance and service - go to 5A5.

review_1088.Review: An amazing treat. Can't wait to go back

review_1089.Review: I took my parents and cousin here for a celebratory dinner. The food was amazing and could not have asked for better service. Great value for the price.

review_1090.Review: This is one of the best steakhouses I have been to. The Lobster Tempura was spectacular…it practically melted in your mouth. My Filet Mignon was mouthwatering and the drinks were on point. The only downside is that the floors are kind of slippery so you have to be careful. My friend took a little fall on our way to the restroom. Next time I'm in San Francisco I'd definitely go back.

review_1091.Review: We had a great experience at 5A5. The food was impeccable and the service always is as well.

review_1092.Review: I've been hearing for months about this being best place to get a streak in the city. It was good but didn't meet the high expectations we had.

review_1093.Review: First class from valet to finishing small bite sample from chef. We started off with a few cocktails and wine while waiting for one of our guest to arrive. Once seated into the dining area we were quickly greeted by our waiter. Since this was our first experience here, he presented us with a quick review the selected beef and a complete review of the menu.We selected the Tuna Tataki of tandoori spice, watermelon, herb puree, candied bacon since the watermelon with tuna combination intrigued us. It was a refreshing bite of wonderful. Main courses were filet mignon, boneless ribeye steak with sides of potatos au gratin & brussell sprouts. Steaks were perfectly rested before presentation to us and the sides were piping hot.

review_1094.Review: Nice spin on the "traditional" steakhouse. More club/lounge feel to it, but without an annoying DJ spinning in the background. Very comfortable seating and service was pretty on point, but not 5 stars worthy imo. Nice range of steak, but a little shocked that you only have Wagyu or A5 choices then a complete step-down to "Choice" steaks. 5A5 you should have some "Prime" in there especially if you are going to offer dry aged on the menu. A standout here were the side dishes. Brussel sprouts, mac n cheese, truffle fries, and oh yes the hamachi small bite all went fast. Would recommend to anyone who wants a good steak dinner, but not necessarily the same old scene.

review_1095.Review: We went there on a Sunday night quite early. When we entered the restaurant just 1/3 of the tables were taken, so the restaurant was not busy (yet). Nevertheless, we've been completely ignored for the first 10 minutes.Our main waiter was friendly but completely impersonal. He didn't even try to have a small talk with us, just took our order and left quickly.The food was good, the truffle fries were amazing but overall the place does not have a good vibe. It's quite soul-less, and lacks on personality that could distinguish it from other places. Being in San Francisco the fact that the food was good is not enough to stand out. There are many other places with great food in the city.

review_1096.Review: This is a real find; wonderful food and I don't even eat steak...the chicken was fabulous and my date said his steak was equally wonderful. The mashed potatoes were outstanding and the service attentive and the waiter was very informed.

review_1097.Review: Got here last minute as I was craving for a good steak! Even better than I could imagine and I had the boneless ribeye. Next time, I will surely splurge for their specialty Wagyu beef :) My Co-worker was amazed at the entire experience. The entire wait staff was wonderful and accommodating.Thank you 5A5!!

review_1098.Review: First time visiting 5A5, and it was quite good. I had the 24oz bone in ribeye, and my wife went with the 4oz strip. Both were cooked perfectly, and both were tasty. Sides we went with string beans and brussel sprouts, again, both good.The gem on the menu that we didn't touch was the Kobe beef at $35-40 an ounce. I hope to be back at some point to try it, and they did have a sampler of all 4 varieties at $525 for 16 ounces of meat. Worth it? Unknown yet.Only negative I would say would be the overall time it took to get our meal out. It took in excess of 40 minutes for our meal (which they did warn us before hand though)Definitely recommended for a special occasion or meat quenching visit.

review_1099.Review: This was my third trip to 5A5, it is a cool scene. Food is delicious and service is outstanding. Every time I go I think to myself I should come back more often. Highly recommend!

review_1100.Review: I had lunch here on March 14th. I had been wanting to eat here, but they just recently opened for lunch. Our food was very good, but small portions. Also, I felt the menu was very limited.

review_1101.Review: The wagyu was just as promised - a spiritual experience.The service was also outstanding!

review_1102.Review: We came here on business and it turned into a wonderfully fun experience. Our server (Ali) had a special personality...charming and so attentive which made us comfortable and helped us enjoy the evening.

review_1103.Review: Thank you 5a5 for the amazing service, ambiance, food and wine.This made our business dinner celebration perfect.I left on cloud 9 from the amazing food.Cheers!~ Anjou

review_1104.Review: fun place, looks like a scene outta the jetsons, not typical steak-looking place. food ok, not the best cuts of meat, unless you order their wagyu beef. don't understand some of their trimmings, like the pico de gallo on top of our steak. it did not belong there. food, otherwise, ok. not the greatest, just 'ok'. their cocktails, on the other hand, are excellent. the bar/lounge is nice.

review_1105.Review: If you are gluten free. Avoid this restaurant. They say they understand it but they don't. Not worth the money.

review_1106.Review: I am not a huge beef eater. I eat a steak perhaps twice a year. This experience may have swayed that habit. We began with a delicious shrimp appetizer then sampled an American filet mignon, which was quite delicious. However, when our wagyu beef A5 "experience" arrived, I never imagined the gift I was about to present to my tastebuds. Unbelievable. There was absolutely no comparison to the regular steak. Pricey and certainly best kept for special occasions, but do yourself a favor and treat yourself to this menu. Coupled with impeccable service and a comfortable atmosphere, you'll have an unforgettable experience.

review_1107.Review: Very good execution. The hamachi shooter was delicious as was the Tataki Tuna and lobster tempura first course. My steak was tasty although slightly cooked beyond medium rare and a bit over sauced. I recommend if you get any steak, have them put the sauce on the side and get it done one less temp than they recommend, for medium rare, order rare. Service was friendly and attentive. The wine list is manageable and has many interesting choices. They have a sommelier so take advantage of his knowledge of the wine list. The check is not for the faint of heart. Taking full advantage of the dining experience here will set you back $200/person+ with tax, tip, license and doc fee. All in all a really nice dining experience.

review_1108.Review: The prime rib and truffle mac and cheese were to die for!

review_1109.Review: Literally the best steak I have had in my life. Great service and amazing wine pairings. Would recommend as a place to impress and plan to spend a few hours here. Suggest business casual attire.

review_1110.Review: We live in the bay area and often find we go back to our favorites in downtown SF before trying something new. Wow were we glad we branched out a bit and tried 5A5. Everything was perfect, from the split glass of white wine in the bar to start, to even more excellent service as we were explained the menu down to the last detail enabling us to order the perfect amount and type of food.The mac and cheese with lobster was awesome, as was the incredible meat. We have a 6 oz count to share which was perfect for us.All 5 of our senses left happy (the "5" in 5 A5), and while we did not try the A5 qualify beef (a tad pricey for our wallet), we loved what we did get.Bill

review_1111.Review: Beef sashimi was excellent. LOVED the NY Bone In steak with the bacon jam and egg! We had brussel sprouts and shrooms as sides, and while they were good, we weren't wowed by either of them.

review_1112.Review: EXCELLENT FOOD AND SERVICES. GREAT VALUE!

review_1113.Review: When I first walked in the place looked so nice, very moderen. The server we had was AMAZING, everything she did was on point. She was so kind,sweet, and very helpful. She knew what she was talking about, I have to say one of th best servers I've ever had. The food was outstanding!!!! The T-bone steak was just on point! By far the best steak I've ever ate!

review_1114.Review: Off all the wonderful offerings (truffle fries, check - hamachi bites, check - ribeye, check!) it was the lobster tempura that put it over the top for our entire table. We enjoyed the heck outta our evening at 5A5, which is billed as an 'Asian steakhouse' but doesn't distract with an overbearingly ethnic agenda. Food was better than cocktails but I'd go back for both.

review_1115.Review: I HIGHLY HIGHLY RECOMMEND THIS PLACE!! Their food is top notch. I had their rib eye and mashed potatoes with curry gravy...had so much flavor..incredible!! Dont fill up on the bread...I learned from that mistake...overall...perfect spot.

review_1116.Review: Carnivore cravings quenched by multiple Wagyu offerings. Certainly the attraction of this place, and on that front, 5A5 delivers an A5.Service and seating a notch off the highest echelon. Some accompaniments forgotten and occasional plates were delivered without any comment except, "plates are really hot."Also, arrived at early seating but placed in awkward dark back corner, which was soon filled with an 8 top of loud and profane male diners (bachelor party?). Really dampened the atmosphere.

review_1117.Review: You can never go wrong dining at 5A5 for dinner. This was our first lunch there, and it was just as awesome. If you haven't gone here yet, you should!

review_1118.Review: Wow - this was nothing that I expected. Everything was perfection from the moment I dropped my car with the valet, who was so helpful and remembered that I would be back with some packages prior to my reservation and he ran up to me and offered to carry them and put them away for me. The Maitre' d was charming, kind, and very attentive having our coats ready for us when we went to leave. The space is gorgeous in a modern and retro way. Young cool and hip but not in an irritating way (if you are not that young). The food innovative and delicious with a wide range of offerings - including the specialty drinks which are worth a try even though they sound a little strange. We skipped dessert but we couldn't have eaten another bite anyway.

review_1119.Review: Very tasty and creative dishes including the scallops and tempura lobster. Our server tried the hard sell on the wagyu beef, but took up a bunch of our time with an annoying sales pitch. I suggest they simply bring out bites to taste instead of uncooked slabs of fatty beef.

review_1120.Review: Great short menu. Don't fill up on sides. The steak is the best part

review_1121.Review: the rib eye was huge. the sides were better though. I would recommend the truffle fries, the shrooms, as well as the green beans. service was great. I would definitely recommend taking a date here because the staff was so professional. Kudos to the service!

review_1122.Review: We were celebrating a friend completing her schooling.We were a little early, but got seated immediately. After we ordered, they bought us a sausage & duck dish to whet our appetites (compliments of the chef). To start we ordered some oysters, which were delicious and presented wonderfully. For entrees we had the rib eye and the lamb chops with shards & mushrooms as our sides. Everything was mouth-watering good - all of it was cooked to perfection.For dessert, we shared an tobacco ice cream which sounds strange but was indescribably delicious - you have to try it!. They knew were celebrating an occasion and gave my friend a congratulatory (free) Beignets. It was a nice touch.Service was outstanding and attentive. we'll be back!

review_1123.Review: We had a great time at this modern take on a steak house. It had a great feel with even better food. We enjoyed all our courses and the service was efficient without being intrusive. We will be back and I would recommend this place to anyone visiting the city.

review_1124.Review: Several reasons to eat here. 1). The environment is fun and energetic. It's likes 60's lounge meets 2014. Vibrant lights, crocodile texture lounge chairs and a modern rotunda with pastel lighting. 2). The food was crazy good. I had the 10 oz prime rib and it melted in my mouth. My partner had the flier and he loved it. Our sides, were the mac and cheese and chard. IT WAS FLIPPING GREAT!!!! Oh by the way....Bacon bread. Ever had it? I didn't until our dinner. Wow is all I have to say. 3). Service was great. We were celebrating a Birthday and our waitress was great. She went over the menu, made great recommendations and had a "Happy Birthday" plate sent over at the end of our dinner. A great experience and will return!

review_1125.Review: was our first time there. we enjoyed the food. had a great night.

review_1126.Review: The food here is just good, plain and simple. Great steaks, appetizers and sides. Delicious!

review_1127.Review: Made reservations to go to after work and entered a vibrant, happening place with lots of energy --and this was on a Thurs. night!. Thought I had walked into a great Manhattan steak house without the stuffiness. We were seated promptly and the service was excellent. We had the "normal" steaks, which were excellent and cooked to perfection. Truffle fries are a "must have." Would I go back??? You bet.

review_1128.Review: liked the space and ambiance, but the food was not good. i love steak and i actually did not like the one i had here, a first for me. and the appetizers were mediocre so it was not simply a steak issue. that said, others at my table liked their steaks.

review_1129.Review: Had a lovely time eating here. The service was attentive and excellent. The kitchen and the pastry chef was also kind in sending our table a few small bites as palate cleansers which added a lot to the experience. Food was moderate for the price, but the overall experience was very positive and would recommend 5A5 to anyone who can afford it.

review_1130.Review: 5A5 is hands down one of the best steakhouses in the city. From the moment we walked in we were taken care of. We came in late on a Saturday night and the place was packed. We started with the hamachi bites which were amazing, then split a heirloom tomato salad which was simple yet perfectly done. I had the bone in ribeye and my girlfriend had the duo of lamb, both were cooked perfectly and tastes amazing. And the truffle mac on the side, to die for. Our server was also awesome, it took her a minute to get to our table but once she came it was like she could read our minds about what we wanted/ needed. We will definitely be back to 5A5, and next time will have to get the wagyu.

review_1131.Review: I was rather disappointed this time around. I had mentioned on the reservation that I was celebrating my birthday and my fiancé's. Hostess said Happy Birthday to us, but towards the end of the dinner, while all the other bday tables got a nice dessert plate, all we got was the bill. To make matters worse, our waiter gave us the wrong dessert wine and charged us more for the one we got. He didn't even apologize or offer to give us the other one in exchange for his own error. To add to our bad experience, service was rather slow. I spent three hours in the restaurant. They were not busy to be lacking the service I expected and to charge a premium for everything when the food was just okay. I will be going to another steakhouse in the future.

review_1132.Review: From the moment we arrived on a Fri night, they made us feel special. 2 of us had the Sea Bass, which was moist and fresh. Husband had his Rib Eye, which was perfectly medium rare, not fatty. 3 sides of mash potatoes, swiss chard, and mushrooms were all excellent. Maitre D' was on top of the details, waiter happily filled my ice tea numerous times. Couldn't have been a better evening.

review_1133.Review: i dine frequently at $$$$ restaurants. I was thoroughly satisfied with all aspects of my group's experience at 5A5. I will definitely return.

review_1134.Review: If you are looking to try 100% Wagyu beef, this is the place to go. Japanese Whiskey and above average wine list add to the meal. The rest of the meal was above average though you can probably find better individual dishes (e.g., HOPR for prime rib). The service was incredible and made the meal more memorable. Not a restaurant to go everyday though certainly for special occasions or when the mood strikes for a fancy night out.

review_1135.Review: Just about the best Prime Rib around. Tender, moist, succulent and full of flavor. Don't order the big cut unless you brought someone to help you eat it. Finish up with Apple Crisp with ice cream. Does not get better than that.

review_1136.Review: Great place to have a special birthday dinner with friends who are steak lovers. Quite a dining experience. Big bill dining. Really fun.

review_1137.Review: My wife took my to 5A5 for my birthday. I think A5A has the best steak in San Francisco and the food on this meal met my high expectations. The only negative of our experience was that the service was particularly slow, which was a bit surprising as the restaurant was not completely full. Despite the slow service, I will go back again as the food is fantastic.

review_1138.Review: Similar to Alexanders? Fusion that could use taste profile editing(pasty amuse bouches,hamachi "Bite" overpowered by seasoning,but lovely presentation).- To Food enthusiast who understand dry aged beef, wagyu, California cuisine: this is probably a lower end restaurant list option. $40-200/steak: Steak 1 ordered medium rare,arrived medium well. 2nd steak ordered well arrived slightly rare. For the price you pay go to something like Alexanders, Lawry, Harris for better food quality.-Waited 30mins for our steaks after addtnl 20 mins for appetizers(restaurant was qtr filled @arrival, bar tables served appetizers before us); Very loud, appropriate for upscale bar/lounge ambiance, no separate dining area from bar folks, tables not cleared.

review_1139.Review: Was terrific. Loved the bento box idea for lunch. Each one of the four items was fantastic, as was dessert.

review_1140.Review: We we're totally impressed with not only the food, but the friendly, professional service. It could not have been a nicer evening. From the greeting, to the bar, to the dining, it was a wonderful experience - and we travel and dine out quite often.

review_1141.Review: Hosted a group of 10 here & all was flawless; food service, attention to detail-amazing. We also had someone in our party with a ridiculously restrictive diet & hostess/waitstaff still managed to 'please' her (I am grateful!). Although streaks were outstanding, seafood with Asian flair was astounding, as were all our apps, sides & desserts. Definitely returning asap.

review_1142.Review: perfect to take your significant other. thanks!

review_1143.Review: Amazing!Started with the Tuna Tataki. This dish was refreshing with the slices of watermelon!A5 Experience! 4 - A5 Wagu pieces.NY - The best New York I ever had. Each bite was savory and melted in my mouth. Served with a truffle bubbles on top.Filet - Amazing as well. Served with a truffle risotto!Rib Eye - My favorite cut of beef was served with mushrooms.Rib Eye Cap - Meat so tender I tried cutting it with a fork and succeeded!Dinner was amazing. We ended with the Belle Pear dessert. It was really refreshing after all the heavy meats we tried.To end the night, the pastry chef brought out a dish of pastries for us.Our server then brought out a little card that showed the animal from where the heavenly meat came from!

review_1144.Review: 6 for dinner. The filet very good, the bone in rib eye, gross. stringy texture, unediable. Did some things well, but would not go back.

review_1145.Review: A great place for a special event. Beautiful restaurant. The service was 5 star. We made up our own dinner from the menu. They encourage splitting dinners to complete the experience. We had American steak, and Japanese Wagyu Beef. The American beef was very good, but the Wagyu was magical. it should be at $29 an ounce. It is worth trying once. It you ate it regularly, you would have a heart attack in a week. But, it sure was good.

review_1146.Review: Our experience here for my husband's birthday was great. The cocktails and dinner were very well prepared. Our server Ryan was knowledgeable and provided the perfect balance of conversation and service.

review_1147.Review: My daughter, granddaughter and I went there for my birthday, We sampled the wagyu beef which we had only seen on the food network. What an experience at $29 an ounce! The rest of our dinners (filet mignon and prime rib) were delicious as were the appetizers and between course tidbits to freshen our palates and expand our tasteslIt was pricey but a memory I'll cherish.

review_1148.Review: We had an incredible meal at A5A. We tried many different cuts of meat (5 of us) and each one was delicious and cooked perfectly. The truffle fries and tempura lobster were fabulous starters. Our waiter was one of the best, if not, the best, we ever had. A fabulous last night in San Francisco for our family.

review_1149.Review: I've eaten almost everything on the menu and it's all deluctable!! I go once a month.

review_1150.Review: One of the best experience I had in a restaurant. The menu was an infusion of an Asian steakhouse offering a twist with Japanese and American food. Decor itself was nicely set and had a great transition from the doorway to the sitting area, had a very vibrant touch to it. Food was flavorful and exciting, the heirloom tomato salad was fantastic to start with since it was light and refreshing which got us ready for the prime rib and the boneless ribeye. Both were cooked to perfection and was very tender, we enjoyed our steaks with the truffle fries and sriracha aioli . A great combination for a complete meal! But what really caught us was the service, Meghan was a delight and was very knowledgable about the menu.

review_1151.Review: We went in on a fluke and it turned out to be one of the best accidental discoveries of 2013. The dishes are fantastic and service was great. Plan on taking my special lady there for a special occasion.

review_1152.Review: Third visit and still great. Must enjoy meat! Cooked perfect each time. Just saying, their Prime Rib was better then "House of Prime Ribs". And the prime ribs are very good there. Do the math. Definitely going back soon.

review_1153.Review: Lobster. Miso. Soup. The only three words you need to hear.

review_1154.Review: After my favorite restaurant Alexander's got rid of their chef, I haven't been back. I have been looking for a new place ever since. I came across 585 and was amazed!! The jasmine chicken was the BEST chicken I have had! I don't eat pork or beef, so finding a place that can make chicken interesting is difficult. Most places just don't focus on other meat options outside of beef or pork. But 585 has mastered chicken! The chicken was moist and the flavor was so delicious! I also loved their Lobster Tempura. Yum! Their truffle fries were the only thing I wasn't impressed with. The flavor was bland and the dipping sauce just tasted like mayo. I also wish they had more vegetable sides that didn't include bacon.

review_1155.Review: Loved it. Omg. Mac n cheese was fabulous. One of the best meas ever

review_1156.Review: Service was good, but slow. The restaurant wasn't full the Thursday I had lunch for two. In fact, no one was siting in the bar area and that indicated to me, at least, that it was a slow day. The waitstaff were friendly and knowledgeable, but it seemed to take forever for the food to arrive. The woman waiting on us apologized twice for the delays. The four small dishes were good, but not outstanding.

review_1157.Review: I took my husband here and it was both of our first times. We absolutely loved it. I personally don't like steak and am not much of a meat eater, but I love steak now! We both really enjoyed the food and dining experience. We will definitely come back.

review_1158.Review: Great steaks and service. Although there are many steak houses. Many I find are the place to be like Alexander's steak house or epic's; all which are great steaks but the price is twice the price. If money's not an issue then those are the place to go. If your looking for a good steak at a good price and great service; then 5A5 is the place for you.You can't go wrong with 5A5...

review_1159.Review: I am not sure what it is, the food was great but I am not sure I am all that keen on going back. The bento-box small plates is cool, although I could have used a bit more food even at lunch. For a steak place I thought the wine list was a little limited. A fun place to try out, the lobster tempura was really good, ambiance is modern, so we will see if I go back. I should add the bar is very nice, and ll of the folks working there were really great!

review_1160.Review: Food was good except the fish was not really hot when it came to the table. I enjoyed all the small plates and appetizers- They were really tasty. Overall, I was a really good dinning experience.The only weak link was that our waitress kept interrupting our conversations and was very over bearing on introducing the food when each dishes came. She meant well but completely unneccessary- need to be a little more considerate.So I will go back to the restaurant as long as I do not get the same waitress.

review_1161.Review: I was very eager to have a great eating experience at this restaurant, but I was disappointed. The first thing I noticed was the booth couch was so low, I could have eaten of the plate without much effort. And then it was noisy. Several times I couldn't hear our waiter.The "Bites" of tuna sounded really interesting but there wasn't as much "taste" as I had hoped. The truffle fries were very good, crispy and with a nice aioli dipping sauce. I ordered the boneless ribeye, my guest ordered the prime rib. Both came as ordered. The meat was very tender but both were poorly seasoned (in my opinion). After the initial hint of seasoning there was just the taste of meat - not bad but now the "taste sensation" I was expecting - for what it cost.

review_1162.Review: 5A5 is by far the best steakhouse restaurant I have ever been to. This was an amazing dining experience. WARNING: This also happens to be the most expensive Rib Eye steak I have ever had. My steak alone was $300.00 That's right...two zeros after the 3...! Our meal for a party of 4 was $1,950.00 including tip. And amazingly enough, the place was packed with a line waiting for reserved tables! Just an excellent restaurant! Food, service, wine, everything was excellent...!

review_1163.Review: Had a pretty enjoyable experience for Dinner the other night but there was a definite lag between courses. total dining time was way too long. Reservation was originally at 730 but we were running ahead of schedule and able to seat at 630. We did not leave until almost 1030. But our server Rolando did an excellent job with his wine selections. Might return for another special occasion.

review_1164.Review: My friend and I take each other out for birthday dinners. We both like a good steak twice per year. Ruth Chris', Alfred's, Boulevard(fillet), Alexander's etc. Fillet Mignon has been the usual choice. 5A5 tops them all for flavor and tenderness. However, I would not want to take, to the restaurant, a friend I hadn't seen in a while. The noise level at 7:00 on a Thursday night calls for nearly shouting to one another during the most excellent meal. This is not the place for a quiet, romantic special occasion dinner.

review_1165.Review: The food wasn't as great as I expected and I probably would not return. One thing I do remember was the truffle fries though! Those were good.

review_1166.Review: My girlfriend first time here and it was absolutely lovely. We both enjoyed the service there. It was her birthday and they treated her like a birthday queen. She loved it and I loved seeing the smile on her face as we both enjoyed dining there. This restaurant is on the top of her list. Thank you.

review_1167.Review: I had an enjoyable time at 5A5. I've been there three times and this last time was as good as previous visits. I'm a fan of the interior, spacious booths and great piano player in the bar area. Food was wonderful, though the restaurant is know for its wagyu steak, appetizers and sides are also delicious. We had mostly seafood and veggies with a couple of cocktails and had a great experience.

review_1168.Review: Not your old style steak restaurant. This is more of a modern feel with open floor plan and views to the kitchen from almost any seat. The food was fantastic and the service was exceptional. Ali did an amazing job and guided us through the dinner from start to finish. Again if you are looking for a romantic or semi private experience this is not the place but if you are ready for a great steak in an upbeat atmosphere then you should try it.

review_1169.Review: Based on a review in the Chron (thanks Michael B.), we went to an early dinner and it was fantastic. The service was impeccable, the ambiance was outstanding and the food was excellent, particularly the starters, small plates and dessert. With drinks, a bit pricey ($250 for three of us), but well worth the money. Definitely on the list of restaurants to visit again.

review_1170.Review: 5A5 is a great place for a special occasion dinner. The filet mignon was delicious, and so were the sides and dessert we had.

review_1171.Review: For a steak lounge the steak was really disappointing. I had the dry aged NY, which I had a hard time believing it was actual dry aged prime beef (not to be a snob but I've had my share of steaks at high end joints to know the difference). My wife had the waygu NY and it also was disappointing (and yes we've had our share of waygu in the past as well). They smother all of their steaks with one sauce or another, which should have been the first sign of the pending disappointment. If you have a high quality cut, you don't need to or want to mask the flavor of the beef. Enough said...The service was great and the ambience was decent. It was loud but we knew that before going.

review_1172.Review: Parking was easy. Definitely will return.Very consistent in service and professionalism.

review_1173.Review: Went for my wife's bday and had a great time. We had the ribeye to share and it was perfect. Although we ordered the condiments on the side and they came on it.Great desserts and appetizers as well - lobster tempura was incredible

review_1174.Review: Great Steak + Lounge = Steak Lounge. Very well prepared dishes and aged steak. My business guest was 40 min late but they were quite accommodating, as we drank great wine. Good somalier as well. Different vibe from the normal steak joint, ergo the lounge bit. Very fun place.

review_1175.Review: It was my first time at 5A5 Steak Lounge and didn't know what to think when I first walked in. But from the valet to the hostess to our server, it was an excellent customer experience. The food was FABULOUS...one of the best prime ribs I've ever had in my life! The environment was energetic and inviting and I really appreciated the wait staff checking on us and our progress while my good friend and I dined! Definitely will recommend to others for sure! Keep up the excellent work!

review_1176.Review: Had reservation for 7:15, even called and confirmed. Arrived at 7:10 , told it would be 20 minutes before they would seat us. We were going to the Football game , didn't have time to wait. Walked across the street at basils, got seated right away , had a great meal. Made the game on time. Thanks

review_1177.Review: Our service was impeccable, the atmosphere was vibrant, and the food was delectable. The server explained the menu in detail giving suggestions that would work for our gluten free needs. I would have preferred to sit in the stylish lower section of the restaurant with the cool white chairs and glowing table top lamps rather than the upper portion overlooking the stylish seating below; however, the service and food was top notch no matter where our table was located. I would definitely recommend this restaurant to anyone who is looking for a beautiful, delicious, melt-in-your-mouth steak accompanied by interesting sides and a great cocktail.

review_1178.Review: wagyu beff was the best steak i have ever had it melted in your mouth sides so so but the beef is out of this world

review_1179.Review: A5 refers to the top rating for Waygu beef, which was on the menu at $27 per ounce. The other 5 in the name refers to the five senses. Our waitress Megan, was excellent. My Cesar salad that was quite good, and my wife's oyster bite and a hamachi bite were served on spoons and were tasty.. We shared the "shrooms"-- a delightful medley of mushrooms that were delicious. The dry aged 22 oz. t-bone steak for me, and my wife had the 4 ounce New York. The meat is strictly ala carte. The New York was tiny. The filet side of my steak was tender; the sirloin side tough. The sauces made up for the lack of taste in the steak. If you go there, bite the bullet and try the Waygu. 2 glasses of wine and 2 whiskeys plus the food: $177 before tip.

review_1180.Review: Everything we had was terrific. The filet was cooked to perfection. Try the mac n cheese...the best flavors ever with a nice combo of cheeses. The staff was very on the ball. Our water was always filled. Dishes taken away soon after we finished. Waitress checked on us without pestering. An overall fantastic dinner.

review_1181.Review: We had a group of 6 celebrating a birthday. Service was truly awful! We couldn't get the attention of our server, it took us 15 min to get our drinks, half of our appetizers didn't show up until minutes before dinner, and our server's attitude was at best careless…Food was average at best. You pay $44 for a filet with the same quality as you can get at chain steak houses for less than $20. Way overpriced and tasteless food. Avoid this place at all cost...

review_1182.Review: My wife and I were very pleased with the overall service. Plan on visiting the Restaurant again

review_1183.Review: I came here with two other coworkers after work. We took advantage of their happy hour specials before we sat down for dinner. We were tempted to get the Wagyu steaks because they look so good, but too bad the price tag was a little too expensive for us. We ended up getting ribeye steaks and aged T-bone, everything was wonderful. I am only giving 3 star for service because I noticed the waiter was nicer to the couple sitting at the table next to us than to our table, what's up with that? And also they charged us for still water.... if we knew still water cost money we would've chose tap water.

review_1184.Review: I tried this place as it had great reviews and I love steak!Took my friend for her birthday.Service was excellent, food was delicious. Had the prime rib with mushrooms as a side.Very yummy indeed!We ordered dessert but they also brought out a plate with "happy birthday" written in chocolate with a small cake and candle in it. Very nice touch.

review_1185.Review: the food was quite good, but the "scene is the thing" - lots of group of young people. we paid $120. for a small steak, so come prepared to SPEND !!

review_1186.Review: Our party of 4 ordered the Japanese cut, ribeye, plus the prime rib. We were thoroughly please with the qualify of our food.

review_1187.Review: Without a doubt the Wagyu Rib Eye I had was exceptional!. Mi wife ordered the "regular" New York and she love it. We will definetly will come back on our next visit to San Francisco. The restaurant had a great detail for us on the occassion of our anniversary, service was top notch. Give it a try, you won't regret it.

review_1188.Review: We had a great night at 5A5 Steak Lounge, our server was excellent in explaining the menu and the atmosphere with the piano player was perfect. Couldn't have asked for more!

review_1189.Review: I started with a dry aged New York steak that was cooked perfectly along with sides of mushrooms and spinach all very good. The Manhattan from the bar was good but because of the small ice cubes they use it got watered down quickly. The dessert was a tobacco ice cream in Sazarac rye that was EXCELLENT! Very original.Service was very good and our waiter, Meghan, knew the menu and the different steaks well.Overall very good but the noise, expense and tables too close did detract from the experience a bit.

review_1190.Review: We heard about 5A5 from our friend who lives in the city, so we decided to try it out. We decided to look it up online and we liked what we saw (we were in the mood for steak), so we gave it a shot. We were very pleased with the steak lounge concept and it was complimented by spectacular service. The waitress was extremely knowledgeable about the menu and treated us as if we were the only people in the restaurant. The food was spectacular! Possibly the best meat we've ever had. It was a pricy joint but for the high quality of the meat and the fact that it is a steakhouse, it was well worth it's value. Next time we come to the city we will definitely stop by 5A5. Two thumbs up!

review_1191.Review: Great service. Nice setting. Delicious food. It's expensive, as any SF steakhouse would be, but a good choice for a special occasion (let them know ahead of time if it's a birthday and they'll put a candle in a dessert for your party).

review_1192.Review: 5A5 seems to become a fusion restaurant rather than a steakhouse. The meat selection was great however the chef is awful. We did not expect a nice piece of aged NY steak needs to re-cook. When a steak is sent back for undercook, I would expect a new piece done right. Re-cooking it and serve it again totally ruin the texture. The Japanese waygu beef with the chunk of cold butter was so big that ruin the temperature - the medium-rare piece was so cold like rare. Service is slow, waited 25 minutes before the bread basket was served. Order the Hamachi bite and it did not show till after the second appetizer. This is not what you expected from a steakhouse. They tried to make it up toward the end of dinner, unfortunately it was too late.

review_1193.Review: 5A5 advertised:StylishModernVibrantIt did deliver those things.However, we also experienced:A wine list with the option of very pricey wines or unfamiliar pricey winesExcessive noiseExtremely expensive steaksGristle in our meat (maybe to encourage ordering the exorbitant priced Wagyu)Pretentious atmosphere

review_1194.Review: We came here for a business dinner and reserved the room in the back. The food was amazing and the service was impeccable. Would definitely come back!

review_1195.Review: This is a high end steak house. Food is VISUALLY well done and tastefull. Serving staff was outstanding. Price of the food was also high, which makes this restaurant more suited for special occasions.

review_1196.Review: This restaurant had been highly recommended by one of my colleague. Our overall dinning experience was great. First we had a few drinks at the bar along with an appetizer. Once we were at our table we were served water and bread, and our order was taken promptly by our waiter. Over the course of our dinner, I've noticed that the floor manger was greeting the table around us but never came to ours. He greeted them once they were seated, and again to pour them water and wine. Not even once did he say hi or looked in our direction. He then finally came to our table to greet us goodbye. Then I thought to myself, maybe the reason why he didn't stop by our table is because we didn't order a bottle of wine or a fancy glass of water. Go figure!!!

review_1197.Review: We had friends from out of town join us at 5A5 Steak who are foodies, and have also raved about their wonderful trip to Japan a few years back. They admittedly proclaimed that the Wagyu was as close as what they remember having in Japan. They were thoroughly impressed. As always, food is solid and consistent, and service is always very good. A good place to have dinner with friends....and even if we haven't been to Japan yet, nice to know the quality of the Wagyu at 5A5 comes very close...

review_1198.Review: We had great food but it just took too long to get our food. We ordered some sushi, salads and steak. It took almost 2.5 hours to get the food out. Other than that, the place is awesome.

review_1199.Review: We were recommended here from some local friends for our party of 6 get together. Nice spot, good location. We arrived early to meet pre-dinner for cocktails. The lobby lounge/bar area was very nice - decor I loved, except for being just a bit too dark (lighting). Nice wine and specialty cocktails. Our meals were varied - so some nice variety of choices. We were very pleased with our Amouse Bouche treats, compliments of the chef. Be careful of the level of spicey-ness (Tako salad). Sides, al la carte, are great for sharing (as they recommeWait staff was pleasant - available when you wanted/needed them, but not overbearing. A very nice evening...

review_1200.Review: Many reviewers have commented about how good the food is and I can only agree with the positive reviews. However, I need to make a special comment about how professional the waitstaff are, from folks bringing bread and water, to the server to the maitre 'd. In many restaurants today, the waitstaff are either almost non-existent, or too "in your face." Here, they wade sure to take care of you while allowing you to fully enjoy your dining companions and the excellent food at your own pace. Outstanding service!

review_1201.Review: Great food, but take too long to serve and in between courses we waited more than 30mins. It was a Thursdays too.

review_1202.Review: Food was very good. The staff were very attentive. The noise level made anything like a normal conversation impossible. I would recommend them, but just know it was very noisy. I thought the price four two people was reasonable, considering where we were, the quality of the food and they did not charge us corkage. I had prime rib and my guest had a filet. We agreed they were the best we'd had in quite some time. The lobster tempura was unique and delicious. The sides were both very good.

review_1203.Review: We had to dinner at 5A5 lounge to celbrate our last night in San Francisco. This is a very vibrant spot with a younger crowd. Thee setting is somewhat unique and is a combination bar/ restaurant. The choice of steaks is quite broad and our server Meghan was most helpful in helping us make our choices. The prices are expensive but the experience made our last night in San Francisco memorable

review_1204.Review: Waku newyork stake was awesome and it worths high price.Service was also great to be comfortable.

review_1205.Review: Great service and great food. Only complain was tables too close for private conversation.

review_1206.Review: The food was superb and the service was exceptional. We thoroughly enjoyed dining here. It was our anniversary and the staff went out of their way to make it special.

review_1207.Review: We had Wagyu steak selections that were superb and VERY rich because of the high fat content.Heavily marbled fat in the meat isn't greasy, just flavorful and filling.Wagyu is beef to try once--maybe more often--and a costly treat you KNOW you deserve occasionally, right?Most people might be better off choosing a New York Steak or fillet.I haven't tried more traditional steaks here, so cannot comment.Service and ambience good; I'd certainly return.

review_1208.Review: Loved it at this restaurant ...food was outstanding and definitely would go back again!

review_1209.Review: Very good food, very passionate, knowledgable staff, live tasteful pianist, definitely not your average dining room with very creative seating and sectioning. Manager was extremely professional and friendly. A great dining experience.

review_1210.Review: I have been here twice. I have dined in many, many high end restaurants. There is nothing that compares. I will definitely go back everytime I am in SFO!

review_1211.Review: Great place to spend our last night in San Francisco! Especially enjoyed the lobster tempura and crossbred Wagyu beef

review_1212.Review: The food and service was great! However, noise level was louder than expected and parking was hard to find. I would definitely go back to try other dishes, especially some of the appetizers.

review_1213.Review: Great service, wonderful steaks, and nic atmosphere. It was our 25 th anniversary and we celebrated here and what a great choice. My only suggestion is create a private booth or two for couples.Otherwise home runs on all other aspects.

review_1214.Review: Pricey but worth every penny especially for an occasion. Only one of us had a steak - the others had chicken, lamb and fish. All excellent for a steak house. Had numerous sides and starters - all equally wonderful. No room for dessert but none really jumped out as a "must have". Brought our own wine and corkage was less than most places. Service was top notch.

review_1215.Review: Very, very noisy. The music was too loud; couldn't communicate with the person on the other side of the table without repeating sentences at least three times. The food was great, however, and the service was top notch.

review_1216.Review: NO matter who the guests are and what they came in to enjoy... waiters should be timely and not require multiple requests for little things

review_1217.Review: If you want great steak that melts in your mouth, this is the place! Also a good atmosphere to wine & dine that special someone or top customer. Awesome wine list too.

review_1218.Review: The food was fabulous, except for their signature lobster tempura was a bit on the greasy side. Service was very good, but like others said, the noise level is very very loud, and hard to hear the waiter when he did an overview of the menu. Desserts were fine, definitely go for wagyu if you can afford it. Its terrific.

review_1219.Review: We went to 5A5 steak house on a Sunday night. The food and service were sub-par by miles from a top notch steak house standard. Here are what we ordered: French onion soup - fair. Lobster Miso Soup - too salty. Wagu beef sashimi - fair, not much taste. Both dry-aged NY strip and dry aged t bone were super salty with the sauce all over the steak. The sauces were totally over powering the meat. Creamy spinach and mushroom as side dishes were also fair. Overall, nothing positive from the food that stood out for us, especially for a well known steak house. The service was not genuine at all. The waiter came to ask us how we are doing because he felt he has to ask. Won't go back there for steaks!

review_1220.Review: I was in San Francisco for the America's Cup races and visited 5A5 for dinner on my last night in town before heading home. Located a few blocks from the Embracadero, this is a true star in the San Francisco dining scene. Billed as a "steak lounge", it has a slight Vegas feel to it in terms of decor and style. The cocktail menu was interesting and Alana behind the bar was up to the challenge when asked to come up with something not on the menu. Table service was classy, prompt, and quietly professional; the wait staff complemented the meal rather than being a distraction. The meal was, without a doubt, one of the most enjoyable in recent memory anywhere I've traveled. From the hamachi "bite" to start the meal to the prime rib, awesome.

review_1221.Review: The food and service was absolutely fantastic. Just one downside, the live music and bar noise was a little too loud that it was difficult to hear my dinner companions.

review_1222.Review: They have the best steak selection I think I have ever seen - but at very high prices for the high end (A5 - hence the name) .... approx $30 per ounce .... yes that's not a mistake. Translates to $420 for a 16 ounce steak.Wine list was superb.Service excellent and very helpful in learning about their food

review_1223.Review: 5A5 is a great special-occasion restaurant; it's a little pricey for everyday dining, but a nice place to celebrate something or impress a date. Great variety on the menu make this a step up from your standard steakhouse (although if you order chicken or the veggie plate, you might be wasting your money here), and the service is attentive without being unctuous. Terrific filet mignon and the usual interesting assortment of sides, all a la carte, with a large wine list and creative desserts. Best of all, since we'd included the info that it was our anniversary, they brought us a lovely plate with a beautiful message and a little fig cake -- so sweet!

review_1224.Review: Great place to go to get your prime steak fix. The A5 wagyu beef literally does melt in your mouth. The sides are fabulous- especially the truffle mac and cheese with lobster accompaniment, and creamed spinach (old school with modern twist)...Salads are old school steak restaurant salads with a "unique twist" - different enough to differentiate 5A5 from the usual steak restaurants...Great experience.

review_1225.Review: Best Steak and Service in San Francisco. Chef Allen Chen is a talent, and veteran General Manager Kevin Lee has the place in tip top shape.

review_1226.Review: Glamorous trendy steak house. Great food and service.

review_1227.Review: We were really hesitant about dining here when the dining area was totally empty and so pricy.We heard from open table that this was a diners choice but grim the empty area and pricy steaks were were hesitant.They have us all kinds of additional tastes if chef delights that made the experience enjoyable. The bread had bacon in it andan impressive selection of meat. The server was excellent and the rear of the staff was also professional and created and enjoyable experience. If you want an exciting busy feel, don't go here!

review_1228.Review: The food and service were wonderful. 5A5 was as good on this visit as I has been previously.

review_1229.Review: One of us hated it, one of us liked it, and the third felt like a chump for suggesting it. No one LOVED it. Very, very, very loud and service was late to start and delinquent throughout the meal. For this price range, we all prefer an exceptional experience and it was, overall, lacking. Food was moderate in portion and flavor.

review_1230.Review: Bring your appetite and get ready to have your taste buds explode. Just make sure the wallet is full, this kind of food comes at a high price.

review_1231.Review: My husband & I came here for our anniversary which i noted on opentable. Right off the bat our server acknowledged that it was a special occasion for us. She was attentive but not overbearing. However, 1 of the bus person was very fast to clean up our empty plates, which would be a good thing normally, but our server gave us a special desert that said happy anniversary on it & right when we took the last bite, he swept in & took the plate away. I was hoping to admire it for a bit longer but oh well. Dinner was delicious, our server was amazing. On our way out, the hostess wished us a happy anniversary which was amazing, with all the people that were there that night, she actually remembered that it was us celebrating our anniversary.

review_1232.Review: The waiter was very helpful and informative.

review_1233.Review: If you can splurge on the expensive Wagyu steaks go for it! We had the regular prime rib and ribeye steak and they were just as great! My prime rib was so tender. it was the best I've had in a long while. Service here is very attentive. The bar makes great martinis! Save room for the unusual desserts.

review_1234.Review: Great food, great service, and great ambiance. The Wagyu was the best we've ever had, and each dish was magnificently prepared. I highly recommend 5a5 to anyone who loves steak.

review_1235.Review: Great atmosphere. Beautiful downtown San Francisco. Some of the best steak would have ever had. I highly recommend trying this establishment. We were very impressed with the food service and atmosphere.

review_1236.Review: Best steak I’ve ever had. Absolutely the best service I’ve ever experienced!

review_1237.Review: 5A5 had very, very good food and very attentive, knowledgable servers. The real problem with the place was what initially attracted me to it - the decor. The restaurant's decor could some some updating and refreshing, including adding some noise seoftening elements. Loud noise bounced off the walls in the restaurant so much that my date and I wanted to leave as soon as possible (no dessert, no extra drink = revune lost for the business). Oh - and the seating was uncomfortable.

review_1238.Review: This was my second time dining here. The first was a work dinner, this was a birthday dinner for my spouse.I wanted a place with a great lounge area and bar - this restaurant delivers on this.The food was fantastic. A great slightly Asian-influenced take on a stakehouse. Unique twists on dishes, but not to go to far as to be inaccessible to more traditional palates. The service in general (bartenders, hostess, wait staff) was very good, but our waitress was just good, not great. She never shared the specials (heard that from another waiter a table over an hour into our dinner), for example.The place is a bit noisy and the spacing is generous between seats, so it does allow for a louder environment, but not enough to stay away.

review_1239.Review: It was the perfect blend for my graduation night dinner with my parents.Memorable moments:1. excellent service: the waiter was friendly & knowledgable & took the time to answer ALL our questions2. learning about the Japanese meat was quite fun & great visual experience having the samples in front of you3. the atmosphere: lighted ceiling and projected burning fireplace was a nice touch

review_1240.Review: This was our first time to 5A5 and definitely won't be the last. We came to celebrate my boyfriend Tyler's birthday. We arrived 15 minutes late and the host was still more than accommodating. We got a nice romantic seat for two and had a wonderful server! We ordered a reasonable priced Zinfandel and it went wonderful with our steaks! I got the 6oz filet and my boyfriend got the 22oz tbone! Both were phenomenal! I recommend if you can eat more than I do (I eat like a bird) then get the 10z, otherwise the 6 is a good size.The sides were great as well, we got macaroni and cheese and the Swiss chard. I would recommend those to anyone! In the end, they gave Tyler a free dessert and it tasted great! It was unnecessary but greatly appreciated!

review_1241.Review: Appetizers and Main courses were outstanding! The chef offered a few sample bites of various items prior to our meal and they were excellent. We had the smoked salmon pastrami which literally melted in your mouth. We both had filets for dinner - again - melt in your mouth tender and perfectly cooked - the beef and the sauce were a perfect pair. Sides were excellent as well: recommend the creamed spinach and truffled mac-n-cheese. The marbled potatoes were good, but a bit oily. Skip dessert - they were very small and were not very sweet - this is the one area where they could improve.

review_1242.Review: Mostly I can find things to eat at a steak Resturant but this was very limited.The Appetizers were good & boyfriend enjoyed his steak. The premium & priced gin cocktails were servedat first with club soda instead of tonic. Then when we did Get the tonic it was from the fountain &taste like flat fountain syrup. Splashed into the $14 shots of Orley & 209 gourmet gin.

review_1243.Review: I had the Rib-Eye and it was by far the best I have ever had.

review_1244.Review: My husband and I saw the great reviews of this restaurant on open table and decided to try it out for my husband's birthday. Everything was beyond our expectations - service, food quality, plating of food, etc. 5A5 really has it down and knows how to treat customers very well. I'd highly recommend coming here - you won't be disappointed.

review_1245.Review: Loved the steak and service was awesome

review_1246.Review: I wanted a neighbor gem, off the beaten path, and a place where tourist hardly go, but where San Franciscans can’t get enough of, and that place would be 5A5. The bar and lounge area was very hip and upbeat, but catered to a more sophisticated crowd, which enthused me even more. A great Asian flare in an American style steakhouse. Yakimono shrimp, tuna tataki, five-spice cold beef salad, heirloom tomato salad, and A5 Wagyu ribeye 4 ounce A.Q. Beautiful.

review_1247.Review: I took a client here and I was really impressed. Great services, outstanding food, but pretty pricey.

review_1248.Review: Each bite is terrific - attention to detail in the food prep, food design, the presentation, and the service. This was our third visit and in all three events they did not mis-step once! A really fun restaurant with create food. This is why we dine out.

review_1249.Review: This restaurant was beyond spectacular. Every single bite was a surprise and delicious. Our server Megan was excellent. I don't live in San Francisco but would come back again and again if I did.

review_1250.Review: Undoubtedly one of the best steak experiences yet, and a whole new level of enjoyment!I will be back!!!

review_1251.Review: Steak is fantastic. The Mac & Cheese is phenomenal - a must try because of the gruyere blend. Service from entire staff was excellent. 5A5 is a must dine experience.

review_1252.Review: Every thing was Great I really enjoyed the food, drinks and our Server Layla was the Best

review_1253.Review: I absolutely loved the starters, 'bites', and the main course of steak. It was truly phenomenal food, and the wine paired perfectly. The whole experience, including service and ambiance, was perfect for the date I was on.

review_1254.Review: EXCELLENT FOOD AT GREAT VALUE. ATTENTIVE SERVICES AND COMFORTABLE ATMOSPHERE.

review_1255.Review: Great resto for entertaining clients, good balance of food wine and ambience

review_1256.Review: One of the few places where one can get truly outstanding prime rib. Moist, tender and delicious. Our server, Lyn, was a delight. Made us feel like we were her special guests. She is very attentive, but not the least intrusive. I intend to become a regular.

review_1257.Review: Dinner was superbly delicious and unforgettable. We will be back for the amazing meat and everything else. You are not going to be disappointed!

review_1258.Review: Very beautiful restaurant, great atmosphere, food prepared exquisitely

review_1259.Review: Went here for my anniversary and it was great. Service was very attentive and the A5 is not like any other steak I've ever had. I would recommend the A5 ribeye. Also had the truffle fries and the seabass. My wife really liked the seabass which was moist and very flavorful.

review_1260.Review: 5A5 was a more interesting twist on the steakhouse than the typical, predictable steakhouse with sides kind of menu and ambiance. It was a cool, retro place, small in scale. Great ambiance and very romantic. My companion and I had a large "booth" to ourselves so we were able to sit next to each other and enjoy our perfect dinner and great wine. Just the right amount of food. Not too skimpy but not the steakhouse food coma effect afterwards either. We walked away feeling like we had an amazing dining experience, unique in the world, rather than just had another good steak. Would highly recommend from two people who have dined the world over and are very picky.

review_1261.Review: Outstanding service - lives up to the buzz.Some of the starters are rather crude for this class of restaurant.Did I mention how great the service is?

review_1262.Review: I had the tbone and my lady had the filet mignon. Food was delicious. Everything from the starters, drinks and the entree. Hands down great food.

review_1263.Review: Although the food was very tasty, I was most impressed by how friendly and accomodating the staff was.

review_1264.Review: The wait help was overwhelming. We had at least 4 staff members at our table. Our actual waiter - the one that took our order - let me wait for at least 8 minutes before he came over to see if I wanted water or anything else to drink (my dinner companion was late so I was sitting by myself). He also tried to be TOO nice. Absent that, dinner was good. I had the sliders and the beet salad and that was more than enough food - we shared a mac and cheese order. My companion did have dessert. Not sure I would go back on my own dime - but it's a great place to treat an important client.

review_1265.Review: Dishes:Wagyu: This beef melts in your mouth like butter so it's really good for a special occasion: 5/5Filet mignon is good but I have had something with a bit more flavor in the beef before: 4/5Mac and cheese is good but it is not the perfect mac n cheese. It is very good: 4/5The service:Truly wonderful. I hesitated to take my boyfriend to Alexander's for his birthday despite the great steak reviews because some people had really bad experiences with snooty service. At 5A5, the waiters were really pleasing: they don't judge you for how much or what you order, they helpfully show you the 4 cuts of Wagyu meat, and the chef may surprise you with extra amazing dishes.

review_1266.Review: Really don't need to say much other than that the food is so beautiful and the service is prompt, friendly and extremely efficient. Definitely give this place a try!

review_1267.Review: the host and hostess were fantastic...very helpful...they coordinated sending a bottle of champagne to a group of friends dining next door...

review_1268.Review: Be prepared to spend more for the Wagyu; you can get regular steak and prime-rib anywhere. Their Wagyu was amazing, and so were the appetizers. The Hamachi bite was like a party in your mouth. The service was exceptional, and the staff, especially Rachel & Lexi helped make our anniversary feel even more special.

review_1269.Review: Lovely culinary experience. The salmon pastrami appetizer is a must have. The Sunday night 50% off on 750ml bottles of wine added value to a pricey meal (particularly if you have Wagyu).

review_1270.Review: Great service and food! Sommelier was fantastic with bottle service as it was my daughter's 21st. They took very good care of us and made her evening special...complete with a birthday treat. It was my first visit to this restaurant so I'm very happy my experience! I have definitely recommended this place for special occasion or a night out.

review_1271.Review: Unfortunately I cannot give a good review at this point. The only reason for that is that I made an Open Table Reservation for 5A5 because you were offering 1000 pts for the reservation. To date I have not received these points, despite my making 2 phone calls to the restaurant. I did receive a call back telling me to take the issue to Open Table. I really don't think that it's my responsibility to resolve this issue. I'm still waiting for the restaurant for call me back with a resolution.

review_1272.Review: The steaks were perfect, the service was very gentle (we were there during our honeymoon). They offered us a dessert. When we come again to san francisco, we will visit again 5a5 steakhouse.

review_1273.Review: Absolutely wonderful steak house. We went for Father's Day with our two young kids and the staff was very accommodating. The steaks were cooked perfectly. The side orders are exceptionally flavorful and complementary to the steaks. We ordered the mac and cheese, potatoes and green beans, each a masterpiece on their own. I highly recommend 5A5 especially for special occasions.

review_1274.Review: It is a very good place for a steak. It is a little pricy, though, particularly if you want to try those Japanese steaks (which are charged by the ounce). Otherwise, we had regular steaks and they were very good.

review_1275.Review: we're seated almost 1.5 hours after our reservation, in the meanwhile none of the waitress came by to take drink orders until we asked thru management, although we're compensated by free drinks, but it was not a pleasant dining experience, food was decent, but the wait and the lack of attention ruined everything else,

review_1276.Review: My girlfriend and I came here for my birthday and got a ribeye steak and truffle fries. The fries were delicious, especially with the dipping sauce, but the steak seasoning and sauces were strange. It was a little sweet...yet sour, and overpowered the taste of the steak. A let-down.The small "palate cleansers" and free desserts were strange as well, often being too sweet or not sweet enough. Overall, the food was a tad disappointing, but the atmosphere and vibe of the restaurant was energetic and fun. 3/5.

review_1277.Review: If you are craving red meat, this is the place to go. They have a huge list of variety of great cuts and an assortment of Japanese Wagyu beef and Australian Wagyu which makes this place special.My wife and I ordered the Australian Wagyu filet mignon and New York cut. Both were cooked to perfection, flavorful, and juicy without fail. This is what we came in for! The service was spectacular, the ambiance was great with a pianist in the background, and the food knocked it out of the ballpark.Overall it was a fantastic place and would recommend to anyone who is celebrating a special occasion, romantic night out or for some who are just craving a great piece of steak.

review_1278.Review: My friends just moved here from London and I knew they really liked steak. For three we got seated in the back where the tables can be extended. The snooty hostess only open one side of the table. It wasn't like the place was packed. A waiter came later to extend the other side of the table. We ended up getting the Dine about Town meals. The clam chowder was over salted and my steak was cooked unevenly, however, it was a large portion. My friend did return her medium rare steak which came out medium. Our waitress was extremely accommodating and very concern about our degree of happiness. My other friend tried the wine pairing which he enjoyed quite a bit. Overall, I wasn't that impressed with the food.

review_1279.Review: The menu looks so good! When you actually eat the food it Rey underwhelming. I feel like I can cook better at home and that shouldn't be the case at this price point. The interior was cool and reminded us how great the old Frisson was, but this new place is lacking. While it isn't awful, the food and service demand to be better given what we are expected to pay. Sorry guys.

review_1280.Review: Everything was great - food, wine, service, atmosphere. Love the Happy hour at the lounge as well. Excellent!

review_1281.Review: We had an early dinner on Sunday, the restaurant was quiet, the food was delicious and the service excellent.

review_1282.Review: My boyfriend and I went to 5A5 for the first time because we also wanted to try Dine About Town. We had the caesar salad as a starter, which was good, but probably had a little too much dressing on it. For our entree, we both chose the rib eye and that was fantastic! The meat was so juicy and tender and cooked to perfection. The mustard seeds on top were a great add as well. Lastly, the dessert was a trio of fondant, butterscotch tapioca (best I've ever had), and a chocolate passion fruit mousse. Overall, the experience was outstanding - the ambiance, the food, and the service. I would highly recommend 5A5 to family and friends.

review_1283.Review: The food is top notch, the service is incredible and each bit of food and sip of wine is better than the last.We went for to 5A5 for Dine About Town and could not believe how exquisite the menu was. We had the wine pairing with the DAT and it was worth every penny. The pinot grigio was incredibly crisp and refreshing paired with our bacon clam chowder soup. The red blend paired with our NY steak was also mouth watering. The NY steak was beautifully marbled and topped with carmelized onions and a bacon demi glaze. For dessert we had a muscat paired with a dessert trio of molten brown, tapioca and chocolate moouse that was amazing.The service and our server Leila was amazing. She explained each pairing in detail before serving.

review_1284.Review: We did the Dine About Town and got there a bit early. Really enjoyed the bar and lounge and piano playing. Happy Hour prices and great appetizers and drinks in the lounge. We enjoyed the style and the friendliness of the lounge staff. Next time we'll probably just do the lounge and bar. Did Dine About Town menu and the Clam Chowder was outstanding buy my wife's Cod and my steak were really not to our liking. Steak had a lot of fat and I ordered medium but it came very rare. Waitress was less than friendly- not unfriendly - but kind of "distant". Had to pay for a side, marbled potatoes, even on the DAT menu. Marbled potatoes were like potatoe skins really but whole potatoes. Desert Trio was kind of "iffy" as well. Lounge next time.

review_1285.Review: Exept that the steak was average...i was expecting better from a steakhouse listed as number 1 on the list.

review_1286.Review: We went for Dine About Town. The meal was very disappointing. We had steak which came with NO side dish. It cost $10 - $12 for each side added. It was NOT a good value. Wine and cocktail list was poor. They could not make a Bloody Mary. We have participated in Dine About Town every year since it started and the last two years have been very disappointing. Participating restaurants have offered smaller portions and less desirable entrees and if this is the trend I think the program should be either discontinued or participating restaurants need to improve what they are offering. Some seem reluctant to offer the Dine About Town menu and they need to use this promotion to create new loyal customers and not drive them away!!

review_1287.Review: I went for Dine About Town. It was good, but the steak could have been warmer. The plate was hot, but the steak was definitely not as hot as the plate.
