The steak was solid, but I have had better steaks. My friend ordered the fish and it was delicious! I think the fish was better than the steak.

review_1288.Review: The Truffle Fries are amazing. Their drinks are average. The service is decent.I had the Boneless Ribeye medium rare on the rare side, which came out deliciously. However, I felt like the sauces that they added on top did not complement the steak itself. The steak on its own was delicious enough on its own to be honest.Also, the lighting was very dim and "romantic" but it was too dim.

review_1289.Review: Best steak restaurant in San Francisco hands down. We will be back on our next visit to the Bay area.

review_1290.Review: If you are looking for a great meal with quality cuts of beef and great service...look no further. One of the best prime rib dinners we've had...melt in your mouth good!

review_1291.Review: We came here as a group of 7 girls and we had a fantastic time. The food was a bit on the pricey side but the service was phenomenal. Our waitress would stop by every now and then to check up on us. She made sure we knew the most popular items and the must-try's. During the end of our dinner, the waitress provided one of my girlfriends and I a congratulations short cake for our graduation! Very generous indeed! We would most definitely return but it will be for another special occasion. I feel that the type of atmosphere is made for special events.

review_1292.Review: My friend recommended this place and so I decided to try it. Right when I walked in I was satisfied already by the surroundings, very friendly and the host was wonderful. The food was OUTSTANDING! Good customer service and as a waitress myself I know what I look for and 5A5 has it.

review_1293.Review: excellant steakhouse; one of the best in SF. Great drinks, wine, apps, etc.my opinion forget house of prime rib, ruth crhirs steak house, etc and go here. it is pricey but so are the o thers snd the food is soooooooooooo much better here

review_1294.Review: We were on an evening layover and came across 5A5 on Open Table and decided to taxi in from the Airport hotel we were staying at to celebrate my birthday. While our reservation was for 5:30, our early arrival was accommodated without issue and welcomed. The evening started with a wondeful wine selection, followed by incredible food selections. We had the steak and with was top notch. Finished off with a wonderful desert for my birthday. Lynnette was an absolute treat to have as our server. We actually ordered a cheese plate to take back with us to our hotel, where we broke that at out for a nitecap at the bar....what a find. Thank you 5A5 for our evening.

review_1295.Review: This restaurant has existed for three years without my having discovered until this past week. What a gem! The food was delicious, expertly prepared, and the service was very attentive and friendly without being overbearing. What more can you ask? I'll definitely be eating at 5A5 again.

review_1296.Review: Second time here.... came with a friend about a year or more ago. I remembered the side dishes.. not the entree. In fact, it was almost the same again. The service was impeccable and the appetizer (scallops) and the side (creamy spinach). The prime rib was average.. but I may be losing my affection for Prime Rib.

review_1297.Review: Food alway good; great for celebrations and service is always attentive and good. Small selection on the menu but steaks are excellent. Foods pricey but worth the price.

review_1298.Review: Food was very good but a bit expensive. Service was excellent. We found the a/c a bit too cold. All in all enjoyed ourselves.

review_1299.Review: The restaurant description is a "stylish take" on the on the steakhouse. It's a modern, contemporary setting and a cool place to take a date. We found the wait staff was attentive without being intrusive or hovering. I will say that upon leaving the hostess went far above and beyond to get us a cab on a difficult Friday night - running down the street and standing out in the cold to hail us a ride.The food was good but not notable. The romaine salad, their take on a Caesar, was bland with the lettuce luke warm. We had the boneless ribeye and a bone in NY, both medium. The steaks were prepared as requested - slightly red in the center but were unremarkably seasoned and very average tasting.In sum, cool décor but an average meal.

review_1300.Review: I always go to 5A5 when I come to SF. Food is delicious, Wagu is always a great treat.

review_1301.Review: I highly recommend the Prime Roast, super delicious and succulent!

review_1302.Review: Outstanding service - They saved a prime rib on advance request for a late Mother's Day dinner (long past after the prime rib ran out) and it was served as requested - medium rare. Great meal and outstanding service.

review_1303.Review: I cannot speak highly enough of 5A5! My boyfriend and I were celebrating our anniversary and we requested private seating or a private booth. The request was met perfectly and set the tone for the evening. Our waitress, Leila, was knowledgable, attentive, and incredibly warm during the entire evening. We were given two or three plates, compliments of the chef, and the food was absolutely incredibly. We both got the filets and they were cooked perfectly, as were our other courses. The music in the background provided a wonderful setting without being overwhelming. I would recommend this restaurant without hesitation and will definitely be returning!

review_1304.Review: This was the first time trying Wagyu beef, it is amazing and very well prepared.

review_1305.Review: You're not going to eat here every week, but it is a great experience and you simply must enjoy the A5 Wagyu. Unique and delicious!

review_1306.Review: The food and service were excellent.

review_1307.Review: I would recommend this restaurant to others

review_1308.Review: An excellent experience. Scallops were velvety smooth and extremely tasty. Crab soup was good and interesting. Prime rib was cooked just right and very tender and tasty. Service was friendly, very attentive without being overbearing or annoying. We'll be back again when we travel to SF.

review_1309.Review: Elegant, hip and romantic restaurant with excellent food, drinks and service.

review_1310.Review: I've had better food and steaks for the price. No different than Ruth's Chris. I would add that the staff was really friendly.

review_1312.Review: We ordered a couple of side dish's and one was wrong and one of the couples we were with did not receive their salad.

review_1313.Review: Brought a special friend here for dinner for the first time and they enjoyed it. We had a good time and experience. Love the food especially the shooters and prime rib.

review_1314.Review: Amazing bone-in filet, unique and tasty appetizers with surprisingly decent portion sizes. Excellent, attentive service. Will definitely come back.

review_1315.Review: Wow! The food and service were amazing! The seating arrangement was a little odd.

review_1316.Review: their staff is always very courteous. Very attentive. Food no matter what you order has the best flavors done to perfection

review_1317.Review: This was my first time to 5A5. I'd made a reservation for 8, but had a couple of extras decide they wanted to come. I called and they easily accommodated moving my group up to 10 by pushing my reservation back 15 minutes. When we arrived, we actually ended up with 11 plus a baby! The staff didn't blink. They were very accommodating.I was surprised by the live pianist in the bar area and really enjoyed that while we waited for our whole party to gather.The waiter was spot on and easy going with a group so large. The food was good. A little pricey for a slightly above average meal. But, it was fun that it was well worth it!They even brought out a few extras for the table to nibble on. Plus they brought bday treats with candles!

review_1318.Review: Great service, great food, just a fun night for my group of friends

review_1319.Review: I wasn't sure how to "score" this place, so it's best to read this instead of focusing on the actual scores. The menu did not have enough options for me in terms of the non-entrees. The food was very good but our experience was definitely soured by the CONSTANT interruptions from the wait staff. It was over the top. Too much attention. Great restaurants know how to service you without making you feel like they are on top of you every 5 minutes. Nuff said.I did find the bartender to be super friendly and warm. And as I said, the actual food was very good. Lobster appetizer is amazing and the meats are excellent. Will go back again but I will warn the waiter in advance to give us some space.

review_1320.Review: Came on a Sunday, so probably much more quiet than how it is normally. Steak was excellent and very filling. Very tasty appetizers too. Took my mom here while she was visiting. I would pass on the wagyu beef, though. Far too rich.

review_1321.Review: San Fran has no shortage of good restaurants. We went here based on the hotel concierge recommendation "with a vibrant ambiance". Glad we did. Our server was excellent - friendly, knowledgeable and attentive. The manager even came by a few times to greet us. I had the wagyu sashimi, kona kampachi cerviche. The table also had steak and tataki duo for mains, along with truffle fries, swiss chard and muushroom as sides. All were excellent - definitely beyond my expectations.

review_1322.Review: We took our son and friends to celebrate his 18th birthday. It's definitely an upscale restaurant and a great experience. The ambiance is understated elegance and contemporary with a great live piano as background music. The food is very, very good with an Asian touch and the service is excellent. They did a superb job of accommodating a special food need for one member of the party and in general, the service was exceptionally attentive without being intrusive. The quality of the steak was excellent and the a great choice for meat lovers who are looking for a contemporary take on a steakhouse.

review_1323.Review: Boneless ribeye was thin and overcooked (well done). Beef flavor was masked by strong sauce. Better than Sizzler, but not as good as a high-quality steak cooked at home.

review_1324.Review: Quickie on this one:1. the steak was really good2. some of the sides were as amateurish as a truck stop diner3. the lobster bites tasted like dried out lobster jerky-literally. Whoever prepared this has no business working in a restaurant of any significance.4. the cocktail list is equally terrible and the drink I had with the cayenne pepper is something that was an interesting concoction in the early 2000's.5. interior looks really worn unless the lights are way down low6. sloppy drink serviceTerrible experience and meal for the price

review_1325.Review: While we had a good time here at 5A5, I was a bit disappointed with the level of noise in the restaurant. It was very loud.So much so that at a table of 4 we had to scream to hear each other. Not the best combo for a nice dinner. The food was good, but not at the level I was expecting from and ex-Alexander's chef. I've been to Alexander's in Cupertino (many, many times) and while this was great, it was not on their level. I had to ask three to have our water filled up, the noise was out of control, especially with a large group of guys (around 12) yelling and screaming throughout dinner like it was their frat party reunion. Perhaps this was not the fault of the restaurant booking such a party and more on the patrons' behavior.

review_1326.Review: 5A5 is okay. I wouldn't avoid it if someone suggests going back but it won't be high on my list to suggest. The menu has good options, execution is good but not great in terms of flavor. I'm a big fan of salt, but most of our dishes had too much even for me. Perhaps the Wague steaks are fantastic but at roughly $200 for the smallest serving I'm unlikely to be trying them unless you are buying. The place was cold when we arrived (early dinner, 7 or so) and the A/C was blowing so hard it seemed like the doors were wide open.... had to wear my jacked for a while. The place is funky inside with round dinning area, super unique.

review_1327.Review: This place is NOT for a romantic evening. One table of loud diners ruined it for all of the tables around us and while the manager asked them several times to lower their boisterous noises the table continued to ruin conversation level talking for others. Management should have asked them to leave. Everyone in the entire restaurant applauded as the rowdy group finally paid up and left. If I had paid a babysitter to enjoy my evening out I would have asked management of 5A5 to pay for my meal AND the sitter. The experience was definitely not a good one.

review_1328.Review: The staff was not that friendly. For the price the waitress and bartender could have been more friendly! Good is great but they tried to rush us! Not cool when your spending 2k for dinner!

review_1329.Review: The filet wasn't very good, but the bacon-laden sides were delicious.

review_1330.Review: Started off with some great happy hour appetizers. Had a nice booth, and we all ordered rib eyes. This was the best RibEye in my life. It was tender, not too fatty, well aged. Our waitress was fabulous, and constantly filled our ice teas, wine glasses, etc. Everyone in the restaurant was very service oriented. We'll definitely be back!!

review_1331.Review: An unusual mix of American and Japanese influenced menu items. The Wagyu beef was a little too pricey for me. Midwest beef was very good, with excellent sauces.

review_1332.Review: the food was fantastic. the service was impeccable. I'll definitely be coming back for future special occasions.

review_1333.Review: 5A5 was a pleasant surprise that exceeded expectations. Modern take on a steakhouse with great starters

review_1334.Review: My Wife and I wnet out to dinner with another couple and we had a fabulous experience. Food was Great, Service was spot on. Defintely recommend for any type of occasion.

review_1335.Review: Wanted to try based on the Kobe beef. It's real, from Japan, not just the technique. Served @ $30 an oz in 4oz increments. DELISH!!! Appetizers were great as well. You're going to pay, but it's a great experience. I brought my own wine. 1st 2 corkage @ $20/bottle. Don't bring just any wine. Look at the wine list and see if you can get it cheaper and bring it in. That's the way to go. Got to see Fmr. Mayor Willie Brown dining in as well.

review_1336.Review: I was simply not impressed with this restaurant from the beginning to end. I dropped almost $300 for two people and have spent half that at other restaurants and had a much better experience. The hostess managing the reservations was a total sourpuss. Our server literally argued with us the whole time about how our experience was going. He was trying to be pleasant but came off as overly aggressive. The hard up sell on the wagyu beef is inappropriate. I know what wagyu beef is. If I wanted it, I would've ordered it. Their wine list leaves A LOT to be desired. The cocktails were good, and the dessert was the best part of the meal. This place is way overrated. Spend your money somewhere else.

review_1337.Review: Included in my group of admitted food connoisseurs were: 2 Parisians, 1 from DC, 1 from San Fran and me (from NYC area)Group consensus: Top 5 steakhouse for all!!Enough said....

review_1338.Review: Our first visit, celebrating our 30th weddding anniversary. Deilghtful experience. Food was excellent, prepared and served to perfection. Our waiter, Ali, was superb. He was engaging, knowledgable, and blessed with a wonderful sense of subtle humor. We will return.

review_1339.Review: My son and I ordered boneless rib eye steaks and were served what seemed to be rump roast; we sent it back. Manager came over and tried to explain that we didn't know our cuts of meat. He brought over two uncooked rib-eyes which were actually rib-eyes and they were very tasty.However, trying to boost margins by not serving what was ordered is WRONG! Picked on the wrong guys...we've been cooking rib-eyes for decades. Watch out at A5A...you have to keep them on their toes!

review_1340.Review: This was a great experience. The food was amazing. I recommend the bacon wrapped scallop appetizers and the maguro bite as a started. The Wagyu beef filet with truffle risotto literally melted in my mouth. I also recommend the lobster tempura as a side. Great wine list, the Argentinian Malbec was fantastic. For dessert, the L'Opera Verte with green tea and the Fondant Cake are a great way to end the evening. Great service. Leila, was an amazing waitress and was incredibly helpful. Fun restaurant and a pleasure to visit.

review_1341.Review: Wonderful experience! Restaurant never fails in service or quality of food.

review_1342.Review: The food was amazing, and the waiter was pretty cool too. Only thing I didn't like was that the seats were really close to each other, felt like the person sitting next to us was at the same table as us.

review_1343.Review: Everything is excellent here! We are definitely coming back soon.

review_1344.Review: they do not know how to cook a steak the inside of the one brought to me was almost raw. Until they fire the chef this is a total waste of money. You could get a better steak at Cattleman chain steak house. At this rate the place will be gone in 1 year.

review_1345.Review: Appetizers (bacon wrapped scallops) and side dishes (shrooms and mac cheese) were very good. My 22 oz. T-bone was undercooked. The service was very good. If a "lounge" scene is mandatory with your steak, you may want to try it, but for the money I would revisit Harris', Ruth's Chris, or Mortons before returning here.

review_1346.Review: Best Kobe I have had!  Waiting for more places like this.  I really enjoyed my dinning experiences here.  Keep up the good beef!  See you soon.  Service was good but she could of been a tad bit more on top of things but maybe she was busy who knows.  Just seemed like I was asking for things more then being offered.

review_1347.Review: Overall experience was good. The food was great. Price is little bit high. Portion are too small . Please do not take your whole family here it will very expensive. I wil be back only with my wife will be more cheaper.

review_1348.Review: 1. The beef sashimi (wagyu) appetizer was disappointing. First of all the beef was cut too thick and wrapped with vegetable. It will be great if it eat seperately. Secondly, the beef was sheared on one side therefore the marbles was cooked and thus it does not melts in your mouth. If it say sashimi it mean raw not shear at all. I rather have the thinly sliced wagyu beef melts in my mouth.2. My guest ordered Medium Rare on the Lamb, it should be medium on the outside and rare in the inside-it turns out that the outside is medium but the inside is also medium. The other steak was ordered rare and the outcome is not rare at all. Fortunately, my was bloody rare and I really liked it.

review_1349.Review: Awesome food and service a must restaurant

review_1350.Review: I was seated very quickly. My meal was exactly as ordered. The wine list was great. The coffee afterwords was fabulous and the sorbet was refreshing. Out of the hundred choices I had for dinner for the last night of my conference I was more than happy with choosing 5A5.

review_1351.Review: We decided to try this restaurant during San Francisco's Dine About Town. There was a definite feeling that we were in the wrong place. The Dine About Town menu was extremely limited. The food was good, but our waitress seemed pretentious. The quality was also lower than I was expecting. I understand cutting cost for the promotion, but this made the experience less appealing.

review_1352.Review: Love the dine about town offers, great service and delicious food!! Will definitely be coming back!

review_1353.Review: Food was good. Didn't blow me away, but didn't disappoint either.Ambiance is great, though. Very attractive interior, and polite wait staff.

review_1354.Review: Overall the experience is good. The waitress was friendly, and they keep serving complimentary appetizers from Chef which was nice. The steak sauce is a bit salty though. It's worth to come back again.

review_1355.Review: It's a girl night out for me and my friend. The food is great except I think the chef forgot to put sauce in my steak, I have a few drops while my friend (same dish) has a normal amount. The service is great and the food is great. We were seated by a pillar which feels a bit strange to us, we asked to be seated in the other table, the receptionist told us that will be used as a table for 5 later, but it turned out not, just another couple, I wished she had just told me it was reserved. Now I felt like either she lied to us or she just didn't want to go through the little trouble to walk us 3 more steps to that table.

review_1356.Review: The food was wonderful. The service was great and the total experience was wonderful. I went with a friend for the dine around town program. The menu options was limited, but a great selection. I will be making another visit real soon!

review_1357.Review: If you want to indulge with excellent steaks, this is the place to go. The ambiance is contemporary and relaxing. There were 4 of us dining, and 2 persons decide on splurging on the wagu steak. The other 2 had their filet mignon. The wagu steaks were excellent (although quite an investment) and cooked exactly as ordered. Both of the filets were overcooked. We found that all other dishes we ordered from the daikon soup, to shots, to side dishes were distracting with flavors. The one strong negative note is that the person who greeted you at the door was very "cold" - not welcoming. In addition, although Open Table confirmation email advised of 1/2 price bottle of wine on Sunday nights, we had to ask about it, and bill was adjusted.

review_1358.Review: Once again, 5A5 excels at creativity, presentation and flavor! Having enjoyed their talents several times before, I went with great expectations to try the "Dine Around Town" menu. Wow! Caesar salad and carrot ginger soup were ample and delicious. My petite filet, prepared rare as I like it, was 6 ounces of tender, exquisitely flavored beef. My friend had the 8 ounce New York syeak with onion jam and crispy onions which he was unwilling to share! We chose the "shrooms" as an extra cost side dish (as the special included none) and could not finish them they were so rich, varied and plentiful. The dessert choices included a small but tasty tapioca brulee and a "pots de creme" style, three-layered chocolate. Value++++!

review_1359.Review: My wifes filet was dry and over cooked and the waiter offered to refire the same steak. We both looked at each other in amazement.we were sat in the both in front of the wine room and back door. Ofcouse I got cold air on the back of my head and down my back the whole night. I said something to one of the waiters and he joked that it was part of the ambiance. It's 40 degrees in San Francisco I want warmth not bone chilling wind down my back. Great company made for a great night despite the other factors.

review_1360.Review: This was our 1st time and it lived up 2 the hype. Nice ambiance and great food. The chef was very creative in the apps and courses. Would definitely go again.n

review_1361.Review: My boyfriend and I went for the Dine About Town special. Although I had already thought about what I wanted to order, the server did a great job explaining the DaT menu and the regular menu. To get the most for our money, my boyfriend ordered the romaine salad with NY strip steak and the chocolate cremeux. I ordered the iceberg salad with filet mignon and tapioca brulee. The iceberg salad, filet mignon and chocolate cremeux were the better options. We also got several small plates: first a short rib, corn, bell pepper shooter, a butternut squash in lychee sauce, french and bacon bread, baby cherry madeleines and pumpkin cubes rolled in sugar. I was worried I wouldn't be full with only 3 courses but the many side dishes sealed the deal!

review_1362.Review: I got the NY Strip and my gf got the prime rib. They were good, but I would suggest going to Alexander's or House of Prime Rib if you are looking for an amazing experience (for example, the medium prime rib my gf got was slightly on the tougher side and somewhat dry).That said, the truffle fries were amazing and the atmosphere was great.

review_1363.Review: Given it is a steak lounge, I was disappointed they did not have grass fed beef as an option. Had the wagyu, it was nice but not quite what I was looking for. Salad and chard side was great. Great wines by the glass.

review_1364.Review: It was so noisy that I could not have a conversation with the person across the table from me(there were only four of us). I will certainly mention this factor when referring friends.

review_1365.Review: loud... Steak and fish was good, calamari was tough and rubbery. I'll try again...

review_1366.Review: Great place for happy hour. The food pricing was expensive and the food options were decent. Definitely a date night or special occassion place to dine. Would come back for a special occassion, but not for regular dining.

review_1367.Review: Normally, dinner at 5A5 is out of my price range, so I was really excited to see it on the Dine About Town list. I'd been a guest at a birthday party a year or so ago and remembered having a great time. The DAT menu had a nice selection of options and everything we tried was delicious and beautifully presented. Obviously, I was most interested in trying a steak and so chose the filet for my entree. It was perfectly prepared and seasoned. I knew from experience that it would also be alone on the plate, so I sprang for the creamy spinach. It was heavenly. If I get that raise, I'll definitely put going back at the top of my to-do list.

review_1368.Review: the food at this place was not bad. was a big fan of their little "bite" size menu, especially hamachi shot. the new york strip was perfectly cooked but the steak in itself was dulled by the sauces that were around it...but overall good. the atmosphere was very loud but likely not the norm. overall...good place for steak and one day would like to try the wagyu beef.

review_1369.Review: Service started out great, but server was overwhelmed? Sat in front of our dinner plates for 10+ minutes after our last guest finished. Never asked if we wanted coffee or about meals, doneness of steaks etc. In fact, never came to table after meal was served. Amuse bouche, delicious and very nice touch as was palate cleanser/cookies. Appetizers tasty but truffle fries were soggy, barely warm. NOTHING in our dinner service was above tepid in temperature. Unfortunate because the food was very good (truffled Mac/cheese, green beans) 5 steaks. Steak perfect doneness but barely warm. Very disappointing if you like your food hot. We went on the dine about town deal and spent $75 pp. Would have been a 1st class meal if food served hot!

review_1370.Review: Dont go, you'll have a better experience at tommy's joint. Food wasn't good at all, and portions are very small. My 20 dollar Steak was over cooked and it was so salty.

review_1371.Review: Definitely a couple of nods to Alexander's but it doesn't quite match up in terms of quality. The food was definitely tasty - but for the price, it could be better. If you're on a biz trip, could be a nice time to try the real wagyu.

review_1372.Review: Another great meal here! Got there early to enjoy their happy hour and started with $5 drinks and appetizers, which are good portions and enough to make a meal out of if you split several plates. There was 5 of us and 3 ordered the New York strip and the other 2 ordered the filet mignon, all off the Dine About Town menu. All the steaks were perfectly cooked, the first course of salads were very large portions and desserts were also very good. We had to order four sides to share since there was no accompaniments to the entrees.

review_1373.Review: Tried out the Dine-about-Town menu, 5A5 did not disappoint. Overall experience was great. The entree's were just excellent.

review_1374.Review: Not a pleasant visit.We are here for the DAT menu, the waitress was not very friendly, and looks annoyed.We ordered filet mignon and NY strip, both asked for median rare. Both stake come out feeling like median, I asked my NY strip to be replaced and boyfriend didn't.The replaced NY strip come out prefect.So I am not sure where the problem is, is either the cooking to too careless or the ordering is not informative.Usually when you go to a stake house or lounge in this case, they should have the knowledge of how the stake(which part of the meat or cut) should be cooked to be enjoyable. The waitress obviously did not care about people who ordered the DAT menu, just quickly write down what we have and off she go. I will not come aga

review_1375.Review: Thanks for a brilliant night. It was a celebration for my birthday, and I was presented with a personal cake with a candle. Between each course there was a complimentary palette cleanser, which was a nice and unexpected touch.I would recommend 5A5, but don't go here if you're on a budget - it is quite pricey.

review_1376.Review: The service was great. The menu from Dine About Town was enough to give us an around flavor of what the restaurant has to offer. We love the complimentary bites from the chef. Their steaks, NY steak and petit filet mignon, were delicious and cooked just right. We love our waitress, she was cheerful, attentive and sociable. Lady but not least, the lobster Mac and cheese was to die for & I don't even like Mac and cheese!

review_1377.Review: I had dinning here several times. I always has great experience with service at my table. This time was so different. I know that i would be late so I called 5a5 at the time of my reservation and confirm with them that I will running late. The receiptionists was not only rude but also a liar and unprofessional. They not honor my table although I did come on time as I promiss. They made me wait for 45 minutes, seated me and my friends last. I wanted to rate 5a5 minus star for this service. I did not have to come to 5a5 for this kind of service. There are so many exellence restaurant in the city. The food was exellence, waiter at the table was exellence. I will not recommend this restaurant to my friends with this check in problems.

review_1378.Review: Excellent food. My friend said it was the best steak she has ever had. I would have liked a bit more seasoning on my steak but both of our steaks were cooked perfectly. Our server was also amazing. She had just the right balance of attention. The only inconsistency was the bartender who seemed to be a bit bothered when we had a drink at the bar prior to eating our dinner. We will certainly be back though. Oh and the dessert was great too.

review_1379.Review: Courteous and attentive, the servers. Generous, the portions. Attentive to detail, the chefs. My favorite restaurant, by far, in the city.

review_1380.Review: I was slightly disappointed with the food this time around. My iceberg salad was bland and so was the dessert, although the filet mignon was cooked precisely the way I ordered it. The service was delightful so overall I would rate my second time here as a good experience with fair food.

review_1381.Review: We went for dine about town and had a wonderful experience. Happy hour in the lounge was great, the service was impeccable, the food (meat!!!) was formidable and we found a wonderful bottle on the wine list.

review_1382.Review: I enjoyed 5A5.  I went there with my husband to celebrate my birthday.  They provided us with an amuse bouche complimentary and they added in a birthday treat as part of our meal with a candle.  The food was gorgeous and tasted great.  The only issues were that it took a long time for each meal to come out and it's a bit on the more pricey side for the "Wagyu" beef they are known for.  We did have the sliders and they were awesome.  I would come back here for a special occassion.

review_1383.Review: 3 points for food specifcally around the appetizers and small bites - seasoning is inconsistent some things were over salted and some were bland. Also the lobster was over cooked which resulted in a dry and rubbery texture. The steak - Wagyu was excellent! and the sides are heart stoppingly good. Service was attentive and but not suffocating. When you spend this kind of money, you expect consistent and the high standards need to show up the enitre meal.

review_1384.Review: Delicious! I had a flavorful prime rib, my friend had the bacon wrapped filet. He didn't talk the whole time he was eating, ha!

review_1385.Review: First time at the restaurant. Extremely favorable. Food beyond great,server attentive and pleasant, a wonderful experience.

review_1386.Review: My friends and I had the best time. Our server was pleasant, knowledgeable, and made some terrific suggestions. They knew we were on a time limit as we caught a showing of the Lion King so they knew time was of the essence. The hostess called us a cab once we were done and left with a great dining experience!!! I've already raved about 5A5 to my friends on FB and will definitely be back!!! I'll make up a special occasion if I have too!!!

review_1387.Review: Wonderful food, but pricey. We didn't do the Waygu tasting, but still managed to spend a pretty penny. There aren't many places in SF where you can get good sea bass anymore, and this one was nice, but sadly not perfect. The cocktails and small plates were delish, and we opted for the corkage and a nice bottle of wine to celebrate the big bday.

review_1388.Review: I felt that the cuisine was overpriced and pretentious. Is beef from Japan really worth 5 times more than that from Iowa? Like blind testing expensive wines, I am sure most of us could not tell the difference if put the task.

review_1389.Review: Everything was absolutely amazing! The tartare duo and filet were awesome! Would go back in a second.

review_1390.Review: 5A5 is my favorite restaurant in the world because of the exceptional food and service. Not only are the steaks phenomenal but so is everything else on the menu. Everything is delicous! I always have a great time when I go there and have never been disappointed. LOVE!

review_1391.Review: 5A5 was outstanding! The server was very knowledgable and attentive. I had the filet mignon and lobster tempura. Melt in your mouth delicious!

review_1392.Review: Best prime rib i've had in a long time. Appetizers(chicken popcorn and chicken wings) were very bland and the Creme Brulee dessert was the smallest dessert i've ever been served, especially for the price. The prime rib made the overall meal enjoyable.

review_1393.Review: My husband and I ate here for second seating on New Year's Eve 2012. This is where the question East Coast vs West Coast rears its ugly head. The food was good, the drinks were fair, the service was rushed, and there was no dining entertainment to entice you to hang out until the Midnight Toast. This was our most expensive dining experience in San Fran, and the most disappointing because of the lack of New Year's Eve experience we're used to. It seems expensive dining was rushed so attention could be given to those who bought "After Party" tickets, which was a DJ in a small dance area. Even in D.C. dining establishments do not put you in a vice grip like this. No worries though, our lack of tip reflected our disappointment.

review_1394.Review: My fiancee and I dined for the first time at this restaurant on New Year's Eve, so it was a unique occasion and likley not a typical representation of this restaurant. They offered a Prix Fix menu for this holiday. We had very good service - a great balance of being warm and very professional. The food was very good, and beautifully presented. I will say this is the most money I have ever spent on a meal for two, so for me, it is definitely a special occasion restaurant. The food and the ambiance also has a subtle Asian influence, which work, but it is not a classic steakhouse.

review_1395.Review: We came to 5a5 for New Year's Eve. They had a prefix menu the food was good however one of the members of our group had to send back the same steak 3 times because it was over cooked. Once that was fixed the food was great. The service on the other hand was sub par they could have had a McDonalds employee do a better job. Also beware the club is immediately behind where the dining area is so it can get very loud which it did and it made the experience not as nice as it could have been.

review_1396.Review: Best Prime Rib I have ever had.

review_1397.Review: Everything was excellent - a very creative menu!

review_1398.Review: Service was excellent. Steaks prepared perfectly.

review_1399.Review: Really great, inventive cuisine. Great service, nice ambience, very comfortable, and we particularly like all the appetiziers.

review_1400.Review: We are still talking about this meal! Great food and wine and service. We had a great time. I definitely recommend it!

review_1401.Review: Great food with great service. Can't go wrong eating at 5A5.

review_1402.Review: one of the best steaks I have ever had and the swiss chard was fantastic

review_1403.Review: $27 for 1 ounce of steak really seems ridiculous - nothing could be that good. I chose lamb, which was excellent, although the spring roll of some sort was rather mushy and greasy. We also shared the Shrooms which were also quite greasy. If I go back, it will be for the happy hour and the bar menu - very nice bar/lounge area.

review_1404.Review: Perfect attention to detail, spacing of various courses,and no hovering. Just a delightful evening of coversation, great wine and delicious food.Thank you

review_1405.Review: Superb food. Excellent service. Very modern decor.

review_1406.Review: Our group was very happy with all our choices and we are still talking about our experience!!

review_1407.Review: Worst corkage fee gouging I've ever experienced, and without any prior warning (until the bill came). We had 5 guys gathering for a holiday steak dinner, and everyone brought one nice bottle of wine. The first 2 were charged at $20/btl, but thereafter it jumped to $50 per bottle! Outrageous - I'll never go back.

review_1408.Review: Great Place, Great food, Tip: This place gets full and consequently noise level goes up a little bit. So for special occasion pick early evening time slot. We went there at 530PM and had a really good experience. By the time we left, the place was full, there were few large groups also. And one can definitely witness effects of great cocktails and wine selection on the lively conversations.

review_1409.Review: outstanding!! the only reason i rated it very good overall is because I wish they offered smaller portions on the non-wagyu beef dishes. Best beet salad i have ever had. we were there on a sunday night, so it was pretty full yet quiet. The bar area is cool but no one there prob because it was a sunday night. waitress very knowledgeable but seemed to be pushing the wagyu. definitely returning!

review_1410.Review: This is a place to take someone if you're celebrating something very special, or if you generally are someone who lives a life in culinary splendor. This restaurant is very expensive and its specialty is wagyu beef/steak - beef that is treated very specially so you get the richest, most flavorful meat that melts in your mouth. Unfortunately, we chose to skip it as it is very expensive. We chose our favorite - prime rib. And it was amazing.This place is for people who frequent high-end restaurants on a regular basis, and probably people who earn six digits at least, and/or people who do a lot of traveling because of their career. We're teachers - as much as we liked this place we probably won't come again.

review_1411.Review: The dry aged steaks are definitely not as good as EPIC.

review_1412.Review: Our group decided that although everything was good, with so many restaurants in the city we probably would not come back. Nothing seem over the top to warrant a return visit. But we do believe that this restaurant is worth a visit.

review_1413.Review: The atmosphere for this location is outstanding. Beautiful, sophisticated interior with delicate focus and incredible details. Service was the main focus behind this outstanding review. Ali provided a world class experience with humor, wit, and great advice. We were unrushed and with the place being completely packed, felt no rush to leave. A great experience, I would recommend this restaurant for all who love meat and enjoy a nicely paced, relaxing meal.

review_1414.Review: Staff was amazing very knowledgeable and efficient. Highly recommend this place. Amazing food and presentation.

review_1415.Review: lives up to it's name! had a great selection of A5 wagyu...AND the seating is more "lounge" like than other traditional steak houses i've frequented. service was 'okay' hostess and bartender were friendly...umm...waiter and the guy who brought out our food...not so much....food was great! passed on the $28 per ounce wagyu and went for the bone in ribeye and truffled mac n cheese. delish! highly recommend this place. i will definitely return!

review_1416.Review: The food was very good and the service was even better. A restaurant worthy of celebrating a special occassions.

review_1417.Review: Very pricey for such small steaks. Although my rib eye was good, the chicken was overcooked.. I wouldn't go back again because of the portion... way to expensive for such small portions of steak...quite disappointed...

review_1418.Review: Fantastic food! The sliders are to die for,and the wagyu melted in the mouth.

review_1419.Review: It is a steakhouse selling prime waygu beef...or A5 beef selectiongs beginning at $27 an ounce. If this is what you're there for, it should be a good experience. There's a great bar with good coctail selections and wine. The 50% off on wine lists, which is on Open Table does not hold during the holidays (which we are in now). the food is too over dressed and spiced and plain too salty at times.We will not dine there again. It was overpriced for what you received on some items and a great too many of others so it's difficult to know what to order and how much to order.

review_1420.Review: Of all the recommendations I've had from Open Table, this is the 1st one that was quite disapointing - it started by being seated outside the kitchen order, then after asking them to move us, being unable to make the drink we ordered, then moved onto them not being able to alter the sauce on a steak, then after changing my order, screwing up the sauce on that steak and completed this experience by serving one of the most hideous creme brulee deserts I've ever eaten - for those that read my reviews, this was definitely NOT a do over!

review_1421.Review: I went here for an anniversary dinner with my girlfriend the other night and we received by far the best service we have ever had in our lives!Food - 5/5- the food was melt in your mouth and absolutely amazing!Service - 5/5- the staff provided great recommendations and continually checked on us to ensure we were having a good time- after we finished a plate, there was no lag time at all for the next plate to come outAmbiance - 5/5- the plate is extradinarily nice with a kind of futuristic and retro feel- definite great date night type of joint!

review_1422.Review: My boyfriend and I chose 5A5 for a special occasion, and had a wonderful experience regarding the menu choices, the fantastic service shown by Ryan, the scrumptious cuisine, and notable wine list! We enjoyed the vibe, and will return soon! I had the 5A5 and it was dreamy. My boyfriend had the filet mignon and loved it. Excellent quality meats, and I was surprised at how many non-meat choices were on the menu as well (veggies, seafood (we loved the scallop wrapped bacon appetizer)

review_1423.Review: Had the Boneless Ribeye done medium well. It was ok, but I was expecting more based on the reputation of this place. Next time, I guess I'll get the Wagyu cut. Compared to Hillstone's (former Houstons) nearby on Embacadero, the Hawaiian Ribeye there is much better. Waiter and hostess were excellent at 5A5 though.

review_1424.Review: The star of the menu, the steaks, were excellent. The sides were less impressive. The restaurant takes itself very seriously.

review_1425.Review: Food was ok, nothing great tataki was fishing, didn't even eat it steak was chewy and service was slow... Not really a great night. The beet salad was good though...

review_1426.Review: Great steaks and great time. will return.

review_1427.Review: Great service and amazing steaks. My filet literally melted in my mouth. A bit pricey but worth it.

review_1428.Review: great steaks and ribs. i dream about their menu afterwards.

review_1429.Review: A bit noisy for conversation. Excellent food.

review_1430.Review: Everything up to the main course was pleasantly delicious. The bone in ribeye was NOT "melt in your mouth". In fact, the sauce on top made it too sweet and the ribeye was not flavorful nor tender. Very disappointed with the maincourse since I enjoyed the hamachi shooter and the mizuno salad.

review_1431.Review: The roast beef was cooked to perfection. All dishes are a la carte but the sides are large enough to share. The French fries were excellent. The only dish I would not recommend is the creamed spinach whose earthy taste I found unpleasant.

review_1432.Review: The NY steak strip was good, but not what I expected. The beet salad was absolutely delicious.

review_1433.Review: I have mixed feelings about this place. I am not sure I really like the decorations, they remind me of a somewhat modernized 70's style, which never really appealed me.Service was generally good, but I was disappointed when I ordered a boneless rib-eye, the waitress came after few minutes asking if I wanted a boneless or a bone-in, I confirmed the former, and I finally got a bone-in rib-eye. Albeit the food was good, the final bill was way too expensive.

review_1434.Review: Wagyu. Wagyu. Wagyu. That is all. It's San Francisco's oldest "Steak Lounge," and it certainly doesn't disappoint. Go for the hamachi shooters too!

review_1435.Review: We went for our 5 year anniversary and the food was phenomenal. Truly fantastic. Nice ambiance but, the acoustics lend towards a really loud room. It was like having a fantastic meal in a crowded bar.

review_1436.Review: Most amazing desserts!Pastry Cheif-Mr.Robert Byrd is geneous!Elegant,sofisticated,imaginative,tastfully presented desserts was a culmination to most spectacular dinner.

review_1437.Review: I had the 50%/50% 8oz steak; well cooked and melt in your mouth but not over rich as Wagyu can be. Sides of swiss chard was good, mushrooms were ok. The rest of the food is mediocre though. I ordered 4 shooters to start off with. Interesting concept that doesn't really work; most of the ingredients just get stuck in the shot glasses and you can't really "shoot" them. The Hamachi shooter was by far the best of the four. The oysters had a funny combination that didn't quite work for me and the lobster shooter had dry over cooked lobster meat, a real let down.

review_1438.Review: This place has great service. Food is amazing but be prepared to pay a hefty price for the good stuff. Its great to try wagyu for the first time but be prepared to pay about 30 dollars an ounce. I recommend getting one order of that and another order and just sharing. Wagyu is very rich in flavor and melts in your mouth. The waiter, forgot his name, a middle eastern gentleman, older,  really knows the food and explains everything. Really enjoyed this restaurant

review_1439.Review: Service was excellent the menu was explained well & with 50% off a bottle of wine on a Sunday was excellent value.

review_1440.Review: Incredible Wagyu selection and prepared very well. We landed on a wine bottles 1/2 off night, Sunday, and enjoyed some Opus One with the Wagyu. Nice combination!! One downside, the kitchen is loud and wide open to the whole Dining room. The Maitre D sat us at the table facing the wide open kitchen (the restaurant had many, many open tables) and was rude to us when we asked to be moved. He visited every table except ours. Lucky us. Food outstanding and the Wait staff was outstanding and all despite the child of a Maitre D/Manager. I recommend it despite him.

review_1441.Review: Our server Jade did an excellent job. We were celebrating an anniversary and she allowed us to take our time in ordering and she was attentive but not intrusive. If you go, definitely ask for Jade to be your server. We dined on a Sunday evening, so it was not too busy so the noise level was low. The food was very good, but the prices of the entrees and the wine list were unreasonable.

review_1442.Review: We have a couple of favorites in SF and have decided to branch out using Open Table. This was a great find. It is expensive but the food was well prepared, seasoned and presented. One of our party had checked it out and insisted we order a side of mac n' cheese. I would never but did and it was amazing. So order it even if you avoid carbs! Staff was friendly and helpful. It was modern and happening. I will go there again.

review_1443.Review: Hands down one of the greatest, most creative meals I've ever had the pleasure of consuming. As daring as the chef was, there were no misses with any dishes. We were even brought tastes of 3 other creations for free. The ambiance was chic and warm and the waitress was bubbly and knowledgeable. Couldn't have had a better experience.

review_1444.Review: Great space with a comfortable, innovative interior, great service, and all in all a very nice night out with friends. The steaks though, were only just good. One was mildly overcooked but mostly they were simply a bit lackluster. In a non-steakhouse I would have been perfectly happy with my steak, but in a steakhouse - and at these prices - I expected something better.

review_1445.Review: Everything was AMAZING. EVERYTHING. From the Palate cleanser, to the service, to the apps and steaks. I am a foodie. A food snob. This is where to go. You will not be disappointed. I live in Scottsdale and was here on business. Wow.

review_1446.Review: Good stuff. Kevin (GA) does an awesome job to make you feel welcome.

review_1447.Review: We were visiting from Texas as a bachelorette party of 8! 5A5 was the best food we had in San Francisco! We were called earlier on our reservation day to ask if we would like a complimentary upgrade to the chef table! It was a great experience! Amazing cocktails, great appetizers and phenomenal steak! We couldn't have asked for better food or better service! Thank you to everyone at 5A5 for making our night out special! We would recommend it to others that were visiting or living in San Francisco!

review_1448.Review: Everything was very good. I will go back!

review_1449.Review: Best steak in city for high end steaks. Wagyu to die for. The bill will make you die young too.

review_1450.Review: It's a great restaurant. terrific service, delicious food. it can get a bit loud overall, though.

review_1451.Review: I was there for the 5A Wagyu. $29/oz for the filet and the ribcap. It's worth trying.

review_1452.Review: Excellent meal and great service. The best rib-eye I've ever tasted. BUT, the bar is at the front as you enter and is very noisy. Request to sit in the very back of the dining room if you'd like to be able to have a conversation over dinner without shouting. Still highly recommended.

review_1453.Review: Finally the embargo on Japanese Beef is finally over. Great steak, only one of the two restaurants in SF that offers 100% pure japanese beef

review_1454.Review: delicious food! Loved the apetizers - we ordered a few to start. The entrees were fabulous, well presented, well plated, perfectly cokked!Felt we were seated in th middle of people coming in and the servers going back and forth with food.

review_1455.Review: Food/service/atmosphere was excellent however pricing is quite steep and all items are a la carte which made for a costly final bill in order to sample items across the menu from apps, salad, main, side dish, dessert. Nice surprise was wine was 50% off on Sundays, so was able to choose a great bottle of wine. And side dishes are substantial enough to share with another person. Also, the chef's sent out a variety amuse bouche's between courses for us to try which were very interesting/delicious. I would definitely reserve this restaurant for a special occasion if budget it not an issue.

review_1456.Review: Overall experience was excellent. One of the next restaurants we have been to. Outstanding service, exceeded expectations. Extensive wine list. Good steaks, cooked right. Entire staff was very professional & attentive.

review_1457.Review: Very expensive, but you get what you pay for!!! Everything exceeded our expectations, but the wagyu filet was literally fork tender....no knife necessary. The marble was so perfect, it literally tasted buttery, but you didn't actually see or trim ANY fat. My first trip here, but certainly not my last! Having said that, what actually made the meal most memorable was our server Erika. Close attention to every detail yet not breathing down your neck and extremely knowledgeable about the menu as well as the wine list. I can assure you, your drinks wont run dry.

review_1458.Review: Good food but nothing too exciting for the price. Two of us had dinner consisting of beer/cocktail, each had a glass of wine with our meal, 2 appetizers, a main, one side dish and a dessert= $220. Def not worth it.

review_1459.Review: It's official...this is my fav place in SF.There was nothing bad about this place.The food was to die for!!!Loved every minute of it!!!

review_1460.Review: Great food in a great place. Very special for a birthday!

review_1462.Review: Great food as usual. Service was a little slow compared to previous visits, but the staff was still friendly and helpful.

review_1463.Review: Very nice food & a very good wine list. I was there as part of a large group and the service was very good as well.

review_1464.Review: Delicious and generously portioned appetizers, inventive new creations like Carpaccio with fixings and tried and true staples like truffle fries. The prime rib was excellent but the t-bone wasn't all that large of a steak. The cocktails were wonderful.

review_1465.Review: The food was delicious! The service was great, however our particular waitress was not attentive to our needs and always seemed preoccupied despite it being a seemingly slow night. We waited quite a while for our drinks and then at the end of our meal waited a while again for the check. Also, we thought the atmosphere/ambience was very odd and the restaurant was also very noisy. The environment was not very conducive to a quiet, romantic date, which is what we were hoping for.

review_1466.Review: The only reason I am giving it two stars is for the great server and the delish green beans. We had the special bone in fillet. There is a difference between aged and old! Our steaks crossed the line. Chewy and dry on the edges on their way to jerky. Table by the kitchen, I kept putting my elbow in the extra silverware tray they we storing on the back of our banquette. Over priced and over rated. We will not be back

review_1467.Review: My boyfriend and I came here for our 5yr anniversary and we had never heard of it before. We found it on Yelp and saw they had good reviews. The food was delicious! To start we had Lobster Tail Tempura to share, Main dish was boneless Ribeye medium well with marble potatoes and mac & cheese. We also had a bottle of wine because Sundays all the wine bottles are 50% off! So we had a Chardonnay Whispering Angel white wine. We were so full that we had no space for dessert but they gave us the cutest complimantery mini dessert to share that said "happy anniversary" on it and we ate it but we were so full haha. But seriously its pricey but a nice romantic place to go to.

review_1468.Review: 5A5 was a surprising steakhouse experience because the food was terrific and the tone was so much more upbeat and modern than the tired old wood-paneled steakhouses that are standard fare. The decor is modern and fresh. The menu is diverse and the choices are different than many steak-specialists.The beet salad was excellent; the macaroni and cheese was very tasty and NOT the same old thing you expect. And, as one should expect, the beef was exceptional. Try 5A5!

review_1469.Review: Food and service were great. In a word, though, EXTREMELY NOISY!!!! Very young bar crowd. Those of us over 30 could not talk to each other without yelling. Would not pay that much for the experience again.

review_1470.Review: Spectacular beef, magnificent fish, great cocktails, perfect veggies, excellent service.

review_1471.Review: Solid place with modern decor, good service, and interesting takes on old favorites. The cocktail menu had some good drinks, and it's a great option for happy hour if you're in the area. For dinner, the food was good - not the best steak I've ever had (Wagyu ribeye), but this isn't a bad choice at all. It's not an old school steakhouse like Harris or Bob's, but it's a modern take with Asian influences.

review_1472.Review: I went to have dinner on a Monday night with some colleagues.The restaurant was almost full and the noise level was high, but nothing disturbing. Decoration is good; has a slightly retro style.The waitress was very nice, and service not pretentious. Amuse-bouche was very good, and we ordered kobe beef sashimi as a starter. The meat was not that great, definitely not "kobe" grade. Too little fat and to much ginger that killed the flavor.For the mains we ordered different steaks. The New York Steak was that great. It had some strange kimuchi flavor that was overpowering. The T-Bone was Ok.The Bone in Steak was very good, and the Filet mignon was outstanding, one of the best I've had.Depending on what you order, highly recommen

review_1473.Review: The food was tummy. The service was excellent. We recommend a vist.

review_1474.Review: LOVED everything we ordered, not to mention the complimentary bread (YUM), Wasabi mashed potatoes (YUM), and Candied ginger berry solid jelly to clense our pallet!!! Can't wait to re-visit this restaurant again.

review_1475.Review: I thought we were going to a steakhouse because that's how they are identified. While I thought the menu was very good, my friend, who is a very basic steak guy, had a tough time with it.Our waiter was great though.

review_1476.Review: As far as a San Fran steakhouse, I would rate this place average. Nothing in particular made it stand out. Although the food was good and the service was great, it was normal.The chef did supply us with complimentary treats for palette cleansing and other reasons which was nice, and I would recommend going at least once since the other steakhouses in the area are much more expensive and fill up quickly.

review_1477.Review: I've heard about 5A5 for a while and finally got the chance to try it out. WOW.. What was I waiting for? If you haven't tried this place.. GO.. NOW.. stop reading this and go... :-) Seriously.. Every dish we had was outstanding, so flavorful and delicious. We will go back again soon.

review_1478.Review: The food was amazing but the service was not! It took 30 minutes for drinks to arrive and although the waitress said it would take 40 minutes for the food to come out it ended up taking at least an hour if not more. It felt like long periods of time where no one came to check on us--for either more drinks or how everything was going. Plus that night we had two servers (I had assumed one was being trained), I thought since there were two of them they would be more on top of it. Also, our waitress was so soft spoken we could hardly hear her. I had assumed based on reviews and being a more upscale place that they would be on top of good service and good food--I was completely wrong.

review_1479.Review: Bad service at the bar, killed over all experience especially after dropping $450 on a meal for 3.

review_1480.Review: I would go back again! Staff was attentive and really knew their menu. The decor at this restaurant is what originally caught my eye. I am originally for NYC and I am always looking for restaurants that may ooze with the Manhattan feel, along with quality food. The decor was quite close and I was defintitely pleased by the energy of those eating at the restaurant. Some things to note:Truffle FriesI was super excited to try them and it smelled delicious when arrived at the table, but the fries were not cripsy and a bit soggyLobster TempuraExcellent!Misoyaki SeabassWell cooked fish but there could have been more flavor in the light broth sauceCreamy SpinachWould for sure recommend if you want to opt for veggie inste

review_1481.Review: My husband and I dined here upon a recommendation from a friend while visiting from DC in San Francisco. Had the NY Strip, Filet Mignon, iceberg wedge salad, truffle fries, and truffle mac & cheese. Great wine recommended and a yummy martini that had a good pour. Food was perfect, and that is a strong assessment coming from me, I'm very particular. Water glass stayed full, delivery of each course was well timed, knowledgeable server, excellent ambiance. Nice enough to dress up on the right evening but don't have to go all out and can do dressy casual alternatively. Highly recommended

review_1482.Review: Beautiful decor, the bartender poured drinks like I do at home...strong. Comfortable table arrangement. Food was excellent. Perfect steak. Attentive but not overly so service. A definite "Do it again".

review_1483.Review: Our waiter was the kind of server who scans the room while he is talking to you and acts as though you are something of an inconvenience for him.

review_1484.Review: Attentive and polished service.Billed as a "Steak Lounge" which seems to be a reference to the menu front page full of snack-size items.The steak was very good, very well prepared. The side dish of cremini mushrooms was very good. The wine list was overpriced but plausible.Location is very good.Worth it? Well, sort of pricey all in all. I'd say about 20% overpriced, but otherwise plausible.

review_1485.Review: All four in our party ordered a different steak. All were fantatstic.We enjoyed our experience very much.Would go again in a minute.

review_1486.Review: I would like to say thank you to all 5A5 personnel. My wife and I had a wonderful time last night. The food was stellar and the service was impeccable.  My wife and I have careers that don't allow us to have much time with each other so when our schedules match it is important that our time together be memorable and that's what your restaurant gave us.....a memorable night.  Thank you so much and we will see you again soon with friends and colleagues.PS.Leila thank you for taking great care of us last night. My wife had a wonderful birthday and we are planning on returning soon.Jaime & Anna

review_1487.Review: One of the worst meals I have ever had in San Francisco. Not only was the food just ok, the service was aggessive and inflexiable with an attitude unusual for the city.

review_1488.Review: My Fiance and I were in San Francisco for her Sorority's conference.. We had a wonderful meal at 5A5. The tenderloin was magnificent as was the shrimp appetizer.. Keep up the good Work

review_1489.Review: Fun Atmosphere and the was one of the goals of the evening for us...Appetizers, shooters and sides simply lovely, and the Waygu was well executed. HOWEVER! Stay away from the specialty steaks, T-Bone, Bone in Strip and Ribeye, all poorly seasoned, poorly cooked, at all temps.

review_1490.Review: A great experience overall. The only issue was slow service at the bar; only one bartender on duty. But she was hot. I had the Kobe beef, or the Australian version, which was great. My date, who was late, again, but only by one minute, had the lamb, which was excellent as well. The butter served with the bread was a much too soft and room temperature, and was quite bland. Might I suggest the excellent butter as at Salt House? It would improve things. Also included was a free hamachi and tofu appetizer that was quite good. And there was also a palate cleanser which was interesting.

review_1491.Review: Amazing food & service. We'd absolutely go back. Loved the menu! Not crazy gourmet where it was hard to find something you wanted to order but lots of variety at the same time. Just my kind of place.

review_1492.Review: I had a tomahawk cut steak here with fois gras on top, tough life. Overall the service and food here is amazing. The main compliant actually is the layout. The entire place is a big circle and the tables are cut into various parts. You sense you are watching others eat and they are watching you, which isn't the right vibe for a steak place - so that part doesn't really work. Having said that the food is awesome and I think this is a great place to blow out a few hundred bucks on clients, but maybe less often of a date spot.

review_1493.Review: The misoyaki fish was completely inedible. I happen to have a 3 of my colleagues from Europe and all of them were dissastified with the food. The manager in the end came an apologized for the bad fish and replace d it but the fish tasted the same.

review_1494.Review: My guest had a filet mignon, which he described as his "best ever."I accepted the server's recommendation of the bone-in New York steak, and it wasfull of unchewable gristle. It's the most expensive item on the menu at $48, andI felt as if I was fighting it the whole time in order to find just a few edible bites.Bread, expensive side dishes and dessert were all delicious, however. There werenumerous "treats" from the chef on a slow night, and the server kindly brought anice little birthday cake for my guest on a platter reading "Happy Birthday," which Iappreciated very much.

review_1495.Review: We were overall disappointed by the restaurant. The food was average. When we decided not to have desert it was as if the server took it as a personal front. We would not recommend this restaurant to friends.

review_1496.Review: I cannot say enough how outstanding our meal was here.  We are big foodies and eat at some of the best restaurants everywhere we go.  We were in SanFran for a week of vacation and this was the best meal we had there.  I cannot say enough that this was the best steak I have ever eaten.  The appetizer shooters were incredible!  Service outstanding as well, and "ahead of any request" we could have had.  My steak was so good that I asked to tell the cook myself which he appreciated.  Cannot say enough, don't miss this place!

review_1497.Review: Okay, not too special. There were four if us and we had reservations. The food was good, but nothing was outstanding. We probably will not return. No real ambiance. It was difficult to hear and background music was nill.

review_1498.Review: The food was to die for and the service was great. I will definitely return and try more things from the menu. Everything we ordered was scrumptious!

review_1499.Review: No comment. Just perfect. All my partners luv it.

review_1500.Review: Nice ambiance, The manager Mr. Lee was very helpful and knowledgable but the waiter appeared a little overwhelmed.Shooters were good but average. (3)Taco salad was amazing and likely the best I have ever had. (5)Steaks were absolutely awesome. (5)Desserts were below average. (2)

review_1501.Review: We enjoyed this place so much we went twice in 5 days during our stay in San Fran!

review_1502.Review: We came for my friends going away dinner. This was one of my first very nice dinners in San Francisco since I moved here. We had an amazing experience and the food was above and beyond many of the places I have been to in the city. I had the bone-in ribeye and was blown away. Also the Kobe Beef Sashimi melted in your mouth. I have already recommended to many people and plan on coming back for the next special occasion.

review_1503.Review: Everyone in my party loved the food, ambience and service. My son said the filet was the best he ever had.

review_1504.Review: Best prime rib I have ever gotten in a restaurant. Most places are afraid to season prime rib and turn out something that has to be slathered in horseradish to avoid having it taste like cardboard. Not true at 5A5. I have had it twice and it was perfectly seasoned and cooked to medium rare both times. The decor is pleasing even though it is a bit noisy.

review_1505.Review: Service was exceptional. Cocktails were also very good. Restaurant was a bit too loud for my taste though. My steak was cold when it arrived, then over-cooked when it was reheated. The staff was very attentive and offered me another one. I declined and they ended up comping the steak. Given their efforts and service, I would definitely give them another try.

review_1506.Review: The restaurant's look is very modern with a Vegas style flair, reminds me of the movie Ocean's Eleven, which I loved! The service was great, the cocktails were superb but the food unfortunately wasn't anything special. We ordered the truffle fries, monsuni salad (spelling) and the prime rib. The waiter recommended the "aged" steaks ($$$) I guess we should of took his advice because the prime rib with peppercorn and mushrooms was bland and chewy. I probably will give it another try since the place has a good vibe to it and the cocktails are spot on.

review_1507.Review: Food was good, not fantastic. I went there because the chef was from Alberts Steakhouse a few blocks away.Again food was good but not special, theref or this is a pricey place. I expected amazing and got good.

review_1508.Review: Guilty pleasure - steaks of all kinds with green peppercorn sauce - and other interesting sauces. Loved the scallops wrapped in bacon. Nice wine. Was pricey but we had a special Fathers' Day celebration.

review_1509.Review: Great concept and great food. Good value....no, we did not have the Wagyu!

review_1511.Review: My waiter kept interuppting us. He checked in with us every 5 - 10 mins which we felt it was quite distrurbing. But overall the service was good. Food was only so-so. Menu doesn't give much of a choice either.

review_1512.Review: The service was excellent, they definitely read my notes that I put into Open TABLE when i made the reservation. The waitress, Erica, WAS EXCELLENT.

review_1514.Review: I have high expectation about having steak but the rib-eye was not so good. Disappointed!

review_1515.Review: This is our favorite spot to go for steak! We went 2xs for DAT this month, and I decided to get the halibut. Since 5A5 is a steak place, if they're as good as we think they are, then items they don't specialize in should be just as amazing... and it was.

review_1516.Review: My party and I enjoyed their Dine-About Town menu. Food and service were good as this is my personal favorite for this promotion. If you want to impress a date or that meat lover, this is a great destination.

review_1517.Review: ah-ma-zing... If you love steak.... Never mind. If you love great food. This is a restaurant you have to put on your " try" list.

review_1518.Review: Great food, great service! would come back again

review_1519.Review: I enjoyed this place completely! Being able to use the Dine About Town option was awesome since it's rather pricey and not some place that I would normally go to. They brought out an amuse bouche (deviled egg with rock shrimp) and a palate cleanser of rose petal jam in between courses too. I loved every bit of my meal (crab soup, halibut, & creme brulee) & so did my hubby (ceaser salad, steak, & chocolate mousse). I would DEFINITELY suggest foodies to check out this place!

review_1520.Review: 5A5 never disappoints, I've never experienced a bad meal here, and if it wasn't up to par, the managers always make sure you're satisfaction is guaranteed.

review_1521.Review: Excellent dinner! I brought my wife for her 30th birthday there and she LOVED it. We had never been there before and I was very happy that she enjoyed her experience. That isn't the sort of thing that you get a second chance on so my bet on 5A5 paid off wonderfully. It is a "must visit" place in the city. They certainly treated her right on her very special day!

review_1522.Review: Excellent for it's price compared to other more expensive steak houses

review_1523.Review: I had been wanting to check this place out for some time and almost veered off-course when I found out my fave restaurant Kokkari was right next door. I gave this place a shot. Ambience needs a facelift. This may have been considered "cool" in the 80's or 90's but lighting in main dining room needs some updating. Also, the open floor plan to bar & dining area does not help noise level (which was high). Finally, the restaurant was FREEZING so we needed to ask that manager lower air conditioning. Food was otherwise okay. Bacon-wrapped scallops were delish and bone-in rib eye was fabulous. Unfortunately, this is one of those "been there, done that" restaurants. For $250.00 for two people, there are a lot of other exciting options

review_1524.Review: Business dinner friendly - Pleasantly surprised by the "steak lounge" experience fearing a "hipster" mob. Food was very good with some eclectic options on the starters and sides. Beef was very good and the Wagyu mix tasty. The non-beef choices were respectable as we had a vegan with us.Wine selection was respectable as guests had differing pov's on Bordeaux Vs Russian River with good options for both sides. Good cocktails and deserts. Service was outstanding with very attentive staff and servers. Highly recommend for business dinner and good meeting spot near financial district and hotels.

review_1525.Review: It was my daughter's 16th Birthday and we had a great experience overall, food was delicious, service was great.

review_1526.Review: We enjoyed our dining experience. And look forward to going back

review_1527.Review: great went on a Sunday night so it was quiet! waygu f1 filet like butter! shrooms to die for!

review_1528.Review: The food was excellent and we were so impressed with the staff and making us feel so special.

review_1529.Review: I would not recommend, too expensive for average Steak. Side dish Cream spinach has good favor but the Marble potatoes just boiled mini potatoes with skin on, taste skin more than its potatoes. We order carrot cake for dessert, it has no spice taste, just like a small piece of muffin top with cream cheese,it cost 9$, that's unacceptable.

review_1530.Review: Awesome steak. Bone in ny with mush sauce and onions

review_1531.Review: PROS - The dark atmosphere works, the ceiling you see in the pictures really is cool. The steaks are cooked perfectly , and there's a respectable variety of steak cuts, non steak entrees and sides. Also, cocktail prices are reasonable, the bar won't gouge you.CONS - Service was NOT up to standard for this level of restaurant. They brought out the wrong dishes to us, then came back and brought them to a different table AFTER I had poked the steak (with my finger) and even told the server I had. REALLY??? The server started out great, then dissapeared for 20-25 minutes when we had finished - leaving our empty plates on the table for that whole time.OVERALL - Give 5A5 a whirl if you have the wallet to gamble on the service.

review_1532.Review: Was great, they were so sweet for my friends birthday they wrote out happy birthday in chocolate and gave her an amazing dessert!

review_1533.Review: Overall, I couldn't be happier, food was top notch, service was great, I will DEFINITELY come again!!!!!!!!!

review_1534.Review: Excellent food, boneless ribeye cooked exactly to my specification, although the peppercorn sauce was a bit overpowering...will try one of the other steaks next time. Liked the complimentary samples, and the lime palate cleanser was a nice touch. Service was fantastic, helpful and friendly. Only real downside was the noise. Also they ran out of the Malbec I ordered and the Italian wine (can't remember the name) they recommended instead was not to my liking. But overall a great experience - I will definitely be back.

review_1535.Review: The menu was so good it was difficult to make a decision. Also, the entire waitstaff was helpful and friendly!

review_1537.Review: Oustanding steak restaurant with great service.

review_1538.Review: Excellent service to match very good food. Loved the bacon bread!!

review_1539.Review: The meal was great. Not a single complaint. The options are a bit eclectic but that is what makes it!!!

review_1540.Review: Food and service were excellent. Lounge atmosphere of the dining area is unique and a little noisy due to its proximity to the bar, but we loved it. We would definitely recommend.

review_1541.Review: The steak is superb and the vegetarian I was with feasted on a combination of the excellent salads and sides. Pacing was perfect and the overall service was the best that I have experienced in a long time. The waiter went out of his way at the end of the meal to flag a cab for us.

review_1542.Review: I've been to 5A5 three times. The first time the steaks were to die for! Absolutely delicious. The side orders were also excellent. I became an evangelist for 5A5 encouraging all my friends to patronize it. Unfortunately, my experience the 2nd time, particularly the 3rd time, was very disappointing. The steaks were bland, tough, & frankly speaking inedible. When I told the waiter, he kinda just looked at me, and said okay. Nothing was done to remedy the situation and no attempt was made to satisfy me. I got charged as normal. Something must have happened in the past few months that has caused 5A5's quality to go down. I'm hearing the same from others. I won't go back until I know things have improved. Oh, one more thing, the service is slow

review_1543.Review: Outstanding prime rib 100 % better than House of Prime Rib.The service is excellant.We highly recommend the best food

review_1544.Review: Great steak. Arguably the best in SF

review_1545.Review: Overall a good experience but probably would not recommend or come back as two of the three steaks ordered were flavorful but sadly way overlooked (medium rare was bordering on medium well) For a steakhouse and $40 steaks this is nott acceptable especially in an area with so many great dining options to choose from.. The alacarte sides were very good especially the truffle fries (which just might be enough to bring me back for fries/starters and a drink at the bar. Service was very good and should be noted server offered to bring us new steaks but there would be a 30mi ute wait for our new steaks and half the party would be sitting there while the others ate.

review_1546.Review: one of the best kobe/wagu beef i have had.  top notch steak. great service.  treated my boyfriend wonderful for his birthday, we loved it!

review_1547.Review: Amazing dinner. We came here to celebrate our anniversary and left not only with a full stomach but great memories. The service was on point and the food...
