Well what can I say, nothing short of perfect. The lobster tail tempura is a must! You can't leave without it. Overall grea restaurant, will go back!

review_1548.Review: This was just ok for the price point. I have had better service and steak. It was also a little loud.

review_1549.Review: had a great time, the food was fantastic and our waiter Ryan topped it all off!

review_1550.Review: Absolutely great experience except for how loud the bar area was and it made eating in the dining area next to it unpleasant.

review_1551.Review: Everything was great...but the steak!!! This place is supposed to be known for their preparation of Wagyu beef. The menu described it as "melt in your mouth". Maybe it was that good, but I couldn't get past the charred tasted on the outside to enjoy it. I will say that the lobster tempura, beet salad, and maguro shooters were amazing! Go for appetizers and skip the steak.

review_1552.Review: Not impressed with the prime rib I ordered.

review_1553.Review: I have been here several times and I have always been so pleased with my experience. The food, the service and the experience is just amazing and would recommend to anyone who wants a superb dining experience!

review_1554.Review: Everything was fabulous from the server to the menu. The steaks were flavorful, all of the sides were tasty. I would recommend the shooters. They really different but combined great flavors. It was a birthday and they gave us a cool chocolate decorated plate with cake.

review_1555.Review: It was a hip and modern take on a steakhouse. The decor was definitely nightclub inspired. The food was good, the portions very generous. The service was excellent.

review_1556.Review: Steak was as good or better than anything I have had in the great steak restaurants in NY and the Mid-West.

review_1557.Review: Great food, excellent service and a vibrant energy level.

review_1558.Review: Great steak. Very good wine list. Excellent service.

review_1559.Review: The deco and atmosphere is good but the food was just ok and I feel like it's over priced for it's food quality. The receptionist isn't really friendly too. I don't think I will come back next time.

review_1560.Review: This has to be one of the best restaurants in San Francisco.

review_1561.Review: 5A5 has become one of our favorite date night spots. We always try a new dish when we are here. I had the prime rib. The garlic mustard rub made the dish. Prime rib beat that at The House of Prime Rib. My husband had the filet mignon. It wasn't even Wagyu but the beef melted like butter in our mouths. Loved the Lychee Martini as well.

review_1562.Review: Pretty easy to make a res. Convenient parking. Not too crowded. Good food and service. Just a tiny bit chilly in there so dress warm :-)

review_1563.Review: Great ambience but food was just okay. Not okay as in average. Just okay as far as Top Notch food goes. Just wasn't spectacular. I wouldn't say no to going again but I wouldn't exactly rush out to go again. I think the waiter did an excellent job of up selling an expensive appetizer that was REALLY just so-so. Maybe that's what really sticks to mind when I think of this place now.

review_1564.Review: waiter dumped tabasco sauce on me, won't be going back.

review_1565.Review: This was my first time there.This was the first time in many years - that every dish we ordered was prepared to perfection. The chefs knew how to prepare shellfish andof course the steaks ---Even though it is a steakhouse -- I am planning on my next visit - to orderas many of the starters,appetisers and side -- and not a serious entree.The Mac and cheese with truffle oil is a must - as well as the lobster tempura.For those who want to sink their teeth in a properly cooked marbled steak - I do recommendthe bone-in ribeye-- and for a little thinner steak - then the bone-in filet if on the special. The bone-in filet - is the filet side of a porterhouse with the bone.that night.This is a restaurant for foodies.

review_1566.Review: OMG- excellent! The food was so good that everyone in our group fell silent in awe. The bites and starters were tasty and balanced. We enjoyed the truffled mac and cheese side as well as the mushrooms. If my fillet was not the best one I have ever eaten, I cannot remember any other fillet that was any bit better.

review_1567.Review: 2 young adults were in our group of 7. 2 beef sliders were ordered and both requested Well Done. The orders came extremely rare. They were sent back and two new entrees were prepared. By the time they came back to the table the rest of the group was finished with our meals. They were then wrapped up to go. This was not a good dining experience. Especially when they did not honor the request of how the meat was to be cooked.

review_1568.Review: The service was superb...from Amy greeting us at the bar to Shea handling my coat and our reservations at the door. This place i a class act. The food borders on spectacular and the ambiance, though contemporary is not overdone. Thanks! ~steveT

review_1569.Review: I always enjoy eating at this restaurant; the servers are very attentive. the food is great it has a wonderful ambiance.

review_1570.Review: Took a while to get our food but it was well worth it.

review_1571.Review: Nice interior decor and presentation of food, but it's very loud inside! Too difficult to hear conversations around the large tables.

review_1572.Review: The restaurant was extremely accomodating as I had originally made reservations for 2 and on the day of the reservation I called and they were able to make it a table for 3.Food was excellent.We started with the chicken yakitori and the lobster tempura which were devine. The main courses were excellent. I cannot wait to come back!

review_1573.Review: Excellent steak LOUNGE tending more toward the Lounge than the steakhouse..... Service was especially good Tuesday night. $20 corkage fee was very generous allowing us to bring in a very special bottle of Domaine Serene Pinot Noir.

review_1574.Review: Pricey for what you get. Fun atmosphere, but at the end of the day you go for the food, and the food here was comparable to a mid-market steak chain.

review_1575.Review: Great stakes, very innovative menu. great Ambiance.

review_1576.Review: Let me start by saying that the service was impeccable. My water glass was never empty, and it didn't take much more than a look to get the waiter's attention. However, the Bone-In Filet did leave something to be desired. Filets are generally a lean cut of meat, but the bone in Filet seemed to have a significant amount of fat in it. Not marble...fat. Definitely not the quality of meat I would expect at a finer steakhouse. Nevertheless, I would go back and order the filet (no bone), as I did see the cut at an adjacent table. The ambiance of the restaurant was very romantic, and despite the disappointment with the steak, the night was an overall success.

review_1577.Review: We ate at this restaurant and I thought it was a bit pretentious and overrated. We ordered sides to go with the meat and they forgot to make them. They gave us free dessert wine as an apology -- but really I would have like the sides. The decor seemed like it was trying too hard - fancy but a little too much, could have used a good editor.

review_1578.Review: Celebrated a 2 year anniversary here. My girlfriend and I had already peeked at the menu before arriving so we already had an idea of what to get. The drinks we started off with were delicious. i believe my girlfriend got the lychee martini and I can't seem to remember the name of mine. Our server, Linh, was super friendly and nice. She gave great recommendations because they ended up being what my girlfriend and I had planned to order! Venue was beautiful, food and drinks were delicious, service was awesome, and noise level was kept to a minimum so we were able to enjoy the evening!

review_1579.Review: i just cant fathom why a steak would need a sauce other than butter. my t-bone steak was not only not seared as I requested but it came slathered in this cheesy butter sauce that totally overpowered the flavor of the meat. the sides(macaroni, bacon and potatoes) were better than the steak. plus, i wasn't even full afterwards. i wouldn't call this place a steakhouse. the menu seems more concerned with other culinary fusions, primarily japanese.

review_1580.Review: Good not great. Service and atmosphere were awesome. Thought the steaks themselves would be better. They were just ok. Shooters were great.

review_1581.Review: We went on a Wednesday we a group of friends to have dinner and some drinks. the food was incredible but we expected to be more crowded and being able to join the lounge afterwards, but it was empty.Amazing food and service. Would love to go back on a Friday or Saturday to enjoy the lounge.

review_1582.Review: Had been there several times in the past.....last night food was way below average and service was totally unprofessional, bordering on absurd.

review_1583.Review: On a Monday evening - quiet, relaxed atmosphere with decent service, which, considering the relatively few cusotmers was lacking for an upscale restaurant. The half price on the wines was very attractive but since I was driving, we could not take advantage of the offer. Where this restaurant lacks is in the food.Chicken Yakitori appetizer seemd like it was warmed over and some Japanese sauce poured over. I had the special, a bone in filet - overcooked and no flavor. My wife had the sea-bass and again, no flavor. Very disappointing. The cheddar cheese potatoes was overcooked.

review_1584.Review: Very loud, poor service, too few servers for the entire restaurant, way to expensive for food quality, ambience and service. It felt like eating $45 dollar steak at denny's, will not recommend for any romantic or a quite dinner, find another place for a special occasion or a romantic dinner

review_1585.Review: Best steaks in the Universe and all the other places too. Service was outstanding and the ambience was tip top uber contemporary. I will be returning a few times before I leave San Francisco. The waitress even charged my dieing cell phone. This place is absolutely champion

review_1586.Review: Always a perfect meal. Steaks are cooked to perfection and service is great. I always come here when in town.

review_1587.Review: Wine list is over priced, but great place.

review_1588.Review: We had several service issues during our meal & felt the restaurant was painfully loud (we're young professionals & aren't overly sensitive). It was NOT a good date spot. Excited by the menu & reviews, we ordered a few shooters, Kobe beef sashimi, lobster tempura & grilled prawns as our small plates, but they brought them ALL at once, crowding our tiny table & making us feel rushed. Who wants to shove $100 worth of apps in their mouth like that? Then there were wine issues, our steak wasn't cooked the way we wanted it, was mediocre ($68!) & was missing the seared foie gras we ordered. For that price point, it ranks lowest of restaurants we've tried in the city (& that's a lot).

review_1589.Review: appetizers were off the hook however,service spot on, ambiance noisy but hip and now, the steak the main reason we went there was just ok, I had the Kobe steak at 20 bucks per ounce and honestly it was not better than a regular steak at Ruths Chris, and this is from an Exec chef and my dining companions felt the same.

review_1590.Review: The cocktails, food, and dessert are truly outstanding.

review_1591.Review: This place was amazing we went on Valentines day and they had a fixed menu at 95 per persionfor 4 courses. The choises were great and the portions were just right didn't go home hungry and not super stuffed. And let me tell you this was one of the best steaks I've ever had it was like butter and they was just the regular steak Yumm. I plan on going back just to see the real menu. If you want to treat yourself to SF fine dineing and still be able to have fun wile there then 5A5 is the place to go.

review_1592.Review: We went to 5A5 for Valentine's Day 2012 and we are extremely disappointed with our experience, to say the least. I had made a reservation nearly 6 weeks before, received numerous confirmation calls from the restaurant, and not once was I informed that it would be a prefix menu. It was an upsetting surprise when we sat down for dinner as we had already picked out what we wanted from their regular menu. We had no choice but to pick items from a 4-course menu that we did not care for. Worse yet, considering the price of the dinner, I thought the quality and creativity of the food was mediocre at best. I'd love to go into detail, but there aren't enough characters. The only saving grace was the Wagyu beef, our champagne, and a nice waitress.

review_1593.Review: we love the menu at 5A5, however I would not recommend the prixfix menu if it can be avoided. the service is still excellent, and tge experience is quite enjoyable, but the choices were not some of the best from their regular dinner menu, which was a little disappointing.

review_1594.Review: Service was good. Food was OK. There was a cool breeze from the A/C that made us wear our jackets while dining. I think it was Valentine day so they didn't want people too comfortable since they were booked all night. Don't think it was really worth the $200+ for the both of us. O'well, Probably won't make it back here again.

review_1595.Review: Topped off my Valentines Day with a very good dinner. Would I say it was the best? No, but it was close to it...The waiter was great with a good sense of humor and was very attentive with suggestions. He made the evening smooth and enjoyable. The rib eye steak was cooked to perfection but lacked flavor. Everythting else was outstanding and the pre- fix menu was great, but not cheap at $95.00 a person, although it was Valentine Day.

review_1596.Review: Very nice atmosphere!! 5 stars! Unfortunatly the food didn't live up to the price. :( Good food, not great. But Great food pricing. Wouldn't mind going back for cocktails and appetizers but probably won't go back for dinner again.

review_1597.Review: pumpkin bread putting and hamachishooter is awesome but everythingelse is just average. do not order the Mac n cheese!!

review_1598.Review: I was celebrating a birthday with a friend who also was celebrating a birthday. Our food choices were well prepared although the sea bass was a little cool. The kitchen fixed it right away. The portions were good and the food was very tasty, especially the barbequed ribs and sea bass. The foie gras was delicious. The bar was very busy and loud so we opted to sit away from the action upstairs. There it was cozy and atmospheric with python printed banquettes and mood lighting. We were each given a dessert on a beautifully decorated plate with Happy Birthday and our names. Not an inexpensive meal but a good dining experience.

review_1599.Review: Great for foodies, steak AND non steak eaters, everyone will love it! Seabass calamari dish was seasoned and cooked perfectly beet salad was gorgeous. Wagyu appertizer, prime rib & creamed spinach stunned the steak eaters. Mo one missed the house of prime rib that night!

review_1600.Review: fantastic as always.......best steakhouse in the city

review_1601.Review: I've been to my fair share of steak houses, but this was one of the best steaks I have ever had. I highly recommend 5A5 Steak Lounge.

review_1602.Review: First of all, the service is beyond stellar. Our waiter was actually an integral and welcome part of the overall dining experience.  The perfect combination of helpfulness, personableness and attentiveness.  He was knowledgeable without being pretentious and attentive without being overbearing. Secondly, the food is some of the best the City has to offer. Everything we had (bacon wrapped scallops, filet mignon, lamb) was interesting and flavorful. I can't say enough good things about 5A5. Highly, highly recommend.

review_1603.Review: Perfect steaks and enjoyed the modern atmosphere!

review_1604.Review: Excellent service from the moment we entered the door. Our waitress was extremely helpful in picking the perfect wine. The manager even acknowledged the celebration of the birthday being celebrated. Would definitely recommend to others and will return.

review_1605.Review: DAT all the way here. The Ribeye was awesome and big, my wife could not eat hers. It still tasted good the next night after a day in the fridge.

review_1606.Review: For the Dine About Town menu, simply amazing for the value. Had impeccable service. Didn't get the wine flight , but should have. Would come here again.

review_1607.Review: Great Dine About Town selections. Steaks were perfect. Very busy yet relaxing atmosphere. Service was outstanding, not stuffy. We will recommend this restaurant to all of our out of town guests.

review_1608.Review: I ordered medium rare steak but it was cooked a little too much and the steak was overall dry. I wouldn't come back for the steak (sad, since 5A5 is called 5a5 STEAK house) but the other dishes were pretty good (truffled mac and cheese, truffle fries, daikon soup).

review_1609.Review: Great steak lounge with a hint of Asian influence. I ate here for the Dine about Town and had the Ribeye. It was delicious! I'd definitely do the soup over the salad since it is something different. The service was great and so was the overall feel of the restaurant.

review_1611.Review: A wonderful dining experience from the ambiance to the food and impeccable service. The chef is a master at his craft. Everything we had was amazing. The rib-eye steak was aged and cooked to perfection. The cod melts in you mouth like butter. The Foie Gras is very tasty and is complimented with a fuji apple salad...delicious. Loved it and would return over and over.

review_1612.Review: Awesome food in a very sophisticated setting!!! All I can say is A-mazing! We will definitely be back...

review_1613.Review: Went there on DAT and thought the food was wonderful...had the romaine salad (large size), the rib eye, which was removed from the bone and the chocolate ???? which was sooooo good. I was surprised we did not feel rushed as it was crowded....Couldn't recommend it more.

review_1614.Review: The noise level was so high that we could not carry on a conversation with the couple dining with us. I would recommend this restaurant to people who only want to eat and not socialize.

review_1615.Review: The meal was very good but the service was outstanding.

review_1616.Review: This was a really good find-- good food and good service. I had the daikon soup, ribeye steak, and the chocolate mousse cake, all of which were DELICIOUS. The venue was also really comfortable and trendy. I would certainly return and recommend this restaurant to others!

review_1617.Review: My wife and I went their for our anniversary and it was just the perfect spot. It was a Thursday night and the restaurant was filled with a buzz at the bar that reminded us of our NYC dating days. We were given an intimate table that was quiet enough where we could talk yet close enough to the buzz that we still felt like part of the scene. The food was amazing. We were even given a special "Happy Anniversary" cake for dessert which was greatly appreciated. I highly recommend 5A5 for any occasion. It is fun and the food is fantastic.

review_1618.Review: The food was good. The service was average. The salads arrived minutes after the complimentary amuse bouche with no room on the table to set the salads. There was no room for both amuse bouche and salads on the table. The servers did not help or try to make room. So some of us barely had a chance to eat the amuse bouche before giving it back to make room for the salads on table. After the salad, there was about 15 minutes gap before the main course arrived. We knew it would take time for the steaks but they could have timed serving of the salads better so it was not rushed at the beginning then with a long wait for the main.

review_1619.Review: Decided to try it during Dine About Town. Food was very good, and the service was excellent. They provide some amuse-bouches before each plate which was very nice. The servings were very generous. I was impressed enough to want to go back and try their full menu.

review_1620.Review: In our party of four, we all ordered steaks. We were mostly pleased with our steaks, except that my brother ordered his rare and I ordered mine rare-plus. My steak came out exactly the way I wanted, but my brother's came out about medium, which is not what he wanted. We ended up trading, so it worked out, but it would be nice to have gotten exactly what we wanted. The bacon wrapped scallops were great, too. Also, the pistachio cake was unique. Great Dine About Town menu!

review_1621.Review: Service was very good. We ate here during Dine About Town and the restaurant was full, but servers managed it well. We were not rushed and the servers were knowledgable. Would be pricey during non-Dine About Town time of year, but normal for a high-end steak house (sides priced separately, etc).

review_1622.Review: We had a great dinner and great service. The only negative comment is the space is a little cold and too confusing with all of the decorative shapes and lighting.

review_1623.Review: This was my first time at the restaurant and it was really nice. Service was excellent. Food was delicious, although a bit rich for my stomach. All in all a great experience.

review_1624.Review: I wanted to like this place, but everything was just good, nothing stellar. The decor is nice. We were seated in the center of the room. The chairs were comfortable but the room was rather drafty. Food:The amuse bouche chawanmushi (steamed egg) with crab meat was overly salty.The truffled fries were really good, the iceberg wedge salad was okay but hardly seems 'fine dining' since it's just two hunks of lettuce with some thousand island dressing on top. We had the rib eye steak, which was flavorful, but the texture was more tough than tender. My friend requested rare but the rare looked practically the same as the medium. However, dessert was easily the best part of the meal. Probably will not return.

review_1625.Review: If a hip night club mated with a Asian Steakhouse, this would be there baby. The music is loud and ambiance is dizzying. The food is well plated and of course exciting.

review_1626.Review: This was my second time here, my first was for a business dinner and the second was for my GF's birthday...5A5 is more than suitable for both types of occasions, my review here is from my most recent visit with my girlfriend since it wasn’t quite the free-for-all my business dinners end up turning into.  I had a 9:30pm reservation on a Friday, used the valet and were seated promptly on arrival.I came back to 5A5 for the bison which is unfortunately no longer on the menu, and for someone who does not typically eat red meat, I find the bison to be nice alternative to the fattier cuts my more carnivorous friends enjoy on the regular. I find myself only eating red meat at ‘upscale’ steakhouses like 5A5 where I know the meat has been cared f

review_1627.Review: The service was exceptional as was everything we ordered. While there was such a flurry of activity among the staff who were all attentive and accomodating we never once felt rushed or that their presence was an intrusion- what a remarkable balance they have struck. The menu is diverse and the spin on the dishes provides a contemporary and ecclectic menu. If we visit SF again, it would make our to do list for sure.

review_1628.Review: Very tasty food - had the DAT menu, which was a great deal. We had the 12oz ribeye and 8oz kalbi strip. We also ordered a side of mushrooms, which sounded better on the menu but in the end the exotic medley tasted pretty uniform and a bit too similar to the shiitake on my ribeye. It also came with two types of bread, one studded with bacon, an amuse bouche of chawanmushi, and a palate cleanser. The best part though was the dessert, in particular the multi-layer chocolate mousse cake was amazing, esp. with all the extra bits accompanying it. The pistachio cake was also a pleasant surprise, much better than I expected.

review_1629.Review: The steaks we order deserve 5 stars, how ever, the side dish we had: "Sautee Swiss lark" was too salty. Staffs are friendly.Nice ambiance and dinning room layout.

review_1630.Review: I came here with a group of five, I don't recommend really big groups since it's a pretty small dining area with fixed seating and booths. There is a very nice big party room for 20 plus downstairs. I really liked the service, the wait staff was very attentive and they explained the menu very well. The bar area is very too, with good five dollar drinks and wine. There are also plenty of appetizers and bar food where you can sample the menu to see if you like the place for a fraction of the actual me u price.

review_1631.Review: Waited about 40 minutes for our table even with reservations. Wagyu was tender but flavoring overpowering; not as good as last time. Was looking forward to the evening, but overall, disappointed.

review_1632.Review: Went for Dine About Town. Ordered the DAT menu and also ordered one appetizer and one side. I know they were packed, but my only gripe is that we waited an hour and fifteen minutes between the time we sat down and the time we were eating our entrees. WAY too long! The stars of the meal were actually the desserts (pistachio cake and chocolate mousse gourmand) and the swiss chard side dish. Everything else tasted good but those items stood out.

review_1633.Review: My friend and I were on a search for the best steak in San Francisco. We didn't find it here. Good steak, but not great. Poor beer selection. Waiter was an "interrupter" meaning he would approach the table and start addressing us when we were in the middle of a conversation. He was over attentive and interrupted our conversation several times. Waiters in nice places like this should develop a sense of timing with the customers so that they don't feel interrupted mid-sentence.I was disappointed with the sides, a little plate of mac n cheese and mashed potatoes. $10 each. Simply way too pricey for what you get.The place is pretty, elegant, classy though, but not enough to recommend the place over other restaurants. Sorry.

review_1634.Review: A true find for any serious carnivore. Amazing cuts of beef, cooked to perfection. You can cut the filet with a fork. The waitstaff is attentive and very helpful.

review_1635.Review: I chose a DAT 3-course menu with sides: 1)clear and tasty daikon with mushroom soup; 2)beautifully seared cod; 3) ribs and chips, ribs cooked to perfection, falls off the bone when forked, delicious and finger licking good. 4)truffle fries were over-rated. 5)muffin pistachio cake, served warm and light. This was a nice ending to a delicious meal. I was surprised to find that the restaurant served an amuse bouche and an intermezzo even on a DAT menu. They were not skimby;we were served perfect portions at reduced prices. The wait staff was attentive, friendly, and professional. The large dining room was spacious and comfortable. The decor and ambiance were striking. Overall, I was very satisfied and I will definitely return.

review_1636.Review: Tried with the Dine around town. It is definitely good value, and the food is very well prepared, the service is of high standard. The regular menu is not "cheap", but well worth the money. Very happy with the experience.

review_1637.Review: the steak dinner was fabulous. it helped us forget about the overcooked shrimp we ordered as an appitizer.

review_1638.Review: The food was delicious and while they did have some very unique menu items, they weren't too weird as sometimes can be found at high end restraunts. They had a very unique cocktail menu as well.

review_1639.Review: Great experience, food was outstanding from the bread with pieces of bacon to the sushi shooters to the octopus salad (which two could share) to the steak everything was delicious. The atmosphere is cool and hip. I was told they stop serving dinner at 9:00 and then the place turns into a club, could definitely see that happening but didn't experience it. Will be back.

review_1640.Review: I took my boyfriend here for his birthday. The service was excellent, the food was good and I did like the look of the place, really cool. It was pretty sleepy since it was a Monday night, so I'd love to come back when the place is hopping. Also, the staff went the extra mile since it was a bday, and I appreciate it.

review_1641.Review: I guess I just had high expectations after reading all the 4-5 star reviews. We had great Valet parking. Didn't have to wait long for our table. We had a party of 3....we hung out at the bar for drinks and oysters. Server at the bar was awesome. Server at our table was awesome. No complaints on Service. My only disappointment was the food. We were recommended a 30 oz. Tomahawk Bone in aged Rib Eye. Waiter kept saying it was his favorite. We waited a long time for it so we were expecting it to be very very good. We were so disappointed when it came. The steak temperature was warm. I am use to eating a really hot juicy steak. This dry aged rib eye did not have any flavor to me. Sorry, I hate leaving bad reviews.

review_1642.Review: we did know of 5A5 and ended up there when we could not get into kokkari.But we had a wonderful experience there and very much want to make it a regular spot for special occasions.

review_1643.Review: This was a great dining experience. Everything was exceptional and the atmosphere was very lively and fun. I will differently be coming back and would recommend it to anyone.

review_1644.Review: Its swanky and has a great bar scene while you wait and on weekends nice dj sounds with a fine dining experience of outstanding steaks and great service

review_1645.Review: Excellent and creative food. Great interpretation of old standards plus many unexpected surprises!

review_1646.Review: I would dine at 5A5 anytime I have the chance - the service was impeccable from the greeting to the bill....and the food was outstanding! I recommend the special 9OZ filet - the meat actually would melt in your mouth. The ambiance is like a snazzy but comfortable Las Vegas bar and lounge, with great food! Try the Lobster Tempura for an opener - fantastic!

review_1647.Review: Never had a bone-in Ribeye that was on the tough side until this visit. Flavorful, but on the tough side. Service was good, but our waitress seemed like she was on 'automatic' and not personalble.

review_1648.Review: Wonderful meats cooked perfectly. Nice place for a couple or group. This is not a place to rush a meal. As they tell you right away, the streaks will take a while to cook. They pace the appetizers accordingly. Fun place with great food. Pricey, but quite tasty. Nice that they have quality wine at all price levels.

review_1649.Review: Our waiter, Damiel, was the best waiter we.d ever had in our lives

review_1650.Review: The food was brought out in a timely manner. I was thoroughly impressed by the service!

review_1651.Review: I wouldn't go back. Dinner was ok, service was good but quite slow. Watch out, they press quite hard to upsell you on dishes. And if you're not clear on the price - ASK. Unfortunately we had a few surprises on the check, our fault for not clarifying. Best tasting steak of the night was the NY strip... and we had tried the ribeye, the wagyu... scallop starter was fantastic!

review_1652.Review: Wonderful everything! Our server Ryan was fantastic. Our dinner was amazing. The steaks were cooked to perfection. We will be telling all of our family and friends thatchy must dine here.

review_1653.Review: great service, good dinner environment. fairly noise but it doesn't feel annoying. rather, it feels like a great place for friends gathering. however, foods are so so. they are comparable with restaurants that cost half of what ate being offered at 5a5. for great steak, i would highly recommend everyone to dine at Alexander instead :( for friendly group dinning environment, 5a5 is not bad at all.BTW, we called a week ago for a Saturday reservation for 8. we were told that nothing is available unless we can make it at 5:30. we arrived a few min before 5:30, waited half an hour to be seated. during the 2 hours we spent there, almost half of the restaurant is empty...however, we all got good parking spaces since we arrived early, so it waso

review_1654.Review: Came here to enjoy a romantic dinner, and it was anything but... Food was pretty good, but it did not meet the dining experience ambiance I was hoping for.

review_1655.Review: We went there for the first time and everything started good but after ordering it took over an hour to get our food, server hardly checked up on us. All in all it was an ok experience but i'd think twice before going back.

review_1656.Review: Overall experience was outstanding, thanks to our waiter (I wish I knew his name).

review_1657.Review: Food was fabulous, however very rich. Very chic bar and restaurant. Service was professional and unobtrusive. Would definitely go again.

review_1658.Review: Good appetizers, steak and sides came to the table cold. Too loud. will not be returning to this place

review_1659.Review: Very true to its purpose - this is a steak house, so don't expect the breadth of extras that other venues offer. The meat is incredible, not a chain production but an honest passion for doing meat right. Our sides could have been more done, green beans were too tough, but he sauces and flavors were great.Service was as close to perfect as it comes.Good bar service, and really good wine list. Not overly extensive but wonderfully paired to the menu.

review_1660.Review: After getting seating at about 8.20 pm, our orders were not put in till 8.50 pm. We waited forever for our server to appear and had to flag down other servers to get him. And when we finally got him and ordered; bread came but waters and drinks did not get to us for another 15 minutes.We got our mains at bout 9.35 and by then we were so hungry, we filled up on bread and truffle fries so we barely got to enjoy the mains and left more than 50% of each on the plate. Food was of great quality, well prepared & served timely..I informed our server that I wanted to order the choc dessert with a birthday msg but he ends up remembering the Birthday part on a complimentary dessert but never did serve the dessert I specifically requested.

review_1661.Review: We went on a Saturday night, 7:00 pm. Service was extremely good, prime rib was excellent, served just as we requested. They make an authentic Caesar salad with Romaine lettuce, Spanish anchovies and excellent dressing. We split both salad and meat, which they willing did, for no extra charge. Some of the starters and side dishes were not to our taste (either a little too salty or too spicy), but they were fresh, and excellently prepared. We were the oldest people, by 20 years, in the restaurant (which was almost completely filled), so our taste for the side dishes may not reflect a younger crowd. I am writing this review because I have seen a lot of negative reviews about the service or the food, and I wanted to add our perspective

review_1662.Review: Great food, service and overall experience!

review_1663.Review: Lots of delicious options if you don't want steak. BUT the steak is fabulous.

review_1664.Review: Average food. Alexander's is better place for the same price.

review_1665.Review: Was given. $250 gift certificate from a friend had a chance to try a lot of things. Everything was way over priced and portions were small. Wagyu beef prices were exorbitant. Steak and prime rib were very fatty. Not worth the money - glad I didn't ave to pay.Most diners came in dressed too casual so it doesn't make the experience special.

review_1666.Review: Great steaks but they use grain-fed as opposed to grass-fed, too bad. Great selections and well displayed. While I will be back, three things kept this from getting more stars:1. Steaks were slightly overcooked (we had a party of 10 and that was a common comment among the group.2. Great sauces but a terrible mistake of pour it all over the meat. The flavor of the steak was lost to showcase the sauce. On the side would have been perfect, it didn't need to swim in it.3. Side dishes were an afterthought, at best. The Au Gratin potatoes where hardened and the three orders on the table where uneaten.They do a lot right but they could benefit with the details.

review_1667.Review: The Japanese steak is fantastic at 5A5.  I have been back several times just to get the rib cap.  The only problem I have is with the traditional steak.  They find it necessary to drown the beef in sauces and gravy even when the cut is fine the way it is.  Ask them to leave the sauce on the side.

review_1668.Review: We ordered the 10oz Filet added foie gras on the top, the Filet is dried and juiceless. The meat quality is really bad. The waiter Ryan told us the filet is good but ended up with disappointment. Lucky the foie gras tasted okay. We also ordered the Lamb Duo and it came on the table the same way as the Filet, I guess the chef is not on duty today? Totally unsatisfied with the quality and I can't believe I can only get this quality for the price I paid. The only dish I was satisfied that night was the Sashimi Kobe which requires no cooking.

review_1669.Review: The food was delicious. I loved the truffle fries! The dessert was also delicious.

review_1670.Review: Between the food & the service...it's the closest description to heaven I will EVER be able to give. The filet melted in my mouth. The bacon bread was to die for. The himachi shooter was fabulous. We left here filled to the brim & completey satisfied. So satisfied infact, we haven't been able to talk about anything else.Not kidding. This place is excellent. If you're not hungry - hit the bar - their drinks are well worth the prices. The Bramble On & the spiced pear are my top drink suggestions....the bartender really knows how to pour a drink. Keep on being amazing, 5A5.

review_1671.Review: Love love love this place because the service is great., the restaurant is pretty and the food is great ;)

review_1672.Review: I don't eat red meat, so this was a mistake on my part. But, for the price, I expected the food to be better. I wasn't impressed with the food or atmosphere. It wasn't poor quality, just too pricey for food I did not find absolutely delicious. My sister insists we were paying for the ambiance. Frankly, I go to a restaurant for the food. Atmosphere was a little too noisy for me.

review_1673.Review: I hadn't been to 5A5 for happy hour before. Since a friend started working in the neighborhood I decided to check it out. The bar staff are friendly and the happy hour deals are solid - highly recommended! We moved onto dinner, which I've had before. Though I've usually gone for the A5 steaks and this time were trying to be more budget conscious. I tried the bone in ribeye. It is ENORMOUS. I could barely finish a quarter of it. The sauce is rich and it's definitely hearty. Had the brussel sprouts, which was a first and the mash with candied bacon, which is a personal favorite. We also had a bottle of wine, which at half price on Monday's is a steal. Daniel the waiter gave a great recommendation on the wine. I'll be back on Mondays!

review_1674.Review: Go here if you're looking for:* A trendy steakhouse that's unlike the traditional stuffy steakhouses (you know which one)* A great variety of meats -- from buffalo, to tomahawk ribeyes, to of course their re-knowned wagyus.* A terrific array of wines (the Russian River Pinot rocked)* A great vibeSome of the must haves:* Hamachi shooters* Lobster Tempura* Shishiso (sp?) peppers* Mac & Cheese* Banana bread Pudding* Any of their wagyu beef (you can't eat a whole lot -- it's like foi gras)* Foi Gras* Any of the ribeyes

review_1675.Review: It was my first time going here. The food was excellent. I would like to go back but given the cost ($166 for two people), it will have to wait for a special event.

review_1676.Review: There are very few good steakhouses in SF; this is not one of them. The food is salty- I want to say it has almost a Chinese food flavor. The presentation is average. They were out of some items (6pm on a week night?!?!) Better off going somewhere else if you want a solid steak. Maybe just check out the bar area for a pre-dinner cocktail; seems like a pretty good choice there

review_1677.Review: Wonderful food that is beautifully presented. Attractive decor. Attentive staff.

review_1678.Review: We had a group of 8 for dinner, and we were running late to the reservation - we let them know and got there an hour after we should have. Even arriving that late, we had to wait another hour to be seated.

review_1679.Review: Food is overpriced and not prepared well. The dishes are so overpowered by the preparation, that the flavor of the food does not come through. For a 150 piece of Wagyu steak, you don't want truffle oil and soy flavors overpowering the meat. The mashed potato side is covered in bacon fat to the point you simply can't taste potato. The kitchen has a very heavy hand with the seasoning that does not allow the expensive ingredients to speak for themselves.

review_1680.Review: Cool space. Took twenty minutes to get a cocktail but service improved after that. But the great food made up for the deafening noise levels. Were it not for slow service and a crushing noise level we would go back...but probably not give all the choices in SF.

review_1681.Review: Awesome food. Brilliant service. Inventive menus. Nice wines.What else ???

review_1682.Review: The staff and food was amazing! From the hostess, to the bartender to the Servers, the service was top knotch! The food was amazing and reasonably priced. Can't wait to go back!

review_1683.Review: Comfortable Fun Great selection. Food was fantastic large portions.

review_1684.Review: Good Food, nothing overly outstanding. We were a party of 4. Server was a mechanical,light speed verbal delivery of specials and little eye contact and we had the first seating of the evening! Why so rushed with only one table for her to serve at 5:30pm? Atmosphere was frenetic. I am just as interested in the dinning experience as the food and this lacked much positive experience. Wonderful desserts. Doubtful return from all of us.

review_1685.Review: steak cooked to perfection! hamachi shooters excellent. the mashed potatoes with the cubed maple glazed bacon were incredible. I couldn't stop eating the bacon. We had the pumpkin bread pudding for dessert, which I'm sure is seasonal...it was great. Everything was tasty!!

review_1686.Review: Excellent food. Knowledgable staff. Accomodatimg times.

review_1687.Review: Just as I read from previous reviews, the food was exceptional. The service was prompt, and our server was very helpful in introducing us to the concept as first-timers.

review_1688.Review: Service was fair, ordered a beer three times before I received it. The waiter left us alone mostly, which I prefer, but it was to the extreme of being absent.Food was adequate but nothing to rave about. I was really unimpressed with the price for the sea bass considering the small size.

review_1689.Review: food was good; portions smaller than previous visits; service agonizingly slow. Should not have taken over 3 hours to get through dinner; the only delays were our waiter disappearing for 20 or more minutes at a time. There was a good crowd; I don't know if the floor was understaffed, the kitchen or both; at this price point get your game on! With so many options in SF I don't think I'll be back.

review_1690.Review: Best steak! And the lobster tempura was to die for

review_1691.Review: Steaks were very fatty, not to my taste at all. Side dishes were described by our waiter as 'best to share' but when they arrived they were tiny, quite disappointing. 'Hot chocolate and cookies' desert was just odd, far too spicy and out of the four orders for our table, no one really enjoyed it. Appetizers were good but the menu just did not live up to expectations and with so many other steak houses that deliver so much more than this for similar pricing I don't think we would bother with 5A5 again. Service was very good and the setting was very nice but food a big disappointment.

review_1692.Review: Some very good wines. Steak was good but not spectacular, which is a bit of an issue for a steak restaurant.

review_1693.Review: One of the best meals I have ever had. This place was truly amazing.

review_1694.Review: Delicious meal! Really incredible bone-in steaks, nice sized (yummy!) sides. We had the shrooms, which was a surprising selection of assorted varieties, and a iceberg salad- classic and tasty but with big chunks of smoked bacon- nice touch, Monday nights offered a great surprise of 50% off all bottles of wine under 200.00, with a great selection to choose from. Made the still steep bill a little easier to face at the end of the meal. A delucious and fun date night out on the town.

review_1695.Review: Our food was delicious. We had the best cream corn we have ever ordered.

review_1696.Review: The best dining experience we have had in a very long time. Great restaurant with great food. Exceptional service!

review_1697.Review: Loved the Truffle Fries and the Mazuna salad with truffle vinaigrette, orange. and truffle cheese. It was difficult to eat the salad off the long narrow plate as pieces kept falling off the edge of the plate. It was very cold but when we asked the temperature was turned up to an acceptable degree.

review_1698.Review: Great for pre or after theater at 42nd Street Moon, just across the street.

review_1699.Review: It's always a treat to eat at 5A5. Great space and great food.

review_1700.Review: Low quality restaurant all around. Very slow service, inexperienced wait staff. Cold food, tables are about 3 inches too high (or seats too low) - can't believe ownership allows this to persist.

review_1701.Review: The service was amazing, food was delicious and out of this world. If your looking for a great resturant and steaks that absolutly melt in your mouth this is the place to try. You wont be disappointed. We went for a friends 27th birthday and made a comment in our reservation and they prepared an amazing desert for the birthday girl, something that I've never seen done before and was quite amazing.

review_1702.Review: Great food in a spec hip place. Some dishes are super pricey. The shooters are amazing.

review_1703.Review: We celebrating our anniversary at 5A5 and wewe had a lovely evening! The food was deliciousand we had wonderful service thanks toJim! I would highly recommend it!

review_1704.Review: Good food, but way over priced.

review_1705.Review: It was a good place to eat. Close to my hotel (Hilton). The services was good and the food was as expected.

review_1706.Review: Very good service. My companions seemed to enjoy their meals. My small filet was dry, cold and lacked taste. We ate under the dome and found it extremely hard to hear each other - while this was partly our age, it was clearly loud and hard to carry on a conversation.

review_1707.Review: Best steak I've had in a long time. Not cheap.

review_1708.Review: Went here over a holiday wknd and it was pretty quiet. That was to be expectes though given the time of our visit. We were one of three parties in the place but our service reflected that amd were treated like rockstars. wait staff was politely attentive, responsive and prompt, our food arrived hot fresh and delish. atmosphere is a little darker, loungey type feel. Very chic. Food was top notch, had the strip and the filet. Also, if you have the option, get the fried cheesecake dessert. Doesnt matter how full you are, make room fpr this one, its unreal.

review_1709.Review: An interesting experiment in steak house-Asian fusion...but each of the three main courses and 2 salads and sides that we had were covered with too much and too strong a dressing/topping...so the food itself was lost in the seasonings

review_1710.Review: Good for a group who wants to enjoy a decent meal, maybe special occasions but in SF there are too many better places to go for this. We decided to bring our own wine to dinner with us as the wine list left much to be desired (seems to be a part of the experience or intentional by the owner). They don't even have an espresso machine, so no after dinner cappuccino! The food was great and very tasty so we can't knock that but if you want to be considered the top of our list there needs to be a nice wine pairing followed by an after dinner libation/cappuccino. The bar scene left much to be desired as well with very limited selection on beverages and relying heavily on mixed cocktails to carry the bar. For the price go to Union Square!

review_1711.Review: Service was good, but food was not as good as I would have expected. Overpriced for the quality and taste of food. The filet mignon was tasteless and not warm, but the t-bone was pretty good. My bf had a separate table for his birthday because they could not accommodate more than 10 people per table without a $1200 minimum. His table service was very slow and it took almost an hour before the food arrived. As a result, his table received two free entrees, which was good. Everyone agreed that we would probably not come back to eat here again for a meal. However, happy hour drinks and appetizers are definitely worth it and we'll be back for that!

review_1712.Review: When you first walk in, you know you are in a nice establishment. The bar/lounge area was vibrant and the dining room vast and crowded with good people. The food was great. If you are in the mood for a steak, try the Dry Aged T-bone with the Bone Marrow sauce. Excellent! Can't wait to go back there and have it again.

review_1713.Review: The food was excellent, service was impeccable, and the decor was beautiful. I would definitely be returning to this place.Only thing is, when my husband asked the hostess to find us a good table because it was my birthday, she sat us right in front of the kitchen... and I mean right in front. We were there very early so it not because of the lack of options. However, she didn't make an issue out of it when we asked our server for a table change. After that though, everything was amazing.

review_1714.Review: Food was good, didn't expect the Buffalo steak to be completely covered with the mesquite rub.

review_1715.Review: Service was spotty at best. Took too long for waiter to take a drink order. Food was only ok kitchen seemed to have alot of problems that night. will not go back, it's San Francisco..too many other choices.

review_1716.Review: We ordered the seared foie gras and truffle fries to start. The foie gras was delicious - interesting, served over ricotta filled crepe drizzled with balsamic reduction and side of poached pears. Delicious. For our main course, we split a 25oz. rib eye. It was perfectly cooked, tasty and tender. We ordered shrooms and creamed corn as sides and they complemented the steak perfectly. The creamed corn had chorizo which added a nice kick. As good as the food was, the service was impeccable. It was our anniversary and we were treated very well. The complimentary choc tort for dessert with "happy 14th anniversary" beautifully scrolled on the plate with chocolate was a delightful surprise and a definite bonus. Very classy place.

review_1717.Review: Ceiling was eye-catching. Food was mediocre. Service did not meet the standard. Not sure if it was short-staffed that evening, I had to raise hands so many times for everything. Frankly, I got tired and grouchy. Good experience but will not return.

review_1718.Review: Celebrated my husband's birthday.The appetizers were amazing(hamachi & Maguro Shooters & lobster dumplings).For starters we had the truffle fries which were delicious & for dinner were shared the Shrooms & Hericot Vert which were also very good. I had the 6 oz filet mignon(very good) & my husband had the 4 oz Wagya(pricey at $20 an oz).His steak came out well done instead of med rare. We sent the steak back & was advised it would take another 20 minutes to cook a new one. It was very loud & could barely hear each other. The wait staff was great & the manager was very apologetic. For such a high class restaurant we should never have an issue with a $80 steak. But all in all it was a very nice place, would go back for a speacial occasio

review_1719.Review: Awesome experience! We went here for our wedding anniversary and so glad we did. Our waitress was great!! So helpful since it was our first time she took a lot of time explaining the menu and recommending the 'favorites' and what they were known for. You must try the "shooters" as a starter - amazing! And the scallop wrapped bacon - just melted in your mouth.For entrees... The best filet mignon ever - with a balsamic reduced reduction. For dessert you must try the fried cheesecake and the 7* chocolate platter - a fantastic choice!! It was worth every penny for dinner.

review_1720.Review: Went for my 40th birthday with family and friends! Was fantastic in every way!!!

review_1721.Review: Food quality is high - meat lovers paradise - pricey to say the least

review_1722.Review: Outstanding cuisine, carefully prepared; Asian culinary influences in some of the garnishes and preparations; meat dishes (the specialty) were delicious & well-prepared; vegetable side dishes were also delicious; the menu features selected specialty beef for the connoisseur; hostess was very courteous; service was attentive and energetic, perhaps a little too rushed at moments, but not problematically so; our single major complaint was the excessive height of the tables (or insufficient height of the chairs and booth-benches): I am 5' 11" tall and our table met my sternum (roughly mid-chest). This required lifting our arms uncomfortably high up to reach the food! WUWT? Our waiter was consulted on this glitch but did not respond.

review_1723.Review: I was pleasantly surprised. We just stumbled on to it, as it was a place we could get a Saturday reservation day of. It turned out to be one of the best dining experiences I have had in a while. We were looking for a steak house and ended up with a complete culinary adventure. I would definately go back. Great food, good service, cool vibe.

review_1724.Review: Steak was great, the Brussel Sprouts appetizer was too salty with the soy sauce.

review_1725.Review: We celebrated my birthday at this top steak restaurant. I had the prime rib. The first bite almost brought tears to my eyes. We had spinach and gratin potatos. Gene had the Buffalo, which he enjoyed. The service was great. All in all, one of the top three meals.

review_1726.Review: Food and service were excellent. However I would have preferred that the sauces on the steak be served on the side. This is truly a carnivore's haven. The choices open to the customer are truly amazing.

review_1727.Review: Very nice place with great food and service. Portions are pretty darn big, so plan to split them with a friend/spouse.

review_1729.Review: One of the best rib-eyes I've ever had --- and I try these steaks all over the country. (Just wish they had a baked potatoe...). Fries were nice and crunchy. Brussel sprouts and mushrooms were done just right. Even the bread was fresh and tasty. And our server was extremely attentive and observant -- filling our wine glasses/soft drinks/margaritas/martinis whenever low. SF needed a top rate steak house, and 5A5 is it!

review_1730.Review: This past Labor Day just happened to our wedding anniversary. After reading a few of the on-line restaurant wasn't yet busy, so we could enjoy our quiet evening and meal that much more. Oh yeah - the meal. In a word, Fantastic! The buffalo filet was amazing, very tender and flavorful. My wife really enjoyed the bone-in ribeye. The side dishes (mashed potatoes and haricot vert) were delicious and perfectly sized for sharing. Service was outstanding; our server was very attentive and made sure we were well taken care of. Overall, a great place for premium-quality food. If you're a steak lover, come to 5A5 - you'll love it!

review_1731.Review: Awesome steaks and service. Sent a comment threw open table stating it was for our first wedding anniversary, waiter helped make the dinner extra special.

review_1732.Review: Excellent! Very pricey for the Wagyu but definitely worth it.

review_1733.Review: Yes in deed the steaks were tough! We had the bone in ribeye and Australian wagyu...expecting the best they had to offer. First of all the steaks took nearly an hour to arrive and then both of the steaks were tough with horrible sauces...nearly in edible. Costco ribeyes off my foreman grill are at least 10 times better. I would recommend to grill on the weber with costco meat or go to Alexanders for some worthwhile steaks.

review_1734.Review: We returned to 5A5 after our first visit a few years ago, looking forward to the exquisite quality of their beef, as well as their delicious side dishes. Unfortunately, everything we had was quite salty, from the sauce the steaks were covered in to the two vegetable dishes we had. Ironically, the macaroni and cheese, which we remembered very fondly, was bland!The service was good, and I enjoyed the cocktails before dinner, but, considering the thousands of other untried restaurants the city has to offer, my husband and I will not be coming back to 5A5.

review_1736.Review: We went to this place because it was self-promoted as having the "best steak in the world." The wagyu beef was good, but certainly not the best, in my opinion, and definitely not worth the price! $18-20/oz! That is a little over the top, in my opinion.

review_1737.Review: Food was great, staff was friendly, Parking was easy.

review_1738.Review: Everything was high quality and very well cooked and presented

review_1739.Review: Though I don't agree 5A5 should be listed as a $50/person restaurant since 2 drank tap water, had no dessert and no Wagyu steak and with tip broke $100, I give it a thumbs up.

review_1740.Review: Food was excellent, especially the 7" Chocolate. The one thing we did not like was when one of us arrived, they will not seat you at the table even though it was empty at the restaurant and I was only a few mins early, instead they want you to seat by the bar area which you will look weird sitting alone if you dont want to order drink. So, I ended up waiting for my friend outside.

review_1741.Review: Very intimate atmosphere. Food was prepared and presented like we were VIPs. One thing that I noticed was that every table had the salt and pepper absent. It put more expectation on the flavor of the food we ordered. It was an excellent gamble- the food was outstanding. Adding any kind of condiment would be completely vulgar and uncalled for. Most upscale restaurants in SF either have great service and terrible food or great food and terrible service. 5A5 had great food and service - something that is a rare commodity (like their waygu beef). Hopefully other restaurants in SF take notice. I hope more diners find this gem of a restaurant. I know I would go back there (budget permitting).

review_1742.Review: The waygu beef was delicious! I had the 8 oz new york and my boyfriend had the 12 oz. The smaller waygu was too salty; I tried to mention it; but, I think the server shut out the words. My boyfriends 12 oz was perfect, however. I think the chef may have seasoned the steaks the same, even though one was a lot smaller.

review_1743.Review: We went primarily as we had a need for a meat fix after a day of wine tasting, and were super pleased with the buffalo, which is healthier than beef in so many ways. But all the food was delicious, espcially the sides of Mac & cheese, Brussel sprouts, and truffled fries. The wine list is more than fairly priced and the staff well trained and helpful. Our only complaint was that the restaurant advertises valet parking but fails to tell you they do not offer it on Sunday. Otehrwise, a lovely experience all around.

review_1744.Review: A nice place that is so well worn with the trend setters that I thought I would see someone famous. I didn't. The food is good. I don't think the 150 dollar steak I had was all that much of an alarm but it was at least tasty. Okay spot to try once just so you can say that you know about things like Wagu and impress your friends, I guess. It reminds me a lot of Ozuma Sushi in Oakland.

review_1745.Review: Unique seating setup, circular dining room with a semi-private section near the back. Bone-in ribeye (medium-rare) and filet(medium) were both perfectly cooked and delicious. Server was attentive but not overbearing. Quickly turned into a club environment once we were wrapping up dinner (9:30PM)

review_1746.Review: The shooter apps are the best!! don't go without ordering those.

review_1747.Review: 5A5 is a great place to eat.. I eat there quite a bit..

review_1748.Review: Food was great. Husband and I dressed up that night, but was really surprised to see other guests walk into the restaurant in jeans... A little bit disappointed because it definitely took away that fine fining experience feel. Also, it is a bit loud there so be prepared to shout across the table at tines to be heard.

review_1749.Review: Fabulous place. Had a great birthday dinner there with friends. Food is fantastic. Overall great time and food.

review_1750.Review: The food, wine, service and ambiance at 5A5 were all superb. My new favorite restaurant for a great steak!

review_1751.Review: 5A5 is a very nice upscale modern steakhouse. The bar is happening, and the service is astounding. The filet was excellent-but maybejust a tad over cooked. Otherwise, the food was very yummy!

review_1752.Review: great steaks and other food. apps good too as well as cocktails, desert and very extensive wine list. 1/2 off any wine on mon's. it is very pricy.

review_1753.Review: Great service. Great food. Steak is amazing. Prices reasonable.

review_1754.Review: Not worth the price, they have good, better and best steaks on the menu, I think all of them should be the best when you go to alleged 5 star venue.

review_1755.Review: A true find off the beaten path in a city full of tourists. One of the best steak houses we have eaten at in a while. Prices are very reasonable and the service was second to none. I would recommend this to any of my friends or family.

review_1756.Review: WAITRESS WAS A KNOW IT ALL - SPENT $1.2K FOR 8 AND SHE INTERRUPTED CONVERSATIONS AND DIDNT KNOW THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN WAGYU AND KOBE BUT TRIED TO FAKE IT! BAD MOVE IN THIS GROUP.

review_1757.Review: There was a dramatic lack of attention to detail when it came to service. The staff was very over worked and attention to our service suffered. The wine list was extremely out of date and inaccurate. I ordered 6 different Cabernets from the wine list only to have the wait staff return to inform me that they did not have that bottle in stock. The real shame hear is that the food was good, but the front of the house was awful.

review_1758.Review: gluten-free bread on request at tables would be much appreciated

review_1759.Review: While we knew the space would be fun since they did little to alter the Frisson decor, we weren't sure what to expect from the food, so were very pleasantly surprised when the food (and in particular the seafood preparations) turned out to be so good. The wagyu was excellent (but then again it better be for the price), but the best surprise was the quality and value of the non-steak dishes we ordered, such as the lobster tempura. Service was knowledgeable, observant/attentive and friendly. And you can't go wrong with the 1/2 off wine bottles on Mondays special.

review_1760.Review: We were looking for a steakhouse in San Francisco not far from our hotel on California St. We found 5A5 and are we ever glad we did. The restaurant is beautifully decorated. The ambiance is perfect. The service couldn't be better. The waiter was friendly and knowledgeable but not pushy. The food was outstanding not your usual steakhouse offerings. The hostess called us a cab after dinner and kept checking on us until the cab arrived to take us back to our hotel. On our next visit to SF, we will definitely eat at 5A5 again. It would be worth the trip just to go for dinner ; ) ! The prices were reasonable for such excellent food.

review_1761.Review: There's a reason why Wagyu beef is so expensive. It tastes better than any other steak I've ever had. Even the half-Aussie, half Wagyu NY was like 'buttah', it melts in your mouth. About the only reason I wld not give this 5 stars was the starter courses came too quickly, while we were still enjoying the sushi shooters. This followed the slight delay even ordering when the server had not even uncorked the wine we brought. Aside from slightly inconsistent service, the place was great; the steaks are worth it.

review_1762.Review: I made the reservation with a good steak dinner in mind. I left the restaurant haapy as a clam after a great steak dinner. There are no wrong choices on the menu and I will sure be back before long...

review_1763.Review: This is my first time at 5A5. I am a big fan of bone in rib eye steak. I've dined at Alexanders in Cupertino numerous times and thought I'd try 5A5. I was not disappointed at all; from start to finish, my experience at 5A5 exceeded all of my expectations. Our server for the evening Leah or Laila was very patient and explained the menu items very well. We considered her food recommendations and boy it was delish! For apps we ordered truffle fries, tempura lobster and hamachi shots. For our entree we shared a 4oz wagyu and a bone in rib eye. Sides included shrooms and steamed spinach. I would definitely recommend this restaurant to anyone who loves good food! I'm coming back! Oh, and corkage was only $20.

review_1764.Review: One of the better steakhouses in San Francisco.  You will get what you pay for here.  Nothing to complain about.  The co-ed bathrooms leaves you to your own devices ;)

review_1765.Review: Wagu beef filet mignon - the best I have ever had. Very Good Dining Experience. Great Vipe

review_1766.Review: I can't think of anything bad to say about the restaurant other than it is extremely expensive. The food is great, the service is great, and the ambiance makes you want to stay there longer. However, it is quite painful when the bill arrives...

review_1767.Review: I did not expect an Asian style steak house with Wagyu sold by the ounce and tons of it. This is not your traditional steakhouse and those looking for a variation on the Ruth's model should stay away. But if you want slightly hip, good energy, and lots of steak with Asian infusion, A5A is a good find. I really appreciated the option of a 4 or 8 oz NY strip. 4oz was a perfect size for me.

review_1768.Review: The food and the setting were fantastic. Our server was excellent and made great recommendations.

review_1769.Review: I has a steak and it was underdone and I had to send it back. My husband had the roast beef and that was underdone too! They take themselves regarding steak too seriously and they shouldn't because they are not great at it. Had better steak elsewhere.

review_1770.Review: It was not a good experience for one person in our party. She found a piece of glass in her food on a cracked dish. Even though the restaurant did not charge her for her dish, but still it kind of ruined the evening. The food was not cheap and all the side dishes are separately charged, and I was not impressed with the taste of the sides. The meat is good, so I would only recommend just to order the steaks and not the other stuffs. The dinning room is also small and it's situated along with the bar/lounge, so the noise level was high.

review_1771.Review: Watress talked our ears off... overall it was good, but felt like it was trying too hard.

review_1772.Review: To be quite honest the steaks we had at 5a5 last Wednesday night  were cooked right to order and tasted great, the service sadly left us reconsidering our choice for my best friend's birthday dinner. We arrived early for our 8pm reservation and were asked to sit and wait at the bar.  We were seated  at 8:20pm, this worried my guest who is a host/server in Palo Alto. He felt we might have already been de-prioritized  considering our age. Our server arrived at 8:40pm (my server friend was quite clear that he was taking note). Our server seemed rushed, as if the guests around were of greater concern, and only furthering my friends suspicions.It would've been ok up until that point, forgivable if the steak had redeemed it. And it could

review_1773.Review: The "steak lounge" concept was new to me, but the food was amazing.

review_1774.Review: #rd time there food is fantastic. However they insist on letting people use the middle back (albeit outdoors) section for smoking. Had 5 colleagues bill $1000 bucks and we had to smell the nasty smell of cigarettes by this one guy like 6 times in 3 hours. He smoked right by the door close to the back tables even after I asked my waiter to do something about it. Never again.

review_1775.Review: it was delicious!!!! LOved the edamame and kobe beef sliders.

review_1776.Review: Steaks were delicious, sides were good, but our server wasn't particularly kind or helpful. He didn't answer our questions sufficiently, and generally didn't seem like he wanted to be there. They did provide a gorgeous piece of cake for dessert because we were celebrating a birthday, which was great.Unfortunately though, I can't recommend this place despite the good food when there are so many other great places in the city to eat that have great food and great service.

review_1777.Review: Too long a wait for the entrees but excellent food and creative desserts.

review_1778.Review: Food was very good but the length of time for the main entree was ridiculous. They make a point to explain their cooking process and that a 22 ounce steak will take 30 min. We had 8 and 9 ounce steaks and it took almost an hour to come to the table. They were not that busy. Took 3 hours to have a starter, salad, entree and leave.

review_1779.Review: We went there for Dine About Town a couple of days ago, and all three courses were excellent. Our waitress was also great - very helpful, well-informed, and friendly. Would definitely go back for a special occasion when it's not DAT.

review_1780.Review: Great food and service. We went there for an early Father's Day dinner and also to try out the Dine-About-Town menu. My son really enjoyed the Rib-eye steak he ordered. Said that it was one of the best he has eaten. Ambiance and decor were very nice too. My family had a good time.

review_1781.Review: We got there a few minutes late for our reservation, but they seated us right away. What they didn't tell us is that we would get the table from hell. We were seated right next to the kitchen so I got the extreme pleasure of watching the kitechen staff prepare food all night.

review_1782.Review: What a pleasant surprise. Wonderful food, service and ambiance. This was a real treat and we will go back!

review_1783.Review: One word: Phenomenal. The waitstaff was outstanding, the food was ridiculous. We all shared each other's meals and nobody was disappointed. The steak was melt-in-your-mouth tender and the portions were perfect. Nobody went home hungry. We went to celebrate our son's 29th birthday and the waitress brought out a beautiful dessert with candle and 'happy birthday' and a beautiful design written out in chocolate on the plate. It was almost too beautiful to eat.

review_1784.Review: Our server was attentive and helpful. We were celebrating a special occasion and they made it special ; )

review_1785.Review: Very disappointing. didn't live up to all the hype. maybe it was the dine about town menu? Fish or short ribs (no steak)

review_1786.Review: Fantastic service, incredible fusion on "steakhouse" menu. Must go.

review_1787.Review: The food was amazing, but the bar service was slow. There was only four people at the bar and it took awhile to get the drinks we ordered. The wait staff was knowledgable and very helpful. The decor needs to be revamped. its the same decor as the prior place, and honestly a bit outdated. We did not try the special japanese beef because it was cost prohibitive. Overall a wonderful food experience.

review_1788.Review: We were 4 of us going for the Dine About Town event and we had a wonderful dinner. Beautiful decor, very nice service and the food was totally succulent. They truly have an incredible meat. A bit pricey, but if you can afford a $50 steak with the side dishes extra, this is your place.

review_1789.Review: Just to try out since this place is ranked a famous steakhouse in Bay Area.

review_1790.Review: Disappointing. Too expensive for mediocre food and service.

review_1791.Review: The food was just ok, I was expecting to be really impressed with the food...I ordered the short ribs and for the price I paid, I couldve gotten a big steak at Ruths steak house ...the trout did not taste good at all...the cucumber soup was not tasty and it didnt even look appetizing...however the service and the drinks were great, the French A5 is s great concoction by the bar...I wouldn't recommend the place for dinner but I may go back to hang out at the lounge.

review_1792.Review: Ambiance is trendy and great for a young professional crowd. The service was was excellently trained, asking us if it was our first time. Letting us get settled with water first and proceeded to fully explain the menu. Best of all she wasn't pushy when we decided to stick with water for our menu and just enjoy the food. Food was excellent and additional au jus for my prime rib was promptly provided when requested. Gave us the check at the correct time without us asking and proceeded to make sure if we needed a taxi or valet service it would be in a timely manner. In our case we had parked nearby so it wasn't necessary. I will be back for our next special occasion.

review_1793.Review: I believe that for a steak house to participate in the dine about town program, they should offer steak on the pre-fix menu. The short rib plate that I did have was ok but not special. It also contained a large amount of fat on one of my short ribs which was a major turn off. I've been to this retaraunt before and have had some good meals there. But last night was a definate let down. Not sure if I will return.

review_1794.Review: I've heard some good reviews on this place and decided to give it a try when I saw that they were participating in Dine About Town. The truffle fries and fried cheesecake was amazing!

review_1795.Review: Why offer a dine about town menu? I wanted to try the restaurant but the only options on the dine about town menu were fish and short ribs. It's a steak restaurant. If I wanted fish I would have made a reservation at a fish restaurant.

review_1796.Review: The food was exquisite! I was able to take my time dining and didn't feel rushed or pressured by the waiter.

review_1797.Review: I feel badly about saying that we were pretty disappointed with 5A5. Our server, though pleasant, seemed fake and hyper. She didn't even mention the dine about town deal and we had to ask about it. We had a caesar salad and iceberg salad - the iceberg salad on the menu looked like it was going to have blue cheese on it - chunks - but it was blue cheese dressing only - the bacon on the salad was complete gristle. We both had short ribs which were half fat and full of gristle and not at all tender. We had a side of mac and cheese and it tasted like the salt shaker and garlic salt fell into it - too bad because the cheese combo in it would have been good. Dessert was deep fried cheese cake - we didn't like that at all. Sorry.

review_1798.Review: The food is the big disappointment at 5A5. It's really just not THAT good. The fries are outstanding, but everything else is really just OK. The steaks come drenched in sauce, the mac n cheese tastes way too much of truffel (which I didn't think was possible), the spinache was bland and the desserts were actually not good. The lime creme brule was way too sweet, amd the 7 degrees of chocolate managed to have a plate full of chocolate yet nothing I'd want to eat. If it was half the price it would still not be a great restaurant, though one would expect less.I should say the service was fantastic.

review_1799.Review: I was looking forward to eatting at 5A5 for dining about town. I had been wanting to try this restaurant for a while and dine about town was the perfect opportunity. We ordered the dine about town menu along with two sides and it was not good. The spare ribs had so much fat on them that there was very little meat to enjoy. We ordered two sides Mac n Cheese and the Shrooms. The mac n cheese was good but the shrooms were under cooked. I LOVE dessert and I did not care fore the deep fried cheese cake. The panna cotta tasted great with the lemon sauce but solo it was bland. Overall i was pretty disapointed with this restaurant. What a shame : (

review_1800.Review: Everyone said they had one of the best steaks ever!!

review_1801.Review: Other reviews are correct in that it is a bit pricy, but it's not your average once a week steak place. It was worth it for our special occation.PRO's: Very good food, attentive server, nicer place without feeling stuffy.CON's: Great place before 9pm then it gets a little loud for dinner, $200+ for two with a glass of wine.I would go again only for a special event.

review_1802.Review: I had not been to 5A5 for a couple of years and the food is still outstanding. What shocked me was a group that was in the bar area when I arrived of some women's club and the noise was deafening. It sounded something like the wild bird exhibit at the zoo. I think the management should have addressed the noise before it got out of control for the sake of diners in the restaurant. During dinner (which was excellent) it was almost impossible to hear the other people in my group. I would not consider this restaurant again for a business meeting or at any time that I might want to converse.

review_1803.Review: Great food, wonderful service and always a good experience overall.

review_1804.Review: Absolutely love 5A5! The truffle mac & cheese is my favorite. Great restaurant!

review_1805.Review: Great food and great service. Not cheap, but tastes expensive! We had a great time there. The meat was unreal and the sides were just naughty.

review_1806.Review: Great food and service. One of the most enjoyable meals I have had.

review_1807.Review: Fantastic food and service. Tempura Lobster was dissapointingly small though. Tasty, but small.Will come again.

review_1808.Review: It's described as not your typical steakhouse and it's not. The decor is modern and stylish. The service is absolutely fabulous and while on the expensive side, the food is very good. In addition to the Wagyu and Kobe steaks, they had top grade USDA beef as well as a fairly broad selection of Asian influenced menu items. The bone-in ribeye, which the server will tell you take 35-40 minutes to cook is totally worth the wait. 5 of went together and we ended up sharing our meals so we could all taste the food.
