It Was well worth it because the food was great.

review_1809.Review: server's recommendations were generally very good, but the flavor of the beef was not so superior to other, more reasonably priced steak places--this is the main reason you go there.With so many great restaurants in the Bay Area, this is a one time only visit for me. However, I should note it appears to appeal to a younger crowd & the happy hour menu looked delicious & more affordable.

review_1810.Review: Great booth seating. Good for business dinner. Bar also good. Seating is comfortable and spacious. CouldHave a private conversation. Food was excellent. Service attentive but not overbearing. Suggestions from staff were helpful. The steaks were generous and fabulous. The sides a must. The hamachi and maguro shots were also the best!

review_1811.Review: I was craving a good steak but not keen to eat at typical steakhouse in shorts. I wondered if there was a place that served great steak in a more relaxed and contemporary interior. 5A5 is just that. Everything about this place made for a great evening. From our speedy seating by the smiling hostess to our wonderful server Daniel. And then the amazing food- the Himachi shooter was amazing, I had the filet mignon. The mashed potatoes are to die for (bacon on the side as it's good but quite big chunks and sweet). The steak was melt in your mouth good, the sauces great but not overpowering and did I mention the Himachi shooter?! Tuna with avocado and a bunch of flavors served in a shot glass. The perfect appetizer for the perfect meal.

review_1812.Review: Exceptional in every way. From the opening with the bacon bread, yes bacon bread, to the scrumptious steaks, dessert, and the wine. The overall experience was nearly unparalleled. Menu is a little pricey, but you are getting more than you pay. Highyl recommended!

review_1813.Review: Every dish from appetizer to desert was excellent! Have the Truffle Fries as a side for the best Steak experience ever!

review_1814.Review: It was a great restaurant because the food was outstanding! Fully recomended!

review_1815.Review: Love it! Great food, outstanding service. We enjoy a Romantic dinner for our aniversary and it was Great.

review_1816.Review: Food was great, Bar scene is great. Nice place. Don't miss it.

review_1817.Review: The reviews were certainly accurate regarding the service. It's been years since I've seen such excellent service from all staff members. The server was well informed of the menu and he wine list. My first experience will certainly not be my last.

review_1818.Review: We had a wonderful time there, the waiter was very helpful and friendly. I felt a little underdressed but the place was noisy enough (with chatter) that it didn't really matter.The lobster tempura appetizer was so-so, I wouldn't say it's worth the $24 price tag, but the steak is another story altogether. IT. WAS. DELICIOUS. No argument with that. I don't know what it was...the wagyu flavor itself? The sauce? The way it's cooked? Whatever it was, it was the best steak I've ever tasted. I would DEFINITELY go back again.

review_1819.Review: Absolutely chic and trendy in the decor and great place to meet with large parties and share a few dishes. Their mix cocktails are delish as well as their steak dishes. The prime rib was tender and I requested a medium rare center and they were happy to accommodate the request without question. The sides were just as wonderful but very rich so have that Zumba class ready the next day.

review_1820.Review: Great service, the food was excellent, and the ambiance was very nice. I took my boyfriend there for a birthday dinner and he loved it as well! Totally recommend it for special occasions and parties. We noticed that they had a set up for a DJ and asked about it. Apparently, they have a night club set up for Saturday nights. We wish we would have been there for that! Looked fun!

review_1821.Review: I've made several trips to 5A5 and it is consistently great. The atmosphere, the food and the service are exceptional. Had a group of 6 and were able to taste quite a few differnt entree's. Filet, rib-eye and prime rib all had rave reviews. Sides are plentiful for the table, truffle fries, outstanding.

review_1822.Review: The food was amazing, however, the service was a 10. You rarely receive that kind of service at fine dining. Energetic, knowledgeable and timely. Amazing service!

review_1823.Review: Good food not as good as Alexanders in Cupertino, but with the difference in price it was well worth it.

review_1824.Review: Very loud, hard to hear table conversation; table for four was too wide,couldn't talk easily to table mates; food was ok; server was very attentive; ambiance was ok. Overall experience was pleasant, no great shakes.

review_1825.Review: Nice dinner. Everything was as described. The beef specialties were especially good. Not spectacular but very good and my assumption is that this place is very reliable.

review_1826.Review: We always love this place, and the owner Steve is such a gracious host everytime we come. We stareted with the hamachi shooters au gratis. They were amazing! Then had the garlic soy edamame which i would skip in the future as well as the truffle fries which i thought were just ok.The steak was to die for. So tender and tasty. We had the sides of the mashed potatoes with bacon which were awesome and then a side of the mac and cheese also delicious.We had 4 different deserts between the 3 of us. The apple pie was great adn the chocolate 7 ways awesome. I will definitely go back. Always a great meal. Love this place.

review_1827.Review: We went here for my husbands birthday with his family. It was a Monday night and therefore pretty quiet. The atmosphere is very trendy/cool without being over the top. Service was very good- I didn't give it excellent as we had a mix up with our order (but it was fixed right away). The steaks and sides were delicious. I didn't care for the mac and cheese- it was overly "truffled" in my opinion. But if I liked truffles more I think I would have loved it. The brussel sprouts were amazing. The salads were nothing to write home about but the starters (seared scallops and lobster tempura) were delicious.

review_1828.Review: Enjoyed a 40th birthday celebration! Great atmosphere. Great food! Fantastic Service! I would highly recommend 5A5 Steak Lounge to anyone. Tried bison for the first time.... I'm hooked. It was delicious! Also got to taste the 50/50 Australian/Kobe steak which was tender and very flavorful. 5A5 helped make it a night to remember!

review_1829.Review: Great food and outstanding service thanks Leila

review_1830.Review: I think I died and went to heaven. We had the best dinner ever. We started with the Hamachi Shooters which are bits of Hamachis, scallions, ginger, ponzu sauce in a shoot glass. Next came the delicious mini Kobe burgers.Two on a plate, maybe not enough as a dinner for a guy but definitely enough for a girl. The meat was tender and melted in my mouth. It also came with these yummy fries. The hoisin ribs and chips were delicious. Four good size ribs and the sauce is so good. Smoke salmon squares were great. The were small cubes with a mini, very mini toast. The truffle fries dipped in sriracha aioli is very addicting. Our favorite of the meats... the dry aged bone in NY in truffle sauce was the best. The bone-in rib eye was also great. The pr

review_1831.Review: Food & service were great but it was very difficult to have a conversation due to the noise level.

review_1832.Review: Unfortunately there was a LARGE group in the resturant that evening. We were not told of this prior to showing up, and was very disappointed with the ambiance, food, and service. They should not have booked other people for dinner on the same night.

review_1833.Review: we went on a tuesday nite and it was quiet. after reviewing many of the comments made on yelp, we followed suit and tried a variety of dishes. we had caesar salad which was good; haricot vert which consisted of prosciutto, feta cheese and green string beans which was so-so (don't know why the kitchen didn't cut the stems); mashed potato with cheddar, candied bacon and chives which was outstanding; truffle fries which was very good; mac and cheese which was also very good; and prime rib with seared foie gras which was also good. daniel was our server and he was outstanding with a great personality. he definitely made our evening even better. highly recommended you ask for him.

review_1834.Review: We had a w'ful meal, & our waiter was so friendly & ensured that we had grt service. The Truffle French Fries are the best we've ever had in any restaurant!! We would go back just for that!

review_1835.Review: Incredible steaks in a cool "loungy" atmosphere. We'll be back soon!

review_1836.Review: Food was good, but way overpriced, even if it is Wagyu beef. This is the type of restaurant I would try once, but would not return. I didn't feel that the food was that special to warrant many return visits.

review_1837.Review: We celebrated our anniversary dinner here, and our waiter did a spectacular job in presenting our chocolate dessert with a little surprise. He saved the best for last. It ended our evening with a nice touch. Due to a super busy night, the 25 ounce rib-eye was sold out, which is great for the restaurant! I settled for the 22 ouncer, and the steak was superb!!!

review_1838.Review: Very cool space. Excellent food. Awesome service. We had a great time.

review_1839.Review: I think this restaurant is best suited for business dinners. On a Monday night they were actually pretty busy, which is good for them. Maybe the place turns into a night club on the weekends, but it had the feel of a techno lounge in SOMA instead of a fancy steak house. That said, the food was very good. Hamachi shooter was delicious, the mac-and-cheese is a great side and the dry aged bone-in ny was a very generous portion. Our waitress was lovely, gave great recommendations, which was more than I can say about the hostess, who was dismissive and terse with us even though we had a reservation.

review_1840.Review: Our dining experience was oustanding. Service was stellar. (I don't use these words often when describing restaurants.) We were told up front that our full order would be taken, then our food brought in courses. Nothing was rushed, and we savoured our menu choices. The steaks were cooked to perfection, the sides were wonderful. If you go for dinner, eat a light lunch before hand. With all of our food choices even a 4 oz. steak was filling. And the chocolate dessert plate - oohhhh, my. Perfection on a plate.

review_1841.Review: The food was really yummy here, perfectly cooked. The mac and cheese is from Heaven. The shooter was one of the most delicious flavors I've ever had in my mouth! The lounge is beautiful and feels like Manhattan. The place is dark yet bright, crowded yet intimate, but the food is undeniably delicious.

review_1842.Review: Wagyu was exceptionally good. Service was great and the suggestions were spot on. Based on other steak restaurants I have been to in the city, this one really stands out as far away the best for flavor.

review_1843.Review: Overall experience is nice but what you get for what you pay is not that great. Portion size is too small for the price you pay.

review_1844.Review: This steakhouse is perfect for those that want a romantic dinner at an affordable price. Try the Hamachi, filet and desserts. And the service was exceptional!!

review_1845.Review: Absolutely amazing food and even better ambiance. SUCH a great menu and wonderful drinks. Really loved how spacious the tables were and unlike other trendy restaurants you aren't packed next to other people. The food was incredible and I will most definitely be returning to try more menu items. Very pricey but very worth it!

review_1847.Review: Truffle fries, caesar salad, filet mignon, NY strip steak and brussel sprouts was all we could handle although the deserts were very appealing. The food was excellently prepared and presented well. Service was welcoming, attentative and efficient. Wes was our server and he is knowledgeable about the menu as well as thoughtful to offer getting our car from the valet or calling a taxi after dinner. No, we didn't drink and we took BART but that was a nice personal and thoughtful touch I've not experienced before.

review_1848.Review: I've been many times and I always ask for special requests like be seated next to my date and they always accomodated my request. Our servers were very attentive. I practice ayurvedic eating habits and could not eat meat at night. Their side orders are fit to my ayervedic meal needs. I'd highly recommend this restaurant to my family and friends.

review_1849.Review: The food was excellent, however the service felt very amateurish. When we arrived the hostess was missing for 10 minutes. She had been chatting with a table. Our waitress tried very hard, but didn't seem to know what fine dining was about. Her food suggestions were very basic. We went with our own picks and enjoyed them thoroughly. We ordered two sides with our steaks. The steak arrived but no sides. We pointed it out to our waitress who was taking an order form the next table. They finally arrived after we finished our steak with no concession. All the time I spotted a manaager who would not catch my eye. I knew he had been watching this as well. The ambience felt moe like an 80's disco lounge.

review_1850.Review: Excellent food, excellent service, excellent place!

review_1851.Review: While the steak was good--cooked perfectly--all of the side dishes were overseasoned. My dining companion had an octopus salad that tasted only of daikon, and we had a mushroom side dish that was drowned in sherry. When the only good dish is the steak itself, it doesn't give me a reason to want to go back. Ultimately the restaurant was overpriced for the experience.

review_1852.Review: We had a special occasion meal on an ordinary Monday evening. From the moment we walked into the restaurant we knew we were in for a special meal. The dining room is beautifully decorated. The arrangement and lighting makes each table feel like an intimate corner. The food was equal to the ambience. We started with appetizer shooters and edamame with our cocktails. For our main dish we had the Buffalo filet and Australian f1 NY with green beans and brussels sprouts. The asian flavoring of familiar foods was delicious. Meat has never tasted so good. Our waitress was professional, knowledgeable, helpful and fun. She definitely added to the special feel of the evening. We look forward to dining at 5A5 again.

review_1853.Review: My fiance and I had a very enjoyable dinner experience on a Friday night. Steaks were cooked PERFECTLY (medium rare filet bone-in and medium 25-oz ribeye) and service was outstanding! We also had a side of Mac-n-Cheese that went well with steaks. Everything we had had just the right amount of flavoring, not too excessive and not too bland. They also have a great happy hour which I also enjoy. But the whole dining experience was gratifying since there aren't too many places left with a combination of great food and service. Thanks for a memorable evening!

review_1854.Review: Terrific steak in a lively atmosphere!

review_1855.Review: Wines by the glass grossly overpriced. A "cheap" one at $16.00 was mediocre so I declined. Pay less than that - undrinkable. My salad was very salty - I ate it, but would not get it again. Entrees very good. Don't think I would go back simply because there are too many other great places in San Francisco with a better ambiance and food just as good or possibly better for less money. Also, they had a massive event at the bar - with no separation barrier between the diners and bar patrons, you had to shout at your dinner partner in order to have a conversation.

review_1856.Review: Totally Fab! The restaurant is retro 60's elegant, and would be an excellent choice for a first date or special occasion. We ordered several small dishes all delicious but my favorites were the truffle fries served in a large portion which may easily be shared, and the sea bass, which was phenomenal it melted in the mouth and was incredibly flavorful, served with artichoke hearts and watercress.

review_1857.Review: The waitress paid attention to any Open Table note requests. I had made a reservation previously, and the restaurant closed to the public that particular night, so my reservation was cancelled. I made a new reservation and commented about that. The waitress brought over a special appetizer in addition to our order to acknowledge my reservation experience, which I thought was very personalized. It just made the rest of the dinner go so much further. And the food, the food pretty much can stand on its own merits. Everything was timed very well, and was great to the last dessert bite.

review_1858.Review: Excellant menu for those who love beef with a slight asian flair. Outstanding quality with a broad range from US cuts to imported speciality beef. I also really enjoyed the Hamachi shooters - wow - could have those all night. The circular floor plan provides an intimate setting for special occasions.

review_1859.Review: The food was excellent and the service superb. We are definately planning to return - soon I hope. We have decided that when we meet our weight loss goal, this will be our reward!

review_1860.Review: The lobster tempura and Tofu crab cake were delicious.But the dry aged bone-in New York steak was not so good... It was cooked medium rare as ordered but the meat is pretty tough and chewy.

review_1861.Review: The food was great. The bone in Rib-Eye was excellent. Don't be afraid of the Salmon. It's incredible. Desert was not memorable. The noise was intense from the bar at 8PM on a Friday.

review_1862.Review: The food was good, but not memorable. The atmosphere is energetic as the bar dominates the restaurant and oftentimes makes it challenging to have a conversation at the dinner table. Overall, I would recommend this restaurant for young singles looking for a active bar scene with the option to dine.

review_1863.Review: I split a bone-in ribeye. It was a'ight. Service was attentive, never intrusive. I never felt neglected.I did feel out of place. I got the impression that most diners were going to write off their dinners as a business expense. I was just catching up with a friend who's a picky eater.

review_1864.Review: The food is very good, service is OK; could be better. Highly recommended if anyone is looking for good steak.

review_1865.Review: WONDERFUL! We loved the Waygu ribcap - what a treat. Also service was superb. Fabulous dinner, fabulous night...

review_1866.Review: I love a good steak and was really looking forward to this dinner. I always order my steak rare, and our server made a big deal that rare at 5A5 is really, really red, which was fine with me. When my steak arrived it was medium rare to medium. I was disappointed but didn't want to complain so I ate it anyway. I should have sent it back, since it wasn't enjoyable at all. Unfortunately, that colored the experience for me. However, the mashed potatoes were AMAZING, the appetizers were good (huge portions!) and the other two steaks were fine. Service was very attentive as well. But I'm still disappointed that my steak was completely overcooked.

review_1867.Review: Our server, Dan, was wonderful. He made the evening. Nice ambiance. Wine 50% off on Mon. nights.

review_1868.Review: Wonderful place.  The steaks were juicy and grilled to perfection and the side dishes were fresh and well prepared.

review_1869.Review: Postive experience for our group - Bar services were responsive -For a steak house menu was incomplete.... Variety was fair while restaurant had definite push on Japenese cuts.Bone in filet was outstanding aong with 25 oz Ridy Eye! Service attention was exemplary through form entrees, wine and desert selections --We will return!

review_1870.Review: Great choice for a special date night.  Very interesting menu.  We had the hamachi and toro shooters to start - which were both delicious.  Awesome. We followed that with terrine de foie gra, which was also very good.  Then tried two types of wagyu beef.  As the server promised, the wagyu just melts in your mouth. But for me, not worth the price.  Obviously, if you go to 5A5, you have to eat the wagyu, but at about $19/oz (with a 4 oz minimum), just too pricey.  Corkage was only $20, which is very reasonable so highly recommend bringing your own wine (because the wine list is heavily marked up).

review_1871.Review: It could have had more stars but our Creme brûlée was burnt and our steaks could have been cooked better. It wasn't a bad meal, I actually enjoyed most of it and I would have definitely rated higher. But that Creme brûlée left a bad taste in my mouth literally! Being objective It was an okay experience.

review_1872.Review: Shawna is the best server ever.

review_1873.Review: 5A5 is exactly as advertised, a "steak lounge". There is definitely a nightclub feel in the bar area, which looks like a VIP space at a vegas club. The dining was the draw for us though. We were seated at a comfortable table and served by a very friendly young waitress. I liked the energy of the place, although it loses a bit of ambiance by keeping the dining area open to the bar - and the double doors in front close slowly allowing cold outside air to draft into the dining room. The food was the standout. I had a 4 oz waygu delicacy and my fiance had 6 oz of bison. We shared the haricot verts and au gratin potatoes, and each had an accompanying glass of wine. Excellent all around (except the $5 happy hour wine - pick a better selection).

review_1874.Review: The steaks were of very good quality and there is a variety of sizes for everyone. no cream spinach so settled for the potato au gratin. delicious.

review_1875.Review: For beef aficionados, this is a great place to enjoy succulent steaks. The starters of foie gras and tuna tartare were sublime. We followed that with filet mignon and T-bone steak, both cooked to medium rare perfection. Couldn't resist trying the mac and cheese (I'd never had it in a restaurant before, but it brought this comfort dish to a whole new level). The service was very professional and the wine list had many choices by the glass. To top off this meal we opted for desserts of fried cheese cake and chocolate 7 ways.

review_1876.Review: We had a fantastic experience at A5A. The food, ambiance and service was outstanding. We highly recommend the hoisin ribs with lotus chips as a starter. The iceberg wedge was crisp and the small heirloom tomatoes were outstanding. The presentation of our entrees was fantastic and the food was hot. My husband had the lamb chop/sirloin dish - delicious and cooked to perfection. I had the aged NY strip - tender, juicy and cooked to perfection. Order the potatoes au gratin as a side. A little pricey, but worth every penny. We will definitely be returning.

review_1877.Review: everything we ordered was perfect. The truffle fries were the best fries that I have eaten and I am not a french fry fan. Service was great and not over attentive.

review_1878.Review: Hate to say "OMG", but the fois gras--"OMG!!!!" Excellent Wagyu "shooter", and enjoyed the filet (my husband had the bone-in ribeye, and it was giant and delicious, too). Brussels sprouts were seriously al dente, as we were warned. Ran out of time for dessert, but that will be another time.

review_1879.Review: A vast improvement over Frisson, formerly in this space!

review_1880.Review: We wrote comments on this restaurant before and have the same and unique complaint about the noise level that makes conversation almost impossible, at least where we were seating under the badly designed dome. While it made for some comic moments of misunderstanding, it was quite frustrating for the person who could not comprehend the words in the conversation.

review_1881.Review: Second time there. Steak was again...to die for...Service VERY attentive and friendly. It is pricey. 2 people - salad, steak entree, dessert, coffee and 1 glass of wine...$190.

review_1882.Review: Both the Fillet Mignon and Buffalo Fillet were both extremely tender. We also ordered the Wagyu-smallest serving 4oz to give it a try===at $19/oz any other size was out of the question LOL. Although it was not as tender as the fillet--the flavor was...Fantastic!!! The sides were bigger than I had expected--enough for two to share. Mac and Cheese--I found the flavor too overwhelming (made with Gruyere). The Mushroom "melody" was perfection. Nicely complimented the steak. I must also mention my starter of Hamachi Shooter--you have to try this--a real celebration for the taste buds!! The razor clam chowder was less than exciting.

review_1883.Review: Food is pretty good, but over priced. The ambiance is a little too flashy, at the expense of being tasteful (including the clientel).

review_1884.Review: some of the best soup and steak i have ever had. service was top notch, will definitely go here again. great place!

review_1885.Review: One of the best interiors in the city!

review_1886.Review: This is the new evolution where Frisson used to be and it's 100 times better. I liked the food at Frisson, but this place blows it away. The service staff were excellent, great wine list and the steak was by far the best I've had in SF (and I've tried a few). The sides are to die for and the scallops BLT. Try it!

review_1887.Review: The price for the amount of the steak they give you is very expensive. it is more bone than meat no side dish you have to pay extra for everything else.The waiter who was serving our table was very unhappy and unpleasent. I didnt have a good xeperience.

review_1888.Review: The food was phenomenal and our waitress checked up on us during the right times. She wasn't an overbearing waitress. The steaks were cooked to perfection: juicy and tender. Will definitely go back. This steakhouse is on top of my list of restaurants and we can't wait to go back. The wagyu steaks are a must despite its extremely high price.

review_1889.Review: From the moment we entered, we were greeted warmly, wisked to a cozy table that allowed for vibrant conversation. Our server was quite congenial, enthusiastic about the menu and offered suggestions and descriptions. I was curious to try the bison but also somewhat reluctant as I'd never sampled that type of beef and was afraid that it might be "gamy." Jim K. assured that it was not, and suggested that I order it rare to medium rare. I brought three friends who'd never been there--needless to say they were mightily impressed. Absoluted loved the presentation and flavor of "where's the beef." The highpoint of my dinner (aside from the Bison--OUTSTANDING BTW) was the 7 degrees of chocolate---whoa! Decadence without the guilt! TY 5A5!!

review_1890.Review: There is no denying that the food is excellent. However, the atmosphere is akin to a trendy burger joint. It's too crowded, busy and loud. It turns into a club after hours, so if you have a late dinner there, you'll probably leave with a headache.

review_1891.Review: Great food selection. Incredible find. Worth the money.

review_1892.Review: The Hamachi shooter was definitely the best start for the evening. I followed the advice from other reviewers by orders the shooter. The fillet mignon and the NY strip steaks were cooked to perfection. We order enough in the beginning that we did not have room for desert, but that give us another reason to visit 5A5 Steak Lounge again.

review_1893.Review: If you're looking to have a great ambiance w/o spending too much, go to the HH beforehand. It ends at 7:30 and you can try more food at a lower cost. The shooters are great as well as the fries.

review_1894.Review: Decor is interesting, food was great, dessert was...interesting, cocktails were great, service was friendly, noise level loud. Our group had the server recommended salad, edamame, cocktail shrimp, truffle fries; martinis, orange crush, wine; filets, sea bass; side of mushrooms, spinache; creme brule, panna cotta, 7 degrees of chocolate. We probably should have passed on the dessert.

review_1896.Review: Food was okay but generally very salty. The staffs were professional and courteous even if not the most attentive compared to other places I have been.

review_1897.Review: Had a wonderful experience at 5A5. The food was magnificent and the service was attentive. This was one of the best dining experiences I've had.

review_1898.Review: Our experience here was definite very positive. The food, ranging from the appetizer, to the steaks, to the dessert, was excellent. The presentation was also wonderful, as was the service. It is definitely a place I would go back and to recommend to my friends.

review_1899.Review: Great food, great servce, great evening!

review_1900.Review: Great food - exceptional steak! Great service! Great ambiance! Great experience!

review_1901.Review: I would not recommend this restaurant for any reason. The food was not good and the environment was much more like a lounge than a restaurant. The service was good but the restaurant became increasingly noisy the longer we stayed. I would not return nor would anyone in my party.

review_1902.Review: Nothing about the food was memorable except the first course of hamachi shooters. The rest was fine. Some was bland others just not quite working. Didn't make me want to come back and eat there again. I would go back for drinks at the bar and maybe appetizers--ambiance was good.

review_1903.Review: Pretty noisy, food was very good but the service was very average. Overall, not worth the price

review_1904.Review: Fantastic food!! Filet was cooked perfectly w/ wonderful sauce and sides of spinach and potatoes, delicious! Unfortunately, the service didn't match the meal....starting with the wait person in the bar area (by the time the wine and soft drink arrived, our table was ready)....to the dining room staff. We waited for menus, waited for water, waited to order, waited for food. The person clearing the table was truly the most competent. Staff needs training!!Will give it another try!

review_1905.Review: Food was great from start to finish. We started with the Kobe Sliders with Truffled French Fries. The fries were so delicious that even my husband, who normally doesn't venture far from just simple meat and potatoes, ate these up. We shared the Wagyu Trio. We could've easily finished off two platters of these.  The beef was so tender.  It's like they say - "melted like butter in your mouth"! We'll be back again some day for another special occasion dinner.

review_1906.Review: We went her for Dine about town. The food was good and the service was wonderful. It was pretty packed for a Sunday night, the restaurant was pretty full and had only a few open tables.

review_1907.Review: This is a cute place with the right ambiance. The food is good and the service is great. Portion is just about right.

review_1908.Review: Hamachi shooters are the best and well worth it here!!! love em!

review_1909.Review: Spent our 10 Year Anniversary and had a wonderful time. The servers were very friendly and our table was cleaned up after every meal. The oysters shooter was a great start and even though we didn't have the Wagyu beef, the filet mignon satisfied our taste buds. I have already recommended the restaurant already to a few friends.

review_1910.Review: A nice place to eat- the ambiance and decor was nice. The food was just OK. We had the ribeye and the seabass. The ribeye was just Ok- as cited by my husband who loves steak and hadnt had one in a while. The seabass was good, the sauce a little on the bland side. The truffle fries were very good tho!

review_1911.Review: Excellent steaks -- they take their meat very seriously.

review_1912.Review: The food and atmosphere was great, the presentation was excellent. My wife had a great time and 5A5's take on the steakhouse was very appealing to her. Overall great restaurant for dates, however, it does not appeal to me like a place I would go with a group of guys for a steak.

review_1913.Review: My party came to see what this steak lounge is all about and sample the reputedly amazing steak. What better time to do this than during Dine About Town! We all had filet mignon, prepared medium rare, which pretty much was the highlight of the dinner. The meat literally melted in the mouth. It came with no sides but it was enough for the ladies. The salads and desserts were just okay. We went on a Thursday and expected a more vibrant scene, thought it was a bit quiet for an ultra lounge. We had lots of cocktails, actually spent more on drinks than food. At the beginning, the waiter spilled a drink all over the table and we assured him that accidents like that do happen. It was just surprising that nothing was offered on the house.

review_1914.Review: Going to 5A5 for the first time and for a special occasion. They made sure that it was prepared and served to celebrate this special day but respected the request for discretion. Service was excellent and so was the food although, while it was excellent and well prepared, I would not recommend the Australian "special F1" as its price is definitely not justified versus other choice meat found in the USA.We liked the decor but it is obvious that interior decorators and architects working on this project should take a few classes in noise management and control. There are ways and material that could lower the surrounding noise and make the place even better than what it is.

review_1915.Review: The steak wasnt as good as i thought it would be. The fries and mac and cheese tasted better than the steak and this is suppose to be a steakhouse.

review_1916.Review: We had the dine about time menu, which wasn't a great deal since we still had to order sides. It would have been great if they offered side or desert. Regardless, it was great meal.Food: we had the hamachi shooter and the oyster shooter YUMMYOne Caesar, one iceberg, both greatSpinach and truffle fries. We loved the truffle fries. Spinach was good, but we didn’t finish it.We both had the filet. They were done to perfection and the sauce was great.We took the desert to go and I gave mine to my friend, so I can’t comment.Service: Was GREAT!

review_1917.Review: Excellent steaks and service but definitely above market prices for what you get with the whole experience. I've definitely experienced the same quality and service at several other steakhouses, including Morton's or Ruth's Chris.

review_1918.Review: Why do trendy restaurants tend to have waiters that treat us like "buds".

review_1919.Review: Great Happy hour options in the lounge

review_1920.Review: The bone in rib eye steak is really good. Other than that, nothing is spectacular.

review_1921.Review: Easily the best filet mignon I've EVER had! The service was friendly and attentive, and completely unpretentious. Extenstive wine list, rich desserts. Definitely indulgent considering the bill was well over $300 for four people but well worth it; especially for a special occasion. To try: the b.l.t. scallops, clam chowder, and obviously the STEAK! Maybe someday I'll try the touted Wagyu...The ambiance was nice--not quiet but definitly not loud. They do have a DJ afterhours though and a cool bar.

review_1922.Review: Had the prix fixe dinner, as the $20/ounce (!) steak wasn't what we were expecting at a $$$ restaurant (per OpenTable rating). The squash soup and iceberg lettuce salad were both competent. The New York steak was a bit tough and chewy, and the cheese on top was cold in the middle. The salmon was nicely done, and the filet mignon was good but a very small portion.

review_1923.Review: We went for Dine About Town. We had the Caesar salad and lobster bisque, filet mignon, and both of the desserts. The food is excellent! Our waitress suggested a wonderful full-body glass of Zin, I believe it was. The service was impeccable: attentive without being intrusive; dishes well timed, so we didn't feel rushed or like we had to wait forever in between; water always filled; and any food/water spots on the table were very quickly wiped up. We will definitely be back!

review_1924.Review: Went there for the Dine Around menu. Wonderful atmosphere. Usually avoid steak places as they feel like old white men clubs. this definately is a step above. Waitress recommended the smallest portion of the Waygu beef to share since we were saving $$ on the dine around. very expensive but worth every bite!

review_1925.Review: The servers are super helpful and attentive. The servers provide excellent service, definitely recommend. The atmosphere of this restaurant was pretty relaxing and casual. However, the food was not too satisfying, for it did not come with any sides without paying additional money. I think all entrees should include at least 1 side along with the price to be fair. Overall, this place was a good place, though the food was pretty pricey.

review_1926.Review: Took my wife to 5A5 for her birthday and we had the Dine About Town menu. Fantastic is all I can say. I had the filet and she had the strip. Both cuts were tender and juicy. I'd also recommend the squash soup. It's very flavorful and a good preamble to the steaks. The service was great. Our waiter was very knowledgable and even hailed us a cab after the meal.

review_1927.Review: This place was created to impress, and impress it does. From the moment we walked in to the moment we walked out, my family and I were just taken with the ambiance and classy nature of this restaurant. The food did not disappoint, and although the price does seem a bit steep, it's a price I was all too happy to pay after my meal. The service was also great, and our server was super helpful and always ready with suggestions. Amazing all the way through.

review_1928.Review: Went to 5A5 for SF's Dine About Town; even with a $35 limit, they were able to provide amazing dishes--iceberg lettuce salad, filet mignon and a chocolate mousse dessert! The Wagyu beef looks incredibly pricey, but haven't seen any other steakhouse willing to carry and stock such high quality beef. Will definitely save up and splurge next time on Wagyu! Date had the New York strip and strawberries&champagne dessert, both were delicious. Shared two cocktails, the French A5 (like a raspberry bellini) and the paradise something, which was heavy on the Patron, but yummy. Ambiance is wonderful--romantic setting; lots of couples, some groups. The service is fast and immediate (5 people wait your table at a time), empty plates immediately cleared!

review_1929.Review: Food was good. Lighting was a bit dim. Nice place to bring a date.

review_1930.Review: enjoyed our steaks and the dining for benefit program was a pleasant discount and good cuisine combos.

review_1931.Review: This place made me changevmy mind for the better about filet mignon.

review_1932.Review: first time @ 5A5. went w/ the bf and a gf for dine about town. we all ordered off the dine about town menu. we all liked our food. quick service. we had 5pm reservations. we were done with dinner @ 6pm. we def go back again. will have to try some other items on the menu.

review_1933.Review: The truffle fries are the best! Desserts were very, very good. Overall exceeded any kind of expectation.

review_1934.Review: The sides were pretty good, but I thought the Wagyu steak wasn't all that great.

review_1935.Review: By far the b3est steakhouse in the Bay Area. Phenomenal service from the top down!

review_1936.Review: The 5A5 is a classic lounge scene with delicious food, great appetizers and sides and top notich beef or fish if you don"t eat beef...service is usually over the top..

review_1938.Review: Really great service and reasonably priced menu!

review_1939.Review: From beginning to end.....this experience bordered on perfection. Great service, ambiance, food and energy in an incredibly attractive venue all totaled up to one great evening out. Thanks! steveT

review_1940.Review: The restaurant itself was pretty good. The food was not bad. I was dissapointed with the wagyu beef. I expected it to be fabulous for the price I paid but it wasn't. The coffee was terrible. It wasn't hot and it was poured from a kettle in front of us. The dessert selection wasn't good either. We had the tiramisu and it was not good.

review_1941.Review: I love 5A5 and even wrote an article raving about the quality of food, service and atmosphere. I was however a bit dissapointed that there was no New Years Eve event going on. There is usually a DJ and the lounge is really fun and hip, but New Years fizzled and at 110 dollars per person there could have at least been a DJ there and some noise makers..

review_1942.Review: The food and service were outstanding. I tried Wagyu beef for the first time and was blown away by how good it was. It was well worth the price.

review_1943.Review: We dined here on New Years Eve. There was a Pre-Fix Menu. The appetizer and salads we had were outstanding. The main entrees of steak and sea bass were good but not great. The deserts were also outstanding.

review_1944.Review: The food was outstanding. However, the service at the bar was very slow. We not only had to wait a long time for service, but we noticed this happened to other customers as well.

review_1945.Review: Came here last week. Food - 3 stars, but overall 4 stars (for restaurant and lounge). The bar: We hung out at the bar/lounge for 30 minutes before we were seated, which was great. Happy hour lasts until 7:30 pm, so we had the hamachi shooters (try it!) and wine by the glass at the bar - which is 1/2 cheaper than ordering from the table menu.   The meat: We passed on the wagyu, although I was curious. The reviews just don't seem to justify the price. We had the dry aged T bone ($44), bone in rib eye ($43), and filet ($39).  My favorite was the filet.  I thought the T-bone itself was good, but it was too peppercorny for me.  The rib eye was very good. Overall, meat was yummy, well prepared, and cooked at a true medium rare... but not m

review_1946.Review: The wait staff was exceptional. I guess they have a new menu because it was not what my mouth had been watering for! Expected more organic grass fed beef. Only thing they had was a buffalo steak. Why would you massage a steer and then feed it something (corn/grains) it couldn't digest? The apps were great, the drinks good but pricey. Overall, I would not go back again.

review_1947.Review: This is a great "special occasion" restaurant. The price point is too high for a casual dinner; however, the service and menu are great. My waitress was very familiar with the menu and answered all our questions and gave great recommendations for each course. When a guest at my table mentioned she was looking for a private event venue, she found the the coordinator, who subsequently stopped by our table and followed up over the weekend. She also checked on our table regularly without being overbearing or obnoxious. The food is delicious; some of the best cuts of meat in the city! I would highly recommend this to anyone with the caveat that the final bill will be pricey...but well worth it!

review_1948.Review: Food was excellent. Staff were friendly and accomidating. We were there late and ultamitely the last to leave and at no time did the staff make us feel rushed to get us out of there. Great experience.

review_1949.Review: Okay food for over priced food that taste like you can get at any steakhouse

review_1950.Review: A really nice place to have a great steak. The truffle fries and truffle mac & cheese are unbelievable.

review_1951.Review: The food was excellent. The hostess was not friendly when we checked in.

review_1952.Review: Visually stunning presentation but most importantly, exquisite taste! Refreshing interpretation of "steak house" fare; added bonus--could actually hear our conversation--and it wasn't because the place was empty!

review_1953.Review: service was great, fast and knowledgeable. Food and wine were fantastic. Only valet parking was a challenge. Would definitely go back and eat there again!

review_1955.Review: Pricy considering the taste of foods

review_1956.Review: Excellent food, ambiance, server and food quality! What a great experience.

review_1957.Review: The entrees and sides are really well prepared. don't pass up the truffle fries and mac & cheese. Steaks are always just as ordered. Excellent service all around.

review_1958.Review: The shooter and fries are very good, and buffalo fillet good as well, but I don't recomend for bone in rib eye.

review_1959.Review: I love the relaxed feel of this place - modern, upscale – like a hipsters steakhouse. I definitely would return to try more steak. The table was split on the bread with bacon – one person thought was great, but the other thought the tastes didn’t quite mesh. Everyone loved their steak. Service was well-timed and friendly, but drinks were expensive.

review_1960.Review: Fantastic all around! Had our company holiday dinner here, & loved everything about it - food, atmosphere, & service were all excellent. Best dinner party we've ever had. Hamachi shooters were absolutely divine, the mix of flavors with the melt in your mouth hamachi were the perfect way to start a mealThe Australian F1 steak was the best steak i've had. They were out of the japanese a5 at the time but I can't imagine how it could be much betterThe mac 'n' cheese & mashed potatoes were fabulous, a slight hint of truffle in the mac, and large candied bacon bits on the mash-yum!Nice whiskey selection, perused wine menu but stuck with the brown drinks most of the eveningServer was friendly & attentive, can't wait to come back ag

review_1961.Review: 5A5 steak Lounge is a steak house with an asian flare which is great if you're looking for something different. The food was great, the service was wonderful, and just a nice relaxed environment. I highly recommend coming.

review_1962.Review: Our steak was delicious as always and I loved how the scenery was modern and tasteful for the holidays. Our maitre'd checked in on us during the night which made us feel special.

review_1963.Review: The 25 ounce on-bone ribeye w/balsamic red onions was estupendo, phenomenal. Portions on side dishes were very large, certainly bigger than expected. Potatoes au gratin delicious and like a main course. When I walked in, I expected trendy, but got a great man's meal. Best steak I ever had.

review_1964.Review: The food and the service were exceptional. On return visits I will always request Jim as my server. All of his suggestions were spot on. I look forward to returning to try more items on the menu.

review_1965.Review: Nice Restaurant for business or private dinner. Great Steaks and modern surroundings with some flair. Can recommend it.

review_1966.Review: GREAT FOR AN EARLY SUPPER WITH THE FAMILY.FOOD WAS OUTSTANDING.

review_1967.Review: excellent cuts of meat. Huge portions. Exceptionally prepared. If you enjoy a quiet, calm ambiance, this place is not for you. Very noisy.

review_1968.Review: This restaurant would have provided the perfect dining experience with uniquely prepared delicious meals but the hostess was rude and told us that we can only have 15 minutes in the Happy Hour lounge area and told us that we had to be seated in the dining section when there were no other diners in the restaurant!

review_1969.Review: We had pretty terrible service and the food was average at best. Wouldn't go back. We sat in the bar and waited forever for our food. We had to cancel 2 of our items because we had to leave. We asked for edamame right when we sat down and didn't get it for 30 mins. They brought it with our food even thought we asked the waitress 3x to bring it right away.

review_1970.Review: Food and service are excellent and the ambience is great.

review_1971.Review: From the time my party and I arrived until we left was a very special occasion. Everyone was very warm and friendly. The waitress was delightful and very attentive. The food was excellent. Those steaks are really juicy and well seasoned. The hoison ribs were very good. I celebrated my birthday that night and felt very special and satisfied.

review_1972.Review: Took my girlfriend for her birthday and 5A5 went well out of their way to make our meal special.

review_1973.Review: Meh. No espresso. No real A5 Wagyu IMPORTED FROM JAPAN like it says on the menu's first page -- it's all from Australia.

review_1974.Review: Our party of 6 shared a variety of dishes, some better than others. One of us had the regular filet and thought he preferred it to my daughter's $20 per ounce 5A5 filet. I thought they were both good, just different. The Lobster Tempura was great but the Edamame was bland and the waiter never brought the salt or soy sauce that we requested to perk it up. I guess he knew he was getting the 18% tip that was automatically added to the bill without warning. That may also be the reason it took three requests to bring our bottle of wine from the bar to our table and why they just laughed it off when they put the wrong name on the complementary birthday desert for my daughter. It kind of ruined what should have been a very special $800 meal.

review_1976.Review: I took my husband out for his birthday here. Our first experience with the restaurant was leaving a message to see if we could bring our infant. I didn't have my call returned so I emailed the message through Open Table and asked that they reply soon so we could get a babysitter as needed. They didn't call until the day before, but fortunately it was okay to bring the baby. They even had highchairs. It was just frustrating not hearing back promptly. Once there, the ambiance and service were great. The truffle fries were delicious and the quality of the food was good. The 20 day aged steak was seasoned well, but my husband felt the cut was too thick. My sea bass was good but the sauce was a liitle havy. Overall a good experience.

review_1977.Review: I went to 5A5 with my husband to celebrate my birthday. It is a good special occasion restaurant. The steak I had was delicious. The decor was very chic, and the clientele definitely matches the ambiance. However, I did not feel like we mattered as much to our waiter as some of the larger groups around us did.

review_1978.Review: My wife and I got a night out and had a wonderful time at 5A5. What a great twist on a steakhouse!Super fun menu. We want to come back with a group and grab a batch of small plates (Asian and Western) and some wine. We'll leave room for the steaks (at least the 4 oz portions). We're not huge red meat people, but when we're in the mood, we want it done right. The variety of cuts, age, beef types, and portions was an unexpected delight. Our steaks were literally perfect in every way. Our waiter, and the service in general, was fantastic.Go deep and splurge or get a tremendous value with a group of friends. Check out 5A5, you'll love it!

review_1979.Review: Best part of the meal was my Australian f1 steak-perfectly cooked, melt in your mouth!

review_1980.Review: Amazing meat! I never ate such a good meat like that. Too much noisy, high prices, but it's worthy, you would like to die for another diner in this place.

review_1981.Review: Very good food. Interesting menu. But anything coming from the bar is VERY SLOW. We've been there twice and found that getting a drink or glass of wine takes the longest time of any restaurant we've been to. Not sure if they need more bartenders or what.SA5 appears to encourage noise and they do it well. This is one of the loudest places in town. Even when you sit far away from the bar. The rotunda room has curved walls with hard surfaces that reflect the sound so you can always be sure to hear all the shrieks and shouts and laughs from the bar area. Guaranteed.

review_1982.Review: Food was delicious - we had hamachi shooters, filet mignon, buffalo filet, mac & cheese, and the red velvet dessert, and I can't find a single thing to complain about. I also had a coupon to use for the "lounge" which is apparently different than the restaurant, but they were nice enough to honor the coupon regardless. I have been here a couple of times now, and will continue to come back, as the staff is friendly, the atmosphere is great, and the food is delicious.

review_1984.Review: the "lounge" was over priced for what was delivered and with all the great places to eat in the city I wouldn't call this out as spectacular. The service started out strong yet as the place got busier, the longer it took for refills etc. I will say he fireplace on the wall is neat.

review_1985.Review: Service wasn't great and waiter wasn't very knowledgeable regarding wine list and cuts of meat.

review_1986.Review: I really enjoyed this restaurant and will definitely return.  The ambience was fun, sort of 60s style.  Waiter helpful, acoustics good for conversation.  Overall a great experience.

review_1987.Review: The menu was wonderful and our servicer was fantastic. Our starters and salads were wonderful, especially the mizuna. YUM! The mac and cheese, and the mashed potatoes were great sides. However, our entrees were less than wonderful. The steaks were luke warm at best, our medium orders were much closer to rare and the vegetables were cold, not even warm. It was okay, but there are too many steakhouses. We would return for appetizers and drinks.

review_1988.Review: Unique ambianceInteresting menuNice serverGreat cocktailsWarm atmosphere

review_1989.Review: This place was awesome. Exactly as the name would suggest, a lounge. This did not mean the steak wasn't steak house quality. I had the filet and it was delicious. The mashed potatoes with candied bacon and mac n'cheese were some of the best sides I've had. On top of that the service was on point. We'll definitely be back. My girlfriend thinks I'm the man for finding this place.

review_1990.Review: Kinda pricey for what little I got but the steak was excellent.

review_1991.Review: The food at 5A5 was great. I ordered the filet and it was tender and succulent. The ambiance of the restaurant was also great. The prices are high - but worth it.

review_1992.Review: Went for a special occasion with my husband, food was just decent. Service was very good however; our waiter was not familar with the wine list and could not advise on recommendations. Overall a nice meal. Also, bar area was extremely loud so don't go expecting a quiet romantic meal.

review_1994.Review: This spot is a bit pricey, but the food was fantastic. I and the filet mignon, which was cooked perfectly for me and was tender and juicy and full of great flavor. I also had potato au gratin, which was so rich and tasty! The ambiance is awesome and very chic. The bar area is very lively and vibrant...definitely a place to go to for a special evening.

review_1995.Review: In a city filled with truly great restaurants, A5A is a gem. Anyone that considers themselves a "foodie" MUST add this place to their dining resume. Don't miss the tempura lobster (which is perfect without the dipping sauce, BTW) and if you love garlic (like I do) get the macaroni and cheese side with your entrée. You'll thank me later.

review_1996.Review: I loved the seared foie gras, it was melting in your mouth and made perfect combination with sweet peach and all sauces. Also dry aged bone-in ny steak was good, meat itself is so tasty and huge that spinach and mash was absolutely unnecessary. Mash is one of the best 'cos its not over flavored like you find in most places. Definitely will go again and take my friend over for dinner.

review_1997.Review: All human beings must absolutely must try the lobster tempura... amazing!

review_1998.Review: Valet parking attendant was late to work and not there when I arrived.Happy hour specials not applicable to dinner... bummer.Service was slow, especially for early in the night.While all the meat was cooked properly, the seasoning/saucing was a bit heavy handed. My dry aged NY had equal amounts of blue cheese and meat.

review_1999.Review: Wow, this restaurant is quite a gem. Went for my birthday didn't know anything about it and now have raved to all my friends. I liked the fact that the portions were small but very adequate. The flavor outstanding,decor and ambiance very different from your mundane steak houses in San Francisco. In all a must dine!!!!!

review_2000.Review: Great you could go lower key or splurge but still get a great cut of meat. Waiter was VERY knowledgeable across the board and didn't make you feel bad if you wanted to stay at the lower end of the spectrum. You could even get a small cut of the high end beef if you wanted to dip your toes. Amazing sushi AND steak was out of this world.

review_2001.Review: This was one of those rare dinners where everything we ordered was incredible:cauliflower soup with sweetbreads; scallops b/l/t; lobster tempura; hamachi shooters; 6 oz. filet; mashed potatoes and mac & cheese. I'm not a big mac & chees fan but this mac & cheese will blow you away...ditto on the mashed potatoes. The scallops blt and lobster tempura are a must as well as the hamachi shooters. The steak was incredibly tender, almost like butter. I've been talking about this dinner for two days now! 5A5 you must check out and be willing to spend a little money to really enjoy it to its fullest.

review_2002.Review: A true classy gem of Asian Fusion Steak house with a modern atmosphere. Service was prompt and amiable. Didn't savor the top beef but the basic prime rib and fillet Mignon was tasty.

review_2003.Review: The prime rib was excellent as were the truffle fries and mushroom side. Aside from that, the dishes my party ordered were alright. The lamb was decent, but not stellar. The dry-aged NY strip was a little undercooked for medium rare. It is a great dining location. Would be fit for groups. Our server was scarce, but the water boy was excellent - keeping our glasses full yet being unobtrusive. All in all a good night.

review_2004.Review: how can you deny wagyu beef or even the prime rib?awesome confit with the grapes, figs, and confit-ish jellynoice wine selection

review_2005.Review: First time trying this restaurant, and I was not disappointed food was excellent service was great a bit on the expensive side though.

review_2006.Review: tucked away in the San Francisco FiDi area.. nice eatery for friends or social gathering

review_2007.Review: The wagyu beef did not live up to my expectations. Sauce on top of beef was very salty, making it impossible to taste the good meat. Small bites and appetizers were good however the main reason for dining at this restaurant was to experience the wagyu. A bit disappointed overall...

review_2008.Review: Great variety in their steaks as well as the rest of the menu!!!

review_2009.Review: this was my first time at this restaurant. The steaks were excellent. Service was great too.

review_2010.Review: we arrived early for our reservation and there was no place to sit and wait (small bar packed, special group took over lounge area), we left went for walk and returned but receptionist didn't greet us, ignored us while she spoke to friends. after 10 min acknowledged us and took us to seats. it had rained on our walk, we had no umbrellas and were quite wet, no offer to offer towels to dry even when requested. food was good ( though quite expensive) service good from waiter.

review_2011.Review: We were made to wait 10 minutes for our table although I'd had a reservation for a couple weeks. Because we weren't ready when he first came by, our server ignored us although we could see him chatting with different coworkers on a few occasions. Only once we complained to the host did our server become more attentive, but still intrusive. Plus they brought an unordered side dish, instead of one we ordered, that we sent back. Then they charged us for it until I asked for it to be taken off. The food was quite good but portions very small for the high prices. Not worth the money.

review_2012.Review: Excellent food, fantastic service in an oh so beautifully decorated atomosphere. Our tummys were all very happy after our visit and we plan on going back in the near future!

review_2013.Review: Excellent wagyu beef. Superb fillet mignon.  The food is absolutely gourmet. The chefs here take pride in their work. My wife and myself loved the food and will definitely eat there again.

review_2014.Review: It's just becoming my favorite! I've already written a previous review full of wonderful comments. I really prefer it during the week as it was quiet and intimate. Yet, if you're up for drinks and party, visit on the weekend. the place has a fantastic bar.

review_2015.Review: Very good restaurant. The touted "Wagu Beef" was great - but - would not order it again. We have had Rib Eyes just as good for a lot less. The Truffle Fries are to die for. A little too much butter in the sides (bok choy and mushrooms). Very pleasant experience.

review_2016.Review: Great place to enjoy a perfectly cooked steak. Great with friends or a date. Wonderful wait staff and fun atmosphere without being too over the top.

review_2017.Review: Excellent food and even better service.

review_2018.Review: Didn't care for my bone-in ribeye at all. It was very tough. Rest of the food was great.

review_2019.Review: The steak was divine, no question, but the best part was the service -- the staff was friendly and attentive without being overbearing. I really enjoyed the food and the cocktails.

review_2020.Review: Went to celebrate our anniversary. We arrived early and ordered appetizers and drinks in the bar. The Truffle fries were good, but after reading so many reviews that they were the best thing ever, I was disappointed...just tasted like good fries. Hubby got oysters, which he said were good and fresh. At our table, hubby ordered an Hamachi Shooter and was very disappointed after reading all the hype. For dinner, we each had a salad and then we ordered one 4oz wagayu ribeye, which was heaven, and an 8oz New York, which was average, to split. Dessert was average, at best. For what we paid, I was disappointed. The restaurant is pretty, but very loud (we went on a weeknight so I am sure it is even worse on weekends). Our server was impeccable!

review_2021.Review: Wonderfully visual dinning experience, very modern. Try the lobster tempura to start, very interesting flavors.The Petite Filet Mignon is exceptional, pair it with the Baby Bok Choy.Make sure to make time for 5A5 when you are in the City.

review_2022.Review: half off wines on Monday nights!!

review_2023.Review: This is my second visit to 5A5 and the purpose of this was to try the legendary A5 grade steak. We came here on a Monday night around 7:30pm. The restaurant was alot more quiet and relaxed compared with a Saturday night and had more of a working crowd. It was also half of bottles of wine so we enjoyed a nice reisling.We started with scallops and candied bacon - delightful. My date had a 4oz rib eye and me a 4oz filet mignon, both medium rare. Her rib eye was amazing, slithers of fat that felt like marble on the tongue. My filet was lean and tender, so pick according to your taste. Sides were mash (love it) and spinach (whatever). For dessert, I had red velvet with cheesecake flavored icecream (warm and cold!) and she had smores.

review_2024.Review: I have to say overall I was disappointed. I had the New York strip which was at 100z small and not particularly tender. It was cooked to a perfect medium but was surprisingly tough, it did not cut like a Prime piece of beef. One of my friends had the Wagu, which I tasted; it was good but not great. Another person at the table had the buffalo steak, which shockingly was the best piece of meat I tasted all night. The much vaunted mac and cheese side was ok, but again portions were small. Having eaten at Harris the week before its safe to say there is no comparison. If you are in it for the steak go elsewhere, if you want a hipper "with-it" destination this my be the place for you.

review_2025.Review: I had the bone-in aged filet and we all agreed it was the best of the 4 steaks we ordered. It was fabulous! We all enjoyed the sashimi appetizer, too. The food was good (except for the prime rib) and the decor is still fun, not having changed much from Frisee. Our waiter knew his steaks and our bartendress was a hoot, as we stayed after for cocktails. My only complaint was smoke that kept wafting by our table. We were in the back near what we thought was a back door but someone mentioned there may be a smoking lounge in the back. That would be unfortunate as it may infuse others' meals with that stench when they eat as well. I'll cross my fingers it's just a back door and hope someone was just smoking outside.

review_2026.Review: One of the best steaks I have had in San Francisco. The service was great. The decor is a refreshing change. We will definately return

review_2027.Review: Excellent best-graded beef from Japan. Wait service was very good, attentive.

review_2028.Review: I loved 5A5 at first sight! And I live 2 blocks from there so I've been there several times since! The quality is always excellent, the service very nice -always some guys warmer than others, but always very professional- The appetizers are outstanding for quality and presence. The Foie-Gras is out-of-this-word! I always have it, whatever else... the Sashimi, even the Truffle fries! Meat is the strong point, yet my favorite are the dryaged. excellent price-quality balance. and the great surprise: The sides! I never take sides normally... here they're a whole dish and a whole experience :) don't miss the Portobello! Enjoy! Only one issue: I always go during the week. Yesterday was Friday, very busy and energetic.

review_2029.Review: Beware that the menu doesn't have true A5 wagyu beef from Japan. Our server could not give us a clear reason why. "Cabassi & Rea" is Australian wagyu. That said, steaks are excellent, though a bit heavily sauced. The Australian F1 was not worth the price, but the filet mignon, NY strip (amazing truffle butter), and bone-in rib-eye were. The sides (mac 'n cheese, potato gratin) were delicious. Oyster and hamachi shooters to start, both very good. Red velvet dessert was a nice finish; the french toast dessert tasted of old fried oil and wasn't palatable. Though I could see that our table was ready, the host said it would be 10 minutes & directed us to the bar, an obvious attempt to make us purchase drinks there. I would visit again.

review_2030.Review: Overall, my friend and I enjoyed every minute of our dining experience. The server was very friendly and attentive. The atmosphere was very comfortable, modern, and pleasing to the eye. Food was superb! Best starters: the truffle fries & scallops! The sides, baby bok choy and mac & cheese, were perfect for our steaks. One slight criticism was that the steaks seemed to be a little more medium-well than medium. But, the taste was fine and still thoroughly enjoyable. The cocktail drinks are fabulous! The desserts were excellent. The Breakfast After Dark (French toast) was the best! I will definitely come back to try more food & drinks. I love the bar and the lounge setting. This would be a perfect place to have a small party.

review_2031.Review: If you like to taste or just eat very good, interesting, beef and you don't want it themed--a bordello theme, a ranch theme, or a late 19th century men's club theme--you might give this place a try.

review_2032.Review: One of the best filets I have ever had...The bone-in filet was amazing. Salads through entre, everything was excellent. Desserts were tiny...probably didn't need more, though. Service was attentive and knowledgeable. Will definitely return in the future.

review_2033.Review: Gave 5A5 a try for ONE SIMPLE REASON - they had A5 beef on the menu. Needless to say when I arrived and looked at the menu and did not see it, I was quite annoyed. My server explained to me that Japanese A5 beef is currently very difficult to get, as it is not being exported from Japan; and they they have the comperable Cabassi and Rea black label beef from Australlia. Should have been changed on their website. I called over a manager who was very polite, and gave me the same explanation. He did however insist that their website had been updated with their current menu. Once seeing that it had not been changed he apologized over and over. For the inconvenience he comped our sides, three desserts, and a bottle of port. CLASSY, Overall food A

review_2034.Review: The service was very good, however, the food was just okay. Other than the hamachi shooters, the fish was a little on the "not so fresh" side. The mac and cheese was excellent. Steaks were good. The bok choy was a little over done and the desserts were just so-so.

review_2035.Review: A great find.Dining room service was excellent (5 stars). The food was really good, too. Great cuts of meat and fresh produce. Creative menu. One fall down: We waited in the bar upon arrival before being seated. Cocktail service was very slow.

review_2036.Review: The food was delicious and our server was very good. However, when we arrived at the restaurant, the host insisted that our reservations were at 5:45 rather than the 7:15pm that was on my Open Table confirmation. This was strange since the restaurant called me the day before to confirm the reservation. The host was a bit rude and insisted that it was not his fault. They ultimately seated us but not without a bit of drama. Given this, the overall experience was not as good as it should have been.

review_2037.Review: Excellent food and great service. Great variety as well.

review_2038.Review: For the first course we had the foie gras. Very nicely done, seared on the outside 'til crispy around the edges but like butter inside. The Wagyu rib eye steak main course was excellent. Probably the best beef that I have ever eaten. The seasoning and sauce was a perfect match for the meat that melted in your mouth. Of course, it has to be medium rare to maintain that heavenly texture... Portabella and Bok Choy side dishes were good but not great. Dessert was also good but not great. Otherwise this would have been a five star dining experience. It's one of those "every now and then places" just for special occasions, otherwise you'll need to work extra hard or hit the lotto to make this place a habit... and have a cardiologist on speed dial

review_2039.Review: The restaurant has a very modern ambient atmosphere. Great spot for a nice romantic dinner. The foods were excellent. Please to listen to the server recommendation. The place specialized in meat and steak. So I choose the buffalo filet, and my partner chose Australian sea filet (I think that what it called). Both steak is so tender and juicy. Do also try the lobster tempura.. It was so crispy yet moist.. last we have Peach & Cream for dessert, and it was awesome. The hemechi shots were great also. Dinner for two come out to two hundreds dollar. It was a nice experience. I would go back if there another opportunity.

review_2040.Review: Great if you like steak (hence the name). The bar and lounge is better value. Overall, a must go to place and an enjoyable experience.

review_2041.Review: If you prefer to have your choices made for you, this is the place to go. There are several Japanese beef selections which are interesting if spending $145 for an entree seems a good value. However, if you are looking for a traditional steak house meal, this is not the place. The prime rib, while tender and well cooked, was served in thin slices; baked potatoes are not offered, there was only one non-ceasar green salad.This place is the definition of trendy- the salad plates are narrow rectangles-which makes eating lettuce a real challenge. There is a large bar but if you want a mixed drink stick to those on the menu- anything else isn't available. Eating here was like dining at your mother's- good food but she chooses it.

review_2042.Review: My boyfriend and I had a wonderful meal at 5A5. Great Food for All!

review_2043.Review: Love love love this place! Went for a birthday and the wait staff was amazing! The food was amazing! It was absolutely perfect! Thank you so much!

review_2044.Review: Incredible beef. Great knowledgeable wait staff.

review_2045.Review: Great food and very attentive service!

review_2046.Review: AAAAAAmazing! Everything was amazing the food, the crowd, the atmosphere and especially our waitress Shawna! She made our night :)

review_2047.Review: Great food but this place is really way too loud to be enjoyed.

review_2048.Review: We had a pretty good experience overall at 5A5 only to be slightly spoilded at the end when the busboy (?), not waitress, too eager to collect our plates.The autralian beef (8oz) was slightly overdone at the outside, but perfect in the middle.I would definitely want to go back.

review_2049.Review: The food and service were just fabulous. This was a wonderful dining experience. You could not ask for better.

review_2050.Review: Some of the best food we have ever had, and definitely the best service we have ever experienced. We will definitely return here for future special occasions.

review_2051.Review: Very loud which is made worse by the shape of the interior. Could hear the table on the opposite side of the restaurant. Was very annoying. One of the best steaks I have ever had. Food was excellent. Service was great, our waiter was attentive and engaged us in conversation and answered all our questions.

review_2052.Review: Got rather noisy because there were some large parties there.

review_2053.Review: Other than the fact some UCLA group was there taking the noise level over the top, it was a perfect night...the ever popular Hamachi shooters, the Australian Waygu...affordable and delicious...and the truffle fries, OMG. The service is always over the top, best reason to go there (if they can hear you). Love the decor and it is a very comfortable place to have dinner. Even if you don't eat beef, plenty of delicious fish and sushi on the menu...and the sides are delicious. I was little disapointed in the chocolate dessert (what's with the powder?) but loved the Red Velvet cake.

review_2054.Review: Not kidding when we say that the waygu beef was definitely the most delicious cut of meat we've ever had. Amazing! Great cocktails and laid-back, but knowledgeable, staff as well.

review_2055.Review: Steak was fabulous but all other courses average to below average for price

review_2056.Review: Great food & service. Had the Lobster Tempura & Filet Mignon (10 oz.). I enjoyed the fact that all the servers helped each other out, which made everything much more effiecient. Will come back again.

review_2057.Review: The complimentary bacon bread was awesome! Would have given 5 stars if the truffle fries had more truffle oil. All 3 of us loved every dish we ordered, especailly the prime ribs (yes, ribs with an "s", they served 3 large generous pieces in garlic sauce, yummo!), the steak was tender and tasty, and the dessert just topped everything off beautifully! The wine was half off the bottle, (special for Mondays), which was a really good deal. Overall, a great dining experience!

review_2058.Review: The food overall was great! Jason, the manager or owner, was very welcoming and accomodating to ensure our standards were met. The server, Wes, was not as pleasant as he could have been. He seemed very rigid and unwelcoming. He really needs to loosen up and show EACH and EVERY customer the same care. We honestly felt judged due to our appearance, which is quite sad in this day and age. We tipped over 20% still because we enjoyed our runner and Jason. If it wasn't for those two, I would have given 1 star for service.

review_2059.Review: I don't know what all the fuss is about. Food was only "fair", and therefore, somewhat overpriced. We dined on a Sunday night...is that the Chef's night off?

review_2060.Review: Highly recommend if you are looking for a good steak!

review_2061.Review: Try the truffle fries. They were out of this world delicious! The flavor of the potatoes really tasted like potatoes on steroids. Amazing.I ordered the hamachi shooter without avocado. I think that they may have had to make it from stratch for me. When they did, the sauce was so hot that my mouth was on fire for five minutes. My husband got the regular one with the avocado and his wasn't hot at all, so I think that it was just bad measuring. They were very nice and replaced it with another shooter, which was delcious.Other than that unfortunate experience, I found the food to be delicable and the service terrific.It was very noisy there, so be prepared for that.

review_2062.Review: Its beef just melts in my mouth. Close to the real kobe beef. 4 oz was just not enough.

review_2063.Review: Way overpriced and incredibly loud. From a value perspective, not worth it...way too pricy for what was delivered...you pay for the atmosphere. Tried 5-6 dishes, best part was the Filet Mignon (which is their big selling point)Won't go back.

review_2064.Review: I've written a review of this restaurant before and I still only have good things to say! 5A5 is not your grandfather's or even your father's Steak House. 5A5 isn't a tradional Steak House, it's a San Francisco Steak House in every sense of the word. The menu is definitely recognizable w/ classic cuts of meat but it's also contemporary & eclectic. The food, amazing. The service, 1st rate and the vibe is so welcoming. In a city that so often pats itself on the back for its diversity of ethnicities, it's so refreshing to actually experieince it in a Financial District restaurant. Patrons and staff alike. I took my brother there to celebrate his birthday and it was great. The team @ 5A5 is so attentive. It was an over-the-top evening!

review_2065.Review: The most amazing steak I have had in years. Fabulis meal and service.

review_2066.Review: We have been to 5A5 five times since it has opened and each time has been exceptionally wonderful. Of course the wagyu plates are phenomenal, but their other steaks are also very well-prepared and flavorful. We have tried every steak place in the city and nothing else comes close. They have tasty side dishes that fall in the creative category (excellent uni shooters) as well as side dishes that are familiar but elevated, such as Mac n cheese. The wine list is surprisingly good and reasonably priced. An added bonus is the menu of creatively delicious desserts. The service: as always, gracious, welcoming, friendly. Definitely a gourmet experience worth every penny. Certainly easier than flying to Japan for this caliber of steak.

review_2067.Review: Shooters are the best on the menu...Great place for night out. Very pricey though...

review_2068.Review: Absolutely fantastic experience, beyond all expectations. The meal was perfectly well done if not extraordinary, but what stood out most was the impeccable service. Wonderful night.

review_2069.Review: The Lobster Tempura was to die for. My 100% pure bred Waguy Ribeye was DELISH but not worth the $19/oz. price as it's not better than the Dry Aged Bone-In Fillet.

review_2070.Review: Terrible! Made us wait at the bar for 30 minutes even though our table was ready the whole time - a cheap trick to get us to order drinks?
