The host bragged that the server could answer any questions, yet all she did is recommend things in order of expense. Ruined a wagyu steak with cheap sauce. Ordered a 2007 bottle of wine and they brought a 2009.

review_2071.Review: 5A5 Steak loung was not kidding when they decided to call this a steak "lounge". We were expecting a steak house and realized they meant lounged. Very relaxed atmosphere. The food was awesome!! Definitely worth going for. The service made the experience all the more enjoyable. 5 stars!!! If you are a foodie, this is definitely a place you will enjoy! Come prepared to eat and endulge!!

review_2072.Review: Absolutely outstanding. Came here to celebrate our 8 year anniversary and our server, Lynn, took very good care of us. At the end of our meal she even got my keys from the valet and brought them to us. We will definitely come back!

review_2074.Review: It's a good steakhouse but i have seen better ones. We had a nice dinner but not one we will remember for long time.

review_2075.Review: If you want to try some amazing product, this is the place. Don't let the servers sway you, the Wagyu is not too rich and you will definitely need a large portion to be satisfied.

review_2076.Review: Great ambience, food and service. We are serious steak lovers, and this place is a serious steakhouse. And yet, 5A5 also offers a level of sophistication that's not often found in serious steakhouses. Love it. Prices are a little on the high side (especially if you decide on any of the Wagyu beef options), but the place is well worth a splurge.

review_2077.Review: Really solid place. Not your typical "steak house". I've dined in SF for 25 years, and am pretty impressed with this place. I hope they can keep it up.

review_2078.Review: Energetic lounge filled with young patrons that like to eat and drink. The food was delicious, though a bit pricey for the scene. The service was efficiently perfect, and overall we had a great experience.

review_2079.Review: Shauna was a gem, introducing us newbies to 5A5 to all the best parts of the menu: the Hamachi shooter (I wanted an entire bowl of the stuff), the lovely small portions of beef, which were perfect for both of us (no big slabs of unchewable meat here, perfect portions, perfect texture). The sides were delicious -- the bok choy had decadent pork belly bits and the scalloped potatoes were firm and cheesey. A thoughtful custom birthday cake dessert topped a perfect evening. I'm coming back for the cocktails and truffle fries as well.

review_2080.Review: Everyone in our group of six diners expressed that last night A5A served up some of the best steaks anywhere in the City. I had a the prime New York and steak simply does not get any better, though the bone-in rib-eye that I tasted from my neighbor’s plate was terrific too.Yes, the A5A steaks are better than Harris', Morton's and Ruth's Chris. Yes, they are better than Bobo's. Moreover, the starters are wonderfully inventive and tasty. I'd skip the desserts.A+, A5A!

review_2081.Review: Had wanted to try the steaks at 5A5 for a long time, finally made it with a buddy. Friend had the regular filet mignon while I tried 4oz of the A5 wagyu. Delicious tasting meat but the sauces on top smothered it more than I would have liked. Ask for it more rare than you'd like because it comes sadly overcooked. Our server was attentive and very friendly. Sides of mash potatoes (w/ big chunks of bacon), mac and cheese (greasy but tasty), started with truffle oil fries and 2 sets of shooters (those were pretty good). Tasty meal but was it worth $26/ounce for A5? Eh, worth a try at least once in your life. :) I actually liked the steaks at Lark Creek Steak better but this was worth trying.

review_2082.Review: Outstanding service, great food in a modern setting!

review_2083.Review: Great steaks, service and bar scene. The air conditioning could be toned down for early dining ; my guest and I had to keep out jackets on throughout the meal - San Francisco does not get that hot to keep the air condition on so high !

review_2084.Review: Very fine upscale cuisine. Definitely a special occasion destination.

review_2085.Review: Food was good. They pushed their very pricey specialty steaks a bit much. We were seated immediately. However, I noticed on two previous walk-bys and on the the night we dined that there was absolutely no one in their bar lounge area. Not one person for nearly two hours.When we asked how the restaurant was named, it was definitely a stock answer and actually sounded contrived.

review_2086.Review: The food is great and the portions ample. The noise is a bit loud. The waiter (Jim) was great and the owner gave us a ride back to our hotel when we had to wait too long for a taxi. Now that's service!

review_2087.Review: We had a wonderful time at 5A5 Steak Lounge, by far the best food!! The steaks were cooked perfectly to our order. The Kobe beef was so tender it melted in your mouth. I would highly recommend this restaurant for any occasion!! Please ask to be sitted in Ali's section, our waiter was attentive, patient, and very funny!! He had made our evening fun with his vibrant personality and wit!

review_2088.Review: The service was attentive and excellent without being over bearing. The appetizer was very good (we had some shooters and tempura lobsters). The cocktail was delicious. However, my T-bone steak was chewy and drenched in peppercorn sauce that I could not taste the meat--just pepper. It was like "where's the beef ?" My friend had a the bone-in fillet with a lighter sauce and enjoyed it better. Desert was very good (we had peanut butter cheesecake with raspberry and chocolate sauce). Over all a good experience. Food is good not excellent and not a good value overall as the meat entree did not come with any side dishes.

review_2089.Review: I had a great experience here - the burger was fantastic: rich, juicy and flavorful. It's a bit pricey, but the quality is very good and the ambiance/atmosphere is pretty cool.Excellent and friendly service also helped to make this a great dining experience.

review_2090.Review: Unbelievable cuisine and service. We will definitely return to 5A5!

review_2091.Review: Overall, things went well. Our reservation seemed to take a while so we had a drink at the bar and didn't mind. After about 30 minutes we were seated, yes we had a reservation. The chef sent over the lobster tempura immediately because of the long wait which we all thought was sweet. We had the sliders as an appetizer and they were amazing! I had the ceaser salad to start and it blew me away. So refreshing! My only complaint for the whole night was that it seemed like we were in a club eating a filet & a nice bottle of wine. The music would have been WAY too intense if we would have brought anyone over the age of 30. For us, it was an adventure, not typical of a steak house but the food was amazing.

review_2092.Review: Very interesting restaurant a Steak Lounge, food was generally very good, steaks were high quality the AA5 steaks were priced out of my budget but settled for the 12oz Kobe A5 $95 which initially came to me overcooked, they made a new steak which was absolutely outstanding and worth the wait. My only real issue is the noise as it was way too noisy for enjoyable dinner so beware. This restaurant has a Miami ffeel in SF...overall an enjoyable noisy night out on the town.

review_2093.Review: Our waiter Daniel was the best - attentive but never hovered. He remembered me from dining there 3 months ago and remembered how I liked my steak! Unbelievable. One of my favorite restaurants in SF.

review_2094.Review: We selected this restaurant on the recommendation of Open Table, we were not disappointed. This was by far the best meal I've had in awhile. From the Tempura Lobster appetizer to the excellent meat choices, this place has the best meat by far. Unfortunately we didn't have time to try the desserts, we had a show to attend. I will definitely be back.

review_2095.Review: If you want a good steak, go somewhere else.

review_2096.Review: This is THE best steak house restaurant in SF.

review_2097.Review: Excellent service. Knowlegeable and attentive. Good recommendations. Food was good but not spectacular. Sides a little sparse. Mushrooms just ok and Mac/Cheese runny. Great desserts.

review_2099.Review: The food was great and the overall service/atmosphere was excellent! We had the filet mignon, sushi and truffle fries and enjoyed all of it!

review_2100.Review: Great service, great food, great time was had

review_2101.Review: 5A5 Steak Lounge was wonderful. The food was absolutely delicious and our server was great. We were celebrating a birthday and they made it extra special.

review_2102.Review: I'm not a red meat eater, so I might not be in the best position to judge the food as a whole, but the lobster bisque (too salty) and mac and cheese (too runny) were both disappointing. My significant other loved the prime rib, so I wouldn't rule this place out for meat lovers. It would also be a good after-work drink spot.The service was slow and a bit scattered, though the staff generally seemed eager to please.

review_2103.Review: great mealwait staff was knowledgeable and very attentivenew pastry chef hit it out of the park with his take on french toast!!

review_2104.Review: One steak ordered medium rare was well done and had to be sent back. It took 15 min for it to arrive at the table again, which seems a bit excessive for something that only needs to be cooked very briefly. Then the plate arrived without the side orders of mac and cheese and spinach that were on the plate. We had to ask for that to be replaced.We were comped a $3 scoop of ice cream as a good will gesture I guess.Overall, good food but the flaws in the food/service detracted from it.

review_2105.Review: Their 5A5 Filet Mignon is amazing but pay attention.. its $25 per oz. That is not so obvious on the menu. Well worth it though.

review_2106.Review: everything was wonderful. My only complaint is that we had a member of our party join late, just after our food was served. It took a long time for him to get his entree. Other than that, it was great.

review_2107.Review: I would come to this place again with co workers after work for a nice happy hour fun or bunch of friends to relax and enjoy some modern atmostphere. However, me and someone came for a nice romantic heart warming dinner, the music is more of a rave and dance techno so not much of a romantic mood setting for us. We started arguing during first course. Personally I would not return to this restaurant for personal reason, but I would definately recommend to my friends.

review_2108.Review: Our service was perfect, the meal was delicious (love the 3 potato au gratin) and dessert was yummy (brad pudding). Overall, we had a great experience.We took business cards to be sure to give them to friends so they could visit!

review_2109.Review: We celebrated my husband's 40th birthday here. We had a wonderful time. The staff was friendly and knowledgeable. The dessert was amazing!

review_2110.Review: The beef was excellent, but so were the non-meat dishes...

review_2111.Review: This restaurant is a dilemma. The food and service were very good but, especially for the price, there is nothing special about this restaurant. At the price level here, many other San Francisco restaurants offer food with more imagination and dining rooms that are more festive or special. Also, the menu choices here are EXTREMELY limited. Basically, I can't complain about the food or service but this restaurant is boring---if you're trying to impress a client or going out for a special occasion, go elsewhere.

review_2112.Review: Wanted to try out a new place near the office and 5A5 seemed like a cool place with very modern decor. I was expecting good food at a "hip" looking place, but nothing more. Boy was I wrong. We arrived early and had a drink at the bar. Nice bar with good bar food options and tasty cocktails. Next time when we are looking for after work drinks and finger food this will be the place to go. Then we had dinner. I had a hamachi shooter which was fantastic. I could have had a donzen to eat. Then the buffalo filet which was cooked to perfection. For a cut of meat that is lean they did a nice job. Finally, we shared the mac & cheese, which I thought was one of the best I ever had. When we left we both agreed we were pleasantly surprised!

review_2113.Review: My review is slightly mellowed by having gotten a no-show email when I got back to work. Not only did I eat here, but I was just about to write about how amazing the steak sammie is. Had they been busy, not even worth mentioning. However, it is mildly annoying that when only 4 tables were being used, it was not possible to correctly click on my name on their computer so I was officially "present" for opentable purposes. But, I will say when I called, the problem was quickly fixed.Now, the steak sandwich: WORTH mentioning. Heaven on a roll. Such a lovely lunch menu - just the right combination of steak/potato fare and posh but tasty staples. Service was fast an attentive, though again, they were not busy, so I cannot speak to wha

review_2114.Review: definite appears to be great place to stop by after work to decompress; not great for lunch unless one plans on very leisurely service. Food-kobe burgers cooked as requested; nice meat flavor-almost too rich tasting; onion rings looked great; bland flavor; chicken sandwich was reportedly good enough. Specialty non-alcohol nojitos were delish; no time left for dessert-lunch was also hitting 2-hr mark. Our waiter appeared to be able to focus on one table at a time - we had a good 40 min wait to place our orders. He just never came by. Food did not take long to prepare; nice size portions

review_2115.Review: Only had 2 entree available and they where both sandwiches. Was expecting better food choice for the price.

review_2116.Review: Although the food was good, the service was not. We ate here on the "Dine About Town" special and were made to feel like second class citizens because we chose the special menu. I won't go back.

review_2117.Review: I went for Dine About Town, and I was honestly unsure that I would like it. The food was delicious: one of the best filet mignons I have ever had. The mac and cheese was delectable. Even the iceberg lettuce salad (I usually hate iceberg) was amazing; the iceberg tasted more like butter lettuce and it was dressed to perfection. The service was excellent (friendly but not chummy, efficient, unobtrusive), and the ambiance is fashion forward--not your typical steak house.

review_2118.Review: The Ribeye was a GREAT cut but was underseasoned. The glaze wasnt that great. The Mac and Cheese was AWESOME as well as the sliders. Service and tables were good. Place was VERY nice & clean. The music was a nice touch.

review_2119.Review: nice restaurant but way to noisy.

review_2120.Review: Food was very good. A little noisy but it made for a fun evening. We enjoyed our evening there and liked the fact that they did not try to hustle us out the door to turn the table over. Would go back again!

review_2121.Review: Steaks were good but overpriced. Service could be better.

review_2122.Review: Located in the old Frisson restaurant site and kept many of the architectual features. Arrived during the end of Happy Hour and the large crowd raised the noise level throughout the restaurant. First Course: Iceburg Salad (similar to a Wedge Salad). I think that the large chunks of bacon should have been finely cut. Excellent blue cheese dressing. Main Course: Medium rare Beef Fillet. Nice crust but interior was partially rare. Slightly sweet sauce added nothing to an otherwise nice cut of beef. Dessert: Ice Cream Torte was well prepared. Not overly sweet or heavy and crust remained crunchy rather than soggy. Gin Martini was properly prepared and served. Mohito had a bitter aftertaste probably due to the mint.

review_2123.Review: Attractive decor but my kobe burger was overdone. How can you get that wrong at a steakhouse?

review_2124.Review: This is one of those places that I feel is overpriced and definitely overrated. It is almost like they are taking themselves too seriously and it is just not all that it says it is. I will say that the NY steak with truffle butter that we ordered was delicious, but I was unimpressed with the service overall, our 2nd course of seared scallops took more than 30 minutes, and they didn't have a couple of the bottle of wines that we wanted to order.

review_2125.Review: great steaks. good cocktail list and wine list. only thing that i did not like was i went on the dine about town and on a mon when it is 1/e off wine. lst time i went they gave the 1/2 off wine, this time they did not honor it if you did the dine although it was not noted anywhere in their description about dine or their website that it is no longer honored

review_2126.Review: We were very disappointed in the quality of the food.

review_2127.Review: Charming ambiance, kind of a Restaurant in the Round, but not in the normal footpath of people.Near Eureka Theater.Waiters extremely helpful, but not overwhelming.American food, very good.

review_2128.Review: The dry aged steaks were amazing!! And the sides dishes were delicious. We compared the regular filet to the aged one and it was a world of a difference. Never get a non-dry aged cut if you can help it!

review_2129.Review: I totally love the decor here! I felt like I was on vacation in NYC or Vegas. The candied bacon on the mashed potatoes was to die for--that would work as an appetizer or side dish alone.

review_2130.Review: It's quite noisy so if you're looking for an intimate setting, this isn't the place to go. However, it is an energetic place where there is a vibrant atmosphere so there's alot of animated chatter that can overwhelm your own conversation. Our waiter was incredibly hospitable and allowed my date and I to take our time in conversation as well as make suggestions to us on the menu. We both ordered the Caesar Salad with anchovies and 6oz filet mignon. We also added some side dishes to go with the filet mignon, which were the mushrooms and the cheesy mash. Filet mignon was heaven and I'll definitely go back for more. The cheesy mash was also delightful with bits of bacon in it. We're planning on going back again soon!

review_2131.Review: This was good but not amazing. I am still surprised at how good the steaks are here. I was disappointed to find the bread pudding in a different form from last time. Smaller and not as amazing but still extremely good.

review_2132.Review: I took my whole out-of-state family here the other night. Sometimes it's hard to find a place that will please everyone, but this worked out well. Everyone cleaned their plates (including those of us doing the Dine About Town meals), the service was excellent, and the environment was very enjoyable. I don't eat beef, but I understand that it's quite delicious.

review_2133.Review: 5a5 is a great place. The service is impectable, the food superb and the experience unforgetable.

review_2134.Review: Great classy place! Staff, very good. Young, shiek vibe. Prices were up there for everything. But, you chose if you want a$100 bill, or $500. A great place for a date!

review_2135.Review: Great place and I plan to host a function there.

review_2136.Review: 5A5 is an interesting take on a steakhouse. Was not willing to part with $160 for a Kobe Steak, but the regular steak was amazing. The steaks we had were cooked to perfection - medium rare. The Bok Choy was fresh and prepared perfectly. Our dessert was great a Peanut Butter souffle with chocolate - it had home made butterfingers that were amazing. The service was OK - it started great and finished great, but we had long stretches of being ignored as the place was surprisingly busy for a holiday weekend, they seemed to be staffed OK - but rush hour was a bit much. With that said our server was very nice and very professional.

review_2137.Review: Awesome customer service & excellent food & wine

review_2138.Review: average for the price. would not go back for food maybe a drink. Houstons 100 times better per value at liveliness.

review_2139.Review: Every element of this meal was beyond expectations. Not only was the food spectacular in flavor but also in appearance. If I had my camera with me I would have taken a picture of every plate that come out of the kitchen., We had a party of 5 and everyone was impressed! even a former chef.... I recommend this for business or pleasure-a winner all the way around!

review_2140.Review: We had a great time! They made our anniversary a very special night for us!

review_2141.Review: the food is first class.The steaks are cooked to perfection.they melt in your mouth.the service is always the best. It is a great dining experiance.

review_2142.Review: Excellent food and service, and from the appetizer to dessert, we enjoyed every bite of our meal. I got a bone in New York steak, and my wife got a Wagyu New York ( 4 oz. because it cost $26 an ounce!)..My NY was good, but that Wagyu was unbelievable. "Experts and gourmets who have recently discovered Wagyu meat consider it to be the most tender, most succulent and tastiest meat in the world." And so do I ! 5A5 is not a traditionally designed steak house at all, it is modern and spacious. Service was perfect, gracious, helpful, it seemed like our waitress was there whenever we needed her, and only then. It is quite expensive, but worth it (for special occasions).

review_2143.Review: Not sure on noise rating as only a few people were there at 5:30 when we went. Top 5 all time dinners.

review_2144.Review: The menu is versatile and tasty. Some of the male waitstaff, one in particular(tall, very handsome dark haired guy), is outstanding.

review_2145.Review: Everything was wonderful at 5A5 from the outstanding service to the fabulous food. The best meal I have had in a long time.

review_2146.Review: Service was great. The atmoshere was mid-century. The food was disappointing. I had a $44 bone-in NY that was tough. Given to huge emphsis on beef, I would think this was in their wheelhouse.

review_2147.Review: Great food, quiet surroundings and attentive servers who know alot about the menu. I would definitely go back again!

review_2148.Review: Best steak in town. The Wagyu is out of this world.

review_2149.Review: We had the A5 waygu filet mignon and new york steak, it was just ok compared to other A5 waygu we've been to. Ambiance is nice but overall nothing to wow about.

review_2150.Review: The 4 oz. kobe filet was outstanding and the hamachi shooter was good. Everything else was a disappointment though. For the money that we paid ($250), I expected more. The concept is great but the execution was lacking. The sashimi "bites" were underseasoned and there was so little sauce on each piece that overall it was bland. The lobster bisque was too watery; a little cream and salt and it would have been perfect. The macaroni and cheese contained such an over amount of truffle oil (not mentioned on the menu description) that we couldn't eat it and it was not removed from our bill though the waitress apologized. The salmon entree was passable; the tofu cake was good but the salmon skin was soggy and unappetizing. Desserts were good.

review_2151.Review: The 15oz Ribeye Steak was somewhat rare although ordered medium, and it can't beat a regular steak house (especially for a big time red meat eater).  But the ambience is really nice, it feels like you are in a fancy restaurant (not an old dark steakhouse decor).  Staff was very friendly.  Highly recommend for hangout with friends, but don't expect a conventional steakhouse quality food

review_2152.Review: The food was EXCELLENT, but it was very loud!!! A great place, but not for a romantic NIGHT OUT!!!

review_2153.Review: Food was good, one of our steaks came overcooked and the waiter noticed one of us looking at it and came on his own, saw the steak, and took it away and changed it. Great way to address issues. The other steaks were great, and so the side dishes.

review_2154.Review: Went for the "Neighborhood Special" 3 course Sunday dinner. The noise level was way down....much different from the after work experience at the bar on week nights. The steak was the best I have ever experienced. My husband had the salmon. It was prepared to perfection on a bed of bok choy with mussels and clams. Desserts to die for. Only down side was that the lettuce on the Ceasar Salad would have been fresher, but GO FOR THE BEEF!!!

review_2155.Review: 5A5 is a modern, hip, spin on the traditional steak house. The wait staff is very gracious and knowlegable. I like the fine variety of Angus, Buffalo and Wagyu beef.Be prepared for a very active bar scene. Drinks are superb. The management was very welcoming and attentive to our needs .

review_2156.Review: The A5 steak lived up to its billing. The sampler platter provides a great opportunity to compare and contrast the different grades of beef. If you are a carnivore and have lots of steak experience, the menu will challenge you to place this at the top of your list.

review_2157.Review: We went there for our Anniv. and we had a great time. The place looks nice and comfortable. The food was great, I thought they were going to be small portions so we ordered different kind of food but had alot of left overs. The truffle fries were BOMB in a good way. I wish they had a smaller portion in the bone in rib eye.

review_2158.Review: very interesting for a meat lover--it is not just a Harris or Chris type gob of meat. but also very expensive. without wine we spent about $300 for two people. we could have spent a lot less but the feature dish is $130 per each just for openers.

review_2159.Review: The look of the place is fabulous, the service is excellent and the food is wonderful! And I have to say we were on vacation with my 5 year old son (who loves being in "grown up" restaurants) and were treated really well...

review_2160.Review: Notably food was good, but service lagged. Finished plates weren't collected quick enough. Literally for 5-10 minutes.

review_2161.Review: I really wasn't impressed by this steak house. The scallop app was over cooked and measly, and the hamachi and salmon shooters were just so-so. Overall, I felt it was overpriced, and the food was sub-par. You can get a much better steak at Boulevard...

review_2162.Review: stopped in for a quick bite on my way home Friday. Walked in at 6:30 and had no problem getting a seat. My experience: My steak was good, tasty, and cooked correctly (and handled correctly). Mashed Potato side, as recommended by my server, very so/so. wouldn't reorder them. Had the lobster bisque for a starter, pretty good. Ok - so food was good (not Morton's good but better than average). Ambiance: the place is a bit confused and maybe tries a bit too hard. Let the food and the bar speak for themselves. The vibe and customers will follow. Service: This was the gaping hole. I couldn't finish one dish without being clobbered over the head with the next dish. staff needs to relax and give me a good experience.

review_2163.Review: The aged bone-in fillet mignon was the best steak I have eaten in a restaurant. The buffalo fillet my wife was served was excellent as well. Eat here if you want a great steak in San Francisco. I will not visit another steakhouse in San Francisco as long as the 5A5 Steak Lounge is open.

review_2164.Review: Their lobster was very good. Just slightly battered and flash fried. It was yummy. The truffle fries was good too. I will definitely go back there again to have their bites...

review_2165.Review: Fantastic food + attentive service what more could you ask for! Worth every penny. Lots of beautiful people having a good time in the bar/lounge. Gorgeous decor too!

review_2166.Review: The A5 steak was really delicious. All of our meals were great. Try the Hamachi shooters for the opening course. The Bleu Cheese steak was the best taste to value ratio at our table.

review_2167.Review: I was very excited about going to 5A5. I was very disappointed with the food. If you spend $42 on a steak, it should not be dry. Very disappointed.

review_2168.Review: I liked it. We went on a quiet night, so the resturant wasn't noisy or too busy. My boyfriend had the oyster shooter, which he said has the typical sour/acidic taste, nothing special. We also tried the truffle fries which was good because they were crispy and hot out of the fryer. The spicy sauce also tasted good with the fries. There's no actual truffles in the fries...it might just refer to the shape. Both of us ordered filet migon, but mine was the 4oz. wagyu dish. It was very soft and tender, but not the softest steak that I have ever tried. You are better off ordering the regular filet mignon. The matcha donut dessert with peach tea oolong ice cream was pretty good and different...try it! =)

review_2169.Review: This was an outstanding find. Our reservation was later in the evening and the place was lively. Reminded me very much of a Las Vegas type steak house. Food and service were excellent.

review_2170.Review: Very uneven food: steaks very well prepared, sides were far over-loaded with cheese, butter, bacon (even the greens guys?!) Salads need a rethink, generally underdressed, strangely balanced and lacking in flavor. Shooters were mediocre with clever ideas like pressed watermelon, but suffered from poor prep/cut sizes. Table service was excellent but marred by a seemingly very poorly trained sommelier (wine list admittedly doesn't help him out here much) who kept pushing "his special" bottles that clearly as described and after opening just didnt match what we were asking for, and didnt match well to the food. Felt like we were in Las Vegas - a glitzy, expensive but far from sophisticated experience.

review_2171.Review: Food was over seasoned and sauced.  The complicated flavors didn't work together at all.  Worst steak I have ever had to pay for.  Expensive and not worth it at all.

review_2172.Review: The dining room is too loud - there's no way to have a conversation. After spending $100 + per person for food, it should have been a bit more tranquil - it should be about the food, not the noise from the bar.

review_2173.Review: We wanted a cool, casual place to go after boating with good food&wine. The appetizers came out quickly but once the resteraunt filled up, we were basically ignored by our friendly server, he never came back to check on us, refresh drinks or even serve our food. Slow service after that. The food was very good, everyone loved their steaks and the truffle fries are a must. I had the NY sirloin and it was delicious, very satisfying. I loved the spinach and bok choy sides and my Cosmopolitan was well made. My boss ate the bone in ribeye and it was a huge portion and cooked to perfection. The winos ordered Frank's Family Cabernet, which was delicious. I would go back for the food.

review_2174.Review: We are are still talking about how great the food is.

review_2175.Review: Perfect for a birthday dinner...comfortable booths for 6 people. Our server was super sweet and helpful. Personally, not a big steak-eater but by friends enjoyed theirs. The desserts did not disappoint...yum. Would be a great date restaurant, too...lively and causual but chic.

review_2176.Review: Try the entree sampler of the different high quality beef. Delicious.

review_2177.Review: The food and service was excellent. Our server was tentative and very knowledgeable about the menu. I recommend trying the World Wide Wagyu Sampler…it’s a little pricy, but worth it. Also, the truffle fries are addictive. I look forward to going back and trying other things on the menu.

review_2178.Review: The meat speaks for itself. Incredible and priced accordingly... but worth every penny. Our server's knowledge of the menu was impressive and was a real highlight of the dinner.Only negative comment (but its a big one for me) is that this place must turn into a nightclub at night or something because there were large nightlcub speakers sitting by our table. They weren't on of course, but when you spend that kind of money ($250 for two) you don't want to see some giant concert-grade speaker sitting on the floor. Also, the hostesses were a bit too young and chatty with eachother and did not make for a good first impression. I felt like we interupted their gossiping when we walked in.But back to the good stuff- the food: AMAZING.

review_2179.Review: never had a bad meal at 5a5. love DAniel the server!!! have been here a few times and always delicious! thank you

review_2180.Review: Food was great, but unfortunately it took more than two hours to get the food!

review_2181.Review: Got steak? Yeah, they got steak. Excellent steaks. I think there is fish too...

review_2182.Review: It was a decent steak house, good but not great. I thought it was going to be a lot more modern, but it was more of a retro feel. They push the A5 steaks (of course) but the regular steaks were good, but not the best I've had. We got iceberg salad, mac n cheese and mashed potatoes. Like my husband says, you can't really mess up when you throw bacon on everything. Overall, go for the retro vibe and decent food, but not if you're looking for a top steakhouse.

review_2183.Review: Enjoyed our first visit and will return.

review_2184.Review: Unfortunately, none of the steaks and or side dishes were served hot. Most of the meal was served warm. I understand that the meat is allowed to rest, I don't think it translates into a savory meal. Not sure why side dishes like Mac N Cheese were not hot only warm. All meats were served with a demi glace, while tasty, it didn't allow the flavor of the meat to shine. There were several great buys on the wine list, which is nice to see in a high end restaurant such as this.

review_2185.Review: Hubby and I shared and loved the rib eye steak. I'm not a big fan of steaks and here I am 2 mos later, still thinking about that steak.  Our kid liked his NY steak but clearly our steak was better. Truffle oil infused fries and mac n' cheese were both really good, but we felt "truffled out" after all that.  Desserts were OK, not memorable now that a few months have passed.  If you like red meat and rib eye steak, this is a great place for that.

review_2186.Review: delicous food with some moderate choices ad nsome menu items are insane like steak for $19/oz. waiter while efficient adn polite wqs pushing hig end wine and hig end dishes too stronly fo rmy taste. how weve mondays are winenights at discount

review_2187.Review: My overall dining experience went well. My husband and I arrived late for our reservations due to heavy traffic. When we were seated to our table, the host mentioned a time when we would no longer have our table reserved. It gave us 2 hours for the table. It was fine and all, but thought that was tacky.

review_2188.Review: Great steak, and great veggies on the side! A different, trendy vibe for a steak house, which made it an even more enjoyable. The wine list was way over priced, but with the good food you take it for what it is. The Kobe steak was some of the best I've ever had.

review_2189.Review: The food was excellent. Not knowing anything about this restaurant, the website did it proud. It was a great place to have our Valentine's dinner and we plan on going back. It was easy to find and parking was great with the valet. It was even nice to have the waitress call up our car to have it waiting for us when we left. Just an overall nice place. Even the bar looked very cozy and inviting. Definately a place to grab some drinks with friends after work.

review_2190.Review: Be sure to get the Wagyu beef it will change your mind about steak forever. Half price wine by the bottle on Monday is also very appealing.

review_2191.Review: Service was a bit slow at times and flow of food was poor. Server forgot to pack a dish that I had requested. Steak was super yum but I've had better service at other steak houses.

review_2192.Review: One of our diners is on a gleuten free diet for health reasons. Our server did an excellent job at working with the chef to suggest glueten free options or alterations to the menu items and dessert which was much appreciated. On top of an overall great service experience, a5a gets 5 stars for Service

review_2193.Review: Overall, a very nice dining experience, especially with the dine-about promotion. The waiter stood out in his thoroughness in describing the menu and attentiveness.

review_2194.Review: Overall the dining experience was very good. The seating area appears like the tables are crowded yet when you sit you barely notice other patrons. The design and layout of the restaurant is very vibrant. The food very cooked very well and the dine about town menu was perfect. The ceaser salad was perfect and I loved the pieces of anchovie, my new york steak was perfectly cooked and the sauce it was laid in definately added to each bite. The only food issue was that the filet mignon my date ordered, it appeared to be a little over cooked. The banana creme tart was declious! The sides were interesting, mini potatoes and mini mushooms, definately an experience.

review_2195.Review: We went for the SF dine about town dinner, and figured it would be a good way to try out a new restaurant. The NY strip they served was excellent, although I didn't really care for the stuff that was piled on top the steak - I came to eat steak, not some pickled ginger/basil/pesto. The sides were great, especially the truffled mac-n-cheese!! Dessert was hands down, the best dessert I've ever eaten - toffee bread pudding! I'd like to come back and splurge on a filet, and possibly the red velvet soufflé .

review_2196.Review: The ambiance of 5a5 is enjoyable and there is a pleasant, trendy and upscale feel to the restaurant. The service was great although the waitress brought out a 6 oz steak instead of a 10oz steak and didn't realize her mistake and she also poured the wrong wine into someone's wine glass. However, she was very nice and very attentive. The busboy refilled the water promptly. The wine was great.I did not like my steak. It was small. I understand that high quality steak is expensive and I am ok with a small steak for an expensive price. The problem was that I did not like having multiple sauces, pesto and ginger drizzled all over my steak. A $40+ steak should be delicious with no additives to mask the flavor. The mushroom were chewy.

review_2197.Review: The Aussie F1 Kobe steak was amazing! I only ordered a 4oz cut because that is usually all I can eat, but it was so good, I know I could have eaten more. The mac and cheese was also very good. Definitely a place we will go back to.

review_2198.Review: I felt that the food here was somewhat overpriced for what you receive.

review_2199.Review: Entree portions were small. Not sure if size was scaled down due to Dine About Town promo. We were looking forward to the Dine About Town menu that was posted online. Unfortunately, the menu changed and everyone was a little disappointed. Truffle fries were very yummy as was dessert.

review_2200.Review: My friend ordered a diet coke which I think was $1.50. My same-size watered down lemonade was $4. We both had caeser salad which had too much dressing. I ordered the beef medium rare. It was tasty w/the dressing (avocado and pickled ginger?), but more on the rare side and tough to cut. Neither of us finished dessert. I had the lemon custard tart. The crust was cold so I couldn't break it w/my spoon and had to use a fork. She had the bread pudding which was tasty, but very sweet which is why she didn't finish it.The service was polite and efficient. I think it was supposed to be jazz music because it was Mon, but I only heard that kind of club/electronic stuff in the background. Comfortable seating and warmly decorated for a trendy place.

review_2201.Review: We had a fine dining experience overall. The food quality is excellent but quite expensive... the Wagyu beef is priced at $19/per oz. That's right per ounce!!! You can specify the size of your steak when you place order. The beef tartar shooter was great. The bread pudding was excellent.The most disappointing is the service. Our server is young and very inexperience. She was a bit nervus, totally not engaging and got a few things wrong.

review_2202.Review: We tried 5A5 for dine about town after hearing so much hype about this new spot. My group was quite pleased with food, ambiance, and service. I recommend trying it out if you have not yet.

review_2203.Review: excellent and unique bone in filet!!! truffle fries were to die for

review_2204.Review: Food was good. Service was so so. We had to ask twice about what had happened to the bottle of wine we had ordered after 15-20 minutes had passed. The bread we were promised when we sat down materialized after our starters were cleared off the table and we asked again. Very noisy, tables are round and wide making it extremely difficult to hear what is being said directly across from you. Be prepared to lean forward the duration of your meal and speak loudly.

review_2205.Review: Just ok for the regular rib-eye steak but the A5 @$20/bite-size steak melted in your mouth. The sauce combo all seemed pretty odd to complement with the steak.

review_2206.Review: We tried this restaurant because of the Dine About Town special and since we were going o be in the city to see a ballet. Service was excellent, our server was very attentive and polite! We did not feel rushed, or pushed into trying anything. She answered all our questions with seemingly thorough knowledge of the menu. Definitely will go back to this restaurant, would love to try happy hour as well.

review_2207.Review: Nice, hip spot for dinner and drinks. Cool bar/lounge area. Ordered a medium-well NY steak, but it tasted like well done. Best to ask for medium. My boyfriend ordered a filet mignon, medium...and loved it. Get the mac & cheese as a side dish - it's phenomenal! The mushroom medley side dish is also amazing. Service was great. Overall, a great dining experience!

review_2208.Review: Terribly overpriced, particularly given the level of service. Waitress was not attentive, slow and not apologetic for forgetting items or for running out of items on wine list. Food itself was good. Though food was still overpriced, it would be more palatable if service had been excellent.

review_2209.Review: Had a reservation booked for BEFORE the place opened for dinner! My husband and I went for Dine About, which was an excuse to try a new place. The dining room was modern-looking, the booths were pretty comfortable and the lighting was interesting. The food was tasty, however the side dishes were served in larger portions than the some of the steak entrees. Overall a nice experience but rather pricey

review_2210.Review: This was the first time that I have ever been to 5A5 and the experience was great. The food was very well prepared, down to the smallest detail. The presentation of the food was also very pleasing to the eye. There were a total of 7 dishes that were ordered and each one tasted great; in comparison to "good dining", the flavors of the food at 5A5 steak lounge do not compare, at all. It's almost a sin to categorize 5A5 as a regular "nice restaurant", this place deserves it's own category. It's made me look at steak so differently, and nothing compares to the taste of the steak I had here.

review_2211.Review: Great dinner and food. Not super pricey, but up there. I had a great time with my GF there.

review_2212.Review: Great place to go for good quality meat. I love the ambiance with the very open dining space and comfortable seating. There are great happy hour deals. 2 for $5 oyster shooters, a $5 drink menu as well as $1 bites that vary by weekday will definitely draw me back after work. Happy hour goes until 7:30PM. The toffee bread pudding was excellent and the dine about town menu was a good value.

review_2213.Review: The best steak I've ever had, and one of the best overall meals in quite awhile.

review_2214.Review: Steak was very good, interesting mix of ginger and wasabi on the steak which was delicious! Waiter was very helpful and informative.

review_2215.Review: great hamachi shooters. Didn't have the 5A5 steak, but the normal steak cuts were pretty good. Mac and cheese was tasty too. Not a ton of seating, but a very nicely decorated spot.

review_2216.Review: We enjoyed the food, especially the steaks. The service was very good. Unfortunately, the noise level was too high and it was difficult to carry on a conversation with friends we hadn't seen in a while. The prices are high, so although the meal was good, we would only return if someone else were footing the bill!

review_2217.Review: I would eat here again! The service was impeccable, from the hostess to the waiter to the bus boy, everyone here was polite, and kind. The food was absolutely delicious. My husband had the rib eye, one of their shooters, we shared potatoes and spinach as our side dishes and we had their red velvet souffle. Satisfying and delicious!

review_2218.Review: Service was fantastic. Great Happy Hour specials. Quite possibly the best steak dinner I've ever had, it melted in my mouth! As for the sides, the mushrooms are wonderful, but I'd pass on the marbled potatoes. Half priced bottles of wine are a great deal every Monday!

review_2219.Review: great food and service. one of the best restaurants that i've been to. the steak was one of the best i've had. cocktails are very good. great wine list and 1/2 off bottles on mon nite.

review_2220.Review: My partner and I ate there recently for Dine Around Town and the food was really bad. For the most part the salads were awful. The chef needs to gain an understanding of seasonings and taste the food before you serve it. The meat selections for the Dine Around was good because it gave us a chance to sample some of the food. The salmon was flaky but again no taste to it. The desserts frankly were really bad. I could tell that 5A5 has no pastry chef because the desserts tasted and looked as if, someone else made the tiny plain desserts and a sous chef stuck on a plate. Another negative was despite the fact they had a full bar, they had no iced tea and the lemonade which came in a small tumbler was $4 with no refills.

review_2221.Review: 5A5 is a great place if you like high quality meat. An A5 rating is one of the highest grades a meat can have and the prices definitely reflect that. The service was lacking for the price that I was paying to dine, but the food was amazing. Everything was cooked to perfection except for the red velvet souffle, which I'd rather just eat the cupcake, but nice try. Overall I highly recommend this place for meat eaters, special occasions, or just to self-indulge.

review_2222.Review: The steaks were wonderful. The dessert was orgasmic (caramel bread pudding?). Apps and salads were an afterthought. Very cool bar area with fire flames pumped in and video feeds of the same behind the bar. Seating/decor was amazing, very highend/modern posh. Service was pretty good as well. Just order the steak and dessert and skip the rest...

review_2223.Review: Hamachi shots are off the hook. Beautiful place. Took my lady here for her birthday. She loved it. Service was awesome. Gonna take my friends here for sure.

review_2224.Review: Our party of 6 all loved our dining experience at 5A5 Steak Lounge. It was truly a mix of the steak house and lounge atmosphere. Food was excellent. The Dine About Town is what brought us in and the choices were great. We'd go again.

review_2225.Review: The food was good. I would not return because of the service. The waiter was rude, but more disappointing was when we asked to speak with the manager, he was also rude. I would not return.

review_2226.Review: Similar comment as others. Food was good, but the service was very poor.

review_2227.Review: I had the Bone in Ribeye and it was amazing. My cousin and I have sort of done a "tour de steak" around SF. When i heard your restaurant had opened, i was pessimistic as i did not like Frisson and did not think a steak house with such a modern vibe could deliver. I was wrong. The ribeye was massive and cooked (or i should say, not cooked - i ordered it black and blue) to perfection. And the price was more than fair for what we received. well done. we will be back! and i will be sure to tell friends.

review_2228.Review: This is a very beautiful Restaurant and everything was perfect. We loved our waiter who was very friendly. Food was very nice and beautifully presented. Great cocktails and delicious deserts. Its not a cheap steak house but its worth the price if you are looking for somewhere hip, chill and romantic to dine. Its a great place for a special evening.

review_2229.Review: Enjoyed a filet, caesar salad and great mac and cheese. Service was good. Price was maybe a touch high, but reflects nice scene.

review_2230.Review: I celebrated my birthday here and had a great time !!! The food was great as well as the service.

review_2231.Review: Our waiter was less that thrilled when he found out that we were vegetarians, and his service reflected his disapointment. There were plently of items on the menu for us to order including a vegetable platter (and the food was excellent), but the waiter's attitude prevented me from ordering another alcoholic beverage or dessert because quite frankly at that point I didn't want to give any more business to the restaurant. Keep in mind we had already ordered 2 appetizers, 2 salads, a veggie platter, and 3 side orders for 2 people.

review_2232.Review: Service, food, ambiance are great. We enjoyed the vibrant crowd during our NYE dinner.

review_2233.Review: Chef Allen Chen brings the excellence of Alexander's and adds SF sophistication and flavor. The 4 course NYE menu included all our favorite foods prepared to perfection: hamachi and Kobe beef shooters, seared scallops and fois gras, misoyaki glazed Chilean sea bass... so it was no surprise that my A5 Wagyu filet mignon main course was the highlight of dinner!

review_2234.Review: Simply a wonderful time. Loved it

review_2235.Review: Great service, but the food was only so so and it is very $$$$$ to dine there. For these rates the food should be better.

review_2236.Review: This was my second trip in just a week. Celebrating a 1 year anniversary with my girlfriend. As we entered the restaurant, a gentleman looked at us and picked up the phone. After he ended his call he assisted us. My first visit last week, I experienced the same treatment. I asked my girlfriend if she noticed anything as we walked in the door. (I said nothing) She said, "there was no there to assist us" I'm not going to comment any further on my experience. I won't return unless someone else is paying or making the reservation. Our server was great and we treated each other well. I don't feel welcome here. As we were leaving, the same person we saw putting his phone ahead of arriving guests was outside on a cell phone. He said nothi

review_2237.Review: Great steak house, better than Alexander’s in Cupertino and less expensive.

review_2238.Review: Great spot to take a date to impress. It is a energetic and trendy place, but with really good food.

review_2239.Review: I had the best steak and I never eat steak.  The himachi shooter was to die for!

review_2240.Review: The food was very good.Enjoyed the 10oz Filet and sampled the mac and cheese, spinach and mushrooms brought to the table.After dinner, donuts were served with ice cream and we also had the banana tart.Three stars for service because the hostess made us wait and never said she'd be right with us.It was my first time and a recommendation to other friends and I was getting heat early.The first round of drinks was very slow too.Before making reservations at the restaurant with the initials RC or at the one that is Spanish for water, give this place a try.

review_2241.Review: Dining experience was awesome. Thank you so much for helping us get a cab on time so we could make our Wicked showing. Food and service were on point :)

review_2242.Review: The restuarant was accomodating for large parties - and did not rush us. The food was great but wine service was a bit sloppy. They were attentive and helpful. Our waiter was very good - however others serving the table appeared inexperienced.We will go back and hopefully service will see improvement.

review_2243.Review: Bench seating was uncomfortable, felt like I needed abooster seat to be able to reach my food. Wine listwas excellent and our waitress was attentive. Theproteins were well cooked, but the sides were ahuge dissappointment. I had the fish and it camewith a mound of frozen peas and some diced ham.And the fish came with foam, which made it veryunappetizing. It was green, like something my catcould have done. We skipped dessert because welost interest after the foam. I would go back ifthey fixed some things, but not till then.

review_2244.Review: the food was out of this world. The service was first class.We are so happy we found 5a5. This restaurant is excellant. we will be back soon.

review_2245.Review: 5A5 was an outstanding experience. It was the best dinner my husband and I have had in years! We were celebrating our wedding anniversary and 5A5 greeted us with a complementary glass of champagne and it only got better from there. The lobster tempura, buffalo filet and bone-in NY were cooked to perfection!! We couldn't believe the creativity and attention to detail the chef had in creating the dishes. Dessert was incredible. We had the donoughts and the bread pudding. Again, spectacular! The vanilla salt on the ice cream was a surprising taste and very enjoyable. We will be back!!

review_2246.Review: Food was fabulous! The Tuna shooter.. to die for... Scallop appi, killer too... We like the American and Australian Wagyu the best. The Kobe was a little too "rich" for our liking.. All in all, a wonderful meal...

review_2247.Review: Service was good, but I was hoping for more given the prices of the food, etc. The A5 beef wasn't as nice as I had heard.

review_2248.Review: Foodwise, the appetizers were only so-so, but the steak was GREAT. Service was great - knowledgeable, yet down-to-earth/friendly waitstaff. It's got a noisey bar scene, so is definitely not romantic, but for sure upbeat and fun. Overall, would definitely recommend it.

review_2249.Review: It was amazing. I ordered the worldwide a5 steak, and it was very unique because i get to try different types of meat from the US, Australia, and Japan. They have valet parking in which I love, because once I don't need to find parking. Just enjoy your dinner, and have a great time.

review_2250.Review: A very, very good night out. Full review at philippage.blogspot.com/2009/11/rave-5a5-steak-lounge.html

review_2251.Review: This place was quite expensive for food that was okay. The ambiance is nice.

review_2252.Review: The steak was excellent, the selection of wines by the glass were disappointing.

review_2253.Review: Loved this restaurant. The Wagyu steak was outstanding and worth the money. Highly recommend.

review_2254.Review: Order the three filets. Each one you will write home about. Sides are fine, but you are hear for the meat, so go to town. Lovely tables, nice ambience, and excellent outstanding service. I'm so excited to eat here again next time we are back in SFO.

review_2255.Review: A must try: the hamachi shooters.I brought a friend here for her birthday. The whole ambiance of the place is perfect, the inner decor is simple, trendy and classy, definitely a great venue to have dinner or even just have a drink.My friend enjoyed it and she's coming back with her co-workers for a holiday get-together. I would recommend anyone who is looking for a great steak dinner in an upscale/ trendy place.By the way ask for Jim (he's your dream waiter. Empeccable service, personality and attentive).

review_2256.Review: This was likely our top meal of the year! Great, modern yet 60's retro atmosphere. Hubbie's t-bone steak was cooked to perfection, medium rare was spot on. My seabass had an exquisitely crisp exterior, yet moist almost creamy inside. Best mac n cheese. Save room for the green tea donuts, so freshly made and light tasting, served warm. friendly, attentive service.

review_2257.Review: If you want a Kobe steak, head to 5A5. They do it right.

review_2258.Review: We know it seems odd to given an overall rating of fair after having given good and very good to other aspects of the restaurant, but that is how we felt. It is unlikely that we'll go back as there are other places in SF where you can spend less for just as good of an experience, this was $100.00 per person. It was interesting to watch diners being seated too, two table were seated and asked to be moved to other tables, one table came in, was seated and then left. Perhaps their feng shui needs to be worked on. Our server Jim was very good and helpful.

review_2259.Review: Everytime we eat here it is always the best. This is our 3rd time.

review_2260.Review: Excellent appetizer! The dinner was nice and was not met with my taste but acceptable. Although the dessert was absolute superb, tea doughnuts (dipping raspberry sauce) and tea ice cream. Yum! Love the vibe and decor. I felt at home since I'm from L.A. Definitely will go back there again.

review_2261.Review: Not only are the steaks top-notched here, I was blown away by their Hamachi, Poke, and Oyster Shooters, along with the Kobe sliders. The Matcha Green Tea Doughnuts with Oolong Tea Ice Cream and Huckleberry Goat Cheesecake were simply amazing! The friendly staff, impeccable service, and highly vibrant atmosphere - just love their "spaceship" ceiling -all made it a fun night. We are looking forward to returning.

review_2262.Review: This is a great steak option for all budgets and occasions. You can go for the quality beef dishes in the $20 - $40 range and have an amazing time, or the $275 Japanese Wagyu that is just beyond this world. If you love what is offered at Alexander Steakhouse, the Wagyu here is very comparable. The only suggestion I'd make is that there does not need to be much additional ingredients or condiments to go with the Wagyu. The meat is already rich. To have dripping butter and saucy mini sides with ribcap, for example, may over "enrich" the taste and experience. Service was top notch. "Alena" made it perfect.

review_2263.Review: Great dinner experience. The food was fabulous, from the edamame to the green tea doughnuts (heaven on a plate). The service was impeccable and our server was very helpful with suggestions. The extensive wines by the glass list was impressive and appreciated if you do not want to buy a full bottle of wine. As expected, they are known for their steaks and they did not disappoint. The Mac-n-cheese was perfect, not too trendy, but definitely steps above the blue box. Please be sure to try the doughnuts for dessert, the best.

review_2265.Review: Delicious food and nice ambiance. Pea soup, filet mignon, hamachi shooter and doughnut dessert were big time highlights. Cod was a little too salty, but not a deal-breaker by any means.

review_2266.Review: Our first time. Our waiter was extremely helpful. He walked us through the menu & we tried a wide variety of dishes, and all of them were very good. We tried the shooters, the chillis, fries, and we both had a very good steak entree.Overall we were very pleased, and are looking to return to try some different dishes.

review_2267.Review: We went for the YELP EATS event. Incredible value, otherwise rather costly but worth it if you want a beautiful, romantic restaurant with great service and food.

review_2268.Review: The environment was great. The service was great. The food was great. Me and my friend really enjoyed the night at 5A5. I will definitely dine at 5A5 again.

review_2269.Review: Hot! Got crazy and felt a little rushed once it hit 10pm. Considering what we spent I felt a little disrespected as it got later into the evening. Could've just been a full moon, but I will definitely go back to confirm.

review_2270.Review: Go for the Japanese wagu! Outstanding.

review_2271.Review: Buffalo Filet was wonderful as were all the items the accompanied it.  I have since stolen the crispy boursin balls idea and make them when I serve filet at home.

review_2272.Review: We were on an anniversary dinner. Instead of sitting us in a corner of the restaurant, they sat us between a very loud bachelorette party of 15 girls and another noisy table/large group on the other side. It is too bad that this created such a bad experience for us because the food was excellent.

review_2273.Review: This restaurant was great! I chose to celebrate my bday here & it went well beyond my expectations. The food was absolutely exceptional (the A5 grade steak is well worth the visit to this restaurant), the service was extremely good, the staff was super friendly & I enjoyed the scenery & ambiance of the restaurant. At the end of the night our waiter brought out a desert plate with my name & Happy Bday on it, that was super thoughtful. I will definitely visit this restaurant whenever I visit San Francisco again! I wish we had one in Chicago, IL....

review_2274.Review: Good food, Good steak, Good drink.  Overall pretty decent.  Definitely worth saving a 1 hour drive to SJ for something similar.

review_2275.Review: We were very impressed with this restaurant.The service was impeccable.We were especially pleased with the special attention from the General Manager who helped us select an excellent wine.Our steaks were perfectly prepared. Hope to come back soon!

review_2276.Review: The most delicious steak ever! Wagyu from Japan was pure heaven and the Mac and Cheese will forever haunt my dreams. Now I know what I want as my last meal.

review_2277.Review: A great dining experience from start to finish. I had the regular 10oz filet mignon, not the A5,was cooked to my liking: just red enough and tender on the inside and a bit seared on the outside. My other friend ordered the 8oz Australian F1 kobe steak and thought it was very tender as well. The lobster tempura appetizer was just out of this world! The doughnuts served with ice cream reminded me of Malasada's in that it was warm, fresh, soft and not overly sweet. Everything was fresh! We came on a Thursday night so it wasn't too crowded or noisy. The DJ was spinning cool lounge music so it added to the ambiance. Our waiter seemed knowledgeable and provided great service. The manager visited us and ensured we were taken care of, nice touch.

review_2278.Review: went here with a buddy from NYC - reminded us both of the "slick" places from NY & Miami.very un-San Franciscan vibe - which is definitely welcome. food & drinks were EXCELLENT. service was very good as well. a great dining experience. will definitely be taking the wife here for dinner and drinks VERY soon. BRAVO!

review_2279.Review: Food and service was great on the Wed night we ate there. The place was pretty empty (only about 3-4 other tables were being served), which could have contributed to our exceptional service. We got the bone in ribeye and the mac n cheese, both were excellent! They cooked the steak perfectly (med rare) and the flavor was just what we liked - - just salt and pepper (you could get this bbq-like sauce on the side, but it's more of a hoisin sauce flavor.) The prices were comparable to any other steak house in this price category. The ambiance is really unique - - not the old school steak house with a bunch of old men sitting around. There's a lot of variety on the menu, so we'd definitely go back.

review_2280.Review: Food was great, service was great. We were there with a large group for a "guys night out" and enjoyed it. It's definitely a little on the pricier side, and I was surprised that the lounge wasn't more crowded. but there were enough people there that it had a quiet buzz.

review_2281.Review: The hamachi shots were horrible because the ginger was dry, the hamachi wasn't fresh, and the sauce didn't taste good. The truffle fries are ok, but lacked taste like most items on the menu. We had a nice bottle of wine. Service was good. The steaks were the biggest disappointment. We ordered a rare bone-in ribeye that was served medium rare. It was dry and tasteless. The two gentlemen who ordered the ribeyes only managed to finish half of it and did not want to bring the rest home. The rare filet mignon also came medium rare served with a thick sauce that was just salty. My friend's Australian F1 was good. The beet salad was ok, but lacked any flavour.The Mac and Cheese was fabulous! That was the best part of our meal!

review_2282.Review: 50% off all wine bottles on Mondays, great deal. The Misoyaki Seabass was delicious. It was cooked just perfect. Couldn't really appreciate the truffle oil on the truffle oil fries.

review_2283.Review: Was craving a steak, one that could rival my own, for times when I don't feel like cooking but want one. I also needed a place my vegeterian wife could find some options. I liked the restaurant design, it reminded me of NYC, very modern and cool. But it was WAY TOO loud for a romantic meal. Our waiter was very nice and attentive for the most part (minus a small lapse re: wine). As with most current trends we found the sides and small plates outshined our entres. The Snap Pea soup with dungeness crab was amazing (and I don't normally like pea soup) as were the truffled fries. While I couldn't justify the Kobe, I did get the T-Bone. There's no way that it was ever 22oz. The flavor was good, but not as good as the steak I cook at home.

review_2284.Review: Pricey but divinely delicious. Fantastic service!

review_2285.Review: Service was attentive and food was excellent. Recommend the Truffle Fries and Buffalo Filet. Large space where sound carries. Bar evolves into a lounge @10 PM, which brings the energy and noise level up later in the evening.

review_2286.Review: I had just about given up on finding a really good steakhouse in San Francisco. 5A5 restored my faith. All of our steaks - and we tried four different cuts - were first rate and perfectly prepared. Spring for at least one plate of the A5 Waygu even if it's just for comparison. It's buttery and has a fabulous finish. But the bone-in New York was equally excellent for some had a better mouth-feel. The service was terrific and although the room wasn't really to our taste they are obviously going for something a little different. My only complaint would be the wine list which was highly priced and unimaginative. There's really no excuse for that in the Bay Area.

review_2287.Review: We went with a group of 6 and I wasn't disappointed. They didn't make any changes from the old Frisson, but none were realy necessary truthfully. The place is fantastic looking and the hipness factor is very high. The food was fantastic. We all ordered steaks, all started with salads and ordered a couple of the sides. Everything was great. Would definitely love to come back and try the Wagyu!The restaruant was very accomodating. We were running a bit behind, and called ahead to let them know. They were very pleasant over the phone, unlike many restaurants could be. This was a great find and we had an amazing time.

review_2288.Review: Overall, we thought this was a great restaurant. It has a very New York feel with a great bar scene and the food is very good.

review_2289.Review: Steak was huge, cooked perfectly (my friends and I like it rare, which it was), truffle fries yummy, asparagus a little stringy, beet salad fabulous.

review_2290.Review: Good overall. (They're still getting off the ground. Not sure I"d want to be opening a high-priced steak restaurant in these times.)Menu is definitely pricey - not just the Wagyu items. Food very tasty. Service very strong and attentive - though we didn't really need to server practically reading the entire menu to us, since both me and my dinner partner can read well enough.I've eaten at both Craft and Craftsteak in NY. 5A5 seems like it's shooting for something similar. Not quite there, but I'm crossing my fingers.New, expensive restaurant on a Mon night meant it was pretty slow. That's kind of a buzz-kill, but I can imagine the vibe would be great on a weekend night.

review_2291.Review: Definitely try the World Wide Wagyu. It's pricey but definitely worth every bite. We ended up sharing all our dishes so we could try more things from the menu. I would definitely recommend that. The desserts were also really good. I was only slightly disappointed with the creme brulee trio. The flavors were there but the texture was not what I expected.

review_2292.Review: Presentation on the food is 5* as well. Service is exceedingly attentive that we feel like we were dinning on a cruise ship. We were prepared for the high price tag. When we got the check we thought it is resonably acceptable for a fine dinning establishment such as 5A5. It is worth the experience! Everything we ordered are excellent and we'll return soon.

review_2293.Review: I ordered the A5 filet and it was so soft and tasty. Definitely the best meat that I have ever had and I've eaten at a lot of steak places. The service was great and friendly.

review_2294.Review: loved the Hamachi and Poke Slider appetizers. The steak was really good - not the best steak of my life, but it was good; and the sides were really good too! AMAZING SERVICE!

review_2295.Review: Very loud. Bordering on too loud. Waygu is a delicacy. You can only have so much. I'd take a Peter Luger's Porterhouse over Waygu or Kobe anytime. A good description is it is like beef flavored butter. It is that melt in your mouth.Service was knowledgeable, timely, friendly and attentive. Good Happy Hour specials.

review_2296.Review: Great Sommelier. Fun DJ. Yummy steaks. Cool vibe.

review_2297.Review: We never been to 5A5. We only tried this restaurant after searching on Open Table. Food was not cheap subject to the quality provided. We did enjoy the hip decor and friendly staff, but I guess those would be the only two things we enjoyed. Husband did complain a bit, said rather going to Morton's again for that night (which was celebration in advance for my birthday). It would be more money worth. They have different high quality steaks shown on menu for your choices (cost USD16 to USD19 per oz), supposed they should know a lot about how to make good food. It was kind of disappointed.We will never go to A5A again.

review_2298.Review: I have been here more than 10 times and each time I go back it only gets better. The food is wonderful and their steaks are out of this world, especially the Japanese kobe (a must try!!). This place is a great place for a date (although the music might be too loud for some people) or a group (very fun and trendy place to hang out with friends who appreciate good company, food and wine). MUST TRY AT LEAST ONCE..You won't regret it!

review_2299.Review: The food & service was great! It took awhile to actually recieve our food, but other than that this is a great restaurant. Our server was very nice & helpful. Giving a complimentary glass of wine was a great way to have start the meal. I would definatly recommend this restaurant.

review_2300.Review: Great Addition to the Jackson Sqaure Nightlife, great steaks and the sides are good too.

review_2301.Review: Wow, we loved it. Food was outstanding, from apps to shooters, to mains. The steaks are sold by the ounce, so you can splurge or go economy. The service is excellent. Decor has lightened a bit from Frisson and looks great. Highly recommended.

review_2302.Review: Have not been to a place that specializes in top notch beef. It was amazing with a mix of style and grades of meat. Very open air and you are able to see all the action around you. Loved the Dj while dinning. Bar staff was polite. All were approachable and ready to serve. One note on the other side. Tried to ask the bus person for some help and I think the language barrier was a problem. I don't speak Spanish that well and he was not really wanting to listen to my request for lemon slices for the delicious King Crab legs. Got to have them. I will have to go back often because after the word gets out, this place will be packed.sddd

review_2303.Review: We were there early on a Wednesday, so there wasn't much of vibe...just us, some oldies and some bankers. The food was fantastic!! The server was the nicest guy, but not a waiter...beer served with no glass, empty dishes left on the table. For the price, the food saved the day because it was a moderate experience.

review_2304.Review: Posh, clubby, jumping joint--very hip but with a friendly vibe. I'd have guessed 90% atmosphere/10% everything else. WRONG. Food was terrific and only some of it pricey. A huge, sublime T-bone ($35) deserves special mention. Side dishes ($8) were equally bountiful. (We seemed to graze all night on to-die-for truffle fries.) Beet salad and iceberg appetizers were more fussy, but still gratifying. The wine list, although slightly thin, yielded a splendid Spanish ($56). Let 5A5's not-just-gorgeous sommelier introduce you. (Seriously, he's a must.) Dessert menu was however vexing. Overall, I'd like to compliment the owner/managers on an excellent crew, as we met several in the course of our dinner. A++ for our superstar server (+ SFAI daytimer)

review_2305.Review: Great food, beautiful decor, fun atmosphere. One of the best dining experiences i've had in sfTried a small a5 new york steak, cost a little over $60 and oooooh soooo good, incredibly tender and flavorful! Sampled the regular filet - really good and super tender, but the a5 was still far superiorWine list was lacking in certain areas, but found a great value with my bottle of the BV latour private reserve for only $100

review_2306.Review: They serve the rare wagyu steaks, and makes for quite an experience. It's the most expensive dinner I've ever had, yet not the most memorable. I didn't find it worth the money.

review_2307.Review: Below par.. Service lacking in areas, menu overpriced for value.

review_2308.Review: Wow, this place is amazing! They just opened up this week - food and service were spot on. Regular steaks were really good, but the A5 ones were the best steaks i've ever had - they just melted in our mouth (our group ordered four different A5 steaks - my fav was the New York). Wife really liked the Sea Bass (at a steakhouse?) and beet salad.Hamachi shooters were really tasty, although a little difficult to 'shoot'. Truffle fries and mac 'n' cheese are out of this world. The A5 is expensive but worth it, other items on menu were very reasonably priced. Desserts ranged from ok - really good, apple tart was the best. Creme brulee was eh.Definitely not a regular steakhouse with its trendy decor, but our group loved it!

review_2309.Review: They were still in their soft opening, but it did not show. The service was great, the food was excellent. I had the A5 filet which literally melted in your mouth. The wine list was impressive and very good. We will definately go back.

review_2310.Review: We were there during the soft opening so hard to know how this will translate to reality, but all the foundations are there. Excellent steaks, perfectly cooked, tasty cocktails and terrific service. That's all good, and what I expected, the bonus is the decor & ambiance. Who doesn't enjoy an good old school steakhouse, but it's nice to see a twist on the tradition. I'll be sending a lot of people there, if only because it seems like the steakhouse San Francisco deserves.

review_2311.Review: WOW this will be one of the hottest places in town turning Jackson into the "new" Filmore or Chestnut for Restaurants . Nice job. Send me an invite for the launch opening.

review_2312.Review: great time, meet with more friends once we got there could of stayed all ngiht, great party in the loung. And the food was some of the best I've eaten in a long time. All the spots in the city this is an A+ we will be back

review_2313.Review: This place rocks. I went there twice in less than a week during a recent business trip to SF, the first at the rec. of a friend, the second because I thought it was worth returning before I left. They were still in soft-opening, but nevertheless, it was excellent. Definitely would recommend it to anyone visiting the Bay Area.

review_2315.Review: The porterhouse steak is wonderful. Hamachi shooter, truffle fries & mixed mushroom are must try. Th food can be hotter when it gets the table.Services are great.

review_2316.Review: Wagyu A5 steaks are amazing - tiny nodules of fatty flavors popping in mouth with every bite. Warm apple tart is a must have. Mushroom side dish is a great compliment to the steaks. Kobe NY was a total disappointment - that's even b4 trying out the A5. Need more appetizers - only have hamachi and soup shots. Entres are too small to share. Need bigger wine list and more full bodied reds to pair with super rich A5 steaks.

review_2317.Review: WOW this will be one of the hottest places in town turning Jackson into the "new" Filmore or Chestnut for Restaurants . Nice job. Send me an invite for the launch opening.

review_2318.Review: great time, meet with more friends once we got there could of stayed all ngiht, great party in the loung. And the food was some of the best I've eaten in a long time. All the spots in the city this is an A+ we will be back

review_2319.Review: This place rocks. I went there twice in less than a week during a recent business trip to SF, the first at the rec. of a friend, the second because I thought it was worth returning before I left. They were still in soft-opening, but nevertheless, it was excellent. Definitely would recommend it to anyone visiting the Bay Area.

review_2321.Review: The porterhouse steak is wonderful. Hamachi shooter, truffle fries & mixed mushroom are must try. Th food can be hotter when it gets the table.Services are great.

review_2322.Review: Wagyu A5 steaks are amazing - tiny nodules of fatty flavors popping in mouth with every bite. Warm apple tart is a must have. Mushroom side dish is a great compliment to the steaks. Kobe NY was a total disappointment - that's even b4 trying out the A5. Need more appetizers - only have hamachi and soup shots. Entres are too small to share. Need bigger wine list and more full bodied reds to pair with super rich A5 steaks.

review_2323.Review: WOW this will be one of the hottest places in town turning Jackson into the "new" Filmore or Chestnut for Restaurants . Nice job. Send me an invite for the launch opening.

review_2324.Review: great time, meet with more friends once we got there could of stayed all ngiht, great party in the loung. And the food was some of the best I've eaten in a long time. All the spots in the city this is an A+ we will be back

review_2325.Review: This place rocks. I went there twice in less than a week during a recent business trip to SF, the first at the rec. of a friend, the second because I thought it was worth returning before I left.
